{"_id":"1a9091174116f6ff","name":"Strong Bellow","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Use your Bellow ability without moving down the Condition Track.","prerequisite":"Ithorian","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["condition_track","feat","racial","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-ithorian"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Ithorian</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter when you use your Bellow ability, you move one less step down the<br>Condition Track<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_Bellow</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["movement.while-moving","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Strong Bellow: Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["movement.while-moving","turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"non_numeric_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Strong Bellow now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","reactionRules":[],"resourceRules":{"phase10Special":[{"type":"REDUCE_BELLOW_CONDITION_TRACK_COST","trigger":"useBellow","stepsReduced":1,"oncePer":"encounter","description":"Once per encounter when using Bellow, move one less step down the Condition Track."}]},"status":"non_numeric_rule_phase10","description":"Strong Bellow now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"Use your Bellow ability without moving down the Condition Track.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_Bellow","rawImport":{"name":"Strong Bellow","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_Bellow","pageTitle":"Strong_Bellow","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\strong_bellow.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Ithorian","prerequisites":["Ithorian"],"effect":"Once per encounter when you use your Bellow ability, you move one less step down the\nCondition Track\n.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Ithorian","indexBenefit":"Use your Bellow ability without moving down the Condition Track .","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou can use your lungs to Bellow without growing fatigued.\n\nPrerequisite:\nIthorian\n\nEffect:\nOnce per encounter when you use your Bellow ability, you move one less step down the\nCondition Track\n."},"prerequisitesText":"Ithorian","effect":"Once per encounter when you use your Bellow ability, you move one less step down the\nCondition Track\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.379Z","detectedPredicates":["movement.while-moving","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.strong_bellow"}}}
{"_id":"1d0291d930abda15","name":"Wrruushi Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"martial_arts","benefit":"Gain bonus hit points on Unarmed attacks. Deny target Equipment bonus.","prerequisite":"Constitution 13, Martial Arts I, Wookiee","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["durability","feat","feat_chain","hit_points","martial_arts","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Constitution<br>13,<br>Martial Arts I<br>,<br>Wookiee</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per round when you make a successful<br>Unarmed Attack<br>, you gain a number of<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>equal to your<br>Constitution<br>modifier. Damage is subtracted from the<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>first, and any<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>remaining at the end of the encounter are lost.<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>do not stack.<br><br>Once per encounter, you can make an<br>Unarmed Attack<br>against an enemy&#x27;s<br>Fortitude Defense<br>instead of the enemy&#x27;s<br>Reflex Defense<br>. If the attack is successful, the enemy not only takes damage but also loses any<br>Equipment<br>bonus to<br>Fortitude Defense<br>until the end of the encounter.<br><br>You must be wearing<br>Light Armor<br>or no Armor to gain the benefits of this Feat.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you have the<br>Wrruushi Expertise<br>Talent, once per encounter when you score a Critical Hit with an<br>Unarmed Attack<br>against an enemy, you can deal normal damage and move the target an additional -2 steps down the<br>Condition Track<br>, regardless of the damage result. You must be wearing<br>Light Armor<br>or no Armor to gain this special benefit.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wrruushi_Training</em></p>","martialArtsFeat":true,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex","defense.fortitude","attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Wrruushi Training: Converted from false defense bonus to an unarmed Fortitude-targeting option and bonus-hit-point rider metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","defense.fortitude","defense.reflex","turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Converted from false defense bonus to an unarmed Fortitude-targeting option and bonus-hit-point rider metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","defense.fortitude","defense.reflex","turn.once-per-round"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"wrruushiFortitudeStrike","label":"Wrruushi Fortitude Strike","control":"toggle","requiresUnarmed":true,"targetDefenseType":"fortitude","targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"REMOVE_EQUIPMENT_BONUS","defense":"fortitude","duration":"encounter","description":"Once per encounter unarmed attack vs Fortitude also removes the target equipment bonus to Fortitude for the encounter."}],"oncePer":"encounter","summary":"Once per encounter, make an unarmed attack against Fortitude instead of Reflex."}],"status":"wrruushiFortitudeStrike_attack_option_phase12","description":"Converted from false defense bonus to an unarmed Fortitude-targeting option and bonus-hit-point rider metadata.","hitRiderRules":[{"id":"wrruushi_bonus_hit_points","type":"BONUS_HIT_POINTS_ON_UNARMED_HIT","valueFormula":"constitutionModifier","oncePer":"round","armorLimit":"lightOrNone","description":"Once per round on a successful unarmed attack, gain bonus hit points equal to Constitution modifier until encounter end."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonus hit points on Unarmed attacks.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wrruushi_Training","rawImport":{"name":"Wrruushi Training","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wrruushi_Training","pageTitle":"Wrruushi_Training","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\wrruushi_training.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Constitution\n13,\nMartial Arts I\n,\nWookiee","prerequisites":["Constitution\n13","Martial Arts I","Wookiee"],"effect":"Once per round when you make a successful\nUnarmed Attack\n, you gain a number of\nBonus Hit Points\nequal to your\nConstitution\nmodifier. Damage is subtracted from the\nBonus Hit Points\nfirst, and any\nBonus Hit Points\nremaining at the end of the encounter are lost.\nBonus Hit Points\ndo not stack.\n\nOnce per encounter, you can make an\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst an enemy's\nFortitude Defense\ninstead of the enemy's\nReflex Defense\n. If the attack is successful, the enemy not only takes damage but also loses any\nEquipment\nbonus to\nFortitude Defense\nuntil the end of the encounter.\n\nYou must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain the benefits of this Feat.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"If you have the\nWrruushi Expertise\nTalent, once per encounter when you score a Critical Hit with an\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst an enemy, you can deal normal damage and move the target an additional -2 steps down the\nCondition Track\n, regardless of the damage result. You must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain this special benefit.","indexPrerequisites":"Constitution 13, Martial Arts I , Wookiee","indexBenefit":"Gain bonus hit points on Unarmed attacks. Deny target Equipment bonus.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Martial Arts Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nMartial Arts Feats\n\nYou are trained in the Wrruushi\nUnarmed\nfighting style of the\nWookiees\nand feel more invigorated in the heat of battle.\n\nPrerequisites:\nConstitution\n13,\nMartial Arts I\n,\nWookiee\n\nEffect:\nOnce per round when you make a successful\nUnarmed Attack\n, you gain a number of\nBonus Hit Points\nequal to your\nConstitution\nmodifier. Damage is subtracted from the\nBonus Hit Points\nfirst, and any\nBonus Hit Points\nremaining at the end of the encounter are lost.\nBonus Hit Points\ndo not stack.\n\nOnce per encounter, you can make an\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst an enemy's\nFortitude Defense\ninstead of the enemy's\nReflex Defense\n. If the attack is successful, the enemy not only takes damage but also loses any\nEquipment\nbonus to\nFortitude Defense\nuntil the end of the encounter.\n\nYou must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain the benefits of this Feat.\n\nSpecial:\nIf you have the\nWrruushi Expertise\nTalent, once per encounter when you score a Critical Hit with an\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst an enemy, you can deal normal damage and move the target an additional -2 steps down the\nCondition Track\n, regardless of the damage result. You must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain this special benefit."},"prerequisitesText":"Constitution\n13,\nMartial Arts I\n,\nWookiee","effect":"Once per round when you make a successful\nUnarmed Attack\n, you gain a number of\nBonus Hit Points\nequal to your\nConstitution\nmodifier. Damage is subtracted from the\nBonus Hit Points\nfirst, and any\nBonus Hit Points\nremaining at the end of the encounter are lost.\nBonus Hit Points\ndo not stack.\n\nOnce per encounter, you can make an\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst an enemy's\nFortitude Defense\ninstead of the enemy's\nReflex Defense\n. If the attack is successful, the enemy not only takes damage but also loses any\nEquipment\nbonus to\nFortitude Defense\nuntil the end of the encounter.\n\nYou must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain the benefits of this Feat."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.379Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex","defense.fortitude","attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.wrruushi_training"}}}
{"_id":"1d27dfb8ce491836","name":"Medical Team","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Treat Injury checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Treat Injury","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","healing","skill_synergy","skill_treat_injury","support","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8","manual_resolution","teamwork_base_skill_bonus_phase15"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Treat Injury</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +3 competence bonus on<br>Treat Injury<br>checks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).<br><br>Additionally, when you use the<br>Aid Another<br>Action to assist an ally who has this Feat with a<br>Treat Injury<br>check to restore Hit Points, your ally restores an extra 4 Hit Points to the target.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Medical_Team</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_with_manual_teamwork","applicationScope":"skill_roll_plus_manual_teamwork","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Medical Team: +3 competence skill bonus applies normally; nearby-ally scaling and other battlefield/teamwork clauses are GM/player managed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 avoids automating nearby-ally/battlefield positioning clauses; base skill bonuses are implemented where unambiguous and teamwork clauses are preserved as manual metadata.","implementationStatus":"base_skill_bonus_manual_teamwork_phase15","description":"Medical Team: base +3 competence skill bonus implemented; nearby-ally scaling and special teamwork clauses remain table-managed flavor/manual metadata.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"medical-team","skillKey":"treatInjury","type":"competence","featName":"Medical Team","description":"Medical Team: +3 competence bonus to treatInjury checks. Nearby-ally scaling is manual/table-managed.","value":3}],"teamworkRules":[{"type":"AID_ANOTHER_HEALING_BONUS","skillKey":"treatInjury","extraHealing":4,"requiresAllyHasFeat":true,"description":"Aid Another on Treat Injury to restore HP grants +4 extra HP restored when assisting an ally with this feat.","automation":"manual","manualResolution":true}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Treat Injury checks when near allies.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Medical_Team","rawImport":{"name":"Medical Team","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Medical_Team","pageTitle":"Medical_Team","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\medical_team.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nTreat Injury","prerequisites":["Trained\nin\nTreat Injury"],"effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nTreat Injury\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nTreat Injury\ncheck to restore Hit Points, your ally restores an extra 4 Hit Points to the target.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Trained in Treat Injury","indexBenefit":"Gain bonuses on Treat Injury checks when near allies.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Team Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nTeam Feats\n\nYou and your allies know the value of keeping soldiers alive and perform as a cohesive healing unit.\n\nPrerequisite:\nTrained\nin\nTreat Injury\n\nEffect:\nYou gain a +3 competence bonus on\nTreat Injury\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nTreat Injury\ncheck to restore Hit Points, your ally restores an extra 4 Hit Points to the target."},"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nTreat Injury","effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nTreat Injury\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nTreat Injury\ncheck to restore Hit Points, your ally restores an extra 4 Hit Points to the target."},"effects":[{"_id":"2c1ca71e-4e78-4270-8b8c-35c1ebd97839","name":"Medical Team","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Medical Team","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.379Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.medical_team"}}}
{"_id":"1dfbddf5f1aa57c3","name":"K'tara Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"martial_arts","benefit":"Deal extra damage against Flat-Footed enemy. Render target Mute.","prerequisite":"Martial Arts I, Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","feat_chain","martial_arts","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Martial Arts I<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Stealth</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You roll an extra die of damage against a<br>Flat-Footed<br>enemy on one<br>Unarmed Attack<br>during your turn.<br><br>Once per encounter, when you deal damage with an<br>Unarmed Attack<br>to a target that has been denied its<br>Dexterity<br>bonus to<br>Reflex Defense<br>, make a second<br>Unarmed<br>attack against the target&#x27;s<br>Fortitude Defense<br>as a<br>Free Action<br>. If successful, you render the target incapable of speech until the end of your next turn. This is a<br>Stunning<br>effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you have the<br>K&#x27;tara Expertise<br>Talent, you can spend two<br>Swift Actions<br>to cause a single adjacent enemy to be<br>Flat-Footed<br>against your first attack during the same round.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/K&#x27;tara_Training</em></p>","martialArtsFeat":true,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex","defense.fortitude","turn.on-current-turn","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"K'tara Training: Converted from false defense metadata to an unarmed flat-footed target damage option.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.fortitude","defense.reflex","turn.on-current-turn","turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Converted from false defense metadata to an unarmed flat-footed target damage option."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["defense.fortitude","defense.reflex","turn.on-current-turn","turn.once-per-round"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"ktaraFlatFootedStrike","label":"K'tara Flat-Footed Strike","control":"toggle","requiresUnarmed":true,"requiresTargetFlatFooted":true,"damageExtraWeaponDice":1,"summary":"On one unarmed attack during your turn against a flat-footed target, add +1 weapon die."},{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"ktaraMuteStrike","label":"K'tara Mute Strike","control":"toggle","requiresUnarmed":true,"requiresTargetDeniedDexBonus":true,"targetDefenseType":"fortitude","targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"CONDITION","condition":"mute","duration":"untilEndOfNextTurn","descriptor":"stunning","description":"Once per encounter follow-up unarmed attack vs Fortitude can render the target unable to speak until end of your next turn."}],"oncePer":"encounter","summary":"Once per encounter after damaging a target denied Dex to Reflex, resolve the follow-up unarmed attack vs Fortitude to mute the target."}],"status":"ktaraFlatFootedStrike_attack_option_phase12","description":"Converted from false defense metadata to an unarmed flat-footed target damage option."},"shortSummary":"Deal extra damage against Flat-Footed enemy.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/K'tara_Training","rawImport":{"name":"K'tara Training","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/K'tara_Training","pageTitle":"K'tara_Training","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\k_tara_training.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Martial Arts I\n,\nTrained\nin\nStealth","prerequisites":["Martial Arts I","Trained\nin\nStealth"],"effect":"You roll an extra die of damage against a\nFlat-Footed\nenemy on one\nUnarmed Attack\nduring your turn.\n\nOnce per encounter, when you deal damage with an\nUnarmed Attack\nto a target that has been denied its\nDexterity\nbonus to\nReflex Defense\n, make a second\nUnarmed\nattack against the target's\nFortitude Defense\nas a\nFree Action\n. If successful, you render the target incapable of speech until the end of your next turn. This is a\nStunning\neffect.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"If you have the\nK'tara Expertise\nTalent, you can spend two\nSwift Actions\nto cause a single adjacent enemy to be\nFlat-Footed\nagainst your first attack during the same round.","indexPrerequisites":"Martial Arts I , Trained in Stealth","indexBenefit":"Deal extra damage against Flat-Footed enemy. Render target Mute .","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Martial Arts Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nMartial Arts Feats\n\nYou are trained in the K'tara style of\nUnarmed\nfighting, which enables you to neutralize enemies before they even know that you are present.\n\nPrerequisites:\nMartial Arts I\n,\nTrained\nin\nStealth\n\nEffect:\nYou roll an extra die of damage against a\nFlat-Footed\nenemy on one\nUnarmed Attack\nduring your turn.\n\nOnce per encounter, when you deal damage with an\nUnarmed Attack\nto a target that has been denied its\nDexterity\nbonus to\nReflex Defense\n, make a second\nUnarmed\nattack against the target's\nFortitude Defense\nas a\nFree Action\n. If successful, you render the target incapable of speech until the end of your next turn. This is a\nStunning\neffect.\n\nSpecial:\nIf you have the\nK'tara Expertise\nTalent, you can spend two\nSwift Actions\nto cause a single adjacent enemy to be\nFlat-Footed\nagainst your first attack during the same round."},"prerequisitesText":"Martial Arts I\n,\nTrained\nin\nStealth","effect":"You roll an extra die of damage against a\nFlat-Footed\nenemy on one\nUnarmed Attack\nduring your turn.\n\nOnce per encounter, when you deal damage with an\nUnarmed Attack\nto a target that has been denied its\nDexterity\nbonus to\nReflex Defense\n, make a second\nUnarmed\nattack against the target's\nFortitude Defense\nas a\nFree Action\n. If successful, you render the target incapable of speech until the end of your next turn. This is a\nStunning\neffect."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.379Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex","defense.fortitude","turn.on-current-turn","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.ktara_training"}}}
{"_id":"1e0222988b4e8714","name":"Force Regimen Mastery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You learn a number of Force Regimens equal to 1 + your Wisdom modifier (minimum 1).","prerequisite":"Force Sensitivity, Trained in Use the Force","special":"You can take this Feat more than once. Each time you take this Feat, you learn a number of additional Force Regimens equal to 1 + your Wisdom modifier (minimum 1). If your Wisdom modifier permanently increases, you immediately gain a number of Force Regimens equal to the number of Force Regimen Mastery Feats you have taken.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Jedi Academy Training Manual","page":31,"tags":["ability_wisdom","feat","force"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Sensitivity<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Use the Force</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You learn a number of<br>Force Regimens<br>equal to 1 + your<br>Wisdom<br>modifier (minimum 1).</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can take this Feat more than once. Each time you take this Feat, you learn a number of additional<br>Force Regimens<br>equal to 1 + your<br>Wisdom<br>modifier (minimum 1). If your<br>Wisdom<br>modifier permanently increases, you immediately gain a number of<br>Force Regimens<br>equal to the number of Force Regimen Mastery Feats you have taken.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Regimen_Mastery</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"usetheforce"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"grant_unlock","applicationScope":"force_regimen_picker_and_force_tab_cards","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Force Regimen Mastery now has Force Regimen data/pack stubs, but selection and active-regimen UI are intentionally pending dedicated picker/sheet work.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase18-force-regimen-stubs","metadataNotes":"Phase 18 creates Force Regimen data/pack stubs by name only; individual regimen text/effects are pending.","implementationStatus":"implemented_selection_and_activation_phase22","description":"Grants Force Regimen selections through the Force Regimen progression step. Known regimens appear as Force-tab cards and roll Use the Force when performed.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Force Regimen Mastery data stubs exist; selection picker and Force-tab UI pending.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"force_regimen_picker_required","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase18-force-regimen-stubs"}],"deferredReason":"Requires dedicated Force Regimen selection step and Force-tab UI before learned regimens can be chosen or activated."},"shortSummary":"Learn a number of Force Regimens equal to 1 + your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1).","prerequisitesText":"Force Sensitivity, Trained in Use the Force","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Regimen_Mastery","effect":"You learn a number of\nForce Regimens\nequal to 1 + your\nWisdom\nmodifier (minimum 1)."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.379Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.force_regimen_mastery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Regimen_Mastery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]},"forceRegimenStubPhase":"phase18-force-regimen-stubs"}}}
{"_id":"1e21ddf471811265","name":"Tumble Defense","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When an opponent attempts to Tumble through a square you threaten with a melee weapon with which you are proficient, add your Base Attack Bonus to the DC of the Acrobatics check made to Tumble. If the target fails the Acrobatics check to Tumble, you can make an Attack of Opportunity against that opponent as normal.","prerequisite":"None","special":"You cannot use this Feat when you are Flat-Footed.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":30,"tags":["defense","feat","general","mobility","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When an opponent attempts to<br>Tumble<br>through a square you threaten with a melee weapon with which you are proficient, add your<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>to the DC of the<br>Acrobatics<br>check made to<br>Tumble<br>. If the target fails the<br>Acrobatics<br>check to<br>Tumble<br>, you can make an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>against that opponent as normal.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You cannot use this Feat when you are<br>Flat-Footed<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tumble_Defense</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Makes it harder for opponents to Tumble past you.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"targeted_defense_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Makes it harder for opponents to Tumble past you.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"conditional_defense_metadata_phase14","passiveStateRules":[{"type":"TUMBLE_DC_BONUS_AGAINST_YOU","value":5,"description":"+5 to Acrobatics/Tumble DCs to move through your threatened area."}]},"shortSummary":"Your martial ability makes it harder for opponents to Tumble past.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tumble_Defense","effect":"When an opponent attempts to\nTumble\nthrough a square you threaten with a melee weapon with which you are proficient, add your\nBase Attack Bonus\nto the DC of the\nAcrobatics\ncheck made to\nTumble\n. If the target fails the\nAcrobatics\ncheck to\nTumble\n, you can make an\nAttack of Opportunity\nagainst that opponent as normal."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.379Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.tumble_defense","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tumble_Defense","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"1ea7da65feb15b18","name":"Exotic Weapon Proficiency","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Select a single weapon from either the Exotic Weapons (Melee) or Exotic Weapons (Ranged) weapon groups; you make attack rolls with the selected weapon without penalty.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"You can gain this Feat multiple times. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Exotic Weapon.","normalText":"A character who uses a weapon without being proficient with it takes a -5 penalty to attack rolls.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["build_enabler","feat","general","offense","weapon_access","choice_required","immediate_choice","weapon_choice","exotic_weapon_choice","legacy_choice_alias","choice_source_fixed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Select a single weapon from either the<br>Exotic Weapons (Melee)<br>or<br>Exotic Weapons (Ranged)<br>weapon groups; you make attack rolls with the selected weapon without penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> A character who uses a weapon without being proficient with it takes a -5 penalty to attack rolls.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can gain this Feat multiple times. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different<br>Exotic Weapon<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Exotic_Weapon_Proficiency</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Choice-backed proficiency with one exotic weapon.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"grant_choice_required","applicationScope":"proficiency_grant_choice","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choice-backed proficiency with one exotic weapon.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"proficiency_choice_metadata_phase14","proficiencyGrants":[{"type":"EXOTIC_WEAPON_PROFICIENCY","targetFromSelectedChoice":true,"description":"Grants proficiency with the selected exotic weapon."}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"tagged_for_later_dialog_backfill","choiceKind":"weapon_proficiency","routeThrough":"Weapon Proficiency","branch":"exotic","repeatable":true,"legacyChoiceAliasOf":"Weapon Proficiency","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#weapon_proficiency.exotic","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.weaponProficiency","notes":"Legacy feat row retained for compatibility; future UI should prefer the grouped Weapon Proficiency feat exotic branch.","choiceSource":"fixed","provides":"weapon_proficiency","resultShape":"exotic_weapon"},"shortSummary":"Wield an Exotic Weapon without penalty.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Exotic_Weapon_Proficiency","effect":"Select a single weapon from either the\nExotic Weapons (Melee)\nor\nExotic Weapons (Ranged)\nweapon groups; you make attack rolls with the selected weapon without penalty."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.379Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.exotic_weapon_proficiency","requiresImmediateChoice":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Exotic_Weapon_Proficiency","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"1ec2b64343aca60e","name":"Close Combat Escape","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you successfully use Acrobatics to escape a Grapple, you can spend a Swift Action to make a single attack with a melee weapon or an Unarmed attack against the opponent that had Grappled you. If the attack hits, it deals normal damage, and your opponent is considered Flat-Footed until the start of its next turn.","prerequisite":"Trained in Acrobatics","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":20,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Acrobatics</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you successfully use<br>Acrobatics<br>to escape a<br>Grapple<br>, you can spend a<br>Swift Action<br>to make a single attack with a melee weapon or an<br>Unarmed<br>attack against the opponent that had<br>Grappled<br>you. If the attack hits, it deals normal damage, and your opponent is considered<br>Flat-Footed<br>until the start of its next turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Close_Combat_Escape</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"a6c5e98148aad9a9"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Escape a grapple and make an attack.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"action_or_reaction_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Escape a grapple and make an attack.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase14","actionRules":[{"type":"ESCAPE_GRAPPLE_AND_ATTACK"}]},"shortSummary":"Escape Grapple and attack.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Acrobatics","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Close_Combat_Escape","effect":"When you successfully use\nAcrobatics\nto escape a\nGrapple\n, you can spend a\nSwift Action\nto make a single attack with a melee weapon or an\nUnarmed\nattack against the opponent that had\nGrappled\nyou. If the attack hits, it deals normal damage, and your opponent is considered\nFlat-Footed\nuntil the start of its next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.379Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.close_combat_escape","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Close_Combat_Escape","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"1f2f70d34a17667d","name":"Vehicular Combat","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per round (as a Reaction), when you are piloting a Vehicle or Starship, you may negate a weapon hit by making a successful Pilot check. The DC of the Skill Check is equal to the result of the attack roll you wish to negate. In addition, while you are piloting a Vehicle, you are considered proficient with pilot-operated Vehicle Weapons.","prerequisite":"Trained in Pilot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["feat","general","skill_pilot","skill_synergy","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Pilot</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per round (as a<br>Reaction<br>), when you are piloting a<br>Vehicle<br>or<br>Starship<br>, you may negate a weapon hit by making a successful<br>Pilot<br>check. The DC of the<br>Skill Check<br>is equal to the result of the attack roll you wish to negate. In addition, while you are piloting a<br>Vehicle<br>, you are considered proficient with pilot-operated<br>Vehicle Weapons<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Combat</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"b8dad0c963f046c6"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rider_effect_phase7","description":"Vehicular Combat: modeled as a rider/action rule, not a numeric modifier.","rules":[{"type":"REACTION","trigger":"vehicleHitWhilePiloting","skill":"pilot","dc":"incomingAttackRoll","effect":"negateHit","limit":"oncePerRound"},{"type":"PROFICIENCY_GRANT","target":"vehicleWeapon.pilotOperated","condition":"whilePilotingVehicle"}],"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Vehicular Combat: numeric scaffold disabled by Phase 7 (description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus)","mechanicsMode":"metadata_note","applicationScope":"not_a_numeric_modifier","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus","metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"vehicle_reaction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Once per round reaction while piloting: make Pilot check to negate a vehicle/starship hit; also grants proficiency with pilot-operated vehicle weapons.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Negate one attack per round against the Vehicle you're piloting.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Pilot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Combat","effect":"Once per round (as a\nReaction\n), when you are piloting a\nVehicle\nor\nStarship\n, you may negate a weapon hit by making a successful\nPilot\ncheck. The DC of the\nSkill Check\nis equal to the result of the attack roll you wish to negate. In addition, while you are piloting a\nVehicle\n, you are considered proficient with pilot-operated\nVehicle Weapons\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.vehicular_combat","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Combat","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"1f404db00518aeed","name":"Damage Conversion","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you take damage from an attack against you (other than an Area Attack, or an attack that deals Ion or Force damage) and that damage equals or exceeds your Damage Threshold, you can take an additional 10 points of damage instead of moving down the Condition Track. Each subsequent time you use this Feat in a single encounter, the additional damage you take increases by 5 points.","prerequisite":"Droid, Dexterity 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":19,"tags":["condition_track","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>,<br>Dexterity<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you take damage from an attack against you (other than an<br>Area Attack<br>, or an attack that deals<br>Ion<br>or<br>Force<br>damage) and that damage equals or exceeds your<br>Damage Threshold<br>, you can take an additional 10 points of damage instead of moving down the<br>Condition Track<br>. Each subsequent time you use this Feat in a single encounter, the additional damage you take increases by 5 points.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_Conversion</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Damage Conversion: Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"passive_choice_required","applicationScope":"selected_choice_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"non_numeric_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Damage Conversion now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","reactionRules":[],"resourceRules":{"phase10Special":[{"type":"CONVERT_THRESHOLD_CT_STEP_TO_EXTRA_DAMAGE","trigger":"damageEqualsOrExceedsThreshold","excludedDamageTypes":["ion","force"],"excludedAreaAttack":true,"baseExtraDamage":10,"subsequentUseIncrease":5,"description":"Droid may take extra damage instead of moving down the Condition Track; cost rises each use this encounter."}]},"status":"non_numeric_rule_phase10","description":"Damage Conversion now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"Take additional Hit Point damage instead of moving down the Condition Track.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_Conversion","effect":"When you take damage from an attack against you (other than an\nArea Attack\n, or an attack that deals\nIon\nor\nForce\ndamage) and that damage equals or exceeds your\nDamage Threshold\n, you can take an additional 10 points of damage instead of moving down the\nCondition Track\n. Each subsequent time you use this Feat in a single encounter, the additional damage you take increases by 5 points."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.damage_conversion","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_Conversion","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"1f594024b4757109","name":"Lightning Draw","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you can draw a holstered weapon and attack as a single Standard Action.","prerequisite":"Quick Draw","special":"","normalText":"With the Quick Draw feat, drawing or holstering a weapon is a Swift Action.","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":26,"tags":["feat","general","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Quick Draw</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, you can draw a holstered weapon and attack as a single<br>Standard Action<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> With the<br>Quick Draw<br>feat, drawing or holstering a weapon is a<br>Swift Action<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Lightning_Draw</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Draw and fire as a Standard Action.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"action_or_reaction_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Draw and fire as a Standard Action.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase14","actionRules":[{"type":"DRAW_AND_ATTACK_AS_STANDARD_ACTION"}]},"shortSummary":"Draw and fire as a Standard Action.","prerequisitesText":"Quick Draw","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Lightning_Draw","effect":"Once per encounter, you can draw a holstered weapon and attack as a single\nStandard Action\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.lightning_draw","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Lightning_Draw","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"203f7fa521105d0b","name":"Tool Frenzy","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Standard Action, using Appendages not normally considered Weapons, you can make several strikes as a single attack against a single target. Make an Unarmed melee attack with a +2 bonus; until the end of your next turn, you take a -2 penalty to your Reflex Defense. Use the damage die of the highest rated Appendage when determining damage.","prerequisite":"Droid, Small size or larger, 2+ Tool Appendages","special":"True melee or ranged Weapons are not considered Tools for the purposes of this Feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":26,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>, Small size or larger, 2+<br>Tool<br>Appendages</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Standard Action<br>, using<br>Appendages<br>not normally considered<br>Weapons<br>, you can make several strikes as a single attack against a single target. Make an<br>Unarmed<br>melee attack with a +2 bonus; until the end of your next turn, you take a -2 penalty to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>. Use the damage die of the highest rated<br>Appendage<br>when determining damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> True melee or ranged<br>Weapons<br>are not considered<br>Tools<br>for the purposes of this Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tool_Frenzy</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Tool Frenzy: Implemented as CombatOptionResolver/rider metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"passive_choice_required","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as CombatOptionResolver/rider metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Tool Frenzy now has explicit roll-context/rider metadata from its description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"toolFrenzy","label":"Tool Frenzy","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","requiresWeaponGroups":["unarmed","tool appendage","appendage"],"attackModifier":2,"defenseModifier":{"target":"defense.reflex","type":"untyped","value":-2,"duration":"untilEndOfNextTurn"},"summary":"Standard action appendage/unarmed strike: +2 attack, then -2 Reflex until end of next turn."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Tool Frenzy now has explicit roll-context/rider metadata from its description."},"shortSummary":"Gain +2 to attack rolls and damage rolls with nonweapon Appendages in exchange for a -2 penalty to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Small size or larger, 2+ Tool Appendages","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tool_Frenzy","effect":"As a\nStandard Action\n, using\nAppendages\nnot normally considered\nWeapons\n, you can make several strikes as a single attack against a single target. Make an\nUnarmed\nmelee attack with a +2 bonus; until the end of your next turn, you take a -2 penalty to your\nReflex Defense\n. Use the damage die of the highest rated\nAppendage\nwhen determining damage."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.tool_frenzy","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tool_Frenzy","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"21a0af5ef58172a0","name":"Quick Comeback","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Recover quickly after being moved down the Condition Track by damage.","prerequisite":"Gamorrean","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["condition_track","cover_play","feat","racial","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["Gamorrean"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Gamorrean</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you are moved down the<br>Condition Track<br>by an attack that deals damage that equals or exceeds your<br>Damage Threshold<br>, until the end of your next turn you can move +1 step on the<br>Condition Track<br>as a single<br>Swift Action<br>. You can use this Feat only once per attack that moves you down the<br>Condition Track<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Comeback</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Recovery hook after damage moves you down the Condition Track.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"condition_track_recovery_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Recovery hook after damage moves you down the Condition Track.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"condition_track_rider_metadata_phase14","riderRules":[{"type":"QUICK_COMEBACK_RECOVERY","description":"Recover quickly after damage moves you down the Condition Track. Metadata only until the damage/turn hook exposes the trigger."}]},"shortSummary":"Recover quickly after being moved down the Condition Track by damage.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Comeback","rawImport":{"name":"Quick Comeback","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Comeback","pageTitle":"Quick_Comeback","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\quick_comeback.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Gamorrean","prerequisites":["Gamorrean"],"effect":"Whenever you are moved down the\nCondition Track\nby an attack that deals damage that equals or exceeds your\nDamage Threshold\n, until the end of your next turn you can move +1 step on the\nCondition Track\nas a single\nSwift Action\n. You can use this Feat only once per attack that moves you down the\nCondition Track\n.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Gamorrean","indexBenefit":"Recover quickly after being moved down the Condition Track by damage.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nWhen you take damage that sends you reeling, you can recover quickly and get back in the fight.\n\nPrerequisite:\nGamorrean\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you are moved down the\nCondition Track\nby an attack that deals damage that equals or exceeds your\nDamage Threshold\n, until the end of your next turn you can move +1 step on the\nCondition Track\nas a single\nSwift Action\n. You can use this Feat only once per attack that moves you down the\nCondition Track\n."},"prerequisitesText":"Gamorrean","effect":"Whenever you are moved down the\nCondition Track\nby an attack that deals damage that equals or exceeds your\nDamage Threshold\n, until the end of your next turn you can move +1 step on the\nCondition Track\nas a single\nSwift Action\n. You can use this Feat only once per attack that moves you down the\nCondition Track\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.quick_comeback"}}}
{"_id":"223a5c14f2ea4737","name":"Ample Foraging","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Grant a bonus to allies' Fortitude Defense by foraging.","prerequisite":"Ewok","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","racial","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-ewok"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Ewok</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you make a<br>Survival<br>check for the<br>Basic Survival<br>application of the Skill, each creature that consumes the food you find gains a +2 morale bonus to his or her<br>Fortitude Defense<br>until the start of the next day.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Ample_Foraging</em></p>\n<p><strong>Automation:</strong> If you have this feat, the Basic Survival extra skill use displays a reminder that creatures who consume the food gain +2 morale bonus to Fortitude Defense until the start of the next day. The GM adjudicates who consumed the food and when the benefit expires.</p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.fortitude","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.fortitude"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Ample Foraging: Basic Survival food grants consumers +2 morale Fortitude until the next day; this is an applied ally buff, not the actor's static Fortitude.","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_note","applicationScope":"survival_basic_survival_extra_use","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.fortitude"],"conditionSummary":"Basic Survival food grants consumers +2 morale Fortitude until the next day; this is an applied ally buff, not the actor's static Fortitude."}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_note","applicationScope":"survival_basic_survival_extra_use","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["defense.fortitude"],"metadataPhase":"phase23-feat-cleanup","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","skillUseEffects":[{"id":"ample_foraging_basic_survival_food","skill":"survival","application":"Basic Survival","type":"ALLY_FOOD_BUFF_NOTE","bonus":{"target":"defense.fortitude","value":2,"type":"morale"},"duration":"untilStartOfNextDay","description":"If creatures consume the food found by this Basic Survival check, they gain +2 morale bonus to Fortitude Defense until the start of the next day. GM adjudicates consumers and expiration."}],"status":"survival_extra_use_note_phase23","description":"Shown as a note on the Basic Survival extra skill use: creatures that consume the food gain +2 morale Fortitude Defense until the next day.","gmManaged":true},"shortSummary":"Grant a bonus to allies' Fortitude Defense by foraging.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Ample_Foraging","rawImport":{"name":"Ample Foraging","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Ample_Foraging","pageTitle":"Ample_Foraging","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\ample_foraging.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Ewok","prerequisites":["Ewok"],"effect":"Whenever you make a\nSurvival\ncheck for the\nBasic Survival\napplication of the Skill, each creature that consumes the food you find gains a +2 morale bonus to his or her\nFortitude Defense\nuntil the start of the next day.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Ewok","indexBenefit":"Grant a bonus to allies' Fortitude Defense by foraging.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou always seem to find the best food and shelter for yourself and your allies, increasing your ability to resist the hazards of nature.\n\nPrerequisite:\nEwok\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you make a\nSurvival\ncheck for the\nBasic Survival\napplication of the Skill, each creature that consumes the food you find gains a +2 morale bonus to his or her\nFortitude Defense\nuntil the start of the next day."},"prerequisitesText":"Ewok","effect":"Whenever you make a\nSurvival\ncheck for the\nBasic Survival\napplication of the Skill, each creature that consumes the food you find gains a +2 morale bonus to his or her\nFortitude Defense\nuntil the start of the next day."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.fortitude"],"id":"swse.feat.ample_foraging"}}}
{"_id":"225c535ebc74e54a","name":"Deft Charge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"After you Charge, you can take Swift Actions, Reactions, and Free Actions before your turn ends.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"Without this Feat, Charging ends your turn immediately after the attack is resolved.","sourcebook":"Rebellion Era Campaign Guide","page":18,"tags":["action_economy","charge","feat","free_action","general","offense","offense_melee","reaction","swift_action"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> After you<br>Charge<br>, you can take<br>Swift Actions<br>,<br>Reactions<br>, and<br>Free Actions<br>before your turn ends.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> Without this Feat,<br>Charging<br>ends your turn immediately after the attack is resolved.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deft_Charge</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Charge action economy flag; no sheet modifier.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"passive_capability","applicationScope":"charge_action_economy_context","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Charge action economy flag; no sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"deft_charge_metadata_phase13","actionRules":[{"type":"ACTIONS_AFTER_CHARGE","allowedActions":["swift","reaction","free"],"description":"You may take Swift, Reaction, and Free Actions after a Charge before your turn ends."}]},"shortSummary":"Take Swift Actions, Reactions, and Free Actions after you Charge before your turn ends.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deft_Charge","effect":"After you\nCharge\n, you can take\nSwift Actions\n,\nReactions\n, and\nFree Actions\nbefore your turn ends."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.deft_charge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deft_Charge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"22d0f64aa8ac99df","name":"Riflemaster","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make a ranged attack with a Rifle with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of Rifle you use.\n\n- Blaster Carbine: You can Brace a Blaster Carbine set to Autofire, even though it is not an Autofire -only weapon.\n- Blaster Rifle: You treat the Blaster Rifle as an Accurate Weapon.\n- Heavy Blaster Rifle: When you use a Heavy Blaster Rifle, the damage dice increase from d10 to d12.\n- Light Repeating Blaster: You treat the Light Repeating Blaster as if it were Medium instead of Large.","prerequisite":"Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","offense_ranged","weapon_rifle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make a ranged attack with a<br>Rifle<br>with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of<br>Rifle<br>you use.<br><br>- Blaster Carbine : You can Brace a Blaster Carbine set to Autofire , even though it is not an Autofire -only weapon.<br>- Blaster Rifle : You treat the Blaster Rifle as an Accurate Weapon.<br>- Heavy Blaster Rifle : When you use a Heavy Blaster Rifle , the damage dice increase from d10 to d12.<br>- Light Repeating Blaster : You treat the Light Repeating Blaster as if it were Medium instead of Large.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Riflemaster</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Rifle-family bonuses and weapon property hooks.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"weapon_family_rules","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rifle-family bonuses and weapon property hooks.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"weapon_family_rules_phase14","rules":[{"type":"WEAPON_DAMAGE_DIE_STEP","weaponGroups":["heavy-blaster-rifle"],"value":1,"description":"Heavy Blaster Rifle damage dice improve from d10 to d12."}],"weaponPropertyRules":[{"type":"TREAT_AS_ACCURATE","requiresWeaponText":["blaster-rifle"],"description":"Treat Blaster Rifles as Accurate Weapons."},{"type":"ALLOW_BRACE_AUTOFIRE","requiresWeaponText":["blaster-carbine"],"description":"Can brace a Blaster Carbine set to autofire."},{"type":"SIZE_FOR_WIELDING","requiresWeaponText":["light-repeating-blaster"],"effectiveSize":"medium","description":"Treat Light Repeating Blasters as Medium instead of Large."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain benefits when using certain Rifles.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Riflemaster","effect":"When you make a ranged attack with a\nRifle\nwith which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of\nRifle\nyou use.\n\n- Blaster Carbine : You can Brace a Blaster Carbine set to Autofire , even though it is not an Autofire -only weapon.\n- Blaster Rifle : You treat the Blaster Rifle as an Accurate Weapon.\n- Heavy Blaster Rifle : When you use a Heavy Blaster Rifle , the damage dice increase from d10 to d12.\n- Light Repeating Blaster : You treat the Light Repeating Blaster as if it were Medium instead of Large."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.riflemaster","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Riflemaster","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"2357f4a68fe571fb","name":"Sharp Senses","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Increase the die type when adding Force Points to a Perception check.","prerequisite":"Mon Calamari","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase10","feat","force_point_spend","racial","resource_spend","skill_perception","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity","species_rule"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-mon-calamari"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Mon Calamari</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you spend a<br>Force Point<br>to add to a<br>Perception<br>check, increase the die type by two steps (From d6 to d10, or from d8 to d12).</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sharp_Senses</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"species_rule_phase10_executable_hook","description":"Sharp Senses: increase Force Point die type on Perception checks.","rules":[{"type":"FORCE_POINT_DIE_STEP","value":1,"domains":["skill"],"skills":["perception"],"description":"Increase the die type when adding Force Points to a Perception check."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"rule_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Implemented by a rule hook; exact static-sheet behavior depends on the consuming engine.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Increase the die type when adding Force Points to a Perception check.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sharp_Senses","rawImport":{"name":"Sharp Senses","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sharp_Senses","pageTitle":"Sharp_Senses","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\sharp_senses.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Mon Calamari","prerequisites":["Mon Calamari"],"effect":"Whenever you spend a\nForce Point\nto add to a\nPerception\ncheck, increase the die type by two steps (From d6 to d10, or from d8 to d12).","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Mon Calamari","indexBenefit":"Increase the die type when adding Force Points to a Perception check.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYour senses have been honed to the point where you can spot things that others could never see.\n\nPrerequisite:\nMon Calamari\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you spend a\nForce Point\nto add to a\nPerception\ncheck, increase the die type by two steps (From d6 to d10, or from d8 to d12)."},"prerequisitesText":"Mon Calamari","effect":"Whenever you spend a\nForce Point\nto add to a\nPerception\ncheck, increase the die type by two steps (From d6 to d10, or from d8 to d12)."},"effects":[{"_id":"73c8fbc0-142d-460e-ba02-c9455de3a848","name":"Sharp Senses","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Sharp Senses","effectType":"special","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.sharp_senses"}}}
{"_id":"252b67d6e31c377e","name":"Weapon Finesse","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using a Light Melee Weapon or a Lightsaber, you may use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["ability_dexterity","ability_strength","accuracy","dexterity_synergy","feat","finesse","general","lightsaber","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958","21dfe84d159a1b7f"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using a Light Melee Weapon or a<br>Lightsaber<br>, you may use your<br>Dexterity<br>modifier instead of your<br>Strength<br>modifier on attack rolls.</p>\n<h3>Additional Weapon Finesse Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Weapon Focus<br>):<br>When you are wielding a single one-handed weapon for which you have<br>Weapon Focus<br>, you can treat that weapon as a Light Weapon.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Finesse</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Weapon Finesse: Implemented as structured rule metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"passive_choice_required","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as structured rule metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"weapon_attack_ability","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Weapon Finesse: roll hook uses Dexterity instead of Strength for light melee weapons and lightsabers when beneficial.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 converts clear description-guided feats from scaffold modifiers into structured rule metadata.","status":"attack_ability_rule_phase9","description":"Weapon Finesse: roll hook uses Dexterity instead of Strength for light melee weapons and lightsabers when beneficial.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_ABILITY_SUBSTITUTION","weaponGroups":["light","light-melee","lightsaber"],"fromAbility":"str","toAbility":"dex","useBetter":true,"description":"Use Dexterity instead of Strength on attacks with light melee weapons and lightsabers when it is better."}]},"shortSummary":"Use Dexterity modifier instead of Strength modifier on attack rolls with Light Melee Weapons and Lightsabers.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Finesse","effect":"When using a Light Melee Weapon or a\nLightsaber\n, you may use your\nDexterity\nmodifier instead of your\nStrength\nmodifier on attack rolls."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.weapon_finesse","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Finesse","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"25aaf859b6109c02","name":"Predictive Defense","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can use either your Dexterity modifier or your Intelligence modifier to determine your Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"Intelligence 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":26,"tags":["ability_dexterity","ability_intelligence","defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can use either your<br>Dexterity<br>modifier or your<br>Intelligence<br>modifier to determine your<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Predictive_Defense</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Predictive Defense: Implemented by DefenseCalculator as best-of Dex/Int Reflex ability selection.","mechanicsMode":"needs_review","applicationScope":"predicate_context_unknown","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented by DefenseCalculator as best-of Dex/Int Reflex ability selection.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor","staticSheetPolicy":"include","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Predictive Defense now changes Reflex Defense ability selection instead of using a fake attack modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","defenseAbilityRules":[{"type":"USE_BETTER_ABILITY","defense":"reflex","abilities":["dex","int"],"description":"Use the better of Dexterity or Intelligence modifier for Reflex Defense."}],"status":"static_defense_ability_phase10","description":"Predictive Defense now changes Reflex Defense ability selection instead of using a fake attack modifier."},"shortSummary":"Use Dexterity or Intelligence to determine Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Intelligence 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Predictive_Defense","effect":"You can use either your\nDexterity\nmodifier or your\nIntelligence\nmodifier to determine your\nReflex Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.predictive_defense","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Predictive_Defense","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"25ba21b021086a71","name":"Disturbing Presence","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you succeed on a DC 15 Deception check, you can move through the Threatened area or Fighting Space of an enemy as part of your move action without provoking an attack of opportunity. Each Threatened space or occupied space that you move through in this manner counts as 2 squares of movement.","prerequisite":"Trained in Deception","special":"","normalText":"You can Tumble through an occupied enemy square only by using the Acrobatics Skill.","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":18,"tags":["feat","general","multi_target","skill_deception","skill_synergy","social"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Deception</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you succeed on a DC 15<br>Deception<br>check, you can move through the<br>Threatened<br>area or<br>Fighting Space<br>of an enemy as part of your move action without provoking an attack of opportunity. Each<br>Threatened<br>space or occupied space that you move through in this manner counts as 2 squares of movement.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You can<br>Tumble<br>through an occupied enemy square only by using the<br>Acrobatics<br>Skill.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disturbing_Presence</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"deception_movement_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Disturbing Presence: DC 15 Deception lets you move through threatened/fighting spaces without provoking; spaces cost double movement.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_rule_phase16","description":"Disturbing Presence: DC 15 Deception lets you move through threatened/fighting spaces without provoking; spaces cost double movement.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Disturbing Presence: DC 15 Deception lets you move through threatened/fighting spaces without provoking; spaces cost double movement.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"deception_movement_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"MOVEMENT_THROUGH_THREATENED_WITH_DECEPTION","skillKey":"deception","dc":15,"applications":["move through threatened area","move through fighting space"],"movementCostMultiplier":2,"provokes":false,"description":"DC 15 Deception: move through threatened/fighting spaces without provoking; each such square costs 2 squares."}]},"shortSummary":"Make a Deception check to move through a Threatened Area without provoking Attacks of Opportunity.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Deception","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disturbing_Presence","effect":"If you succeed on a DC 15\nDeception\ncheck, you can move through the\nThreatened\narea or\nFighting Space\nof an enemy as part of your move action without provoking an attack of opportunity. Each\nThreatened\nspace or occupied space that you move through in this manner counts as 2 squares of movement."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.disturbing_presence","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disturbing_Presence","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"25ce950a142f969d","name":"Adaptable Talent","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose one Talent that you meet the prerequisites for, from a Class you possess. Once per day, after at least 6 hours of rest, you can choose to swap out one of your current Talents for the Talent you chose for this Feat. The Talent you swap out cannot be the prerequisite for any other Talent you have. You can swap back to your original Talent after at least 6 hours of rest.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":23,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Choose one<br>Talent<br>that you meet the prerequisites for, from a<br>Class<br>you possess. Once per day, after at least 6 hours of rest, you can choose to swap out one of your current<br>Talents<br>for the<br>Talent<br>you chose for this Feat. The<br>Talent<br>you swap out cannot be the prerequisite for any other<br>Talent<br>you have. You can swap back to your original<br>Talent<br>after at least 6 hours of rest.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Adaptable_Talent</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Adaptable Talent","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Choose one owned talent for the adaptable talent swap rule.","metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","disabledReason":"Phase 6: choice captured now; execution waits for roll/action context wiring."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose one owned talent for the adaptable talent swap rule.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated."},"shortSummary":"Temporarily gain access to an additional Talent.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Adaptable_Talent","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"talent_choice","repeatable":false,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.adaptable_talent","choiceSource":"actorState","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.talent_choice"},"effect":"Choose one\nTalent\nthat you meet the prerequisites for, from a\nClass\nyou possess. Once per day, after at least 6 hours of rest, you can choose to swap out one of your current\nTalents\nfor the\nTalent\nyou chose for this Feat. The\nTalent\nyou swap out cannot be the prerequisite for any other\nTalent\nyou have. You can swap back to your original\nTalent\nafter at least 6 hours of rest."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.adaptable_talent","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Adaptable_Talent","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"2624254a23604d5b","name":"Poison Resistance","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 bonus to your Fortitude Defense when attacked by Poison. If the attack succeeds, you take only half damage.","prerequisite":"Constitution 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":28,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Constitution<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +5 bonus to your<br>Fortitude Defense<br>when attacked by<br>Poison<br>. If the attack succeeds, you take only half damage.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Poison_Resistance</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"con","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"+5 Fortitude Defense against poison.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"targeted_defense_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"+5 Fortitude Defense against poison.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"conditional_defense_metadata_phase14","passiveStateRules":[{"type":"DEFENSE_BONUS_AGAINST_POISON","target":"defense.fortitude","value":5,"description":"+5 Fortitude Defense against Poison."}]},"shortSummary":"You are inherently more resistant to Poison.","prerequisitesText":"Constitution 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Poison_Resistance","effect":"You gain a +5 bonus to your\nFortitude Defense\nwhen attacked by\nPoison\n. If the attack succeeds, you take only half damage."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.poison_resistance","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Poison_Resistance","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"2866d953b4b6245d","name":"Dive for Cover","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per turn, as a Reaction to being targeted by a ranged attack, you can make a Jump check to Long Jump. If you land in a square that provides you with Cover from your attacker, you gain the normal Cover bonus against the attack, even if you didn't have Cover at the time the attack was made. When you use this Feat, you always land Prone.","prerequisite":"Trained in Jump","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":22,"tags":["cover_play","defense","feat","general","reaction","skill_jump","skill_synergy","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Jump</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per turn, as a<br>Reaction<br>to being targeted by a ranged attack, you can make a<br>Jump<br>check to<br>Long Jump<br>. If you land in a square that provides you with<br>Cover<br>from your attacker, you gain the normal<br>Cover<br>bonus against the attack, even if you didn&#x27;t have<br>Cover<br>at the time the attack was made. When you use this Feat, you always land<br>Prone<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dive_for_Cover</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Jump for cover as a Reaction.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"action_or_reaction_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Jump for cover as a Reaction.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase14","actionRules":[{"type":"REACTION_JUMP_FOR_COVER"}]},"shortSummary":"Jump for Cover as a Reaction.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Jump","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dive_for_Cover","effect":"Once per turn, as a\nReaction\nto being targeted by a ranged attack, you can make a\nJump\ncheck to\nLong Jump\n. If you land in a square that provides you with\nCover\nfrom your attacker, you gain the normal\nCover\nbonus against the attack, even if you didn't have\nCover\nat the time the attack was made. When you use this Feat, you always land\nProne\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.dive_for_cover","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dive_for_Cover","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"289588197d691d64","name":"Advantageous Cover","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you have Cover, you take no damage from Area Attacks, even if the attack roll exceeds your Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"You take no damage from Area Attacks when you have Cover only if the attack roll misses.","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":32,"tags":["cover_play","defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Stealth</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you have<br>Cover<br>, you take no damage from<br>Area Attacks<br>, even if the attack roll exceeds your<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You take no damage from<br>Area Attacks<br>when you have<br>Cover<br>only if the attack roll misses.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Advantageous_Cover</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"6d2ac22d9fcf402f"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Improves benefits from cover.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"action_or_reaction_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Improves benefits from cover.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase14","actionRules":[{"type":"COVER_BENEFIT_UPGRADE"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain additional benefits from Cover.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Stealth","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Advantageous_Cover","effect":"When you have\nCover\n, you take no damage from\nArea Attacks\n, even if the attack roll exceeds your\nReflex Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.advantageous_cover","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Advantageous_Cover","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"28a02f0e5412dd53","name":"Fortifying Recovery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you take the Recover Action, you also gain a number of Bonus Hit Points equal to 2 x your Constitution bonus (Minimum 2). Damage is subtracted from the Bonus Hit Points first, and any Bonus Hit Points remaining at the end of encounter are lost. Bonus Hit Points do not stack.","prerequisite":"Constitution 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":23,"tags":["cover_play","defense","durability","feat","general","hit_points","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Constitution<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you take the<br>Recover<br>Action, you also gain a number of<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>equal to 2 x your<br>Constitution<br>bonus (Minimum 2). Damage is subtracted from the<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>first, and any<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>remaining at the end of encounter are lost.<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>do not stack.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fortifying_Recovery</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Fortifying Recovery: Old migrated numeric modifier disabled; represented by non-numeric rider/resource metadata.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit"],"conditionSummary":"Old migrated numeric modifier disabled; represented by non-numeric rider/resource metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"rider_effect","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Recover action grants bonus hit points equal to 2 x Constitution modifier, minimum 2.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 removes false numeric scaffolding and records description-driven rider metadata.","status":"recover_action_resource_phase9","description":"Recover action grants bonus hit points equal to 2 x Constitution modifier, minimum 2.","resourceRules":{"recoverAction":[{"type":"BONUS_HIT_POINTS_ON_RECOVER","valueFormula":"conModTimes2Minimum2","description":"Gain bonus HP on Recover action."}]}},"shortSummary":"Gain Bonus Hit Points when you Recover.","prerequisitesText":"Constitution 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fortifying_Recovery","effect":"When you take the\nRecover\nAction, you also gain a number of\nBonus Hit Points\nequal to 2 x your\nConstitution\nbonus (Minimum 2). Damage is subtracted from the\nBonus Hit Points\nfirst, and any\nBonus Hit Points\nremaining at the end of encounter are lost.\nBonus Hit Points\ndo not stack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.fortifying_recovery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fortifying_Recovery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"29173ea2d8416eea","name":"Flèche","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When Charging, turn any natural attack roll of 17+ into a Critical Hit.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":19,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, when you<br>Charge<br>, you can turn any natural attack roll of 17+ into a Critical Hit.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fl%C3%A8che</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Flèche: Converted from false attack bonus to a charge critical-threshold option.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit"],"conditionSummary":"Converted from false attack bonus to a charge critical-threshold option."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Rules text or predicates require a selected choice before the modifier can be safely applied.","predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"fleche","label":"Flèche","control":"toggle","requiresCharge":true,"requiresAttackType":"melee","criticalThreatNaturalMin":17,"oncePer":"encounter","summary":"Once per encounter while charging, treat a natural attack roll of 17+ as a critical hit."}],"status":"fleche_attack_option_phase12","description":"Converted from false attack bonus to a charge critical-threshold option."},"shortSummary":"When Charging, turn any natural attack roll of 17+ into a Critical Hit.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fl%C3%A8che","effect":"Once per encounter, when you\nCharge\n, you can turn any natural attack roll of 17+ into a Critical Hit."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.fl_che","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fl%C3%A8che","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"2942c0676644251b","name":"Tactical Advantage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you successfully damage an opponent using an Attack of Opportunity, you can immediately move 1 square in any direction. This movement does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"Combat Reflexes","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":29,"tags":["feat","general","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Combat Reflexes</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you successfully damage an opponent using an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>, you can immediately move 1 square in any direction. This movement does not provoke<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tactical_Advantage</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_of_opportunity_hit_reposition","staticSheetPolicy":"reaction_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Tactical Advantage: damaging with an attack of opportunity lets you move 1 square without provoking.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"aoo_hit_reaction_metadata_phase16","description":"Tactical Advantage: damaging with an attack of opportunity lets you move 1 square without provoking.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Tactical Advantage: damaging with an attack of opportunity lets you move 1 square without provoking.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"attack_of_opportunity_hit_reposition","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"reactionRules":[{"type":"MOVE_AFTER_SUCCESSFUL_AOO_DAMAGE","movementSquares":1,"provokes":false,"description":"After damaging with an Attack of Opportunity, move 1 square without provoking."}]},"shortSummary":"Make Attack of Opportunity and move 1 square.","prerequisitesText":"Combat Reflexes","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tactical_Advantage","effect":"When you successfully damage an opponent using an\nAttack of Opportunity\n, you can immediately move 1 square in any direction. This movement does not provoke\nAttacks of Opportunity\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.tactical_advantage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tactical_Advantage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"2956acfbfd27967d","name":"Hideous Visage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, as a Swift Action, you can make a Deception check against one opponent that can see you. If the check equals or exceeds the opponent's Will Defense, you move the target 1 square away from you and it takes a -1 penalty on all attacks until the start of your next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting Fear effect.","prerequisite":"Shapeshift Species Trait","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":24,"tags":["feat","general","skill_deception","skill_synergy"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Shapeshift Species Trait</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, as a<br>Swift Action<br>, you can make a<br>Deception<br>check against one opponent that can see you. If the check equals or exceeds the opponent&#x27;s<br>Will Defense<br>, you move the target 1 square away from you and it takes a -1 penalty on all attacks until the start of your next turn. This is a<br>Mind-Affecting<br>Fear effect.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hideous_Visage</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"deception_fear_encounter_power","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Hideous Visage: once per encounter swift Deception vs Will pushes the target and gives it -1 attack until your next turn.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_action_phase16","description":"Hideous Visage: once per encounter swift Deception vs Will pushes the target and gives it -1 attack until your next turn.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Hideous Visage: once per encounter swift Deception vs Will pushes the target and gives it -1 attack until your next turn.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"deception_fear_encounter_power","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"DECEPTION_VS_WILL_FEAR_PUSH","skillKey":"deception","action":"swift","oncePer":"encounter","targetDefense":"will","targetEffectsOnSuccess":[{"type":"PUSH","distance":1,"direction":"awayFromActor"},{"type":"ATTACK_PENALTY","value":-1,"duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn"}],"tags":["mind-affecting","fear"],"description":"Swift action once per encounter: Deception vs Will; on success push target 1 square away and impose -1 attack until your next turn."}]},"shortSummary":"Deception check to push opponent away.","prerequisitesText":"Shapeshift Species Trait","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hideous_Visage","effect":"Once per encounter, as a\nSwift Action\n, you can make a\nDeception\ncheck against one opponent that can see you. If the check equals or exceeds the opponent's\nWill Defense\n, you move the target 1 square away from you and it takes a -1 penalty on all attacks until the start of your next turn. This is a\nMind-Affecting\nFear effect."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.hideous_visage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hideous_Visage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
