{"_id":"2def724bf673c2fc","name":"Impersonate","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can make a Deception check to alter your features to that of a specific person. This Feat also allows you to change your voice to match the target's. You always treat impersonating a person as a Moderate Deception.","prerequisite":"Shapeshift Species Trait, Skill Focus (Deception)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":24,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Shapeshift Species Trait,<br>Skill Focus (Deception)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can make a<br>Deception<br>check to alter your features to that of a specific person. This Feat also allows you to change your voice to match the target&#x27;s. You always treat impersonating a person as a Moderate Deception.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impersonate</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"deception_impersonation_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Impersonate enables Shapeshift-based impersonation as a Deception use; voice/appearance matching and specific-person disguise remain skill-use metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_rule_phase17","description":"Impersonate enables Shapeshift-based impersonation as a Deception use; voice/appearance matching and specific-person disguise remain skill-use metadata.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Impersonate enables Shapeshift-based impersonation as a Deception use; voice/appearance matching and specific-person disguise remain skill-use metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"deception_impersonation_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"DECEPTION_IMPERSONATE_SPECIFIC_PERSON","skillKey":"deception","applications":["impersonate","disguise","shapeshift"],"difficulty":"moderate","description":"Use Deception with Shapeshift to impersonate a specific person, including voice."}]},"shortSummary":"Shapeshift to impersonate a specific person.","prerequisitesText":"Shapeshift Species Trait, Skill Focus (Deception)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impersonate","effect":"You can make a\nDeception\ncheck to alter your features to that of a specific person. This Feat also allows you to change your voice to match the target's. You always treat impersonating a person as a Moderate Deception."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.impersonate","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impersonate","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"2e5ada2de01fff4d","name":"Dreadful Countenance","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you make a Persuasion check or a Use the Force check to activate a Fear effect, you may reroll the check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse.","prerequisite":"Charisma 13, Member of The Sith","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Web Enhancements","page":1,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Charisma<br>13, Member of<br>The Sith</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you make a<br>Persuasion<br>check or a<br>Use the Force<br>check to activate a Fear effect, you may reroll the check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dreadful_Countenance</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"fear_skill_reroll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Dreadful Countenance grants rerolls for Persuasion or Use the Force checks used for Fear effects; the reroll result must be kept.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"skill_reroll_phase17","description":"Dreadful Countenance grants rerolls for Persuasion or Use the Force checks used for Fear effects; the reroll result must be kept.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Dreadful Countenance grants rerolls for Persuasion or Use the Force checks used for Fear effects; the reroll result must be kept.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"fear_skill_reroll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"skillRerolls":[{"id":"dreadful-countenance-persuasion-fear-reroll","skillKey":"persuasion","label":"Dreadful Countenance","outcome":"keepSecond","applicationIncludes":["fear","intimidate"],"description":"Reroll a Persuasion check used for a Fear effect; keep the reroll."},{"id":"dreadful-countenance-utf-fear-reroll","skillKey":"useTheForce","label":"Dreadful Countenance","outcome":"keepSecond","applicationIncludes":["fear"],"description":"Reroll a Use the Force check used to activate a Fear effect; keep the reroll."}]},"shortSummary":"Marked as Sith, your appearance inspires awe, dread, and fear in all who view it.","prerequisitesText":"Charisma 13, Member of The Sith","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Web Enhancements (Behind the Threat: The Sith)"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dreadful_Countenance","effect":"Whenever you make a\nPersuasion\ncheck or a\nUse the Force\ncheck to activate a Fear effect, you may reroll the check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.dreadful_countenance","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dreadful_Countenance","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"2eb0c304d99ef6ee","name":"Hold Together","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Reaction, you can spend a Force Point to delay the effect of damage dealt to a Vehicle you are riding in or piloting until the end of the round. The Vehicle must be of Colossal size or smaller.","prerequisite":"Trained in Mechanics","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":22,"tags":["feat","general","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Mechanics</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Reaction<br>, you can spend a<br>Force Point<br>to delay the effect of damage dealt to a<br>Vehicle<br>you are riding in or piloting until the end of the round. The<br>Vehicle<br>must be of Colossal size or smaller.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hold_Together</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Delay vehicle damage until end of round.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"action_or_reaction_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Delay vehicle damage until end of round.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase14","actionRules":[{"type":"DELAY_VEHICLE_DAMAGE_UNTIL_END_OF_ROUND"}]},"shortSummary":"Delay the damage caused to a Vehicle until the end of the round.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Mechanics","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hold_Together","effect":"As a\nReaction\n, you can spend a\nForce Point\nto delay the effect of damage dealt to a\nVehicle\nyou are riding in or piloting until the end of the round. The\nVehicle\nmust be of Colossal size or smaller."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.hold_together","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hold_Together","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"2ed1a3257175feb9","name":"Wroshyr Rage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Gain Bonus Hit Points when Raging.","prerequisite":"Wookiee","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["durability","execution_mapped_phase9","feat","hit_points","offense_melee","racial","rage","resource_spend","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-wookiee"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Wookiee</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you first enter your Rage, you gain a number of<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>equal to 10 + one-half your level. Damage is subtracted from<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>first, and any<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>remaining at the end of the encounter are lost.<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>do not stack.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wroshyr_Rage</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rage_rule_phase9_needs_amount","description":"Wroshyr Rage is identified as a Rage bonus-hit-point hook. The pack text does not include the numeric amount, so this is tagged but not auto-applied.","rules":[{"type":"RAGE_BONUS_HIT_POINTS","status":"needs_formula","description":"Gain bonus Hit Points when Raging. Numeric amount must be supplied before automation."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"rage_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Only applies while the actor is raging or using rage-specific rules.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Gain Bonus Hit Points when Raging.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wroshyr_Rage","rawImport":{"name":"Wroshyr Rage","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wroshyr_Rage","pageTitle":"Wroshyr_Rage","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\wroshyr_rage.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Wookiee","prerequisites":["Wookiee"],"effect":"When you first enter your Rage, you gain a number of\nBonus Hit Points\nequal to 10 + one-half your level. Damage is subtracted from\nBonus Hit Points\nfirst, and any\nBonus Hit Points\nremaining at the end of the encounter are lost.\nBonus Hit Points\ndo not stack.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Wookiee","indexBenefit":"Gain Bonus Hit Points when Raging.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou have learnt that in the dangerous jungles of\nKashyyyk\n, your mighty Rage must be tempered by wariness so that predators don't get the drop on you.\n\nPrerequisite:\nWookiee\n\nEffect:\nWhen you first enter your Rage, you gain a number of\nBonus Hit Points\nequal to 10 + one-half your level. Damage is subtracted from\nBonus Hit Points\nfirst, and any\nBonus Hit Points\nremaining at the end of the encounter are lost.\nBonus Hit Points\ndo not stack."},"prerequisitesText":"Wookiee","effect":"When you first enter your Rage, you gain a number of\nBonus Hit Points\nequal to 10 + one-half your level. Damage is subtracted from\nBonus Hit Points\nfirst, and any\nBonus Hit Points\nremaining at the end of the encounter are lost.\nBonus Hit Points\ndo not stack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.380Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.wroshyr_rage"}}}
