{"_id":"3a847230d573a623","name":"Melee Defense","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use a Standard Action to make a melee attack, you can take a penalty of up to -5 on your attack roll and add the same number (up to +5) as a dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense. This number may not exceed your Base Attack Bonus. The changes to attack rolls and Reflex Defense last until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Intelligence 13","special":"","normalText":"A character without the Melee Defense Feat can Fight Defensively while using the attack action to take a -5 penalty on his attack roll and gain a +2 dodge bonus to his Reflex Defense.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["defense","feat","general","melee_defense","offense_melee","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you use a<br>Standard Action<br>to make a melee attack, you can take a penalty of up to -5 on your attack roll and add the same number (up to +5) as a dodge bonus to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>. This number may not exceed your<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>. The changes to attack rolls and<br>Reflex Defense<br>last until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> A character without the Melee Defense Feat can<br>Fight Defensively<br>while using the attack action to take a -5 penalty on his attack roll and gain a +2 dodge bonus to his<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Melee_Defense</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"int","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"conditions":[{"type":"WEAPON_CATEGORY","value":"MELEE"}],"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Melee Defense: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"meleeDefense","label":"Melee Defense","control":"slider","max":5,"resource":"baseAttackBonus","requiresAttackType":"melee","attackModifierFormula":"-value","defenseModifier":{"target":"defense.reflex","type":"dodge","valueFormula":"value","duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn"},"summary":"Trade attack bonus for a dodge bonus to Reflex Defense until your next turn."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate attack/combat option, not a passive sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"Trade attack bonus on melee attacks for a dodge bonus to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Intelligence 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Melee_Defense","effect":"When you use a\nStandard Action\nto make a melee attack, you can take a penalty of up to -5 on your attack roll and add the same number (up to +5) as a dodge bonus to your\nReflex Defense\n. This number may not exceed your\nBase Attack Bonus\n. The changes to attack rolls and\nReflex Defense\nlast until the start of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.against-melee","defense.reflex","attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.melee_defense","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Melee_Defense","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"3b1c70b0f6844126","name":"Noble Fencing Style","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When wielding a weapon with Weapon Finesse, you may use your Charisma modifier instead of Strength for attack rolls.","prerequisite":"Weapon Finesse, Noble level 1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Uses the existing attack ability-substitution hook; Phase 13 hardened substitutions so Weapon Finesse and Noble Fencing Style do not stack incorrectly.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Uses the existing attack ability-substitution hook; Phase 13 hardened substitutions so Weapon Finesse and Noble Fencing Style do not stack incorrectly.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"noble_fencing_style_metadata_phase13","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_ABILITY_SUBSTITUTION","weaponGroups":["light melee","light melee weapons","lightsaber"],"fromAbility":"str","toAbility":"cha","useBetter":true,"description":"Use Charisma instead of Strength on attacks with Weapon Finesse-eligible weapons when better."}]},"shortSummary":"When wielding a weapon with Weapon Finesse, you may use your Charisma modifier instead of Strength for attack rolls."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"3b9b60551a3379ce","name":"Gearhead","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you can make Mechanics and Use Computer checks more quickly than normal. A check requiring a Full-Round Action can be attempted as a Standard Action, a check requiring a Standard Action can be attempted as a Move Action, and a check requiring a Move Action can be attempted as a Swift Action. Checks requiring multiple Swift Actions can be reduced by one Swift Action. Checks requiring more than a Full-Round Action can be attempted in one-half the amount of time required at a -10 penalty.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":26,"tags":["feat","general","skill_mechanics","skill_synergy","skill_use_computer"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, you can make<br>Mechanics<br>and<br>Use Computer<br>checks more quickly than normal. A check requiring a<br>Full-Round Action<br>can be attempted as a<br>Standard Action<br>, a check requiring a<br>Standard Action<br>can be attempted as a<br>Move Action<br>, and a check requiring a<br>Move Action<br>can be attempted as a<br>Swift Action<br>. Checks requiring multiple<br>Swift Actions<br>can be reduced by one<br>Swift Action<br>. Checks requiring more than a<br>Full-Round Action<br>can be attempted in one-half the amount of time required at a -10 penalty.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gearhead</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Skill-use timing metadata for Mechanics and Use Computer.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"mechanics_use_computer_time_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Skill-use timing metadata for Mechanics and Use Computer.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"gearhead_metadata_phase13","skillUseRules":[{"type":"REDUCE_RUSH_PENALTY_OR_TIME","skills":["mechanics","useComputer"],"description":"Make Mechanics and Use Computer checks more quickly with reduced rushing penalties where the skill use supports it."}]},"shortSummary":"Make Mechanics and Use Computer checks quickly.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gearhead","effect":"Once per encounter, you can make\nMechanics\nand\nUse Computer\nchecks more quickly than normal. A check requiring a\nFull-Round Action\ncan be attempted as a\nStandard Action\n, a check requiring a\nStandard Action\ncan be attempted as a\nMove Action\n, and a check requiring a\nMove Action\ncan be attempted as a\nSwift Action\n. Checks requiring multiple\nSwift Actions\ncan be reduced by one\nSwift Action\n. Checks requiring more than a\nFull-Round Action\ncan be attempted in one-half the amount of time required at a -10 penalty."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.gearhead","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gearhead","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"3ca2ebe34da486a5","name":"Greater Weapon Specialization","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with the selected weapon group. This stacks with Weapon Specialization.","prerequisite":"Weapon Specialization with selected weapon group, base attack bonus +12","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","general","weapon_mastery","choice_required","immediate_choice","weapon_choice","choice_source_prerequisite"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"damage.weapon","value":2,"type":"untyped","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Greater Weapon Specialization: +2 damage with selected Weapon Specialization target","predicates":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"conditionSummary":"Always available after selection, but only for rolls using the selected weapon group or exotic weapon."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Always available after selection, but only for rolls using the selected weapon group or exotic weapon.","predicateRequirements":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"execution_mapped_phase6","choiceKind":"greater_weapon_specialization","repeatable":true,"optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.greater_weapon_specialization","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.greater_weapon_specialization","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","derivesFrom":["weapon_specialization"],"consumes":"weapon_specialization","provides":"greater_weapon_specialization","effectTarget":"damage.weapon","effectValue":2},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with the selected weapon group."},"effects":[{"_id":"2609e320-82ca-4f97-bbc1-4e5e2b1dbcb9","name":"Greater Weapon Specialization","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":true,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Greater Weapon Specialization","effectType":"combat_bonus","flagType":"Greater Weapon Specialization","migratedToPassive":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"requiresImmediateChoice":true}}}
{"_id":"3cd647b126f1d171","name":"Reactive Stealth","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you may reroll a Stealth check and take the better result.","prerequisite":"Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","skill_stealth","skill_synergy","stealth"],"bonus_feat_for":["21dfe84d159a1b7f","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"skill_reroll_phase8_implemented","description":"Reactive Stealth: reroll Stealth checks once per encounter and keep the better result.","skillRerolls":[{"id":"reactive-stealth","skillKeys":["stealth"],"outcome":"keepBetter","oncePer":"encounter","label":"Reactive Stealth","description":"Reactive Stealth: reroll Stealth checks once per encounter and keep the better result."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"reroll_or_resource_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rerolls/resources are not static sheet modifiers and require a check/encounter/resource context.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Once per encounter, you may reroll a Stealth check and take the better result."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id":"3d4a4e93ced26712","name":"Triple Crit","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose one Weapon with which you are proficient. When you score a Critical Hit with the selected weapon, you deal triple damage. You may select \" Unarmed Attack \" as a Weapon for purposes of this Feat.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +8","special":"You can gain this Feat multiple times. The effects do not stack. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Weapon. It's possible to take Triple Crit with a specific Vehicle Weapon.","normalText":"A Critical Hit normally deals double damage to the target.","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["control","feat","general","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+8</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Choose one Weapon with which you are proficient. When you score a Critical Hit with the selected weapon, you deal triple damage. You may select &quot;<br>Unarmed Attack<br>&quot; as a Weapon for purposes of this<br>Feat<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> A Critical Hit normally deals double damage to the target.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can gain this Feat multiple times. The effects do not stack. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Weapon. It&#x27;s possible to take Triple Crit with a specific<br>Vehicle Weapon<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Crit</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":8}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Triple Crit","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Choose one proficient weapon; actor inventory supplies concrete weapon options when available.","metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","disabledReason":"Phase 6: choice captured now; execution waits for roll/action context wiring."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive_choice_required","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_critical_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose one proficient weapon; actor inventory supplies concrete weapon options when available.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 implements selected-weapon critical metadata through CombatOptionResolver weapon critical rules.","rules":[{"type":"WEAPON_CRITICAL_MULTIPLIER_MIN","id":"triple_crit_critical_x3","selectedChoice":true,"value":3,"targetEffectsOnCritical":[],"description":"Selected weapon critical hits use at least x3 multiplier."}],"status":"triple_crit_critical_phase12","description":"Selected weapon critical hits use at least x3 multiplier."},"shortSummary":"Deal triple damage on a Critical Hit.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +8","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Crit","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"specific_weapon","repeatable":true,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.triple_crit_weapon","choiceSource":"actorInventory","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.specific_weapon"},"effect":"Choose one Weapon with which you are proficient. When you score a Critical Hit with the selected weapon, you deal triple damage. You may select \"\nUnarmed Attack\n\" as a Weapon for purposes of this\nFeat\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.triple_crit","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Crit","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"3eed0b4f1227cf91","name":"Throw","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you successfully Trip an opponent with a Grapple attack, the opponent falls Prone in any unoccupied space you desire up to 1 square beyond your reach and take bludgeoning damage equal to your Unarmed attack damage. A Thrown opponent is no longer considered Grappled.","prerequisite":"Trip, Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trip<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you successfully<br>Trip<br>an opponent with a<br>Grapple<br>attack, the opponent falls<br>Prone<br>in any unoccupied space you desire up to 1 square beyond your reach and take bludgeoning damage equal to your<br>Unarmed<br>attack damage. A Thrown opponent is no longer considered<br>Grappled<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Throw</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rider_effect_phase7","description":"Throw: modeled as a rider/action rule, not a numeric modifier.","rules":[{"type":"GRAPPLE_RIDER","trigger":"onSuccessfulTrip","effect":"throwTarget","maxDistanceSquaresBeyondReach":1,"damage":"unarmed","endsGrapple":true}],"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Throw: numeric scaffold disabled by Phase 7 (description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus)","mechanicsMode":"metadata_note","applicationScope":"not_a_numeric_modifier","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus","metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"grapple_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Successful Trip through grapple can throw the target and deal unarmed damage.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Throw a Grappled opponent up to 1 square beyond your reach and deal damage.","prerequisitesText":"Trip, Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Throw","effect":"If you successfully\nTrip\nan opponent with a\nGrapple\nattack, the opponent falls\nProne\nin any unoccupied space you desire up to 1 square beyond your reach and take bludgeoning damage equal to your\nUnarmed\nattack damage. A Thrown opponent is no longer considered\nGrappled\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.throw","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Throw","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"3f76464c43c73f84","name":"Power Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"On your turn, before making an attack roll, you may choose to subtract a number from all melee attack rolls and add the same number to all melee damage rolls. This number may not exceed your Base Attack Bonus. The penalty on attacks and bonus on damage rolls applies until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Strength 13","special":"If you attack with a two-handed weapon, or with a one-handed weapon wielded in two hands, instead add twice the number subtracted from your attack rolls to your damage rolls. You can't add the bonus from Power Attack to the damage dealt against an object or Vehicle.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","feat_chain","general","offense","offense_melee","prereq_gateway","standard_action","strength_synergy"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> On your turn, before making an attack roll, you may choose to subtract a number from all melee attack rolls and add the same number to all melee damage rolls. This number may not exceed your<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>. The penalty on attacks and bonus on damage rolls applies until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you attack with a two-handed weapon, or with a one-handed weapon wielded in two hands, instead add twice the number subtracted from your attack rolls to your damage rolls. You can&#x27;t add the bonus from Power Attack to the damage dealt against an object or<br>Vehicle<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Power_Attack</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"str","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Power Attack: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"powerAttack","label":"Power Attack","control":"slider","max":5,"resource":"baseAttackBonus","requiresAttackType":"melee","attackModifierFormula":"-value","damageModifierFormula":"value","summary":"Trade attack bonus for bonus melee damage."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate attack/combat option, not a passive sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"Trade attack bonus for damage on melee attacks (up to your Base Attack Bonus).","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Power_Attack","effect":"On your turn, before making an attack roll, you may choose to subtract a number from all melee attack rolls and add the same number to all melee damage rolls. This number may not exceed your\nBase Attack Bonus\n. The penalty on attacks and bonus on damage rolls applies until the start of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.power_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Power_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4025202b97ec451d","name":"Reckless Charge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you charge, you gain a +2 bonus on melee attack rolls but take a -2 penalty to Reflex Defense until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Str 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["charge","feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex","attack.with-melee"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Reckless Charge: Implemented as an explicit attack option or roll-context rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee","defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit attack option or roll-context rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Reckless Charge: explicit charge attack option (+2 melee attack, -2 Reflex rider).","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 converts clear description-guided combat feats from scaffold modifiers into CombatOptionResolver metadata.","status":"attack_option_phase9","description":"Reckless Charge: explicit charge attack option (+2 melee attack, -2 Reflex rider).","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"recklessCharge","label":"Reckless Charge","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","requiresCharge":true,"attackModifier":2,"defenseModifier":{"target":"defense.reflex","type":"untyped","value":-2,"duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn"},"summary":"When charging with a melee attack, gain +2 attack and take -2 Reflex until your next turn."}]},"shortSummary":"When you charge, you gain a +2 bonus on melee attack rolls but take a -2 penalty to Reflex Defense until the start of your next turn."},"effects":[{"_id":"54ed6adb-4bec-4864-9fd4-f8a974f2f3a0","name":"Reckless Charge","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Reckless Charge","effectType":"defense_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex","attack.with-melee"]}}}
{"_id":"40429365d8f28219","name":"Hasty Modification","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can exchange a Trait you have applied to a piece of Equipment or Droid for another one by spending 1 minute to make a DC 20 Mechanics check. If you succeed, the Equipment loses the old Trait and gains a new Trait until the end of the encounter, at which point the device loses all Traits previously acquired through use of the Tech Specialist Feat.","prerequisite":"Tech Specialist","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":24,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Tech Specialist</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can exchange a Trait you have applied to a piece of<br>Equipment<br>or<br>Droid<br>for another one by spending 1 minute to make a DC 20<br>Mechanics<br>check. If you succeed, the<br>Equipment<br>loses the old Trait and gains a new Trait until the end of the encounter, at which point the device loses all Traits previously acquired through use of the<br>Tech Specialist<br>Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hasty_Modification</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"deferred_major_ui","applicationScope":"customization_picker_required","staticSheetPolicy":"deferred","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Hasty Modification depends on Tech Specialist trait swapping and item modification UI, so it is deferred to the dedicated customization UI/picker work.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"deferred_major_ui_picker","description":"Hasty Modification depends on Tech Specialist trait swapping and item modification UI, so it is deferred to the dedicated customization UI/picker work.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Hasty Modification depends on Tech Specialist trait swapping and item modification UI, so it is deferred to the dedicated customization UI/picker work.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"customization_picker_required","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"customizationCapabilities":[{"type":"DEFERRED_CUSTOMIZATION_PICKER","requiresDedicatedUi":true,"description":"Hasty Modification depends on Tech Specialist trait swapping and item modification UI, so it is deferred to the dedicated customization UI/picker work."}]},"shortSummary":"Swap one Trait for another Trait.","prerequisitesText":"Tech Specialist","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hasty_Modification","effect":"You can exchange a Trait you have applied to a piece of\nEquipment\nor\nDroid\nfor another one by spending 1 minute to make a DC 20\nMechanics\ncheck. If you succeed, the\nEquipment\nloses the old Trait and gains a new Trait until the end of the encounter, at which point the device loses all Traits previously acquired through use of the\nTech Specialist\nFeat."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.hasty_modification","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hasty_Modification","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"419a502e59264382","name":"Acrobatic Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you succeed in Tumbling to avoid an Attack of Opportunity, you gain a +2 competence bonus on the next attack roll you make against that foe as long as the attack occurs before the end of your current turn.","prerequisite":"Trained in Acrobatics","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":23,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Acrobatics</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you succeed in<br>Tumbling<br>to avoid an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>, you gain a +2 competence bonus on the next attack roll you make against that foe as long as the attack occurs before the end of your current turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Strike</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"a6c5e98148aad9a9"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rider_effect_phase7","description":"Acrobatic Strike: modeled as a rider/action rule, not a numeric modifier.","rules":[{"type":"RIDER_EFFECT","trigger":"afterSuccessfulTumbleAvoidAoO","target":"nextAttackAgainstThatFoe","attackModifier":2,"bonusType":"competence","expires":"endOfCurrentTurn"}],"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Acrobatic Strike: numeric scaffold disabled by Phase 7 (description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus)","mechanicsMode":"metadata_note","applicationScope":"not_a_numeric_modifier","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus","metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"post_tumble_attack_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Applies only after a successful Tumble to avoid an attack of opportunity and only against that foe before the end of the current turn.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Gain +2 competence bonus on next attack against opponent you Tumble past.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Acrobatics","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Strike","effect":"If you succeed in\nTumbling\nto avoid an\nAttack of Opportunity\n, you gain a +2 competence bonus on the next attack roll you make against that foe as long as the attack occurs before the end of your current turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.acrobatic_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"41a9ce755ecffb5b","name":"Heavy Weapon Proficiency","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You are proficient with heavy weapons and do not take the -5 penalty when using them.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["build_enabler","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged","weapon_access","weapon_heavy","mapped_phase_1","unlock_grant","choice_variant"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"UNLOCK","abilityMeta":{"grants":[{"category":"PROFICIENCY","proficiencyType":"weapon","proficiencies":["heavy-weapons"],"description":"Weapon proficiency: heavy-weapons"}],"mechanicsMode":"grant_unlock","applicationScope":"progression_or_proficiency_grant","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Name and metadata indicate a grant/unlock/proficiency rather than a numeric passive modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"already_resolved_static_variant","required":false,"choiceKind":"weapon_proficiency","value":"heavy-weapons","grants":["heavy-weapons"]},"shortSummary":"You are proficient with heavy weapons and do not take the -5 penalty when using them."},"effects":[{"_id":"8022df9b-54d6-420c-bc56-70dd4666b140","name":"Heavy Weapon Proficiency","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Heavy Weapon Proficiency","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Heavy Weapon Proficiency"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"phase1Mapped":true,"manualMappingResolved":true}}}
{"_id":"423c5fffe7abe449","name":"Veteran Spacer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Gain a bonus to Use Computer checks made to Astrogate.","prerequisite":"Duros","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","skill_synergy","skill_use_computer","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-duros"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Duros</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +5<br>Species<br>bonus to<br>Use Computer<br>checks made to<br>Astrogate<br>aboard a Starship.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Veteran_Spacer</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"skill_bonus_phase8","description":"Veteran Spacer: +2 bonus to Use Computer checks made to Astrogate.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"veteran-spacer","skillKeys":["useComputer"],"value":2,"type":"untyped","context":"astrogate","description":"Veteran Spacer: +2 to Use Computer checks for Astrogate."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"skill_or_grapple_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Current metadata is implemented through skill/grapple helper payloads rather than generic static modifiers.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Gain a bonus to Use Computer checks made to Astrogate.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Veteran_Spacer","rawImport":{"name":"Veteran Spacer","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Veteran_Spacer","pageTitle":"Veteran_Spacer","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\veteran_spacer.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Duros","prerequisites":["Duros"],"effect":"You gain a +5\nSpecies\nbonus to\nUse Computer\nchecks made to\nAstrogate\naboard a Starship.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Duros","indexBenefit":"Gain a bonus to Use Computer checks made to Astrogate .","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYour people are among the oldest explorers to chart the stars, and you benefit from eons of collected knowledge about space travel.\n\nPrerequisite:\nDuros\n\nEffect:\nYou gain a +5\nSpecies\nbonus to\nUse Computer\nchecks made to\nAstrogate\naboard a Starship."},"prerequisitesText":"Duros","effect":"You gain a +5\nSpecies\nbonus to\nUse Computer\nchecks made to\nAstrogate\naboard a Starship."},"effects":[{"_id":"5e810754-78db-4b51-a879-83d55b7439cb","name":"Veteran Spacer","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Veteran Spacer","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Veteran Spacer"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.veteran_spacer"}}}
{"_id":"42dc0158ce091479","name":"Destructive Force","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you deal damage to an object or Vehicle that equals or exceeds the target's Damage Threshold and reduces the target to 0 Hit Points, you deal 1 die of damage (of the same type as the damage used in the attack) to all targets, including allies, that are adjacent to the Vehicle or object.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":21,"tags":["feat","general","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you deal damage to an object or<br>Vehicle<br>that equals or exceeds the target&#x27;s<br>Damage Threshold<br>and reduces the target to 0 Hit Points, you deal 1 die of damage (of the same type as the damage used in the attack) to all targets, including allies, that are adjacent to the<br>Vehicle<br>or object.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Destructive_Force</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"object_vehicle_destruction_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Destructive Force is a destruction rider: when an object/vehicle is reduced to 0 HP and damage equals/exceeds DT, adjacent targets take 1 die of the same damage type.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"attack_rider_metadata_phase17","description":"Destructive Force is a destruction rider: when an object/vehicle is reduced to 0 HP and damage equals/exceeds DT, adjacent targets take 1 die of the same damage type.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Destructive Force is a destruction rider: when an object/vehicle is reduced to 0 HP and damage equals/exceeds DT, adjacent targets take 1 die of the same damage type.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"object_vehicle_destruction_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"destructiveForce","label":"Destructive Force","control":"passive","requiresTargetType":["object","vehicle"],"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"ADJACENT_DAMAGE_ON_DESTROYED_OBJECT_OR_VEHICLE","trigger":"damageEqualsOrExceedsDTAndReducesToZeroHp","damageDice":"1 weapon die","damageType":"sameAsAttack","affectsAllies":true}],"summary":"On destroying an object/vehicle with damage meeting DT, adjacent targets take 1 die of the same damage type."}]},"shortSummary":"Deal damage to adjacent targets when you damage objects and Vehicles.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Destructive_Force","effect":"When you deal damage to an object or\nVehicle\nthat equals or exceeds the target's\nDamage Threshold\nand reduces the target to 0 Hit Points, you deal 1 die of damage (of the same type as the damage used in the attack) to all targets, including allies, that are adjacent to the\nVehicle\nor object."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.destructive_force","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Destructive_Force","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"42e2404790756700","name":"Tech Specialist","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can modify a device, suit of Armor, Weapon, Droid, or Vehicle so that it gains a special trait. Specific traits are given on the table below. You may perform only one modification at a time. Unless noted otherwise, you cannot grant more than one benefit to a single device, suit of Armor, Weapon, Droid, or Vehicle, and you cannot apply the same benefit more than once.\n\nBefore beginning the modification, you must pay one-tenth the cost of the device, suit of Armor, Weapon, Droid, or Vehicle you wish to modify or 1,000 credits, whichever is more. Completing the modification requires 1 day per 1,000 credits of the modification's cost. At the end of this time, make a DC 20 Mechanics check; you can't Take 10 or Take 20 on this check. If the check succeeds, the modification is completed successfully, and the object gains the desired trait. If the check fails, you lose all credits spent making the modification, and the object doesn't gain the desired trait. However, you may start over if you wish.\n\nOther characters Trained in the Mechanics Skill can assist you, reducing proportionately the time needed to complete the modification (for example, 3 people working together on a 1,000 credit modification would take 1/3 of one day). At the end of the modification process, they can make a Mechanics check to aid your check.\n\nThe market value of a modified item is equal to the base cost of the item + double the cost of the modifications made to it (not including credits wasted on failed modification attempts).\n\nARMOR TRAIT | BENEFIT\nAgile Armor | The Armor's Maximum Dexterity Bonus increases by 1.\nFortifying Armor | The Armor's Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense increases by 1.\nProtective Armor | The Armor's Armor bonus to Reflex Defense increases by 1.\nDEVICE TRAIT | BENEFIT\nEnhanced Strength | Increase the device's Strength score by 2.\nImproved Durability | The device's Damage Reduction increases by 1, and it gains extra Hit Points equal to one-quarter of its maximum Hit Points.\nMastercraft Device | Skill Checks made using the device gain a +1 Equipment bonus, or the device's existing Equipment bonus increases by 1.\nDROID TRAIT | BENEFIT\nEnhanced Dexterity | Increase the Droid's Dexterity score by 2.\nEnhanced Intelligence | Increase the Droid's Intelligence score by 2.\nEnhanced Strength | Increase the Droid's Strength score by 2.\nVEHICLE TRAIT | BENEFIT\nEnhanced Dexterity | Increase the Vehicle's Dexterity score by 2.\nImproved Shields | Increase the Vehicle's Shield Rating by 5.\nImproved Speed | Increase the Vehicle's Speed by one-quarter of its base Speed (minimum 1 square).\nWEAPON TRAIT | BENEFIT\nImproved Accuracy | The Weapon gains a +1 Equipment bonus on attack rolls.\nImproved Damage | The Weapon deals +2 points of damage with a successful hit. If the weapon has a damage multiplier (for example, 6d10x2), apply the extra damage before applying the multiplier.\nSelective Fire | An Autofire -only ranged Weapon can be set to fire Single-Shots, or a Single-Shot Weapon can be made to have an Autofire mode. This cannot be applied to Weapons that have a Burst radius or Splash radius.","prerequisite":"Trained in Mechanics","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["feat","general","tech","utility","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":["21dfe84d159a1b7f"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Mechanics</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can modify a device, suit of Armor, Weapon,<br>Droid<br>, or<br>Vehicle<br>so that it gains a special trait. Specific traits are given on the table below. You may perform only one modification at a time. Unless noted otherwise, you cannot grant more than one benefit to a single device, suit of Armor, Weapon,<br>Droid<br>, or<br>Vehicle<br>, and you cannot apply the same benefit more than once.<br><br>Before beginning the modification, you must pay one-tenth the cost of the device, suit of Armor, Weapon,<br>Droid<br>, or<br>Vehicle<br>you wish to modify or 1,000 credits, whichever is more. Completing the modification requires 1 day per 1,000 credits of the modification&#x27;s cost. At the end of this time, make a DC 20<br>Mechanics<br>check; you can&#x27;t<br>Take 10<br>or<br>Take 20<br>on this check. If the check succeeds, the modification is completed successfully, and the object gains the desired trait. If the check fails, you lose all credits spent making the modification, and the object doesn&#x27;t gain the desired trait. However, you may start over if you wish.<br><br>Other characters<br>Trained<br>in the<br>Mechanics<br>Skill can assist you, reducing proportionately the time needed to complete the modification (for example, 3 people working together on a 1,000 credit modification would take 1/3 of one day). At the end of the modification process, they can make a<br>Mechanics<br>check to aid your check.<br><br>The market value of a modified item is equal to the base cost of the item + double the cost of the modifications made to it (not including credits wasted on failed modification attempts).<br><br>ARMOR TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Agile Armor | The Armor&#x27;s Maximum Dexterity Bonus increases by 1.<br>Fortifying Armor | The Armor&#x27;s Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense increases by 1.<br>Protective Armor | The Armor&#x27;s Armor bonus to Reflex Defense increases by 1.<br>DEVICE TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Enhanced Strength | Increase the device&#x27;s Strength score by 2.<br>Improved Durability | The device&#x27;s Damage Reduction increases by 1, and it gains extra Hit Points equal to one-quarter of its maximum Hit Points.<br>Mastercraft Device | Skill Checks made using the device gain a +1 Equipment bonus, or the device&#x27;s existing Equipment bonus increases by 1.<br>DROID TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Enhanced Dexterity | Increase the Droid&#x27;s Dexterity score by 2.<br>Enhanced Intelligence | Increase the Droid&#x27;s Intelligence score by 2.<br>Enhanced Strength | Increase the Droid&#x27;s Strength score by 2.<br>VEHICLE TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Enhanced Dexterity | Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Dexterity score by 2.<br>Improved Shields | Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Shield Rating by 5.<br>Improved Speed | Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Speed by one-quarter of its base Speed (minimum 1 square).<br>WEAPON TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Improved Accuracy | The Weapon gains a +1 Equipment bonus on attack rolls.<br>Improved Damage | The Weapon deals +2 points of damage with a successful hit. If the weapon has a damage multiplier (for example, 6d10x2), apply the extra damage before applying the multiplier.<br>Selective Fire | An Autofire -only ranged Weapon can be set to fire Single-Shots, or a Single-Shot Weapon can be made to have an Autofire mode. This cannot be applied to Weapons that have a Burst radius or Splash radius.</p>\n<h3>Additional Clarifications</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy<br><br>The bonuses provided by the Tech Specialist Feat and the<br>Superior Tech<br>Feat always stack with those provided by<br>Equipment Upgrades<br>; however, upgrades and other gear still follow the normal rules for stacking with one another. Additional clarifications are outlined below.<br><br>Device Traits:<br>Weapons, armor, and vehicles are also devices, so they are eligible for all of these modifications. (Droids are characters, not devices.) In addition to the listed modifications, it is possible to install an additional<br>Upgrade Slot<br>on any device using the Tech Specialist Feat. This modification can be made only once.<br><br>Droid Traits:<br>Any equipment with the<br>Droidification<br>upgrade is technically a Droid, so it is eligible for these modifications.<br><br>Armor Traits:<br>If a device or vehicle has an armor bonus to its<br>Reflex Defense<br>(either normally or because of an upgrade), it can benefit from the Protective Armor modification.<br><br>Weapon Traits:<br>If an<br>Autofire<br>-only weapon has the Selective Fire modification, it is still treated as an<br>Autofire<br>-only weapon for purposes of<br>Bracing<br>. An<br>Autofire<br>-only weapon with a<br>Sniper Switch<br>does not gain this benefit.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tech_Specialist</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"745a5686d6f21e8c"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"customization_context","applicationScope":"workbench_garage_shipyard_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Tech Specialist is intentionally deferred; it requires a dedicated customization UI/picker and should not be represented by fake passive bonuses.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"phase21_contextual_customization_ui","description":"Tech Specialist is implemented through contextual modification buttons in the Workbench, Droid Garage, and Shipyard. Credits are paid through TransactionEngine, a Mechanics check is rolled, and successful traits are stored on the modified item or asset.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Tech Specialist is intentionally deferred; it requires a dedicated customization UI/picker and should not be represented by fake passive bonuses.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"customization_picker_required","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"deferredReason":null,"customizationCapabilities":[{"type":"TECH_SPECIALIST_MODIFICATION","contexts":["workbench","lightsaber","garage","shipyard"],"requiresMechanicsCheck":true,"usesTransactionEngine":true}]},"shortSummary":"You can make custom modifications to Armor, Weapons, Vehicles, Droids, and Devices.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Mechanics","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy","Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tech_Specialist","effect":"You can modify a device, suit of Armor, Weapon,\nDroid\n, or\nVehicle\nso that it gains a special trait. Specific traits are given on the table below. You may perform only one modification at a time. Unless noted otherwise, you cannot grant more than one benefit to a single device, suit of Armor, Weapon,\nDroid\n, or\nVehicle\n, and you cannot apply the same benefit more than once.\n\nBefore beginning the modification, you must pay one-tenth the cost of the device, suit of Armor, Weapon,\nDroid\n, or\nVehicle\nyou wish to modify or 1,000 credits, whichever is more. Completing the modification requires 1 day per 1,000 credits of the modification's cost. At the end of this time, make a DC 20\nMechanics\ncheck; you can't\nTake 10\nor\nTake 20\non this check. If the check succeeds, the modification is completed successfully, and the object gains the desired trait. If the check fails, you lose all credits spent making the modification, and the object doesn't gain the desired trait. However, you may start over if you wish.\n\nOther characters\nTrained\nin the\nMechanics\nSkill can assist you, reducing proportionately the time needed to complete the modification (for example, 3 people working together on a 1,000 credit modification would take 1/3 of one day). At the end of the modification process, they can make a\nMechanics\ncheck to aid your check.\n\nThe market value of a modified item is equal to the base cost of the item + double the cost of the modifications made to it (not including credits wasted on failed modification attempts).\n\nARMOR TRAIT | BENEFIT\nAgile Armor | The Armor's Maximum Dexterity Bonus increases by 1.\nFortifying Armor | The Armor's Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense increases by 1.\nProtective Armor | The Armor's Armor bonus to Reflex Defense increases by 1.\nDEVICE TRAIT | BENEFIT\nEnhanced Strength | Increase the device's Strength score by 2.\nImproved Durability | The device's Damage Reduction increases by 1, and it gains extra Hit Points equal to one-quarter of its maximum Hit Points.\nMastercraft Device | Skill Checks made using the device gain a +1 Equipment bonus, or the device's existing Equipment bonus increases by 1.\nDROID TRAIT | BENEFIT\nEnhanced Dexterity | Increase the Droid's Dexterity score by 2.\nEnhanced Intelligence | Increase the Droid's Intelligence score by 2.\nEnhanced Strength | Increase the Droid's Strength score by 2.\nVEHICLE TRAIT | BENEFIT\nEnhanced Dexterity | Increase the Vehicle's Dexterity score by 2.\nImproved Shields | Increase the Vehicle's Shield Rating by 5.\nImproved Speed | Increase the Vehicle's Speed by one-quarter of its base Speed (minimum 1 square).\nWEAPON TRAIT | BENEFIT\nImproved Accuracy | The Weapon gains a +1 Equipment bonus on attack rolls.\nImproved Damage | The Weapon deals +2 points of damage with a successful hit. If the weapon has a damage multiplier (for example, 6d10x2), apply the extra damage before applying the multiplier.\nSelective Fire | An Autofire -only ranged Weapon can be set to fire Single-Shots, or a Single-Shot Weapon can be made to have an Autofire mode. This cannot be applied to Weapons that have a Burst radius or Splash radius."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.tech_specialist","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tech_Specialist","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4330126d10dccd71","name":"Maniacal Charge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Charge Action, you can make a Persuasion check as a Free Action to Intimidate your target and each enemy you pass within 1 square of. When your check succeeds against an enemy you pass, it cannot make an Attack of Opportunity against you. When your check succeeds against your target, it loses its Dexterity bonus and is considered Flat-Footed until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"None","special":"You cannot use this Feat with the Intimidator Feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":26,"tags":["ability_dexterity","charge","feat","general","offense","offense_melee","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using the<br>Charge<br>Action, you can make a<br>Persuasion<br>check as a<br>Free Action<br>to<br>Intimidate<br>your target and each enemy you pass within 1 square of. When your check succeeds against an enemy you pass, it cannot make an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>against you. When your check succeeds against your target, it loses its<br>Dexterity<br>bonus and is considered<br>Flat-Footed<br>until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You cannot use this Feat with the<br>Intimidator<br>Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Maniacal_Charge</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"charge_intimidate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Maniacal Charge adds a free Intimidate/Persuasion rider while charging; successful checks suppress AoOs from passed enemies and deny the target Dexterity/flat-foot it until your next turn.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"charge_skill_rider_phase17","description":"Maniacal Charge adds a free Intimidate/Persuasion rider while charging; successful checks suppress AoOs from passed enemies and deny the target Dexterity/flat-foot it until your next turn.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Maniacal Charge adds a free Intimidate/Persuasion rider while charging; successful checks suppress AoOs from passed enemies and deny the target Dexterity/flat-foot it until your next turn.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"charge_intimidate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"CHARGE_INTIMIDATE_RIDER","skillKey":"persuasion","application":"intimidate","action":"free","trigger":"charge","affectsPassedEnemiesWithinSquares":1,"targetEffectsOnSuccess":["cannotMakeAttackOfOpportunityAgainstYou","targetDeniedDexterityBonus","targetFlatFootedUntilStartOfNextTurn"],"incompatibleWith":["Intimidator"],"description":"During a charge, make free Persuasion/Intimidate checks against the target and enemies you pass within 1 square."}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"maniacalCharge","label":"Maniacal Charge","control":"flag","requiresCharge":true,"targetDefenseType":"reflexDeniedDex","summary":"Charge rider: use Persuasion to deny AoOs from passed enemies and make target flat-footed on success."}]},"shortSummary":"Intimidate your enemies when Charging, preventing adjacent characters from making Attacks of Opportunity and denying your target its Dexterity bonus.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Maniacal_Charge","effect":"When using the\nCharge\nAction, you can make a\nPersuasion\ncheck as a\nFree Action\nto\nIntimidate\nyour target and each enemy you pass within 1 square of. When your check succeeds against an enemy you pass, it cannot make an\nAttack of Opportunity\nagainst you. When your check succeeds against your target, it loses its\nDexterity\nbonus and is considered\nFlat-Footed\nuntil the start of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.maniacal_charge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Maniacal_Charge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"43a4b873d9a9984d","name":"Ion Shielding","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If the Ion damage (Before being halved) equals or exceeds your Damage Threshold, you move only -1 step on the Condition Track.","prerequisite":"(Droid and Strength 13) or (Cyborg Hybrid and Constitution 13)","special":"","normalText":"If the Ion damage (Before being halved) equals or exceeds your Damage Threshold, you normally move -2 steps on the Condition Track.","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":21,"tags":["condition_track","damage_threshold","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> (<br>Droid<br>and<br>Strength<br>13) or (<br>Cyborg Hybrid<br>and<br>Constitution<br>13)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If the<br>Ion<br>damage (Before being halved) equals or exceeds your<br>Damage Threshold<br>, you move only -1 step on the<br>Condition Track<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> If the<br>Ion<br>damage (Before being halved) equals or exceeds your<br>Damage Threshold<br>, you normally move -2 steps on the<br>Condition Track<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Ion_Shielding</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Caps ion-damage condition-track movement to one step.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"damage_resolution_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Caps ion-damage condition-track movement to one step.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"damage_rule_phase14","resourceRules":{"damage":[{"type":"CAP_ION_DAMAGE_CT_TO_1_STEP","description":"Ion damage that exceeds DT can move you only 1 step down the Condition Track."}]}},"resourceRules":{"damage":[{"type":"CAP_ION_DAMAGE_CT_TO_1_STEP"}]},"shortSummary":"Move only -1 step on Condition Track when Ion damage exceeds Damage Threshold.","prerequisitesText":"(Droid and Strength 13) or (Cyborg Hybrid and Constitution 13)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Ion_Shielding","effect":"If the\nIon\ndamage (Before being halved) equals or exceeds your\nDamage Threshold\n, you move only -1 step on the\nCondition Track\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.ion_shielding","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Ion_Shielding","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"44705a692e2f01a6","name":"Quick Draw","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can Draw or Holster a Weapon as a Swift Action instead of a Move Action.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["action_economy","draw_weapon","feat","general","setup","swift_action"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","21dfe84d159a1b7f"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can<br>Draw or Holster a Weapon<br>as a<br>Swift Action<br>instead of a<br>Move Action<br>.</p>\n<h3>Additional Quick Draw Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Dual Weapon Mastery I<br>):<br>You can draw or holster two weapons with a single<br>Swift Action<br>; you must have both hands free to draw both weapons, and each weapon must be able to be held in one hand.<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Weapon Proficiency (Lightsabers)<br>):<br>You can draw and ignite your<br>Lightsaber<br>as a single<br>Swift Action<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Draw</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Action economy capability; no sheet modifier.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"passive_capability","applicationScope":"action_economy_context","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Action economy capability; no sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"quick_draw_metadata_phase13","actionRules":[{"type":"DRAW_OR_HOLSTER_AS_SWIFT","description":"Draw or holster a weapon as a Swift Action instead of a Move Action."}]},"shortSummary":"Draw weapon as a Swift Action.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Draw","effect":"You can\nDraw or Holster a Weapon\nas a\nSwift Action\ninstead of a\nMove Action\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.quick_draw","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Draw","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"44cce39d67c0979d","name":"Duck and Cover","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you are the target of an Area Attack that misses, once per turn you can Move 2 squares as a Reaction. This movement does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":22,"tags":["cover_play","defense","feat","general","multi_target","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Stealth</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you are the target of an<br>Area Attack<br>that misses, once per turn you can Move 2 squares as a<br>Reaction<br>. This movement does not provoke<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Duck_and_Cover</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"6d2ac22d9fcf402f"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"area_attack_avoidance_reaction","staticSheetPolicy":"reaction_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Duck and Cover: when you avoid an area attack, dive for cover as a reaction/positioning rider.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"reaction_metadata_phase16","description":"Duck and Cover: when you avoid an area attack, dive for cover as a reaction/positioning rider.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Duck and Cover: when you avoid an area attack, dive for cover as a reaction/positioning rider.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"area_attack_avoidance_reaction","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"reactionRules":[{"type":"DIVE_FOR_COVER_AFTER_AVOIDING_AREA_ATTACK","trigger":"avoidAreaAttack","description":"When you avoid an area attack, you can dive for cover. Positioning remains GM/player adjudicated."}]},"shortSummary":"You dive for Cover when you avoid Area Attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Stealth","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Duck_and_Cover","effect":"Whenever you are the target of an\nArea Attack\nthat misses, once per turn you can Move 2 squares as a\nReaction\n. This movement does not provoke\nAttacks of Opportunity\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.duck_and_cover","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Duck_and_Cover","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"44ddf3506444cbbd","name":"Force Focus","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate a specific Force power you select when taking this feat.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use the Force","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":94,"tags":["feat","force","choice_required","immediate_choice","force_choice","choice_source_prerequisite"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"+2 UTF is selected-power only and resolves against the stored Force Focus choice.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"+2 UTF is selected-power only and resolves against the stored Force Focus choice.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"forceFocus.selectedPower","skillKey":"useTheForce","value":2,"type":"feat","applicationFromSelectedChoice":true,"description":"+2 Use the Force checks to activate the selected Force Power."}],"implementationStatus":"force_focus_skill_bonus_phase13","choiceKind":"force_power_focus"},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase13_choice_executable","choiceKind":"force_power_focus","repeatable":true,"optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.force_power_focus","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.force_power_focus","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","derivesFrom":["owned_force_powers"],"consumes":"owned_force_powers","provides":"force_power_focus","effectTarget":"useTheForce.selectedForcePower","effectValue":2},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate a specific Force power you select when taking this feat."},"effects":[{"_id":"c848bbad-3457-473f-93d4-5bf788e39d60","name":"Force Focus","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Force Focus","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Force Focus"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"requiresImmediateChoice":true}}}
{"_id":"45366d4f3a5e443d","name":"Dodge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"During your turn, you designate an opponent and receive a +1 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense against attacks from that opponent. You can select a new opponent on any action. A situation that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense (if any) also makes you lose dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":84,"tags":["defense","feat","general","reflex_defense","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> During your turn, you designate an opponent and receive a +1 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense against attacks from that opponent. You can select a new opponent on any action. A situation that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense (if any) also makes you lose dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses.</p>\n<h3>Additional Dodge Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy<br><br>The<br>Pilot<br>of a<br>Vehicle<br>may use Dodge to grant the<br>Vehicle<br>a +1 dodge bonus against a single opponent (Whether a<br>Vehicle<br>or a single character).<br><br>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Charging Fire<br>):<br>You reduce your penalty to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>against all opponents to -1 when making a ranged attack at the end of a<br>Charge<br>.<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Running Attack<br>):<br>You can add your Dodge bonus to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>against anyone who makes an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>against you while using the<br>Running Attack<br>Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dodge</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","type":"untyped","value":1,"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Migrated from AE system.defenses.reflex.misc","predicates":["defense.designated-dodge-target"],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"targeted_defense_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["defense.designated-dodge-target"],"conditionSummary":"Only applies to Reflex Defense against the designated Dodge target. Never add to static Reflex Defense."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"targeted_defense_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Only applies to Reflex Defense against the designated Dodge target. Never add to static Reflex Defense.","predicateRequirements":["defense.designated-dodge-target"],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Gain a +1 dodge bonus to Reflex Defense against a selected target.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy","Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dodge","effect":"During your turn, you designate an opponent and receive a +1 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense against attacks from that opponent. You can select a new opponent on any action. A situation that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense (if any) also makes you lose dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses."},"effects":[{"name":"Dodge","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.defenses.reflex.misc","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":20}],"disabled":true,"duration":{},"transfer":true,"flags":{"swse":{"type":"feat-defense-bonus","source":"Dodge","defenseType":"reflex","migratedToPassive":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"id":"swse.feat.dodge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dodge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
