{"_id":"4be60753991eec43","name":"Rapid Assault","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you are wielding two weapons or a weapon with which you can use the Double Attack feat, you may spend a Force Point to make two attacks as a Standard Action.\n\nThe normal penalties due to attacking with two weapons or using Double Attack still apply, and you cannot make more than two attacks regardless of how many extra attacks you can make during a Full Attack Action.","prerequisite":"Double Attack or Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"You can only make multiple attacks with the Full Attack Action (a Full-Round Action).","sourcebook":"Web Enhancements","page":1,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Double Attack<br>or<br>Dual Weapon Mastery I<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+6</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you are wielding two weapons or a weapon with which you can use the<br>Double Attack<br>feat, you may spend a<br>Force Point<br>to make two attacks as a<br>Standard Action<br>.<br><br>The normal penalties due to attacking with two weapons or using<br>Double Attack<br>still apply, and you cannot make more than two attacks regardless of how many extra attacks you can make during a<br>Full Attack<br>Action.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You can only make multiple attacks with the<br>Full Attack<br>Action (a<br>Full-Round Action<br>).</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Assault</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Full attack after moving by spending a Force Point.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"action_or_reaction_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Full attack after moving by spending a Force Point.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase14","actionRules":[{"type":"FULL_ATTACK_AFTER_MOVEMENT","cost":"forcePoint"}],"combatActions":[{"id":"rapid-assault-standard-full-attack","name":"Rapid Assault","actionType":"standard","cost":1,"manualResolution":true,"resolutionMode":"manual","useLabel":"Use / Note","relatedSkills":[{"skill":"Attack Roll","when":"Resolve reduced Full Attack sequence manually"}],"resources":["Force Point"],"notes":"Spend a Force Point to make the attack as a Standard action when wielding two weapons or a Double Attack weapon, making one less attack than normal.","description":"Spend a Force Point to compress the qualifying multiple-attack action into a Standard action; resolve the exact attack sequence manually."}],"combatActionCardSource":"phase-t13-ability-combat-action-cards","combatActionCardNotes":"Action card only; execution remains manual until multi-attack sequencing is automated."},"shortSummary":"Through focus and raw determination, you can make multiple attacks even after moving.","prerequisitesText":"Double Attack or Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Web Enhancements (Saga Edition FAQ (E2))"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Assault","effect":"If you are wielding two weapons or a weapon with which you can use the\nDouble Attack\nfeat, you may spend a\nForce Point\nto make two attacks as a\nStandard Action\n.\n\nThe normal penalties due to attacking with two weapons or using\nDouble Attack\nstill apply, and you cannot make more than two attacks regardless of how many extra attacks you can make during a\nFull Attack\nAction."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.rapid_assault","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Assault","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4cc4f4afdcf6e4f8","name":"Collateral Damage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you deal damage with a single, non- Area Attack using the Rapid Shot Feat, once per turn on your turn, you can immediately make a second attack at a -2 penalty against a second target within 2 squares of the first. If this attack hits, you deal half the original attack's damage to that target.","prerequisite":"Rapid Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":20,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rapid Shot<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+6</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you deal damage with a single, non-<br>Area Attack<br>using the<br>Rapid Shot<br>Feat, once per turn on your turn, you can immediately make a second attack at a -2 penalty against a second target within 2 squares of the first. If this attack hits, you deal half the original attack&#x27;s damage to that target.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Collateral_Damage</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":6}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Collateral Damage: Old migrated numeric modifier disabled; represented by non-numeric rider/resource metadata.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit"],"conditionSummary":"Old migrated numeric modifier disabled; represented by non-numeric rider/resource metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"rider_effect","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rapid Shot damage can trigger a once-per-turn secondary attack at -2 for half damage.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 removes false numeric scaffolding and records description-driven rider metadata.","status":"rider_effect_phase9","description":"Rapid Shot damage can trigger a once-per-turn secondary attack at -2 for half damage.","rules":[{"type":"RIDER_EFFECT","trigger":"rapidShotDamage","effect":"secondaryAttackAtPenaltyForHalfDamage","attackPenalty":-2,"oncePer":"turn"}]},"shortSummary":"Gain extra attack upon hitting the first target.","prerequisitesText":"Rapid Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Collateral_Damage","effect":"When you deal damage with a single, non-\nArea Attack\nusing the\nRapid Shot\nFeat, once per turn on your turn, you can immediately make a second attack at a -2 penalty against a second target within 2 squares of the first. If this attack hits, you deal half the original attack's damage to that target."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.collateral_damage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Collateral_Damage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4d6a68d553fb0449","name":"Running Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When making an attack with a melee or ranged weapon, you can move both before and after the attack, provided that the total distance moved is not greater than your Speed.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["feat","general","hit_and_run","mobility","move_action","offense","offense_melee","offense_ranged","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958","f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When making an attack with a melee or ranged weapon, you can move both before and after the attack, provided that the total distance moved is not greater than your Speed.</p>\n<h3>Additional Running Attack Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Dodge<br>):<br>You can add your dodge bonus to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>against anyone who makes an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>against you while using the Running Attack Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Running_Attack</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Running Attack: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"runningAttack","label":"Running Attack","control":"flag","summary":"Movement-dependent option exposed as a flag; movement validation is not automated yet."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate attack/combat option, not a passive sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"Move before and after making an attack.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Running_Attack","effect":"When making an attack with a melee or ranged weapon, you can move both before and after the attack, provided that the total distance moved is not greater than your Speed."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee","attack.with-ranged","turn.on-current-turn"],"id":"swse.feat.running_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Running_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4dc36deda6faf597","name":"Anointed Hunter","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you end your Move at least 2 squares from where you started, you gain a +1 competence bonus on attacks made with Thrown Weapons until the end of your turn.","prerequisite":"Nelvaanian","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":20,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Nelvaanian</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you end your<br>Move<br>at least 2 squares from where you started, you gain a +1 competence bonus on attacks made with<br>Thrown Weapons<br>until the end of your turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Anointed_Hunter</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"+1 thrown weapon attack after moving at least 2 squares.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"+1 thrown weapon attack after moving at least 2 squares.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"attack_option_phase14","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"anointedHunterThrownMove","label":"Anointed Hunter","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresWeaponText":["thrown"],"requiresContextFlags":["movedAtLeastTwoSquares"],"attackModifier":1,"summary":"After moving at least 2 squares, gain +1 competence on thrown weapon attacks until end of turn."}]},"shortSummary":"Move 2 or more squares and gain a +1 bonus on attacks with Thrown Weapons until the end of your turn.","prerequisitesText":"Nelvaanian","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Anointed_Hunter","effect":"If you end your\nMove\nat least 2 squares from where you started, you gain a +1 competence bonus on attacks made with\nThrown Weapons\nuntil the end of your turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.anointed_hunter","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Anointed_Hunter","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4e57ee834c301ad8","name":"Extra Second Wind","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can catch your Second Wind one additional time per day, but you can still only catch a Second Wind once per encounter.","prerequisite":"Trained in Endurance","special":"You can take this Feat multiple times; each time you take this Feat, you can catch a Second Wind one additional time per day. A Nonheroic character that takes this Feat for the first time can catch a Second Wind once per day.","normalText":"A hero can normally catch his or her Second Wind only once per day.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","recovery","second_wind","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Endurance</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can catch your<br>Second Wind<br>one additional time per day, but you can still only catch a<br>Second Wind<br>once per encounter.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> A hero can normally catch his or her<br>Second Wind<br>only once per day.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can take this Feat multiple times; each time you take this Feat, you can catch a<br>Second Wind<br>one additional time per day. A<br>Nonheroic<br>character that takes this Feat for the first time can catch a<br>Second Wind<br>once per day.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Second_Wind</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"35df8faa4878f2c5"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RESOURCE","abilityMeta":{"status":"resource_rule_phase7","description":"Extra Second Wind: metadata is consumed by MetaResourceFeatResolver/resource note adapters.","resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"EXTRA_DAILY_USE_MULTIPLIER","value":1,"description":"Gain one additional Second Wind use per day/recovery cycle."}]},"mechanicsMode":"passive_resource","applicationScope":"secondWind_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Adds one extra Second Wind use per day/recovery cycle; encounter cap remains unchanged.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"EXTRA_DAILY_USE_MULTIPLIER","value":1}]},"shortSummary":"Gain an additional Second Wind per day.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Endurance","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Second_Wind","effect":"You can catch your\nSecond Wind\none additional time per day, but you can still only catch a\nSecond Wind\nonce per encounter."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.381Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.extra_second_wind","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Extra_Second_Wind","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"4eed406661d3313f","name":"Delay Damage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you may delay the effects of damage taken until the end of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Con 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Delay Damage: Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"non_numeric_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Delay Damage now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","reactionRules":[{"type":"DELAY_DAMAGE_EFFECTS","trigger":"takesDamage","oncePer":"encounter","duration":"untilEndOfNextTurn","description":"Once per encounter, delay effects of damage taken until the end of your next turn."}],"resourceRules":{"phase10Special":[]},"status":"non_numeric_rule_phase10","description":"Delay Damage now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"Once per encounter, you may delay the effects of damage taken until the end of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id":"50903195fbb5d090","name":"Blaster Barrage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make an attack with a weapon set on Autofire that deals damage to at least one target within the designated area, you grant a +2 circumstance bonus on any of your allies' Autofire attacks made against that same target until the beginning of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Coordinated Attack","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":33,"tags":["ally_support","area_pressure","autofire","feat","general","offense","offense_melee","offense_ranged","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Coordinated Attack</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make an attack with a weapon set on<br>Autofire<br>that deals damage to at least one target within the designated area, you grant a +2 circumstance bonus on any of your allies&#x27;<br>Autofire<br>attacks made against that same target until the beginning of your next turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Blaster_Barrage</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"autofire_ally_bonus_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Blaster Barrage creates a +2 circumstance bonus for allies making Autofire attacks against targets you damaged with Autofire until your next turn.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"autofire_rider_metadata_phase17","description":"Blaster Barrage creates a +2 circumstance bonus for allies making Autofire attacks against targets you damaged with Autofire until your next turn.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Blaster Barrage creates a +2 circumstance bonus for allies making Autofire attacks against targets you damaged with Autofire until your next turn.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"autofire_ally_bonus_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"blasterBarrage","label":"Blaster Barrage","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAutofire":true,"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"ALLY_AUTOFIRE_ATTACK_BONUS_AGAINST_TARGET","bonus":2,"bonusType":"circumstance","duration":"untilStartOfYourNextTurn"}],"summary":"When your Autofire damages a target, allies gain +2 circumstance on Autofire attacks against that target until your next turn."}]},"shortSummary":"Automatically Aid Another when using Autofire attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Coordinated Attack","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Blaster_Barrage","effect":"When you make an attack with a weapon set on\nAutofire\nthat deals damage to at least one target within the designated area, you grant a +2 circumstance bonus on any of your allies'\nAutofire\nattacks made against that same target until the beginning of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.blaster_barrage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Blaster_Barrage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"513f0d9e7eb6965b","name":"Opportunistic Retreat","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever an opponent provokes an Attack of Opportunity from you, once per turn you can sacrifice the attack to move a number of squares equal to one-half your Speed. Moving in this way does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"Combat Reflexes","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","mobility","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Combat Reflexes</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever an opponent provokes an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>from you, once per turn you can sacrifice the attack to move a number of squares equal to one-half your Speed. Moving in this way does not provoke<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Retreat</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_of_opportunity_trade_for_movement","staticSheetPolicy":"reaction_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Opportunistic Retreat: forgo an Attack of Opportunity to move at half speed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"reaction_metadata_phase16","description":"Opportunistic Retreat: forgo an Attack of Opportunity to move at half speed.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Opportunistic Retreat: forgo an Attack of Opportunity to move at half speed.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"attack_of_opportunity_trade_for_movement","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"reactionRules":[{"type":"TRADE_AOO_FOR_MOVEMENT","movement":"halfSpeed","provokes":false,"description":"Forgo an Attack of Opportunity to move up to half speed as the feat allows."}]},"shortSummary":"Sacrifice Attack of Opportunity to move at half speed.","prerequisitesText":"Combat Reflexes","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Retreat","effect":"Whenever an opponent provokes an\nAttack of Opportunity\nfrom you, once per turn you can sacrifice the attack to move a number of squares equal to one-half your Speed. Moving in this way does not provoke\nAttacks of Opportunity\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.opportunistic_retreat","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Retreat","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"51a2fdd9a7965111","name":"Stand Tall","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter when you take damage, all allies who are within 6 squares of you and within your line of sight can, as a Reaction, make a single attack on the target that damaged you.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":26,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter when you take damage, all allies who are within 6 squares of you and within your line of sight can, as a<br>Reaction<br>, make a single attack on the target that damaged you.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stand_Tall</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"manual_punted","applicationScope":"nearby_ally_or_positioning_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_table_context","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Stand Tall is a nearby-ally reaction feat: once per encounter when you take damage, allies within 6 squares/LOS may attack the attacker. Nearby ally and LOS handling remains GM/table-managed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"table_context_metadata_phase17","description":"Stand Tall is a nearby-ally reaction feat: once per encounter when you take damage, allies within 6 squares/LOS may attack the attacker. Nearby ally and LOS handling remains GM/table-managed.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Stand Tall is a nearby-ally reaction feat: once per encounter when you take damage, allies within 6 squares/LOS may attack the attacker. Nearby ally and LOS handling remains GM/table-managed.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"nearby_ally_or_positioning_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"NEARBY_ALLIES_REACTION_ATTACK_ON_DAMAGE","oncePer":"encounter","rangeSquares":6,"requiresLineOfSight":true,"manualResolution":true,"description":"Stand Tall is a nearby-ally reaction feat: once per encounter when you take damage, allies within 6 squares/LOS may attack the attacker. Nearby ally and LOS handling remains GM/table-managed."}]},"shortSummary":"When you take damage, nearby allies attack your attacker.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stand_Tall","effect":"Once per encounter when you take damage, all allies who are within 6 squares of you and within your line of sight can, as a\nReaction\n, make a single attack on the target that damaged you."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.stand_tall","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stand_Tall","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"526109c14cc81285","name":"Sith Military Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, as a Reaction when you reduce a target to 0 Hit Points or deal damage that exceeds the target's Damage Threshold, you can activate this Feat to cause all enemies within 6 squares of that target to take a -2 penalty to all Defenses until the end of your next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":29,"tags":["background_opportunity","faction_training","feat","general","military","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, as a<br>Reaction<br>when you reduce a target to 0 Hit Points or deal damage that exceeds the target&#x27;s<br>Damage Threshold<br>, you can activate this Feat to cause all enemies within 6 squares of that target to take a -2 penalty to all<br>Defenses<br>until the end of your next turn. This is a<br>Mind-Affecting<br>effect.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sith_Military_Training</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"defense_debuff_reaction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"reaction_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Sith Military Training is a once-per-encounter reaction when you drop a target or exceed DT, imposing -2 defenses on enemies within 6 squares of that target; range/target set remains context metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"reaction_rider_metadata_phase17","description":"Sith Military Training is a once-per-encounter reaction when you drop a target or exceed DT, imposing -2 defenses on enemies within 6 squares of that target; range/target set remains context metadata.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Sith Military Training is a once-per-encounter reaction when you drop a target or exceed DT, imposing -2 defenses on enemies within 6 squares of that target; range/target set remains context metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"defense_debuff_reaction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"reactionRules":[{"type":"ENEMY_DEFENSE_PENALTY_AROUND_DROPPED_TARGET","oncePer":"encounter","trigger":["targetReducedToZeroHp","damageExceedsTargetDT"],"rangeSquares":6,"defensePenalty":-2,"duration":"untilEndOfYourNextTurn","tags":["mind-affecting"],"description":"Enemies within 6 squares of the dropped/overwhelmed target take -2 to all Defenses until end of your next turn."}]},"shortSummary":"Upon debilitating an opponent, you can cause other opponents to lose heart.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sith_Military_Training","effect":"Once per encounter, as a\nReaction\nwhen you reduce a target to 0 Hit Points or deal damage that exceeds the target's\nDamage Threshold\n, you can activate this Feat to cause all enemies within 6 squares of that target to take a -2 penalty to all\nDefenses\nuntil the end of your next turn. This is a\nMind-Affecting\neffect."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.sith_military_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sith_Military_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"52f1a7f7eb33a1f4","name":"Attack Combo (Fire and Strike)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you hit a single target with two consecutive ranged, melee, and/or Unarmed attacks during the same turn, any additional ranged, melee, or Unarmed attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including Attacks of Opportunity and attacks made as Reactions) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other Feats or Talents.","prerequisite":"Attack Combo (Melee), Attack Combo (Ranged), Base Attack Bonus +9","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":15,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Attack Combo (Melee)<br>,<br>Attack Combo (Ranged)<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+9</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you hit a single target with two consecutive ranged, melee, and/or<br>Unarmed<br>attacks during the same turn, any additional ranged, melee, or<br>Unarmed<br>attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>and attacks made as<br>Reactions<br>) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other<br>Feats<br>or<br>Talents<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Fire_and_Strike)</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":9}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee","attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Attack Combo (Fire and Strike): Converted from false attack bonus to a follow-up damage option that adds +1 weapon die after the combo is primed.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee","attack.with-ranged"],"conditionSummary":"Converted from false attack bonus to a follow-up damage option that adds +1 weapon die after the combo is primed."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Rules text or predicates require a selected choice before the modifier can be safely applied.","predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee","attack.with-ranged"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"attackComboFireAndStrike","label":"Attack Combo (Fire and Strike)","control":"toggle","damageExtraWeaponDice":1,"summary":"After hitting the same target twice as required by this feat, toggle this for +1 weapon die on qualifying follow-up attacks until the end of your next turn."}],"status":"attackComboFireAndStrike_attack_option_phase12","description":"Converted from false attack bonus to a follow-up damage option that adds +1 weapon die after the combo is primed."},"shortSummary":"Deal +1 die of damage on Unarmed, melee, or ranged attacks until the end of your next turn after hitting an enemy with two Unarmed, melee, or ranged attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Attack Combo (Melee), Attack Combo (Ranged), Base Attack Bonus +9","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Fire_and_Strike)","effect":"If you hit a single target with two consecutive ranged, melee, and/or\nUnarmed\nattacks during the same turn, any additional ranged, melee, or\nUnarmed\nattacks you make until the end of your next turn (including\nAttacks of Opportunity\nand attacks made as\nReactions\n) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other\nFeats\nor\nTalents\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee","attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.attack_combo_fire_and_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Fire_and_Strike)","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"53444cc061d81627","name":"Force Boon","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You gain three additional Force Points at each level.","prerequisite":"Force Sensitivity","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":94,"tags":["feat","force","force_point_spend","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Sensitivity</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain three additional<br>Force Points<br>at each level.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Boon</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RESOURCE","abilityMeta":{"status":"resource_rule_phase7","description":"Force Boon: metadata is consumed by MetaResourceFeatResolver/resource note adapters.","resourceRules":{"forcePoints":[{"type":"MAX_BONUS","value":3,"description":"Gain three additional Force Points at each level."}]},"mechanicsMode":"passive_resource","applicationScope":"forcePoints_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Always grants +3 maximum Force Points each level.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Gain three additional Force Points at each level.","prerequisitesText":"Force Sensitivity","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Boon","effect":"You gain three additional\nForce Points\nat each level."},"effects":[{"_id":"77311d06-cd4c-4e4e-88a1-3eb53ba7bf60","name":"Force Boon","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Force Boon","effectType":"passive","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.force_boon","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Boon","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"53f600d68f3afdc3","name":"Unwavering Resolve","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 insight bonus to Will Defense against Deception and Persuasion checks.","prerequisite":"Trained in Perception","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":28,"tags":["defense","feat","general","skill_deception","skill_persuasion","skill_synergy","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Perception</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +5 insight bonus to<br>Will Defense<br>against<br>Deception<br>and<br>Persuasion<br>checks.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unwavering_Resolve</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"43c5941072ec78af"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Unwavering Resolve: Implemented as conditional defense metadata; not a global attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.will"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as conditional defense metadata; not a global attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"defense_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Unwavering Resolve now exposes conditional defense metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","conditionalDefenseBonuses":[{"type":"CONDITIONAL_DEFENSE_BONUS","targets":["defense.will"],"value":5,"bonusType":"insight","requiresContextFlags":["againstDeceptionOrPersuasionCheck"],"description":"Gain +5 insight Will Defense against Deception and Persuasion checks."}],"status":"conditional_defense_phase10","description":"Unwavering Resolve now exposes conditional defense metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"Gain a +5 bonus to Will Defense against Deception and Persuasion checks.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Perception","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unwavering_Resolve","effect":"You gain a +5 insight bonus to\nWill Defense\nagainst\nDeception\nand\nPersuasion\nchecks."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.unwavering_resolve","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unwavering_Resolve","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"54d6201340a6757f","name":"Headstrong","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Will Defense against fear effects and may reroll a failed Will Defense check once per encounter.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":25,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.will","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will","effect.fear"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Headstrong: +2 Will Defense against fear effects; failed Will reroll once per encounter.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"contextual_defense","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.will","effect.fear"],"conditionSummary":"+2 Will Defense against fear effects; failed Will reroll once per encounter."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"contextual_defense","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["defense.will","turn.once-per-round"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","defenseRerolls":[{"id":"fear_will_reroll","type":"DEFENSE_REROLL","defense":"will","oncePer":"encounter","trigger":"failedDefense","outcome":"keepBetter","predicateRequirements":["defense.will","effect.fear"],"