{"_id":"5535b5d495f381f5","name":"Recurring Success","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you select this Feat, choose one Talent or Feat that can normally be used once per encounter. You can use that Talent or Feat one additional time per encounter.","prerequisite":"None","special":"You can select this Feat multiple times. Each time you do so, you must choose a different Talent or Feat to gain the benefits of this Feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":23,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you select this Feat, choose one<br>Talent<br>or<br>Feat<br>that can normally be used once per encounter. You can use that<br>Talent<br>or<br>Feat<br>one additional time per encounter.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can select this Feat multiple times. Each time you do so, you must choose a different<br>Talent<br>or<br>Feat<br>to gain the benefits of this Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recurring_Success</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Recurring Success","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Choose one once-per-encounter feat or talent.","metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","disabledReason":"Phase 6: choice captured now; execution waits for roll/action context wiring."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose one once-per-encounter feat or talent.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated."},"shortSummary":"Gain extra use of a 1/encounter Talent or Feat.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recurring_Success","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"once_per_encounter_ability_choice","repeatable":true,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.recurring_success","choiceSource":"actorState","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.once_per_encounter_ability_choice"},"effect":"When you select this Feat, choose one\nTalent\nor\nFeat\nthat can normally be used once per encounter. You can use that\nTalent\nor\nFeat\none additional time per encounter."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.recurring_success","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recurring_Success","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"55483fd350b3ba28","name":"Aquatic Specialists","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Swim checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Swim","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_swim","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8","manual_resolution","teamwork_base_skill_bonus_phase15"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Swim</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +3 competence bonus on<br>Swim<br>checks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).<br><br>Additionally, when you<br>Swim<br>, you swim at half your speed as a<br>Move Action<br>(or you swim at your full speed as a<br>Full-Round Action<br>).</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aquatic_Specialists</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_with_manual_teamwork","applicationScope":"skill_roll_plus_manual_teamwork","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Aquatic Specialists: +3 competence skill bonus applies normally; nearby-ally scaling and other battlefield/teamwork clauses are GM/player managed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 avoids automating nearby-ally/battlefield positioning clauses; base skill bonuses are implemented where unambiguous and teamwork clauses are preserved as manual metadata.","implementationStatus":"base_skill_bonus_manual_teamwork_phase15","description":"Aquatic Specialists: base +3 competence skill bonus implemented; nearby-ally scaling and special teamwork clauses remain table-managed flavor/manual metadata.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"aquatic-specialists","skillKey":"swim","type":"competence","featName":"Aquatic Specialists","description":"Aquatic Specialists: +3 competence bonus to swim checks. Nearby-ally scaling is manual/table-managed.","value":3}],"teamworkRules":[{"type":"SKILL_MOVEMENT_RATE","skillKey":"swim","moveActionSpeedFraction":0.5,"fullRoundSpeedFraction":1,"description":"Swim at half speed as a move action or full speed as a full-round action.","automation":"manual","manualResolution":true}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Swim checks when near allies.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aquatic_Specialists","rawImport":{"name":"Aquatic Specialists","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aquatic_Specialists","pageTitle":"Aquatic_Specialists","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\aquatic_specialists.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nSwim","prerequisites":["Trained\nin\nSwim"],"effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nSwim\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you\nSwim\n, you swim at half your speed as a\nMove Action\n(or you swim at your full speed as a\nFull-Round Action\n).","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Trained in Swim","indexBenefit":"Gain bonuses on Swim checks when near allies.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Team Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nTeam Feats\n\nYou and your allies have trained extensively in\nUnderwater Combat\nand specialize in missions in aquatic environments.\n\nPrerequisite:\nTrained\nin\nSwim\n\nEffect:\nYou gain a +3 competence bonus on\nSwim\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you\nSwim\n, you swim at half your speed as a\nMove Action\n(or you swim at your full speed as a\nFull-Round Action\n)."},"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nSwim","effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nSwim\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you\nSwim\n, you swim at half your speed as a\nMove Action\n(or you swim at your full speed as a\nFull-Round Action\n)."},"effects":[{"_id":"457bea9c-bde5-4d8e-b463-622d2db80636","name":"Aquatic Specialists","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Aquatic Specialists","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.aquatic_specialists"}}}
{"_id":"56367f3943ee8c17","name":"Sniper","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You always ignore Soft Cover (that is, Cover provided by a character, creature, or Droid) when you make a ranged attack.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"","normalText":"You can only ignore Cover if you Aim before making a ranged attack.","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["accuracy","cover_play","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged","setup","sniping"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot<br>,<br>Precise Shot<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+4</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You always ignore<br>Soft Cover<br>(that is,<br>Cover<br>provided by a character, creature, or<br>Droid<br>) when you make a ranged attack.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You can only ignore<br>Cover<br>if you<br>Aim<br>before making a ranged attack.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Sniper: Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-ranged"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Sniper now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"sniper","label":"Sniper","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","suppresses":["softCoverFromCreature"],"summary":"Ignore soft cover from characters, creatures, or droids on ranged attacks."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Sniper now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description."},"shortSummary":"You ignore Soft Cover when making a ranged attack.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper","effect":"You always ignore\nSoft Cover\n(that is,\nCover\nprovided by a character, creature, or\nDroid\n) when you make a ranged attack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.sniper","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5824e2360feb505a","name":"Improved Grapple","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 bonus on grapple checks and do not provoke attacks of opportunity when initiating a grapple.","prerequisite":"Int 13, Grapple","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"grapple_attack_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Improved Grapple: +5 on grapple checks and suppresses the normal attack of opportunity for initiating a grapple.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"attack_option_phase16","description":"Improved Grapple: +5 on grapple checks and suppresses the normal attack of opportunity for initiating a grapple.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Improved Grapple: +5 on grapple checks and suppresses the normal attack of opportunity for initiating a grapple.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"grapple_attack_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"improvedGrapple","label":"Improved Grapple","control":"passive","requiresManeuver":"grapple","attackModifier":5,"suppresses":["grappleInitiationAoO"],"summary":"+5 on grapple checks; initiating the grapple does not provoke an attack of opportunity."}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +5 bonus on grapple checks and do not provoke attacks of opportunity when initiating a grapple."},"effects":[{"_id":"051a0e7f-c11a-44af-95eb-683f9d8d7467","name":"Improved Grapple","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Improved Grapple","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Improved Grapple"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"58d3d0aece0f3bdc","name":"Improved Sleight of Hand","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Sleight of Hand application of the Stealth Skill, you can use your Deception Skill to improve your chances of success. Prior to making the Stealth check, you can make a Deception check as a Swift Action. The opposed Perception check of anyone attempting to notice your action must exceed both your Deception check and your Stealth check.\n\nAdditionally, you can, as a single Action, use Improved Sleight of Hand to simultaneously draw and palm a weapon two sizes smaller than you. Make a Stealth check as a Free Action when drawing your weapon to successfully conceal it in a position in your hand (Or similar appendage), where you can use it on a following Action. Once the weapon is used, you can attempt to palm it again as a Swift Action.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 15, Skill Focus (Deception), Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":23,"tags":["feat","general","skill_deception","skill_sleight_of_hand","skill_stealth","skill_synergy"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>15,<br>Skill Focus (Deception)<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Stealth</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using the<br>Sleight of Hand<br>application of the<br>Stealth<br>Skill, you can use your<br>Deception<br>Skill to improve your chances of success. Prior to making the<br>Stealth<br>check, you can make a<br>Deception<br>check as a<br>Swift Action<br>. The opposed<br>Perception<br>check of anyone attempting to notice your action must exceed both your<br>Deception<br>check and your<br>Stealth<br>check.<br><br>Additionally, you can, as a single Action, use Improved Sleight of Hand to simultaneously draw and palm a weapon two sizes smaller than you. Make a<br>Stealth<br>check as a<br>Free Action<br>when drawing your weapon to successfully conceal it in a position in your hand (Or similar appendage), where you can use it on a following Action. Once the weapon is used, you can attempt to palm it again as a<br>Swift Action<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Sleight_of_Hand</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"deception_stealth_sleight_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Improved Sleight of Hand: use Deception to aid Stealth for sleight of hand and use Stealth to draw/pass hidden objects.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_rule_phase16","description":"Improved Sleight of Hand: use Deception to aid Stealth for sleight of hand and use Stealth to draw/pass hidden objects.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Improved Sleight of Hand: use Deception to aid Stealth for sleight of hand and use Stealth to draw/pass hidden objects.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"deception_stealth_sleight_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"SKILL_AIDS_SKILL_USE","fromSkill":"deception","toSkill":"stealth","applications":["sleight of hand"],"description":"Use Deception to aid Stealth checks made for sleight of hand."},{"type":"STEALTH_DRAW_OR_PASS_HIDDEN_OBJECT","skillKey":"stealth","description":"Use Stealth to draw or pass hidden objects as described by the feat."}]},"shortSummary":"Use Deception to aid your Stealth check to use Sleight of Hand; use Stealth to draw and palm a weapon simultaneously.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 15, Skill Focus (Deception), Trained in Stealth","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Sleight_of_Hand","effect":"When using the\nSleight of Hand\napplication of the\nStealth\nSkill, you can use your\nDeception\nSkill to improve your chances of success. Prior to making the\nStealth\ncheck, you can make a\nDeception\ncheck as a\nSwift Action\n. The opposed\nPerception\ncheck of anyone attempting to notice your action must exceed both your\nDeception\ncheck and your\nStealth\ncheck.\n\nAdditionally, you can, as a single Action, use Improved Sleight of Hand to simultaneously draw and palm a weapon two sizes smaller than you. Make a\nStealth\ncheck as a\nFree Action\nwhen drawing your weapon to successfully conceal it in a position in your hand (Or similar appendage), where you can use it on a following Action. Once the weapon is used, you can attempt to palm it again as a\nSwift Action\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.improved_sleight_of_hand","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Sleight_of_Hand","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"59e495de34a23def","name":"Leader of Droids","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you provide a beneficial, Mind-Affecting effect to your allies, you may select from among these allies a number of Droids equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1). The Droids you designate ignore their Mind-Affecting immunity with regards to this effect, provided they are willing to ignore this immunity.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":25,"tags":["feat","general","social","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you provide a beneficial,<br>Mind-Affecting<br>effect to your allies, you may select from among these allies a number of Droids equal to your<br>Intelligence<br>modifier (minimum 1). The Droids you designate ignore their<br>Mind-Affecting<br>immunity with regards to this effect, provided they are willing to ignore this immunity.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Leader_of_Droids</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"nearby_ally_or_positioning_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_table_context","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Leader of Droids lets selected willing Droid allies benefit from your beneficial Mind-Affecting effects; effect propagation is explicit metadata/table-managed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"table_context_metadata_phase17","description":"Leader of Droids lets selected willing Droid allies benefit from your beneficial Mind-Affecting effects; effect propagation is explicit metadata/table-managed.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Leader of Droids lets selected willing Droid allies benefit from your beneficial Mind-Affecting effects; effect propagation is explicit metadata/table-managed.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"nearby_ally_or_positioning_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"ALLOW_WILLING_DROID_ALLIES_BENEFIT_FROM_BENEFICIAL_MIND_AFFECTING_EFFECTS","countFormula":"intModifierMinimum1","manualResolution":true,"description":"Leader of Droids lets selected willing Droid allies benefit from your beneficial Mind-Affecting effects; effect propagation is explicit metadata/table-managed."}]},"shortSummary":"Allied Droids benefit from your beneficial Mind-Affecting effects.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Leader_of_Droids","effect":"Whenever you provide a beneficial,\nMind-Affecting\neffect to your allies, you may select from among these allies a number of Droids equal to your\nIntelligence\nmodifier (minimum 1). The Droids you designate ignore their\nMind-Affecting\nimmunity with regards to this effect, provided they are willing to ignore this immunity."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.leader_of_droids","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Leader_of_Droids","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5a2ba2f28bc5ee01","name":"Perfect Intuition","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Reroll Initiative checks, always keeping the better result.","prerequisite":"Cerean","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["control","feat","grapple","racial","reroll","skill_initiative","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity","skill_reroll","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-cerean"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Cerean</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you reroll an<br>Initiative<br>check, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Perfect_Intuition</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_reroll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Perfect Intuition: whenever you reroll initiative, keep the better result.","predicateRequirements":["skill.initiative"],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 continues description-guided implementation by improving teamwork skill feats, skill substitutions, force/dark-side skill context, and several remaining action/resource rider feats.","implementationStatus":"reroll_outcome_upgrade_phase15","description":"Perfect Intuition: improves initiative rerolls to keep the better result.","skillRerollOutcomeUpgrades":[{"id":"perfect-intuition","skillKey":"initiative","outcome":"keepBetter","description":"Whenever you reroll initiative, keep the better result."}],"skillRerolls":[{"id":"perfect-intuition","skillKey":"initiative","outcome":"keepBetter","label":"Perfect Intuition","description":"Perfect Intuition: reroll initiative and keep the better result."}]},"shortSummary":"Reroll Initiative checks, always keeping the better result.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Perfect_Intuition","rawImport":{"name":"Perfect Intuition","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Perfect_Intuition","pageTitle":"Perfect_Intuition","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\perfect_intuition.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Cerean","prerequisites":["Cerean"],"effect":"Whenever you reroll an\nInitiative\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Cerean","indexBenefit":"Reroll Initiative checks, always keeping the better result.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYour insights serve you well, giving you some of the fastest reaction times among members of your Species.\n\nPrerequisite:\nCerean\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you reroll an\nInitiative\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities."},"prerequisitesText":"Cerean","effect":"Whenever you reroll an\nInitiative\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.perfect_intuition"}}}
{"_id":"5afd91fb081e576b","name":"Linguist","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a number of additional Languages equal to 1 + your Intelligence modifier (Minimum 1).","prerequisite":"Intelligence 13","special":"You can take this Feat more than once. Each time you take this Feat, you gain a number of additional languages equal to 1 + your Intelligence modifier (Minimum 1). If your Intelligence modifier increases so does the number of languages granted by this Feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["ability_intelligence","feat","general","choice_required","grant_choice","deferred_choice","choice_source_grant_pool"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a number of additional<br>Languages<br>equal to 1 + your<br>Intelligence<br>modifier (Minimum 1).</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can take this Feat more than once. Each time you take this Feat, you gain a number of additional languages equal to 1 + your<br>Intelligence<br>modifier (Minimum 1). If your<br>Intelligence<br>modifier increases so does the number of languages granted by this Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Linguist</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"int","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"implemented","applicationScope":"chargen_language_step","staticSheetPolicy":"implemented","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Linguist is treated as implemented through the chargen/progression language step rather than 