{"_id":"5d17898fc9652370","name":"Droid Hunter","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While wielding a weapon with which you are proficient, you gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls against Droid enemies, or +4 if you are using a weapon that deals Ion Damage.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":21,"tags":["feat","general","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> While wielding a weapon with which you are proficient, you gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls against<br>Droid<br>enemies, or +4 if you are using a weapon that deals<br>Ion Damage<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Hunter</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Damage bonus against droid targets, upgraded for ion weapons.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Damage bonus against droid targets, upgraded for ion weapons.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"attack_option_phase14","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"droidHunterDamage","label":"Droid Hunter","control":"passive","requiresTargetType":["droid"],"excludesDamageType":["ion"],"damageModifier":2,"summary":"+2 damage against droid targets."},{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"droidHunterIonDamage","label":"Droid Hunter (Ion)","control":"passive","requiresTargetType":["droid"],"requiresDamageType":["ion"],"damageModifier":4,"summary":"+4 damage against droid targets when using ion weapons."}]},"shortSummary":"Deal +2 damage to Droid enemies, or +4 when using an Ion Weapon.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Hunter","effect":"While wielding a weapon with which you are proficient, you gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls against\nDroid\nenemies, or +4 if you are using a weapon that deals\nIon Damage\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.droid_hunter","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Hunter","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5e1e84d933295217","name":"Experienced Medic","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can perform Surgery on a number of creatures equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 2) simultaneously. You make Treat Injury checks for each individual creature as normal.","prerequisite":"Trained in Treat Injury","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":22,"tags":["feat","general","healing","skill_treat_injury","support"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Treat Injury</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can perform<br>Surgery<br>on a number of creatures equal to your<br>Intelligence<br>modifier (minimum 2) simultaneously. You make<br>Treat Injury<br>checks for each individual creature as normal.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Experienced_Medic</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"treatinjury"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"treat_injury_surgery_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Experienced Medic: perform surgery on multiple creatures at the same time.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_rule_phase16","description":"Experienced Medic: perform surgery on multiple creatures at the same time.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Experienced Medic: perform surgery on multiple creatures at the same time.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"treat_injury_surgery_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"MULTI_TARGET_SKILL_USE","skillKey":"treatInjury","applications":["surgery"],"targetCountFormula":"max(2,int.mod)","description":"Perform surgery on multiple creatures simultaneously, up to Intelligence modifier minimum 2."}]},"shortSummary":"Perform Surgery on multiple creatures simultaneously.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Treat Injury","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Experienced_Medic","effect":"You can perform\nSurgery\non a number of creatures equal to your\nIntelligence\nmodifier (minimum 2) simultaneously. You make\nTreat Injury\nchecks for each individual creature as normal."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.experienced_medic","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Experienced_Medic","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5e471161ad85b040","name":"Vehicular Surge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If the Vehicle you Pilot is Colossal or smaller and is reduced to fewer than one-half its maximum Hit Points, once per day as a Swift Action your Vehicle gains a number of Bonus Hit Points equal to one-quarter its maximum Hit Point total. Damage is subtracted from Bonus Hit Points first, and any Bonus Hit Points remaining at the end of the encounter are lost. Bonus Hit Points do not stack.","prerequisite":"Trained in Pilot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Rebellion Era Campaign Guide","page":23,"tags":["defense","durability","feat","general","hit_points","skill_pilot","skill_synergy","survivability","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Pilot</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If the<br>Vehicle<br>you<br>Pilot<br>is Colossal or smaller and is reduced to fewer than one-half its maximum Hit Points, once per day as a<br>Swift Action<br>your<br>Vehicle<br>gains a number of<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>equal to one-quarter its maximum Hit Point total. Damage is subtracted from<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>first, and any<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>remaining at the end of the encounter are lost.<br>Bonus Hit Points<br>do not stack.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Surge</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"b8dad0c963f046c6"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Vehicular Surge: Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"non_numeric_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Vehicular Surge now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","reactionRules":[],"resourceRules":{"phase10Special":[{"type":"VEHICLE_BONUS_HP_WHEN_BLOODIED","trigger":"pilotedVehicleBelowHalfHp","action":"swift","oncePer":"day","vehicleSizeMax":"colossal","bonusHpFormula":"oneQuarterVehicleMaxHp","duration":"encounter","description":"Swift action: piloted Colossal-or-smaller vehicle below half HP gains bonus HP equal to one-quarter max HP."}]},"status":"non_numeric_rule_phase10","description":"Vehicular Surge now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"Once per day, gain Bonus Hit Points for a Vehicle you Pilot.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Pilot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Surge","effect":"If the\nVehicle\nyou\nPilot\nis Colossal or smaller and is reduced to fewer than one-half its maximum Hit Points, once per day as a\nSwift Action\nyour\nVehicle\ngains a number of\nBonus Hit Points\nequal to one-quarter its maximum Hit Point total. Damage is subtracted from\nBonus Hit Points\nfirst, and any\nBonus Hit Points\nremaining at the end of the encounter are lost.\nBonus Hit Points\ndo not stack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.vehicular_surge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicular_Surge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"5f479944307731d1","name":"Attack Combo (Melee)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you hit a single target with two consecutive melee and/or Unarmed attacks during the same turn, any additional melee or Unarmed attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including Attacks of Opportunity and attacks made as Reactions) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other Feats or Talents.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +3","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":15,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+3</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you hit a single target with two consecutive melee and/or<br>Unarmed<br>attacks during the same turn, any additional melee or<br>Unarmed<br>attacks you make until the end of your next turn (including<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>and attacks made as<br>Reactions<br>) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other<br>Feats<br>or<br>Talents<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Melee)</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":3}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Attack Combo (Melee): Converted from false attack bonus to a follow-up damage option that adds +1 weapon die after the combo is primed.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee"],"conditionSummary":"Converted from false attack bonus to a follow-up damage option that adds +1 weapon die after the combo is primed."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Rules text or predicates require a selected choice before the modifier can be safely applied.","predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"attackComboMelee","label":"Attack Combo (Melee)","control":"toggle","damageExtraWeaponDice":1,"summary":"After hitting the same target twice as required by this feat, toggle this for +1 weapon die on qualifying follow-up attacks until the end of your next turn.","requiresAttackType":"melee"}],"status":"attackComboMelee_attack_option_phase12","description":"Converted from false attack bonus to a follow-up damage option that adds +1 weapon die after the combo is primed."},"shortSummary":"Deal +1 die of damage on Unarmed or melee attacks until the end of your next turn after hitting an enemy with two Unarmed or melee attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +3","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Melee)","effect":"If you hit a single target with two consecutive melee and/or\nUnarmed\nattacks during the same turn, any additional melee or\nUnarmed\nattacks you make until the end of your next turn (including\nAttacks of Opportunity\nand attacks made as\nReactions\n) deal +1 die of damage on a hit. This extra damage stacks with extra damage granted by other\nFeats\nor\nTalents\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.attack_combo_melee","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Attack_Combo_(Melee)","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"600f43af4edb16f7","name":"Whirlwind Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Full-Round Action, you can make an Area Attack with your melee weapon, striking every target within your reach. This Whirlwind Attack uses the Area Attack rules; you make one attack roll and apply the result to every target in range.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13, Intelligence 13, Melee Defense, Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["crowd_control","feat","full_round_action","general","multi_target","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13,<br>Intelligence<br>13,<br>Melee Defense<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+4</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Full-Round Action<br>, you can make an<br>Area Attack<br>with your melee weapon, striking every target within your reach. This Whirlwind Attack uses the<br>Area Attack<br>rules; you make one attack roll and apply the result to every target in range.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Whirlwind_Attack</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13},{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rider_effect_phase7","description":"Whirlwind Attack: modeled as a rider/action rule, not a numeric modifier.","rules":[{"type":"MULTI_TARGET_ATTACK_ACTION","action":"whirlwindAttack","requiresAttackType":"melee","targets":"eachOpponentWithinReach","attackCount":"onePerTarget"}],"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Whirlwind Attack: numeric scaffold disabled by Phase 7 (description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus)","mechanicsMode":"metadata_note","applicationScope":"not_a_numeric_modifier","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus","metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"multi_target_melee_action","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Full-round melee action against each opponent within reach; no standing attack bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata.","combatActions":[{"id":"whirlwind-attack-area-melee","name":"Whirlwind Attack","actionType":"full-round","cost":1,"manualResolution":true,"resolutionMode":"manual","useLabel":"Use / Note","relatedSkills":[{"skill":"Attack Roll","when":"Resolve the melee area attack manually"}],"resources":["Area melee attack"],"notes":"As a full-round action, make an area attack with your melee weapon against all targets within your reach.","description":"Make a melee area attack as a Full-Round action. Resolve targets and attack rolls at the table."}],"combatActionCardSource":"phase-t13-ability-combat-action-cards","combatActionCardNotes":"Action card only; execution remains manual until multi-attack sequencing is automated."},"shortSummary":"Make one melee attack against each opponent within reach.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13, Intelligence 13, Melee Defense, Base Attack Bonus +4","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Whirlwind_Attack","effect":"As a\nFull-Round Action\n, you can make an\nArea Attack\nwith your melee weapon, striking every target within your reach. This Whirlwind Attack uses the\nArea Attack\nrules; you make one attack roll and apply the result to every target in range."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.whirlwind_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Whirlwind_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6179746c48e30c26","name":"Nikto Survival","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Select a Nikto subspecies: Kajain'sa'Nikto (Desert), Kadas'sa'Nikto (Forest), Esral'sa'Nikto (Mountains), Gluss'sa'Nikto (Ocean), M'shento'su,Nikto (Arctic). In addition to the usual Nikto Species Traits, when operating in an environment advantageous to your native subspecies, you can reroll any Survival check, taking the better result.","prerequisite":"Nikto","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":26,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase10","feat","general","reroll","skill_survival","skill_synergy","species_prerequisite_phase10","species_rule"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Nikto</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Select a<br>Nikto<br>subspecies: Kajain&#x27;sa&#x27;Nikto (Desert), Kadas&#x27;sa&#x27;Nikto (Forest), Esral&#x27;sa&#x27;Nikto (Mountains), Gluss&#x27;sa&#x27;Nikto (Ocean), M&#x27;shento&#x27;su,Nikto (Arctic). In addition to the usual<br>Nikto<br>Species Traits, when operating in an environment advantageous to your native subspecies, you can reroll any<br>Survival<br>check, taking the better result.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nikto_Survival</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"species_rule_phase10_skill_reroll_hook","description":"Nikto Survival: reroll Survival checks in native environment. Context must explicitly indicate native environment.","skillRerolls":[{"id":"nikto-survival","skillKeys":["survival"],"requiresContextFlags":["nativeEnvironment"],"outcome":"keepSecond","label":"Nikto Survival","description":"Reroll Survival checks in native environment; GM/context determines native environment."}],"conditionNotes":[{"id":"nikto-survival","label":"Nikto Survival","severity":"info","text":"May reroll Survival checks in native environment when the GM/context confirms it.","mechanical":true,"gmEnforced":true}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose the Nikto subspecies/native environment package.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","modifiers":[]},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"species","species":["Nikto"]}],"_source":"phase10_species_prereq"},"shortSummary":"Reroll Survival checks in native environment.","prerequisitesText":"Nikto","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nikto_Survival","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"nikto_subspecies","repeatable":false,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.nikto_survival","choiceSource":"fixed","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.nikto_subspecies"},"effect":"Select a\nNikto\nsubspecies: Kajain'sa'Nikto (Desert), Kadas'sa'Nikto (Forest), Esral'sa'Nikto (Mountains), Gluss'sa'Nikto (Ocean), M'shento'su,Nikto (Arctic). In addition to the usual\nNikto\nSpecies Traits, when operating in an environment advantageous to your native subspecies, you can reroll any\nSurvival\ncheck, taking the better result."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.nikto_survival","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nikto_Survival","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"61c053191d05d0a2","name":"Knife Trick","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you have a concealed weapon, you Threaten squares as though armed with a melee weapon. When you can make an Attack of Opportunity, you can draw a weapon you have successfully concealed on your person and make a single attack against the target.\n\nIf you choose not to draw your concealed weapon and attack with it, you cannot make the Attack of Opportunity unless you would otherwise normally be able to do so.","prerequisite":"Lightning Draw, Quick Draw, Trained in Stealth","special":"","normalText":"With the Quick Draw feat, drawing or holstering a weapon is a Swift Action.","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":25,"tags":["feat","general","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Lightning Draw<br>,<br>Quick Draw<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Stealth</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you have a concealed weapon, you<br>Threaten<br>squares as though armed with a melee weapon. When you can make an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>, you can draw a weapon you have successfully concealed on your person and make a single attack against the target.<br><br>If you choose not to draw your concealed weapon and attack with it, you cannot make the<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>unless you would otherwise normally be able to do so.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> With the<br>Quick Draw<br>feat, drawing or holstering a weapon is a<br>Swift Action<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knife_Trick</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"6d2ac22d9fcf402f"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"concealed_weapon_opportunity_context","staticSheetPolicy":"reaction_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Knife Trick: concealed weapon threatens squares and can be drawn for an Attack of Opportunity.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"concealed_weapon_aoo_metadata_phase16","description":"Knife Trick: concealed weapon threatens squares and can be drawn for an Attack of Opportunity.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Knife Trick: concealed weapon threatens squares and can be drawn for an Attack of Opportunity.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"concealed_weapon_opportunity_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"THREATEN_WITH_CONCEALED_WEAPON","description":"If you have a concealed weapon, you threaten squares as though armed with a melee weapon."},{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"knifeTrick","label":"Knife Trick","control":"passive","requiresOpportunityAttack":true,"requiresWeaponText":["knife","dagger","blade","concealed"],"summary":"Draw a successfully concealed weapon and make the Attack of Opportunity with it."}]},"shortSummary":"Attack of Opportunity with concealed weapon to greater effect.","prerequisitesText":"Lightning Draw, Quick Draw, Trained in Stealth","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knife_Trick","effect":"If you have a concealed weapon, you\nThreaten\nsquares as though armed with a melee weapon. When you can make an\nAttack of Opportunity\n, you can draw a weapon you have successfully concealed on your person and make a single attack against the target.\n\nIf you choose not to draw your concealed weapon and attack with it, you cannot make the\nAttack of Opportunity\nunless you would otherwise normally be able to do so."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.knife_trick","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knife_Trick","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"627b92fefdc552d2","name":"Forceful Recovery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"Whenever you catch a Second Wind, choose one expended Force Power and return that power to your Force Power Suite.","prerequisite":"Force Sensitivity, Force Training","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["cover_play","defense","execution_mapped_phase8","feat","force","force_powers","recovery","resource_second_wind","second_wind","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Sensitivity<br>,<br>Force Training</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you catch a<br>Second Wind<br>, choose one expended<br>Force Power<br>and return that power to your<br>Force Power Suite<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Recovery</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Forceful Recovery","mechanicsMode":"manual","applicationScope":"manual_or_unimplemented","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Current abilityMeta explicitly marks the feat as requiring manual mapping and has no enabled numeric modifiers."}],"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"REGAIN_FORCE_POWER_ON_USE","count":1,"description":"Regain one expended Force power when you catch a Second Wind."}]},"mechanicsMode":"passive_resource","applicationScope":"secondWind_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"ActorEngine flags a pending Force power recovery when Second Wind is used.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase8-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics.","status":"second_wind_rule_phase8_hardened","description":"Forceful Recovery: catching Second Wind records a pending Force power recovery prompt."},"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"REGAIN_FORCE_POWER_ON_USE"}]},"shortSummary":"Regain one Force Power when you catch a Second Wind.","prerequisitesText":"Force Sensitivity, Force Training","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Recovery","effect":"Whenever you catch a\nSecond Wind\n, choose one expended\nForce Power\nand return that power to your\nForce Power Suite\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.forceful_recovery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Recovery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"62fdf44c56b24507","name":"Careful Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you Aim before making a ranged attack, you gain a +1 bonus on your attack roll.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot Feat, Base Attack Bonus +2","special":"A Pilot can use this Feat, but since they must spend at least one Move Action operating their Vehicles, they must split their Aim (two Swift Actions) and attack (Standard Action) into two separate turns, making it more likely that the target will break line of sight or avoid you.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot<br>Feat,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+2</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you<br>Aim<br>before making a ranged attack, you gain a +1 bonus on your attack roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> A<br>Pilot<br>can use this Feat, but since they must spend at least one<br>Move Action<br>operating their<br>Vehicles<br>, they must split their<br>Aim<br>(two<br>Swift Actions<br>) and attack (<br>Standard Action<br>) into two separate turns, making it more likely that the target will break line of sight or avoid you.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Careful_Shot</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":2}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Careful Shot: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"carefulShot","label":"Careful Shot","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAim":true,"attackModifier":1,"summary":"When aiming with a ranged weapon, gain +1 on the attack roll."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate attack/combat option, not a passive sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"If you Aim, gain +1 bonus on the attack roll.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot Feat, Base Attack Bonus +2","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Careful_Shot","effect":"If you\nAim\nbefore making a ranged attack, you gain a +1 bonus on your attack roll."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.careful_shot","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Careful_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6335692284f98ec6","name":"Flood of Fire","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make an Area Attack with a weapon set on Autofire, and you are proficient with that weapon, all targets in the area lose all dodge or deflection bonuses to Reflex Defense against the Autofire attack.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":23,"tags":["area_pressure","autofire","feat","general","multi_target","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make an<br>Area Attack<br>with a weapon set on<br>Autofire<br>, and you are proficient with that weapon, all targets in the area lose all dodge or deflection bonuses to<br>Reflex Defense<br>against the<br>Autofire<br>attack.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flood_of_Fire</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Flood of Fire: Implemented as CombatOptionResolver/rider metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as CombatOptionResolver/rider metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Flood of Fire now has explicit roll-context/rider metadata from its description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"floodOfFire","label":"Flood of Fire","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAutofire":true,"requiresContextFlags":["areaAttack"],"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"IGNORE_TARGET_DODGE_DEFLECTION_TO_REFLEX","target":"targetsInArea","description":"Targets in the autofire area lose dodge/deflection bonuses to Reflex against this attack."}],"summary":"Autofire area targets lose dodge/deflection bonuses to Reflex against the attack."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Flood of Fire now has explicit roll-context/rider metadata from its description."},"shortSummary":"Ignore enemies' dodge and deflection bonus to Reflex Defense when making Area Attacks with a weapon set on Autofire.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flood_of_Fire","effect":"When you make an\nArea Attack\nwith a weapon set on\nAutofire\n, and you are proficient with that weapon, all targets in the area lose all dodge or deflection bonuses to\nReflex Defense\nagainst the\nAutofire\nattack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.flood_of_fire","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flood_of_Fire","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6342effd242f0b61","name":"Turn and Burn","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Withdraw Action, you can move up to 2 squares to escape Threatened squares without provoking an Attack of Opportunity, and you can move your Speed. You can spend a Force Point as a Reaction to an enemy ending its movement adjacent to you to Withdraw.","prerequisite":"Droid; Hovering, Flying, Wheeled, or Tracked Locomotion; Dexterity 13","special":"You must be equipped with Hovering, Flying, Wheeled, or Tracked Locomotion to use this Feat.","normalText":"When using the Withdraw Action, you can normally move only 1 square to escape a Threatened square without provoking an Attack of Opportunity and can move only up to half your Speed.","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":26,"tags":["feat","force_point_spend","general","mobility","reaction","resource_spend","skill_pilot","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>;<br>Hovering<br>,<br>Flying<br>,<br>Wheeled<br>, or<br>Tracked<br>Locomotion;<br>Dexterity<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using the<br>Withdraw<br>Action, you can move up to 2 squares to escape<br>Threatened<br>squares without provoking an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>, and you can move your Speed. You can spend a<br>Force Point<br>as a<br>Reaction<br>to an enemy ending its movement adjacent to you to<br>Withdraw<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> When using the<br>Withdraw<br>Action, you can normally move only 1 square to escape a<br>Threatened<br>square without provoking an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>and can move only up to half your Speed.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You must be equipped with<br>Hovering<br>,<br>Flying<br>,<br>Wheeled<br>, or<br>Tracked<br>Locomotion to use this Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Turn_and_Burn</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"withdraw_movement_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Turn and Burn: improves Withdraw movement through threatened squares.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase16","description":"Turn and Burn: improves Withdraw movement through threatened squares.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Turn and Burn: improves Withdraw movement through threatened squares.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"withdraw_movement_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"WITHDRAW_THREATENED_SQUARES_EXTENSION","clearThreatenedSquares":2,"movement":"speed","description":"When withdrawing, clear threatened squares within the first 2 squares of movement, then move your speed as described."}]},"shortSummary":"Withdraw by clearing threatened squares in up to 2 squares of movement, move your Speed when using the Withdraw Action. Withdraw as a Reaction by spending a Force Point.","prerequisitesText":"Droid; Hovering, Flying, Wheeled, or Tracked Locomotion; Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Turn_and_Burn","effect":"When using the\nWithdraw\nAction, you can move up to 2 squares to escape\nThreatened\nsquares without provoking an\nAttack of Opportunity\n, and you can move your Speed. You can spend a\nForce Point\nas a\nReaction\nto an enemy ending its movement adjacent to you to\nWithdraw\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.turn_and_burn","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Turn_and_Burn","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6356fd5ea46b9c6c","name":"Impulsive Flight","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can Withdraw one extra square using the Withdraw Action.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":25,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can<br>Withdraw<br>one extra square using the<br>Withdraw<br>Action.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impulsive_Flight</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"withdraw_movement_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Impulsive Flight: withdraw faster; movement validation remains action metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase16","description":"Impulsive Flight: withdraw faster; movement validation remains action metadata.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Impulsive Flight: withdraw faster; movement validation remains action metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"withdraw_movement_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"WITHDRAW_MOVEMENT_BONUS","description":"Withdraw faster as described by the feat; exact movement/path remains table positioning context."}]},"shortSummary":"Withdraw faster.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impulsive_Flight","effect":"You can\nWithdraw\none extra square using the\nWithdraw\nAction."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.impulsive_flight","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impulsive_Flight","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"63dbb0e9623f7fce","name":"Resolute Stance","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you Fight Defensively, you gain a +2 morale bonus to your Will Defense. If you make no attacks until your next turn, you gain a +5 morale bonus to your Will Defense until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"When you Fight Defensively you only get a dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense.","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":23,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you<br>Fight Defensively<br>, you gain a +2 morale bonus to your<br>Will Defense<br>. If you make no attacks until your next turn, you gain a +5 morale bonus to your<br>Will Defense<br>until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> When you<br>Fight Defensively<br>you only get a dodge bonus to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resolute_Stance</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Resolute Stance: Implemented as conditional defense metadata; not a global attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.will"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as conditional defense metadata; not a global attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"defense_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Resolute Stance now exposes conditional defense metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","conditionalDefenseBonuses":[{"type":"CONDITIONAL_DEFENSE_BONUS","targets":["defense.will"],"value":2,"bonusType":"morale","requiresContextFlags":["fightingDefensively"],"description":"When fighting defensively, gain +2 morale Will Defense."},{"type":"CONDITIONAL_DEFENSE_BONUS","targets":["defense.will"],"value":5,"bonusType":"morale","requiresContextFlags":["fightingDefensivelyNoAttacks"],"duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn","description":"If you make no attacks until your next turn, gain +5 morale Will Defense."}],"status":"conditional_defense_phase10","description":"Resolute Stance now exposes conditional defense metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"Gain +2 or +5 to Will Defense when you Fight Defensively.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resolute_Stance","effect":"When you\nFight Defensively\n, you gain a +2 morale bonus to your\nWill Defense\n. If you make no attacks until your next turn, you gain a +5 morale bonus to your\nWill Defense\nuntil the start of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.resolute_stance","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resolute_Stance","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"643c54c206ed5f64","name":"Swarm","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +1 circumstance bonus on melee attack rolls for each allied character adjacent to your target.","prerequisite":"Coordinated Attack","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":37,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Coordinated Attack</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +1 circumstance bonus on melee attack rolls for each allied character adjacent to your target.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Swarm</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Swarm: Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Swarm now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"swarm","label":"Swarm","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"melee","attackModifierFormula":"context.adjacentAlliesToTarget","maxContextValue":8,"summary":"Gain +1 melee attack per allied character adjacent to your target when adjacentAlliesToTarget is supplied."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Swarm now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description."},"shortSummary":"Gain +1 bonus on melee attack rolls when allies are adjacent.","prerequisitesText":"Coordinated Attack","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Swarm","effect":"You gain a +1 circumstance bonus on melee attack rolls for each allied character adjacent to your target."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.swarm","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Swarm","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"647d77a8f5ab9af3","name":"Keen Force Mind","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate mind-affecting Force powers.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use the Force","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Jedi Academy Training Manual","page":31,"tags":["feat","force"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"+2 Use the Force only for mind-affecting Force powers.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"+2 Use the Force only for mind-affecting Force powers.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"force_power_skill_bonus_phase14","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"keenForceMind.mindAffecting","skillKey":"useTheForce","value":2,"type":"feat","applicationIncludes":["mind-affecting","mind affecting"],"description":"+2 Use the Force checks to activate mind-affecting Force powers."}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate mind-affecting Force powers."},"effects":[{"_id":"53d22820-a807-4a74-bcc8-77674689b0fb","name":"Keen Force Mind","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Keen Force Mind","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Keen Force Mind"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"648a4f16669056f0","name":"Triple Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group. When you use the Full Attack Action, you may make one additional attack when wielding such a Weapon. However, you take a -5 penalty on all attack rolls until your next turn because you're trading precision for speed. The extra attack and penalty stack with those of Double Attack.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +11, Double Attack (Chosen Weapon)","special":"You may select this Feat multiple times. Each time you select this Feat, it applies to a different Exotic Weapon or weapon group.","normalText":"Making a single attack is a Standard Action.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+11,<br>Double Attack<br>(Chosen Weapon)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Choose a single<br>Exotic Weapon<br>or weapon group. When you use the<br>Full Attack<br>Action, you may make one additional attack when wielding such a Weapon. However, you take a -5 penalty on all attack rolls until your next turn because you&#x27;re trading precision for speed. The extra attack and penalty stack with those of<br>Double Attack<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> Making a single attack is a<br>Standard Action<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You may select this Feat multiple times. Each time you select this Feat, it applies to a different<br>Exotic Weapon<br>or weapon group.</p>\n<h3>Additional Triple Attack Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy<br><br>Special:<br>If you take this feat with<br>Heavy Weapons<br>, it works normally with<br>Vehicle Weapons<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Attack</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":9}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Triple Attack","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Choose one Double Attack weapon choice for the second extra Full Attack option.","metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","disabledReason":"Phase 6: choice captured now; execution waits for roll/action context wiring."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose one Double Attack weapon choice for the second extra Full Attack option.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","combatActions":[{"id":"triple-attack-full-attack","name":"Triple Attack","actionType":"full-round","cost":1,"manualResolution":true,"resolutionMode":"manual","useLabel":"Use / Note","requiresSelectedChoice":true,"relatedSkills":[{"skill":"Attack Roll","when":"Resolve each attack in the Full Attack sequence"}],"resources":["Full Attack","Selected Double Attack weapon choice"],"notes":"When using Full Attack with the selected weapon group or exotic weapon, make one additional attack. This stacks with Double Attack; all attack rolls take the combined penalties until your next turn.","description":"During Full Attack with the selected weapon, make a second additional attack. This stacks with Double Attack and applies the normal stacked penalties."}],"combatActionCardSource":"phase-t13-ability-combat-action-cards","combatActionCardNotes":"Action card only; execution remains manual until multi-attack sequencing is automated."},"shortSummary":"Make second extra attack with chosen weapon during Full Attack, additional -5 penalty to all attacks.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +11, Double Attack (Chosen Weapon)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Attack","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"triple_attack_weapon","repeatable":true,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.triple_attack_weapon","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.triple_attack_weapon","derivesFrom":["double_attack_weapon"],"consumes":"double_attack_weapon","provides":"triple_attack_weapon"},"effect":"Choose a single\nExotic Weapon\nor weapon group. When you use the\nFull Attack\nAction, you may make one additional attack when wielding such a Weapon. However, you take a -5 penalty on all attack rolls until your next turn because you're trading precision for speed. The extra attack and penalty stack with those of\nDouble Attack\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.triple_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Triple_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6557f371e55b900a","name":"Distracting Droid","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Standard Action, make a Persuasion check against the Will Defense of all enemies that are within 6 squares of you and that can see or hear you, as determined by the Gamemaster. If the check equals or exceeds an enemy's Will Defense, the enemy loses one Move Action on its next turn. If the attack exceeds an enemy's Will Defense by 10 or more, the enemy is also Flat-Footed until the start of your next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.","prerequisite":"Droid","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":19,"tags":["action_economy","feat","general","move_action","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Standard Action<br>, make a<br>Persuasion<br>check against the<br>Will Defense<br>of all enemies that are within 6 squares of you and that can see or hear you, as determined by the Gamemaster. If the check equals or exceeds an enemy&#x27;s<br>Will Defense<br>, the enemy loses one<br>Move Action<br>on its next turn. If the attack exceeds an enemy&#x27;s<br>Will Defense<br>by 10 or more, the enemy is also<br>Flat-Footed<br>until the start of your next turn. This is a<br>Mind-Affecting<br>effect.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Distracting_Droid</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"persuasion_area_debuff_context","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Distracting Droid is a standard action Persuasion vs Will area effect against enemies within 6 squares that can see/hear you; success denies a move action, success by 10 also flat-foots.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_action_phase17","description":"Distracting Droid is a standard action Persuasion vs Will area effect against enemies within 6 squares that can see/hear you; success denies a move action, success by 10 also flat-foots.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Distracting Droid is a standard action Persuasion vs Will area effect against enemies within 6 squares that can see/hear you; success denies a move action, success by 10 also flat-foots.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"persuasion_area_debuff_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"PERSUASION_AREA_MOVE_DENIAL","skillKey":"persuasion","action":"standard","rangeSquares":6,"targetDefense":"will","requiresTargetCanSeeOrHear":true,"tags":["mind-affecting"],"effectsOnSuccess":["targetLosesOneMoveActionNextTurn"],"effectsOnSuccessBy10":["targetFlatFootedUntilStartOfYourNextTurn"],"description":"Persuasion vs Will against enemies within 6 squares; success removes one move action next turn; success by 10 also flat-foots."}]},"shortSummary":"Attempt to deny enemies within 6 squares their next Move Action, with a chance to make enemies Flat-Footed.","prerequisitesText":"Droid","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Distracting_Droid","effect":"As a\nStandard Action\n, make a\nPersuasion\ncheck against the\nWill Defense\nof all enemies that are within 6 squares of you and that can see or hear you, as determined by the Gamemaster. If the check equals or exceeds an enemy's\nWill Defense\n, the enemy loses one\nMove Action\non its next turn. If the attack exceeds an enemy's\nWill Defense\nby 10 or more, the enemy is also\nFlat-Footed\nuntil the start of your next turn. This is a\nMind-Affecting\neffect."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.distracting_droid","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Distracting_Droid","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6673cd53493a9d6c","name":"Forceful Slam","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate Force Slam.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use the Force, Force Slam","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["feat","force","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"+2 Use the Force only when activating Force Slam.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"+2 Use the Force only when activating Force Slam.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"force_power_skill_bonus_phase14","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"forcefulSlam.forceSlam","skillKey":"useTheForce","value":2,"type":"feat","applications":["Force Slam"],"description":"+2 Use the Force checks to activate Force Slam."}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on Use the Force checks made to activate Force Slam."},"effects":[{"_id":"dd3bb5b5-ed2f-4950-9cb1-faca1dce72c0","name":"Forceful Slam","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Forceful Slam","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Forceful Slam"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"6723270208549f73","name":"Mandalorian Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Charging Fire Feat, you gain a +2 bonus to a ranged attack made at the end of a Charge. As with a normal Charge, you still take a -2 penalty to your Reflex Defense, but you also gain a +2 morale bonus to your Will Defense until the beginning of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Charging Fire","special":"","normalText":"You gain no bonus to a ranged attack make at the end of a Charge with the Charging Fire Feat.","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":28,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Charging Fire</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using the<br>Charging Fire<br>Feat, you gain a +2 bonus to a ranged attack made at the end of a<br>Charge<br>. As with a normal<br>Charge<br>, you still take a -2 penalty to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>, but you also gain a +2 morale bonus to your<br>Will Defense<br>until the beginning of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You gain no bonus to a ranged attack make at the end of a<br>Charge<br>with the<br>Charging Fire<br>Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mandalorian_Training</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"+2 attack only when using Charging Fire.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"+2 attack only when using Charging Fire.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"attack_option_phase14","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"mandalorianTrainingChargingFire","label":"Mandalorian Training","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresCharge":true,"requiresOption":"chargingFire","attackModifier":2,"summary":"+2 attack when using Charging Fire."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain a +2 bonus on attack rolls when using the Charging Fire feat.","prerequisitesText":"Charging Fire","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mandalorian_Training","effect":"When using the\nCharging Fire\nFeat, you gain a +2 bonus to a ranged attack made at the end of a\nCharge\n. As with a normal\nCharge\n, you still take a -2 penalty to your\nReflex Defense\n, but you also gain a +2 morale bonus to your\nWill Defense\nuntil the beginning of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.mandalorian_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mandalorian_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"691b3a9309b28e60","name":"Demoralizing Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you successfully deal damage to an opponent with an Attack of Opportunity, you can immediately make a Persuasion check to Intimidate the opponent as a Free Action.","prerequisite":"Charisma 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":17,"tags":["control","feat","general","offense","offense_melee","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Charisma<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you successfully deal damage to an opponent with an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>, you can immediately make a<br>Persuasion<br>check to<br>Intimidate<br>the opponent as a<br>Free Action<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Demoralizing_Strike</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"aoo_damage_intimidate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"reaction_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Demoralizing Strike: after damaging with an attack of opportunity, make a free Persuasion check to Intimidate.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"aoo_skill_rider_phase16","description":"Demoralizing Strike: after damaging with an attack of opportunity, make a free Persuasion check to Intimidate.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Demoralizing Strike: after damaging with an attack of opportunity, make a free Persuasion check to Intimidate.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"aoo_damage_intimidate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"reactionRules":[{"type":"FREE_SKILL_CHECK_AFTER_AOO_DAMAGE","skillKey":"persuasion","application":"intimidate","action":"free","description":"After damaging with an Attack of Opportunity, make a free Persuasion check to Intimidate the opponent."}]},"shortSummary":"Make an Intimidation check when you deal damage with an Attack of Opportunity.","prerequisitesText":"Charisma 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Demoralizing_Strike","effect":"When you successfully deal damage to an opponent with an\nAttack of Opportunity\n, you can immediately make a\nPersuasion\ncheck to\nIntimidate\nthe opponent as a\nFree Action\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.demoralizing_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Demoralizing_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6b6a0dc594ad4e3c","name":"Tae-Jitsu Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"martial_arts","benefit":"Deal more damage on critical hits. Use Dodge against enemies.","prerequisite":"Dodge, Martial Arts I, Trained in Initiative","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","feat_chain","martial_arts","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dodge<br>,<br>Martial Arts I<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Initiative</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you score a Critical Hit with an<br>Unarmed Attack<br>, the damage dealt by your attack increases by one die step, to a maximum of d12.<br><br>Once per encounter, when you make a successful<br>Unarmed Attack<br>against an enemy, you can spend a<br>Swift Action<br>to designate that enemy as your primary adversary. Until the end of the encounter, you gain the benefit of the<br>Dodge<br>Feat against that enemy and against one other enemy of your choice.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you have the<br>Tae-Jitsu Expertise<br>Talent, when you score a Critical Hit against an enemy who has been designated as your primary adversary, that enemy takes a -2 penalty to attack rolls until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tae-Jitsu_Training</em></p>","martialArtsFeat":true,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Tae-Jitsu Training: Converted false attack metadata into passive unarmed critical/rider metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Converted false attack metadata into passive unarmed critical/rider metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"taeJitsuCritical","label":"Tae-Jitsu Critical","control":"passive","requiresUnarmed":true,"criticalDamageDieStepBonus":1,"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"DESIGNATE_DODGE_ADVERSARY","actionCost":"swift","duration":"encounter","oncePer":"encounter","description":"Once per encounter after a successful unarmed attack, spend a swift action to designate the target as your primary adversary for Dodge."}],"summary":"On unarmed critical hits, increase damage die one step; preserves primary-adversary rider metadata."}],"status":"taeJitsuCritical_attack_option_phase12","description":"Converted false attack metadata into passive unarmed critical/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Deal more damage on critical hits.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tae-Jitsu_Training","rawImport":{"name":"Tae-Jitsu Training","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tae-Jitsu_Training","pageTitle":"Tae-Jitsu_Training","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\tae-jitsu_training.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Dodge\n,\nMartial Arts I\n,\nTrained\nin\nInitiative","prerequisites":["Dodge","Martial Arts I","Trained\nin\nInitiative"],"effect":"When you score a Critical Hit with an\nUnarmed Attack\n, the damage dealt by your attack increases by one die step, to a maximum of d12.\n\nOnce per encounter, when you make a successful\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst an enemy, you can spend a\nSwift Action\nto designate that enemy as your primary adversary. Until the end of the encounter, you gain the benefit of the\nDodge\nFeat against that enemy and against one other enemy of your choice.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"If you have the\nTae-Jitsu Expertise\nTalent, when you score a Critical Hit against an enemy who has been designated as your primary adversary, that enemy takes a -2 penalty to attack rolls until the end of your next turn.","indexPrerequisites":"Dodge , Martial Arts I , Trained in Initiative","indexBenefit":"Deal more damage on critical hits. Use Dodge against enemies.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Martial Arts Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nMartial Arts Feats\n\nYou are trained in the Tae-Jitsu style of\nUnarmed\nfighting and can use a variety of techniques to defeat your enemy.\n\nPrerequisites:\nDodge\n,\nMartial Arts I\n,\nTrained\nin\nInitiative\n\nEffect:\nWhen you score a Critical Hit with an\nUnarmed Attack\n, the damage dealt by your attack increases by one die step, to a maximum of d12.\n\nOnce per encounter, when you make a successful\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst an enemy, you can spend a\nSwift Action\nto designate that enemy as your primary adversary. Until the end of the encounter, you gain the benefit of the\nDodge\nFeat against that enemy and against one other enemy of your choice.\n\nSpecial:\nIf you have the\nTae-Jitsu Expertise\nTalent, when you score a Critical Hit against an enemy who has been designated as your primary adversary, that enemy takes a -2 penalty to attack rolls until the end of your next turn."},"prerequisitesText":"Dodge\n,\nMartial Arts I\n,\nTrained\nin\nInitiative","effect":"When you score a Critical Hit with an\nUnarmed Attack\n, the damage dealt by your attack increases by one die step, to a maximum of d12.\n\nOnce per encounter, when you make a successful\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst an enemy, you can spend a\nSwift Action\nto designate that enemy as your primary adversary. Until the end of the encounter, you gain the benefit of the\nDodge\nFeat against that enemy and against one other enemy of your choice."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.tae_jitsu_training"}}}
{"_id":"6ba02f4dd4c3bfe5","name":"Elder's Knowledge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you can substitute a Knowledge (Galactic Lore) or Knowledge (Social Sciences) check for a Wisdom or Wisdom -related check.","prerequisite":"Skill Focus (Knowledge (Galactic Lore)) or Skill Focus (Knowledge (Social Sciences))","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":20,"tags":["ability_wisdom","feat","general","knowledge","skill_knowledge","skill_synergy","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Skill Focus (Knowledge (Galactic Lore))<br>or<br>Skill Focus (Knowledge (Social Sciences))</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, you can substitute a<br>Knowledge (Galactic Lore)<br>or<br>Knowledge (Social Sciences)<br>check for a<br>Wisdom<br>or<br>Wisdom<br>-related check.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Elder&#x27;s_Knowledge</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Knowledge substitution for Wisdom-related skill checks.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Knowledge substitution for Wisdom-related skill checks.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"skill_substitution_metadata_phase14","skillUseSubstitutions":[{"fromAbility":"wisdom","toSkillOptions":["knowledgeSocialSciences","knowledgeGalacticLore"],"description":"May substitute Knowledge (Social Sciences) or Knowledge (Galactic Lore) for Wisdom-related skill checks."}]},"shortSummary":"Substitute a Knowledge (Social Sciences) or Knowledge (Galactic Lore) skill check for a Wisdom -related Skill Check.","prerequisitesText":"Skill Focus (Knowledge (Galactic Lore)) or Skill Focus (Knowledge (Social Sciences))","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Elder's_Knowledge","effect":"Once per encounter, you can substitute a\nKnowledge (Galactic Lore)\nor\nKnowledge (Social Sciences)\ncheck for a\nWisdom\nor\nWisdom\n-related check."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.elders_knowledge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Elder's_Knowledge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6cf1898b8c3c837c","name":"Scavenger","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can spend 1 hour scavenging materials from other Vehicles or objects. When you do so, you make a Perception check to determine the value of the parts scavenged. You produce raw materials equal in value to the result of your Perception check x 30 credits. You must apply these raw materials toward the cost of construction of a single object (see Build Object), and you can scavenge parts for only a single object at any given time. Additionally, you can scavenge raw materials only once for any given object you are attempting to build.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","knowledge","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":["21dfe84d159a1b7f","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can spend 1 hour scavenging materials from other<br>Vehicles<br>or objects. When you do so, you make a<br>Perception<br>check to determine the value of the parts scavenged. You produce raw materials equal in value to the result of your<br>Perception<br>check x 30 credits. You must apply these raw materials toward the cost of construction of a single object (see<br>Build Object<br>), and you can scavenge parts for only a single object at any given time. Additionally, you can scavenge raw materials only once for any given object you are attempting to build.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Scavenger</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"perception_scavenge_build_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Scavenger: one-hour Perception-based scavenging produces construction materials equal to check result x 30 credits.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_rule_phase16","description":"Scavenger: one-hour Perception-based scavenging produces construction materials equal to check result x 30 credits.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Scavenger: one-hour Perception-based scavenging produces construction materials equal to check result x 30 credits.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"perception_scavenge_build_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"SCAVENGE_MATERIALS","skillKey":"perception","duration":"1 hour","valueFormula":"checkTotal * 30 credits","applications":["build object","scavenge materials"],"description":"Spend 1 hour scavenging; Perception result x 30 credits in raw materials toward one object."}]},"shortSummary":"Gather materials for building objects","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Scavenger","effect":"You can spend 1 hour scavenging materials from other\nVehicles\nor objects. When you do so, you make a\nPerception\ncheck to determine the value of the parts scavenged. You produce raw materials equal in value to the result of your\nPerception\ncheck x 30 credits. You must apply these raw materials toward the cost of construction of a single object (see\nBuild Object\n), and you can scavenge parts for only a single object at any given time. Additionally, you can scavenge raw materials only once for any given object you are attempting to build."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.scavenger","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Scavenger","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6d8ce2807c579289","name":"Trustworthy","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Persuasion checks and may reroll a failed Persuasion check once per encounter.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"skill","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Trustworthy: Implemented by SkillFeatResolver as a skill bonus plus once-per-encounter failed-check reroll.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented by SkillFeatResolver as a skill bonus plus once-per-encounter failed-check reroll.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Trustworthy now uses skill roll metadata: +2 Persuasion and once-per-encounter failed-check reroll.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"trustworthy-persuasion-bonus","skillKey":"persuasion","value":2,"type":"untyped","description":"Trustworthy: +2 on Persuasion checks."}],"skillRerolls":[{"id":"trustworthy-persuasion-reroll","skillKey":"persuasion","outcome":"keepSecond","oncePer":"encounter","trigger":"failedSkillCheck","label":"Trustworthy","description":"Trustworthy: reroll one failed Persuasion check once per encounter; keep the reroll."}],"status":"skill_bonus_reroll_phase10","description":"Trustworthy now uses skill roll metadata: +2 Persuasion and once-per-encounter failed-check reroll."},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on Persuasion checks and may reroll a failed Persuasion check once per encounter."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.382Z","detectedPredicates":["turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id":"6dcb59b199dba6a1","name":"Hijkata Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"martial_arts","benefit":"Make counterattacks. Impose penalties to enemy attacks.","prerequisite":"Combat Reflexes, Martial Arts I","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","feat_chain","martial_arts","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Combat Reflexes<br>,<br>Martial Arts I</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per round, when an adjacent enemy successfully damages you with a melee attack, you can make an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>with an<br>Unarmed Attack<br>at a -5 penalty against that enemy, even if the enemy&#x27;s attack normally would not provoke an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>.<br><br>Once per encounter, when an enemy provokes an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>from you and you successfully damage that enemy with an<br>Unarmed<br>Attack of Opportunity, that enemy takes a penalty to attack rolls equal to your<br>Dexterity<br>modifier (Minimum +1, for a minimum penalty of -1) until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you have the<br>Hijkata Expertise<br>Talent, once per encounter, you can spend a<br>Full-Round Action<br>to designate a single adjacent ally. Until the start of your next turn, any enemy adjacent to you or the designated ally that makes an attack roll against that ally provokes an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>from you. If the ally moves during his or her turn, you can immediately move a number of squares up to your Speed as a<br>Reaction<br>; however, you must end your movement in a square that is adjacent to the designated ally.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hijkata_Training</em></p>","martialArtsFeat":true,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":1,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee","proximity.ally-nearby","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Hijkata Training: Converted from false +1/+2 attack metadata to the actual unarmed opportunity counterattack option.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee","proximity.ally-nearby","turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Converted from false +1/+2 attack metadata to the actual unarmed opportunity counterattack option."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee","proximity.ally-nearby","turn.once-per-round"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"hijkataCounterattack","label":"Hijkata Counterattack","control":"toggle","requiresUnarmed":true,"requiresOpportunityAttack":true,"attackModifier":-5,"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"ATTACK_PENALTY","valueFormula":"negativeDexModifierMinimumOne","duration":"untilEndOfNextTurn","oncePer":"encounter","description":"Once per encounter after damaging with an unarmed attack of opportunity, target takes an attack penalty equal to your Dexterity modifier (minimum -1)."}],"summary":"Once per round when damaged by adjacent melee enemy, make an unarmed AoO at -5; once/encounter rider can penalize attacks."}],"status":"hijkataCounterattack_attack_option_phase12","description":"Converted from false +1/+2 attack metadata to the actual unarmed opportunity counterattack option."},"shortSummary":"Make counterattacks.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hijkata_Training","rawImport":{"name":"Hijkata Training","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hijkata_Training","pageTitle":"Hijkata_Training","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\hijkata_training.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Combat Reflexes\n,\nMartial Arts I","prerequisites":["Combat Reflexes","Martial Arts I"],"effect":"Once per round, when an adjacent enemy successfully damages you with a melee attack, you can make an\nAttack of Opportunity\nwith an\nUnarmed Attack\nat a -5 penalty against that enemy, even if the enemy's attack normally would not provoke an\nAttack of Opportunity\n.\n\nOnce per encounter, when an enemy provokes an\nAttack of Opportunity\nfrom you and you successfully damage that enemy with an\nUnarmed\nAttack of Opportunity, that enemy takes a penalty to attack rolls equal to your\nDexterity\nmodifier (Minimum +1, for a minimum penalty of -1) until the end of your next turn.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"If you have the\nHijkata Expertise\nTalent, once per encounter, you can spend a\nFull-Round Action\nto designate a single adjacent ally. Until the start of your next turn, any enemy adjacent to you or the designated ally that makes an attack roll against that ally provokes an\nAttack of Opportunity\nfrom you. If the ally moves during his or her turn, you can immediately move a number of squares up to your Speed as a\nReaction\n; however, you must end your movement in a square that is adjacent to the designated ally.","indexPrerequisites":"Combat Reflexes , Martial Arts I","indexBenefit":"Make counterattacks. Impose penalties to enemy attacks.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Martial Arts Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nMartial Arts Feats\n\nYou are trained in the Hijkata style of Unarmed fighting and can quickly turn enemies' attacks against them.\n\nPrerequisites:\nCombat Reflexes\n,\nMartial Arts I\n\nEffect:\nOnce per round, when an adjacent enemy successfully damages you with a melee attack, you can make an\nAttack of Opportunity\nwith an\nUnarmed Attack\nat a -5 penalty against that enemy, even if the enemy's attack normally would not provoke an\nAttack of Opportunity\n.\n\nOnce per encounter, when an enemy provokes an\nAttack of Opportunity\nfrom you and you successfully damage that enemy with an\nUnarmed\nAttack of Opportunity, that enemy takes a penalty to attack rolls equal to your\nDexterity\nmodifier (Minimum +1, for a minimum penalty of -1) until the end of your next turn.\n\nSpecial:\nIf you have the\nHijkata Expertise\nTalent, once per encounter, you can spend a\nFull-Round Action\nto designate a single adjacent ally. Until the start of your next turn, any enemy adjacent to you or the designated ally that makes an attack roll against that ally provokes an\nAttack of Opportunity\nfrom you. If the ally moves during his or her turn, you can immediately move a number of squares up to your Speed as a\nReaction\n; however, you must end your movement in a square that is adjacent to the designated ally."},"prerequisitesText":"Combat Reflexes\n,\nMartial Arts I","effect":"Once per round, when an adjacent enemy successfully damages you with a melee attack, you can make an\nAttack of Opportunity\nwith an\nUnarmed Attack\nat a -5 penalty against that enemy, even if the enemy's attack normally would not provoke an\nAttack of Opportunity\n.\n\nOnce per encounter, when an enemy provokes an\nAttack of Opportunity\nfrom you and you successfully damage that enemy with an\nUnarmed\nAttack of Opportunity, that enemy takes a penalty to attack rolls equal to your\nDexterity\nmodifier (Minimum +1, for a minimum penalty of -1) until the end of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee","proximity.ally-nearby","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.hijkata_training"}}}
{"_id":"6e3b0ca6413e607c","name":"Crossfire","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you miss when making a ranged attack against a target that has Soft Cover (that is, Cover provided by another character, creature, or Droid), you can immediately make an attack roll (with the same weapon and at the same attack bonus) against the target that is providing the Soft Cover. You can only use this Feat once per round.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":33,"tags":["cover_play","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot<br>,<br>Precise Shot<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+6</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you miss when making a ranged attack against a target that has<br>Soft Cover<br>(that is,<br>Cover<br>provided by another character, creature, or Droid), you can immediately make an attack roll (with the same weapon and at the same attack bonus) against the target that is providing the<br>Soft Cover<br>. You can only use this Feat once per round.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crossfire</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":6}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"ranged_miss_soft_cover_followup","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Crossfire lets you attack the creature providing Soft Cover after missing the covered target with a ranged attack, once per round.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"attack_option_phase17","description":"Crossfire lets you attack the creature providing Soft Cover after missing the covered target with a ranged attack, once per round.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Crossfire lets you attack the creature providing Soft Cover after missing the covered target with a ranged attack, once per round.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"ranged_miss_soft_cover_followup","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"crossfire","label":"Crossfire","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresContextFlags":["targetHasSoftCover"],"followupAttack":{"trigger":"missedAttack","target":"softCoverProvider","sameWeapon":true,"sameAttackBonus":true,"oncePer":"round"},"summary":"On a missed ranged attack against a target with Soft Cover, attack the cover provider once per round."}]},"shortSummary":"Redirect missed attacks against Soft Cover.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crossfire","effect":"If you miss when making a ranged attack against a target that has\nSoft Cover\n(that is,\nCover\nprovided by another character, creature, or Droid), you can immediately make an attack roll (with the same weapon and at the same attack bonus) against the target that is providing the\nSoft Cover\n. You can only use this Feat once per round."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.crossfire","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crossfire","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6e47c132fbedde08","name":"Deadeye","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you Aim before making a ranged attack and the attack hits, increase the damage you deal by an additional weapon die (3d6 becomes 4d6).","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"The effects of this Feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the Burst Fire or Rapid Shot Feats.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot<br>,<br>Precise Shot<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+4</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you<br>Aim<br>before making a ranged attack and the attack hits, increase the damage you deal by an additional weapon die (3d6 becomes 4d6).</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> The effects of this Feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the<br>Burst Fire<br>or<br>Rapid Shot<br>Feats.</p>\n<h3>Additional Deadeye Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy<br><br>A<br>Pilot<br>can use this Feat, but since they must spend at least one<br>Move Action<br>operating their<br>Vehicles<br>, they must split their<br>Aim<br>(two<br>Swift Actions<br>) and attack (<br>Standard Action<br>) into two separate turns, making it more likely that the target will break line of sight or avoid you.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadeye</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Deadeye: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"deadeye","label":"Deadeye","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAim":true,"damageDiceStepBonus":1,"summary":"When aiming with a ranged weapon, deal +1 die of damage."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate attack/combat option, not a passive sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"If you Aim, deal extra damage.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Base Attack Bonus +4","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadeye","effect":"If you\nAim\nbefore making a ranged attack and the attack hits, increase the damage you deal by an additional weapon die (3d6 becomes 4d6)."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.deadeye","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadeye","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6ef0920984de0ed0","name":"Risk Taker","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You fall only if you fail a Climb check by 10 or more. Additionally, if you make a Jump check and fail to land on a safe or solid surface (such as if you fall into a pit or fail to clear a stream of lava), you can spend a Force Point as a Free Action and add the result of the Force Point roll to your distance jumped. However, you must land in the first available safe square.","prerequisite":"Trained in Climb or Jump","special":"","normalText":"You fall if you fail a Climb check by 5 or more.","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","skill_climb","skill_jump","skill_synergy"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Climb<br>or<br>Jump</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You fall only if you fail a<br>Climb<br>check by 10 or more. Additionally, if you make a<br>Jump<br>check and fail to land on a safe or solid surface (such as if you fall into a pit or fail to clear a stream of lava), you can spend a<br>Force Point<br>as a<br>Free Action<br>and add the result of the<br>Force Point<br>roll to your distance jumped. However, you must land in the first available safe square.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You fall if you fail a<br>Climb<br>check by 5 or more.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Risk_Taker</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Skill-use hook for Climb/Jump risk-taking.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Skill-use hook for Climb/Jump risk-taking.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"skill_use_metadata_phase14","skillUseRules":[{"type":"RISK_TAKER_CLIMB_JUMP","skills":["climb","jump"],"description":"Improve chances with Climb or Jump checks; expose to skill-use UI."}]},"shortSummary":"Improve your chances of success with Climb or Jump checks.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Climb or Jump","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Risk_Taker","effect":"You fall only if you fail a\nClimb\ncheck by 10 or more. Additionally, if you make a\nJump\ncheck and fail to land on a safe or solid surface (such as if you fall into a pit or fail to clear a stream of lava), you can spend a\nForce Point\nas a\nFree Action\nand add the result of the\nForce Point\nroll to your distance jumped. However, you must land in the first available safe square."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.risk_taker","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Risk_Taker","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"6f98dd888bef8d7b","name":"Redirect Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"When you successfully negate a ranged attack with Deflect, you may redirect the shot to another target within line of sight.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use the Force, Deflect","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":94,"tags":["feat","force","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Redirect Shot: Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-ranged"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as non-numeric reaction/resource metadata; not an attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"non_numeric_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Redirect Shot now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","reactionRules":[{"type":"REDIRECT_DEFLECTED_RANGED_ATTACK","trigger":"afterSuccessfulDeflect","target":"anotherTargetInLineOfSight","description":"After successfully negating a ranged attack with Deflect, redirect the shot to another target in line of sight."}],"resourceRules":{"phase10Special":[]},"status":"non_numeric_rule_phase10","description":"Redirect Shot now exposes description-driven non-numeric metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"When you successfully negate a ranged attack with Deflect, you may redirect the shot to another target within line of sight."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"]}}}
{"_id":"6fb0f56dd9b9b75c","name":"Deadly Sniper","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make a ranged attack against a target that is unaware of you, you gain a +2 bonus on your attack roll and deal +1 die of damage on the first attack each turn.","prerequisite":"Sniper, Trained in Stealth, Base Attack Bonus +9","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":21,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged","sniping"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Sniper<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Stealth<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+9</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make a ranged attack against a target that is unaware of you, you gain a +2 bonus on your attack roll and deal +1 die of damage on the first attack each turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadly_Sniper</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":9},{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"6d2ac22d9fcf402f"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Deadly Sniper: Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-ranged"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Deadly Sniper now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"deadlySniper","label":"Deadly Sniper","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresContextFlags":["targetUnaware"],"attackModifier":2,"damageExtraWeaponDice":1,"limit":"firstAttackEachTurn","summary":"Against an unaware target, first ranged attack each turn gains +2 attack and +1 weapon die damage."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Deadly Sniper now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description."},"shortSummary":"Gain +2 bonus on your ranged attack roll and deal +1 die of damage.","prerequisitesText":"Sniper, Trained in Stealth, Base Attack Bonus +9","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadly_Sniper","effect":"When you make a ranged attack against a target that is unaware of you, you gain a +2 bonus on your attack roll and deal +1 die of damage on the first attack each turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.deadly_sniper","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deadly_Sniper","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"70962165bed8e5ed","name":"Gunnery Specialist","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While you are the Gunner of a Vehicle, you are considered proficient with Vehicle Weapons. Additionally, once per encounter, you can reroll an attack roll made with a Vehicle Weapon, though you must keep the second result, even if it is worse. You can declare this reroll after you learn the result of the attack roll, but before damage is resolved.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"Taking this Feat satisfies the prerequisites for the Starship Tactics Feat; however, unless you are Trained in Pilot and have the Vehicular Combat Feat, you may only take [Gunner ] Maneuvers when you select Starship Maneuvers for Starship Tactics.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":24,"tags":["feat","general","offense_ranged","reroll","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> While you are the<br>Gunner<br>of a<br>Vehicle<br>, you are considered proficient with<br>Vehicle Weapons<br>. Additionally, once per encounter, you can reroll an attack roll made with a<br>Vehicle Weapon<br>, though you must keep the second result, even if it is worse. You can declare this reroll after you learn the result of the attack roll, but before damage is resolved.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> Taking this Feat satisfies the prerequisites for the<br>Starship Tactics<br>Feat; however, unless you are<br>Trained<br>in<br>Pilot<br>and have the<br>Vehicular Combat<br>Feat, you may only take [<br>Gunner<br>] Maneuvers when you select<br>Starship Maneuvers<br>for<br>Starship Tactics<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gunnery_Specialist</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Vehicle weapon proficiency while gunning and once/encounter vehicle weapon attack reroll.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_reroll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Vehicle weapon proficiency while gunning and once/encounter vehicle weapon attack reroll.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"attack_reroll_vehicle_weapon_phase14","attackRerolls":[{"id":"gunnerySpecialist.vehicleWeapon","type":"ATTACK_REROLL","oncePer":"encounter","outcome":"keepSecond","requiresVehicleWeapon":true,"description":"Once per encounter, reroll an attack made with a Vehicle Weapon; keep the second result."}],"proficiencyRules":[{"type":"VEHICLE_WEAPON_PROFICIENCY_WHILE_GUNNER","description":"While serving as a vehicle gunner, treat yourself as proficient with Vehicle Weapons."}]},"shortSummary":"Reroll an attack made with a Vehicle Weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gunnery_Specialist","effect":"While you are the\nGunner\nof a\nVehicle\n, you are considered proficient with\nVehicle Weapons\n. Additionally, once per encounter, you can reroll an attack roll made with a\nVehicle Weapon\n, though you must keep the second result, even if it is worse. You can declare this reroll after you learn the result of the attack roll, but before damage is resolved."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.gunnery_specialist","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Gunnery_Specialist","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"70c842436bbb6330","name":"Perfect Swimmer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Reroll Swim checks, always keeping the better result.","prerequisite":"Gungan","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["control","feat","grapple","racial","reroll","skill_swim","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity","skill_reroll","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-gungan"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Gungan</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you reroll a<br>Swim<br>check, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Perfect_Swimmer</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_reroll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Perfect Swimmer: whenever you reroll swim, keep the better result.","predicateRequirements":["skill.swim"],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 continues description-guided implementation by improving teamwork skill feats, skill substitutions, force/dark-side skill context, and several remaining action/resource rider feats.","implementationStatus":"reroll_outcome_upgrade_phase15","description":"Perfect Swimmer: improves swim rerolls to keep the better result.","skillRerollOutcomeUpgrades":[{"id":"perfect-swimmer","skillKey":"swim","outcome":"keepBetter","description":"Whenever you reroll swim, keep the better result."}],"skillRerolls":[{"id":"perfect-swimmer","skillKey":"swim","outcome":"keepBetter","label":"Perfect Swimmer","description":"Perfect Swimmer: reroll swim and keep the better result."}]},"shortSummary":"Reroll Swim checks, always keeping the better result.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Perfect_Swimmer","rawImport":{"name":"Perfect Swimmer","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Perfect_Swimmer","pageTitle":"Perfect_Swimmer","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\perfect_swimmer.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Gungan","prerequisites":["Gungan"],"effect":"Whenever you reroll a\nSwim\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Gungan","indexBenefit":"Reroll Swim checks, always keeping the better result.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou are among the best of your kind when swimming and can navigate even the most difficult waters.\n\nPrerequisite:\nGungan\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you reroll a\nSwim\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities."},"prerequisitesText":"Gungan","effect":"Whenever you reroll a\nSwim\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.perfect_swimmer"}}}
{"_id":"70f27646ad28816a","name":"Instinctive Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use a Force Point when making an attack with a weapon with which you are proficient, you can reroll the attack and take the better result. Apply the results of the die from the Force Point to the better result.","prerequisite":"Cannot be a Droid","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":24,"tags":["feat","force_point_spend","general","offense","reroll","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Cannot be a<br>Droid</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you use a<br>Force Point<br>when making an attack with a weapon with which you are proficient, you can reroll the attack and take the better result. Apply the results of the die from the<br>Force Point<br>to the better result.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Attack</em></p>","executionModel":"ACTIVE","subType":"REROLL","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Spend a Force Point to reroll a proficient weapon attack and keep the better result.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_reroll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Spend a Force Point to reroll a proficient weapon attack and keep the better result.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"attack_reroll_force_point_phase14","attackRerolls":[{"id":"instinctiveAttack.forcePointAttack","type":"ATTACK_REROLL","cost":"forcePoint","outcome":"keepBetter","description":"Spend a Force Point on a proficient weapon attack to reroll and keep the better result."}]},"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"resource":"forcePoint"},"shortSummary":"Spend a Force Point to reroll an attack and take the better result.","prerequisitesText":"Cannot be a Droid","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Attack","effect":"When you use a\nForce Point\nwhen making an attack with a weapon with which you are proficient, you can reroll the attack and take the better result. Apply the results of the die from the\nForce Point\nto the better result."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.instinctive_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Instinctive_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7146640744fdf052","name":"Combat Reflexes","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When opponents leave themselves open, you may make a number of additional Attacks of Opportunity equal to your Dexterity modifier.\n\nWith this Feat, you may also make Attacks of Opportunity while Flat-Footed. You can still only make one attack for each triggered Attack of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"A character without the Combat Reflexes Feat can make only one Attack of Opportunity per round, and can't make Attacks of Opportunity while Flat-Footed.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":85,"tags":["control","defense","feat","general","opportunity_attack","reaction","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When opponents leave themselves open, you may make a number of additional<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>equal to your<br>Dexterity<br>modifier.<br><br>With this Feat, you may also make<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>while<br>Flat-Footed<br>. You can still only make one attack for each triggered<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> A character without the Combat Reflexes Feat can make only one<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>per round, and can&#x27;t make<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>while<br>Flat-Footed<br>.</p>\n<h3>Additional Combat Reflexes Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat (<br>Return Fire<br>):<br>You may use the<br>Return Fire<br>Feat a number of times during an encounter equal to your<br>Dexterity<br>bonus, but no more than once during a given enemy&#x27;s turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Reflexes</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_capability","applicationScope":"reaction_attack_context","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Additional attacks of opportunity equal to Dexterity modifier and may take AoOs while flat-footed.","predicateRequirements":["reaction.attackOfOpportunity"],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 continues description-guided implementation by improving teamwork skill feats, skill substitutions, force/dark-side skill context, and several remaining action/resource rider feats.","implementationStatus":"combat_reflexes_reaction_metadata_phase15","description":"Combat Reflexes: additional attacks of opportunity equal to Dexterity modifier; can make attacks of opportunity while flat-footed.","reactionRules":[{"type":"ATTACKS_OF_OPPORTUNITY_PER_ROUND_BONUS","valueFormula":"abilityModifier","ability":"dex","minimum":0,"description":"Gain additional attacks of opportunity equal to Dexterity modifier."},{"type":"ALLOW_AOO_WHILE_FLAT_FOOTED","description":"May make attacks of opportunity while flat-footed."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain additional Attacks of Opportunity.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Reflexes","effect":"When opponents leave themselves open, you may make a number of additional\nAttacks of Opportunity\nequal to your\nDexterity\nmodifier.\n\nWith this Feat, you may also make\nAttacks of Opportunity\nwhile\nFlat-Footed\n. You can still only make one attack for each triggered\nAttack of Opportunity\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.combat_reflexes","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Reflexes","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"71892687abbed346","name":"Strong in the Force","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"When you spend a Force Point to adjust the result of an attack roll, Skill Check, or Ability Check, you roll d8s instead of d6s.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["feat","force","force_point_spend","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you spend a<br>Force Point<br>to adjust the result of an attack roll,<br>Skill Check<br>, or<br>Ability Check<br>, you roll d8s instead of d6s.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_in_the_Force</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"status":"resource_rule_phase7","description":"Strong in the Force: metadata is consumed by MetaResourceFeatResolver/resource note adapters.","resourceRules":{"forcePoints":[{"type":"DIE_SIZE","value":8,"description":"Roll d8s instead of d6s when spending a Force Point."}]},"mechanicsMode":"passive_resource","applicationScope":"forcePoints_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Changes Force Point dice to d8 when Force Points are spent.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Roll d8s instead of d6s when you spend a Force Point.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_in_the_Force","effect":"When you spend a\nForce Point\nto adjust the result of an attack roll,\nSkill Check\n, or\nAbility Check\n, you roll d8s instead of d6s."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.strong_in_the_force","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strong_in_the_Force","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"72146d8a36d77736","name":"Grand Army of the Republic Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you wear Armor that provides an Equipment bonus to your Fortitude Defense, and you are proficient with that Armor, you also apply the Armor's Equipment bonus to your Will Defense.","prerequisite":"Armor Proficiency (Light)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":24,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Armor Proficiency (Light)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you wear Armor that provides an<br>Equipment<br>bonus to your<br>Fortitude Defense<br>, and you are proficient with that Armor, you also apply the Armor&#x27;s<br>Equipment<br>bonus to your<br>Will Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grand_Army_of_the_Republic_Training</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Grand Army of the Republic Training is armor-contextual; handled by armor/equipped context, not a static modifier.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"equipped_armor_contextual_defense","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.will"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented by DefenseCalculator as armor Fortitude equipment bonus to Will while proficient.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"equipped_armor_contextual_defense","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_derived_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Metadata/contextual only: while wearing armor you are proficient with, apply the armor equipment bonus to Will Defense. Do not treat as an unconditional static feat bonus.","predicateRequirements":["armor.equipped","armor.proficient","defense.will"],"metadataPhase":"phase25-suspect-feat-cleanup","metadataNotes":"Reclassified from static/include to equipped-armor contextual metadata.","defenseArmorRules":[{"type":"APPLY_ARMOR_FORT_EQUIPMENT_TO_WILL","requiresArmorProficiency":true,"description":"Apply the armor's Fortitude equipment bonus to Will Defense while proficient with that armor."}],"status":"equipped_armor_will_metadata_phase25","description":"Grand Army training now applies equipped armor Fortitude equipment bonus to Will Defense when proficient."},"shortSummary":"Apply your armor's Equipment bonus to your Will Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Armor Proficiency (Light)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grand_Army_of_the_Republic_Training","effect":"If you wear Armor that provides an\nEquipment\nbonus to your\nFortitude Defense\n, and you are proficient with that Armor, you also apply the Armor's\nEquipment\nbonus to your\nWill Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.grand_army_of_the_republic_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grand_Army_of_the_Republic_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"72183c573d1cc44e","name":"Unhindered Approach","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Jump checks checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Jump","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_jump","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8","manual_resolution","teamwork_base_skill_bonus_phase15"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Jump</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +3 competence bonus on<br>Jump<br>checks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).<br><br>Additionally, when you use the<br>Jump<br>skill, add 1 square to your total jump distance.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unhindered_Approach</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_with_manual_teamwork","applicationScope":"skill_roll_plus_manual_teamwork","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Unhindered Approach: +3 competence skill bonus applies normally; nearby-ally scaling and other battlefield/teamwork clauses are GM/player managed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 avoids automating nearby-ally/battlefield positioning clauses; base skill bonuses are implemented where unambiguous and teamwork clauses are preserved as manual metadata.","implementationStatus":"base_skill_bonus_manual_teamwork_phase15","description":"Unhindered Approach: base +3 competence skill bonus implemented; nearby-ally scaling and special teamwork clauses remain table-managed flavor/manual metadata.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"unhindered-approach","skillKey":"jump","type":"competence","featName":"Unhindered Approach","description":"Unhindered Approach: +3 competence bonus to jump checks. Nearby-ally scaling is manual/table-managed.","value":3}],"teamworkRules":[{"type":"SKILL_DISTANCE_BONUS","skillKey":"jump","extraSquares":1,"description":"Add 1 square to total jump distance.","automation":"manual","manualResolution":true}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Jump checks checks when near allies.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unhindered_Approach","rawImport":{"name":"Unhindered Approach","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unhindered_Approach","pageTitle":"Unhindered_Approach","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\unhindered_approach.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nJump","prerequisites":["Trained\nin\nJump"],"effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nJump\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nJump\nskill, add 1 square to your total jump distance.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Trained in Jump","indexBenefit":"Gain bonuses on Jump checks checks when near allies.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Team Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nTeam Feats\n\nYou and your allies have trained on worlds where the terrain is unstable, and your team also specializes in vertical insertion into combat zones.\n\nPrerequisite:\nTrained\nin\nJump\n\nEffect:\nYou gain a +3 competence bonus on\nJump\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nJump\nskill, add 1 square to your total jump distance."},"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nJump","effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nJump\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nJump\nskill, add 1 square to your total jump distance."},"effects":[{"_id":"e235e428-f19c-46cb-baa9-10c7a79edc84","name":"Unhindered Approach","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Unhindered Approach","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.unhindered_approach"}}}
{"_id":"723563f70bd7f28f","name":"Acrobatic Ally","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can hoist or toss an ally of your size or smaller up to 2 squares. You and your ally must act on the same Initiative Count and start in adjacent squares. If you succeed on a DC 20 Acrobatics check as a Standard Action, your ally ends up in a square of your choosing up to 2 squares above or away from you. This counts as a Free Action for your ally and ends your turn. Your ally can then continue his or her turn. If you fail your check, both you and your ally immediately become Prone in your square. Your turn is ended, but your ally can take his or her turn normally.","prerequisite":"Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Trained in Acrobatics","special":"This Feat can provoke Attacks of Opportunity against either character.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":18,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>13,<br>Dexterity<br>13,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Acrobatics</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can hoist or toss an ally of your size or smaller up to 2 squares. You and your ally must act on the same<br>Initiative Count<br>and start in adjacent squares. If you succeed on a DC 20<br>Acrobatics<br>check as a<br>Standard Action<br>, your ally ends up in a square of your choosing up to 2 squares above or away from you. This counts as a<br>Free Action<br>for your ally and ends your turn. Your ally can then continue his or her turn. If you fail your check, both you and your ally immediately become<br>Prone<br>in your square. Your turn is ended, but your ally can take his or her turn normally.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Feat can provoke<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>against either character.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Ally</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"nearby_ally_or_positioning_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_table_context","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Acrobatic Ally is a coordinated movement stunt requiring adjacent ally, shared initiative, DC 20 Acrobatics, and positioning adjudication; kept as explicit action metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"table_context_metadata_phase17","description":"Acrobatic Ally is a coordinated movement stunt requiring adjacent ally, shared initiative, DC 20 Acrobatics, and positioning adjudication; kept as explicit action metadata.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Acrobatic Ally is a coordinated movement stunt requiring adjacent ally, shared initiative, DC 20 Acrobatics, and positioning adjudication; kept as explicit action metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"nearby_ally_or_positioning_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"ACROBATICALLY_MOVE_ADJACENT_ALLY","skillKey":"acrobatics","dc":20,"action":"standard","allySize":"sameOrSmaller","maxSquares":2,"manualResolution":true,"description":"Acrobatic Ally is a coordinated movement stunt requiring adjacent ally, shared initiative, DC 20 Acrobatics, and positioning adjudication; kept as explicit action metadata."}]},"shortSummary":"Hoist or toss an ally of your size or smaller up to 2 squares.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Trained in Acrobatics","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Ally","effect":"You can hoist or toss an ally of your size or smaller up to 2 squares. You and your ally must act on the same\nInitiative Count\nand start in adjacent squares. If you succeed on a DC 20\nAcrobatics\ncheck as a\nStandard Action\n, your ally ends up in a square of your choosing up to 2 squares above or away from you. This counts as a\nFree Action\nfor your ally and ends your turn. Your ally can then continue his or her turn. If you fail your check, both you and your ally immediately become\nProne\nin your square. Your turn is ended, but your ally can take his or her turn normally."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.acrobatic_ally","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Ally","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"74dc095d9ab94915","name":"Returning Bug","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you miss with a Razor Bug or a Thud Bug, the weapon returns to your hand immediately.","prerequisite":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":22,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you miss with a<br>Razor Bug<br>or a<br>Thud Bug<br>, the weapon returns to your hand immediately.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Returning_Bug</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"missed_thrown_bug_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Returning Bug: missed Razor Bug or Thud Bug attacks return the weapon to hand.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"miss_rider_metadata_phase16","description":"Returning Bug: missed Razor Bug or Thud Bug attacks return the weapon to hand.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Returning Bug: missed Razor Bug or Thud Bug attacks return the weapon to hand.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"missed_thrown_bug_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OUTCOME_RIDER","trigger":"miss","requiresWeaponText":["razor bug","thud bug"],"effect":"returnThrownWeaponToHand","description":"When you miss with a Razor Bug or Thud Bug, it returns to your hand immediately."}]},"shortSummary":"Thrown Razor Bugs and Thud Bugs return to your hand immediately.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Returning_Bug","effect":"When you miss with a\nRazor Bug\nor a\nThud Bug\n, the weapon returns to your hand immediately."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.returning_bug","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Returning_Bug","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"752b00692fa5376b","name":"Nimble Team","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Acrobatics checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Acrobatics","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_acrobatics","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8","manual_resolution","teamwork_base_skill_bonus_phase15"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Acrobatics</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +3 competence bonus on<br>Acrobatics<br>checks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).<br><br>Additionally, when you use the<br>Acrobatics<br>skill to<br>Tumble<br>, you can<br>Tumble<br>1 extra square.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nimble_Team</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_with_manual_teamwork","applicationScope":"skill_roll_plus_manual_teamwork","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Nimble Team: +3 competence skill bonus applies normally; nearby-ally scaling and other battlefield/teamwork clauses are GM/player managed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 avoids automating nearby-ally/battlefield positioning clauses; base skill bonuses are implemented where unambiguous and teamwork clauses are preserved as manual metadata.","implementationStatus":"base_skill_bonus_manual_teamwork_phase15","description":"Nimble Team: base +3 competence skill bonus implemented; nearby-ally scaling and special teamwork clauses remain table-managed flavor/manual metadata.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"nimble-team","skillKey":"acrobatics","type":"competence","featName":"Nimble Team","description":"Nimble Team: +3 competence bonus to acrobatics checks. Nearby-ally scaling is manual/table-managed.","value":3}],"teamworkRules":[{"type":"TUMBLE_EXTRA_DISTANCE","skillKey":"acrobatics","extraSquares":1,"description":"When using Acrobatics to Tumble, Tumble 1 extra square.","automation":"manual","manualResolution":true}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Acrobatics checks when near allies.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nimble_Team","rawImport":{"name":"Nimble Team","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Nimble_Team","pageTitle":"Nimble_Team","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\nimble_team.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nAcrobatics","prerequisites":["Trained\nin\nAcrobatics"],"effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nAcrobatics\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAcrobatics\nskill to\nTumble\n, you can\nTumble\n1 extra square.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Trained in Acrobatics","indexBenefit":"Gain bonuses on Acrobatics checks when near allies.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Team Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nTeam Feats\n\nYou and your allies train extensively to avoid hazards and to slip through tight spaces, making it difficult to pin your team down.\n\nPrerequisite:\nTrained\nin\nAcrobatics\n\nEffect:\nYou gain a +3 competence bonus on\nAcrobatics\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus 