{"_id":"773ec00effc7e96f","name":"Armor Proficiency (light)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you wear Light Armor, you take no Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls or Skill Checks. Additionally, you benefit from all of the armor's special Equipment bonuses (if any).","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"A character who wears Light Armor with which they are not proficient takes a -2 Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls as well as Skill Checks made using the following Skills: Acrobatics, Climb, Endurance, Initiative, Jump, Stealth, and Swim. Additionally, the character gains none of the armor's special Equipment bonuses.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":85,"tags":["armor","build_enabler","defense","feat","general","mapped_phase_1","unlock_grant","choice_variant","armor_access"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Light)</p>\n<p>You are proficient with Light Armor, and can wear it without impediment.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you wear Light Armor, you take no Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls or Skill Checks. Additionally, you benefit from all of the armor&#x27;s special Equipment bonuses (if any).</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>A character who wears Light Armor with which they are not proficient takes a -2 Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls as well as Skill Checks made using the following Skills: Acrobatics, Climb, Endurance, Initiative, Jump, Stealth, and Swim. Additionally, the character gains none of the armor&#x27;s special Equipment bonuses.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"UNLOCK","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Grants light armor proficiency; armor penalty/equipment bonus handling consumes proficiency state.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"grant","applicationScope":"proficiency_grant","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Grants light armor proficiency; armor penalty/equipment bonus handling consumes proficiency state.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"proficiency_grant_metadata_phase14","proficiencyGrants":[{"type":"ARMOR_PROFICIENCY","armorCategory":"light","description":"Grants proficiency with light armor."}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"already_resolved_static_variant","required":false,"choiceKind":"armor_proficiency","value":"light","grants":["light"]},"shortSummary":"No penalty on attacks and no Armor Check Penalty while wearing Light Armor.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Light)"},"effects":[{"_id":"9781a3c7-4e7e-4af0-9dcc-cdea0524b414","name":"Armor Proficiency (Light)","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.armorProficiency.light","mode":5,"value":"true"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Armor Proficiency (Light)","effectType":"armor_proficiency"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"phase1Mapped":true,"manualMappingResolved":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Light)","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"77c897590b4000f6","name":"Slicer Team","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Use Computer checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use Computer","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_synergy","skill_use_computer","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8","manual_resolution","teamwork_base_skill_bonus_phase15"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Use Computer</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +3 competence bonus on<br>Use Computer<br>checks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).<br><br>Additionally, when you use the<br>Aid Another<br>Action to assist an ally who has this Feat with a<br>Use Computer<br>check, you provide a bonus of +4 instead of +2.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Slicer_Team</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_with_manual_teamwork","applicationScope":"skill_roll_plus_manual_teamwork","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Slicer Team: +3 competence skill bonus applies normally; nearby-ally scaling and other battlefield/teamwork clauses are GM/player managed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 avoids automating nearby-ally/battlefield positioning clauses; base skill bonuses are implemented where unambiguous and teamwork clauses are preserved as manual metadata.","implementationStatus":"base_skill_bonus_manual_teamwork_phase15","description":"Slicer Team: base +3 competence skill bonus implemented; nearby-ally scaling and special teamwork clauses remain table-managed flavor/manual metadata.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"slicer-team","skillKey":"useComputer","type":"competence","featName":"Slicer Team","description":"Slicer Team: +3 competence bonus to useComputer checks. Nearby-ally scaling is manual/table-managed.","value":3}],"teamworkRules":[{"type":"AID_ANOTHER_BONUS_OVERRIDE","skillKey":"useComputer","bonus":4,"requiresAllyHasFeat":true,"description":"Aid Another provides +4 instead of +2 when assisting an ally with this feat on Use Computer.","automation":"manual","manualResolution":true}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Use Computer checks when near allies.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Slicer_Team","rawImport":{"name":"Slicer Team","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Slicer_Team","pageTitle":"Slicer_Team","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\slicer_team.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nUse Computer","prerequisites":["Trained\nin\nUse Computer"],"effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nUse Computer\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nUse Computer\ncheck, you provide a bonus of +4 instead of +2.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Trained in Use Computer","indexBenefit":"Gain bonuses on Use Computer checks when near allies.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Team Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nTeam Feats\n\nYou and your allies are computer specialists, capable of penetrating even the strongest electronic defenses.\n\nPrerequisite:\nTrained\nin\nUse Computer\n\nEffect:\nYou gain a +3 competence bonus on\nUse Computer\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nUse Computer\ncheck, you provide a bonus of +4 instead of +2."},"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nUse Computer","effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nUse Computer\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nUse Computer\ncheck, you provide a bonus of +4 instead of +2."},"effects":[{"_id":"42e2b97a-7c7f-419c-ae1d-42e6080cb792","name":"Slicer Team","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Slicer Team","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.slicer_team"}}}
{"_id":"77dba0a49c63e42d","name":"Biotech Surgery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can install Bio-Implants onto a living being. The surgical procedure takes 1 hour of uninterrupted work, after which you must make a DC 20 Treat Injury check. If the check succeeds, the prosthesis is installed correctly. If the check fails, the prosthesis is not installed properly; however, you can try again after another uninterrupted hour of surgery.","prerequisite":"Trained in Treat Injury","special":"You can install Bio-Implants on yourself, but you take a -5 penalty on the Treat Injury check. If you have the Surgical Expertise Feat, you can install a Bio-Implant in 10 minutes instead of 1 hour.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":17,"tags":["defense","feat","general","healing","skill_treat_injury","support","survivability","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Treat Injury</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can install<br>Bio-Implants<br>onto a living being. The surgical procedure takes 1 hour of uninterrupted work, after which you must make a DC 20<br>Treat Injury<br>check. If the check succeeds, the prosthesis is installed correctly. If the check fails, the prosthesis is not installed properly; however, you can try again after another uninterrupted hour of surgery.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can install<br>Bio-Implants<br>on yourself, but you take a -5 penalty on the<br>Treat Injury<br>check. If you have the<br>Surgical Expertise<br>Feat, you can install a<br>Bio-Implant<br>in 10 minutes instead of 1 hour.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Surgery</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"treatinjury"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"treat_injury_bio_implant_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Biotech Surgery: enables Treat Injury installation of Bio-Implants; self-installation penalty and Surgical Expertise timing are metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_rule_phase16","description":"Biotech Surgery: enables Treat Injury installation of Bio-Implants; self-installation penalty and Surgical Expertise timing are metadata.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Biotech Surgery: enables Treat Injury installation of Bio-Implants; self-installation penalty and Surgical Expertise timing are metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"treat_injury_bio_implant_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"ENABLE_SKILL_APPLICATION","skillKey":"treatInjury","applications":["install bio-implant"],"dc":20,"duration":"1 hour","description":"Install a Bio-Implant on a living being with a DC 20 Treat Injury check."},{"type":"SELF_APPLICATION_PENALTY","skillKey":"treatInjury","applications":["install bio-implant"],"value":-5,"description":"Installing Bio-Implants on yourself takes a -5 Treat Injury penalty."}]},"shortSummary":"Install a Bio-Implant on a living being.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Treat Injury","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Surgery","effect":"You can install\nBio-Implants\nonto a living being. The surgical procedure takes 1 hour of uninterrupted work, after which you must make a DC 20\nTreat Injury\ncheck. If the check succeeds, the prosthesis is installed correctly. If the check fails, the prosthesis is not installed properly; however, you can try again after another uninterrupted hour of surgery."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.biotech_surgery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Biotech_Surgery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7bc21d4a74b95be5","name":"Crush","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"If you successfully Pin an opponent with a Grapple attack (see Pin Feat for more details), you can immediately deal bludgeoning damage to it equal to your Unarmed damage or claw damage, whichever is greater.","prerequisite":"Pin, Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["control","feat","force","grapple","offense","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Pin<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you successfully<br>Pin<br>an opponent with a<br>Grapple<br>attack (see<br>Pin<br>Feat for more details), you can immediately deal bludgeoning damage to it equal to your<br>Unarmed<br>damage or claw damage, whichever is greater.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crush</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rider_effect_phase7","description":"Crush: modeled as a rider/action rule, not a numeric modifier.","rules":[{"type":"GRAPPLE_RIDER","trigger":"onSuccessfulPin","effect":"dealDamage","damage":"max(unarmed,claw)"}],"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Crush: numeric scaffold disabled by Phase 7 (description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus)","mechanicsMode":"metadata_note","applicationScope":"not_a_numeric_modifier","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus","metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"grapple_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Successful Pin can immediately deal unarmed or claw damage; this is not an attack bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Deal Unarmed or Claw damage to a Pinned opponent.","prerequisitesText":"Pin, Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crush","effect":"If you successfully\nPin\nan opponent with a\nGrapple\nattack (see\nPin\nFeat for more details), you can immediately deal bludgeoning damage to it equal to your\nUnarmed\ndamage or claw damage, whichever is greater."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.crush","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Crush","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7cd5ebe725910cb2","name":"Weapon Specialization","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with the selected weapon group.","prerequisite":"Soldier level 4, Weapon Focus with selected weapon group","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","general","weapon_mastery","choice_required","immediate_choice","weapon_choice","choice_source_prerequisite"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"damage.weapon","value":2,"type":"untyped","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Weapon Specialization: +2 damage with selected Weapon Focus target","predicates":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"conditionSummary":"Always available after selection, but only for rolls using the selected weapon group or exotic weapon."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Always available after selection, but only for rolls using the selected weapon group or exotic weapon.","predicateRequirements":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"execution_mapped_phase6","choiceKind":"weapon_specialization","repeatable":true,"optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.weapon_specialization","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.weapon_specialization","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","derivesFrom":["weapon_focus"],"consumes":"weapon_focus","provides":"weapon_specialization","effectTarget":"damage.weapon","effectValue":2},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus on damage rolls with the selected weapon group."},"effects":[{"_id":"58919a68-86ab-4cc5-b2e8-4f7b712e1ff2","name":"Weapon Specialization","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.damageBonus.rifles","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Weapon Specialization","effectType":"combat_bonus","flagType":"Weapon Specialization"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"requiresImmediateChoice":true}}}
{"_id":"7d8366d0481d76e2","name":"Trench Warrior","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you are adjacent to a wall or object that provides you with Cover from your target's ranged attacks, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on your attack rolls against that target.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":28,"tags":["cover_play","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you are adjacent to a wall or object that provides you with<br>Cover<br>from your target&#x27;s ranged attacks, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on your attack rolls against that target.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trench_Warrior</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Trench Warrior: Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-ranged"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Trench Warrior now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"trenchWarrior","label":"Trench Warrior","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresContextFlags":["adjacentCoverFromTarget"],"attackModifier":1,"summary":"When adjacent to cover from the target ranged attacks, gain +1 attack against that target."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Trench Warrior now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description."},"shortSummary":"When you have Cover against an enemy's ranged attacks, gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls against that enemy.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trench_Warrior","effect":"When you are adjacent to a wall or object that provides you with\nCover\nfrom your target's ranged attacks, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on your attack rolls against that target."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.trench_warrior","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trench_Warrior","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7de37c473be72f87","name":"Imperial Military Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, as a Free Action on your turn, you can negate any one Mind-Affecting effect targeting or currently affecting you.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Rebellion Era Campaign Guide","page":19,"tags":["background_opportunity","faction_training","feat","general","military","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, as a<br>Free Action<br>on your turn, you can negate any one<br>Mind-Affecting<br>effect targeting or currently affecting you.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Imperial_Military_Training</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"mind_affecting_negation_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Imperial Military Training negates one Mind-Affecting effect affecting/targeting you once per encounter as a free action on your turn.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"resource_rule_phase17","description":"Imperial Military Training negates one Mind-Affecting effect affecting/targeting you once per encounter as a free action on your turn.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Imperial Military Training negates one Mind-Affecting effect affecting/targeting you once per encounter as a free action on your turn.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"mind_affecting_negation_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"resourceRules":{"mindAffecting":[{"type":"NEGATE_MIND_AFFECTING_EFFECT","oncePer":"encounter","action":"free","timing":"onYourTurn","description":"Negate one Mind-Affecting effect targeting or affecting you once per encounter."}]}},"shortSummary":"Negate one Mind-Affecting effect per encounter.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Imperial_Military_Training","effect":"Once per encounter, as a\nFree Action\non your turn, you can negate any one\nMind-Affecting\neffect targeting or currently affecting you."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.imperial_military_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Imperial_Military_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"7df64382f1a0a892","name":"Overwhelming Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You must spend two Swift Actions in the same round to activate this Feat. If your target attempts to use a Talent, Feat, or other ability to negate your attack (Such as Block, Deflect, or Vehicular Combat), the target takes a -5 penalty to any attack rolls or Skill Checks it makes to negate the attack. This effect applies to the next attack you make before the end of the same round.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":26,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You must spend two<br>Swift Actions<br>in the same round to activate this Feat. If your target attempts to use a<br>Talent<br>,<br>Feat<br>, or other ability to negate your attack (Such as<br>Block<br>,<br>Deflect<br>, or<br>Vehicular Combat<br>), the target takes a -5 penalty to any attack rolls or<br>Skill Checks<br>it makes to negate the attack. This effect applies to the next attack you make before the end of the same round.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Overwhelming_Attack</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_negation_penalty_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Overwhelming Attack: two swift actions; target takes -5 on rolls/checks to negate your next attack this round.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"attack_negation_metadata_phase16","description":"Overwhelming Attack: two swift actions; target takes -5 on rolls/checks to negate your next attack this round.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Overwhelming Attack: two swift actions; target takes -5 on rolls/checks to negate your next attack this round.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"attack_negation_penalty_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"overwhelmingAttack","label":"Overwhelming Attack","control":"toggle","requiresSwiftActions":2,"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"NEGATION_ATTEMPT_PENALTY","value":-5,"appliesTo":["block","deflect","vehicularCombat","negateAttack"],"duration":"currentAttack","description":"Target takes -5 to attack rolls or skill checks made to negate this attack."}],"summary":"Two swift actions: target takes -5 on attempts to negate your next attack before end of round."}]},"shortSummary":"Any attempt to negate your attack takes a -5 penalty on the attack roll or Skill Check.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Overwhelming_Attack","effect":"You must spend two\nSwift Actions\nin the same round to activate this Feat. If your target attempts to use a\nTalent\n,\nFeat\n, or other ability to negate your attack (Such as\nBlock\n,\nDeflect\n, or\nVehicular Combat\n), the target takes a -5 penalty to any attack rolls or\nSkill Checks\nit makes to negate the attack. This effect applies to the next attack you make before the end of the same round."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.overwhelming_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Overwhelming_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"80805c30ea6dd11e","name":"Aiming Accuracy","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you Aim at a target as a Full-Round Action (instead of two Swift Actions), you gain a +5 bonus to your next attack made with a weapon with which you are proficient in the following round against that target. The target must remain in your line of sight.","prerequisite":"Droid, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":18,"tags":["feat","full_round_action","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>,<br>Point-Blank Shot<br>,<br>Precise Shot</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you<br>Aim<br>at a target as a<br>Full-Round Action<br>(instead of two<br>Swift Actions<br>), you gain a +5 bonus to your next attack made with a weapon with which you are proficient in the following round against that target. The target must remain in your line of sight.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aiming_Accuracy</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Droid full-round aim attack option.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Droid full-round aim attack option.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"aimingAccuracy","label":"Aiming Accuracy","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAim":true,"requiresContextFlags":["fullRoundAim"],"attackModifier":5,"summary":"After aiming as a full-round action, gain +5 on the next ranged weapon attack."}],"implementationStatus":"aimingAccuracy_attack_option_phase13"},"shortSummary":"After aiming as a Full-Round Action, gain a +5 on next weapon attack.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aiming_Accuracy","effect":"If you\nAim\nat a target as a\nFull-Round Action\n(instead of two\nSwift Actions\n), you gain a +5 bonus to your next attack made with a weapon with which you are proficient in the following round against that target. The target must remain in your line of sight."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.aiming_accuracy","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Aiming_Accuracy","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"80c52cf7838095c1","name":"Return Fire","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Select one Exotic Weapon or Weapon Group for which you possess the Weapon Focus feat. Once per encounter as a Reaction, you can make a single ranged attack with the chosen weapon against an enemy that misses you with a ranged attack, provided you have line of sight to the enemy.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 15, Quick Draw, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","special":"This Feat does not apply to Vehicle Weapons or Heavy Weapons. You must have your weapon in hand to use this Feat. You can take this Feat multiple times. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Weapon Group or Exotic Weapon.\n\nCombined Feat (Combat Reflexes): You may use this Feat a number of times during an encounter equal to your Dexterity bonus, but no more than once during a given enemy's turn.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":21,"tags":["counterattack","feat","general","new_action","offense","offense_ranged","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>15,<br>Quick Draw<br>,<br>Weapon Focus<br>(Chosen Weapon)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Select one<br>Exotic Weapon<br>or Weapon Group for which you possess the<br>Weapon Focus<br>feat. Once per encounter as a<br>Reaction<br>, you can make a single ranged attack with the chosen weapon against an enemy that misses you with a ranged attack, provided you have line of sight to the enemy.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Feat does not apply to<br>Vehicle Weapons<br>or<br>Heavy Weapons<br>. You must have your weapon in hand to use this Feat. You can take this Feat multiple times. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Weapon Group or<br>Exotic Weapon<br>.<br><br>Combined Feat (<br>Combat Reflexes<br>):<br>You may use this Feat a number of times during an encounter equal to your<br>Dexterity<br>bonus, but no more than once during a given enemy&#x27;s turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Return_Fire</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":15}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Return Fire","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Choose the Weapon Focus choice that can be used with Return Fire.","metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","disabledReason":"Phase 6: choice captured now; execution waits for roll/action context wiring."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose the Weapon Focus choice that can be used with Return Fire.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated."},"shortSummary":"You may make a single ranged attack as a Reaction to a ranged attack against you that misses.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 15, Quick Draw, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Return_Fire","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"return_fire_weapon","repeatable":true,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.return_fire_weapon","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.return_fire_weapon","derivesFrom":["weapon_focus"],"consumes":"weapon_focus"},"effect":"Select one\nExotic Weapon\nor Weapon Group for which you possess the\nWeapon Focus\nfeat. Once per encounter as a\nReaction\n, you can make a single ranged attack with the chosen weapon against an enemy that misses you with a ranged attack, provided you have line of sight to the enemy."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.return_fire","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Return_Fire","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"821e127ba3b83c1a","name":"Multi-Grab","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Standard Action, you may make a Grab attack against two targets adjacent to you (roll a separate attack against each target). You must have two empty hands to use this Feat.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":20,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Standard Action<br>, you may make a<br>Grab<br>attack against two targets adjacent to you (roll a separate attack against each target). You must have two empty hands to use this Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Grab</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"grab_multi_target_action","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Multi-Grab: standard action to make separate Grab attacks against two adjacent targets while both hands are empty.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase16","description":"Multi-Grab: standard action to make separate Grab attacks against two adjacent targets while both hands are empty.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Multi-Grab: standard action to make separate Grab attacks against two adjacent targets while both hands are empty.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"grab_multi_target_action","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"MULTI_TARGET_GRAB","action":"standard","targetCount":2,"requiresEmptyHands":2,"description":"Make separate Grab attacks against two adjacent targets as a standard action."}]},"shortSummary":"You may Grab two opponents as a Standard Action.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Grab","effect":"As a\nStandard Action\n, you may make a\nGrab\nattack against two targets adjacent to you (roll a separate attack against each target). You must have two empty hands to use this Feat."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.multi_grab","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Grab","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8329a353aa3899be","name":"Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You are proficient with heavy weapons and do not take the -5 penalty when using them.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["build_enabler","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged","weapon_access","weapon_heavy","mapped_phase_1","unlock_grant","choice_variant"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"UNLOCK","abilityMeta":{"grants":[{"category":"PROFICIENCY","proficiencyType":"weapon","proficiencies":["heavy-weapons"],"description":"Weapon proficiency: heavy-weapons"}],"mechanicsMode":"grant_unlock","applicationScope":"progression_or_system_access","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Current metadata uses grants rather than numeric modifiers.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"already_resolved_static_variant","required":false,"choiceKind":"weapon_proficiency","value":"heavy-weapons","grants":["heavy-weapons"]},"shortSummary":"You are proficient with heavy weapons and do not take the -5 penalty when using them."},"effects":[{"_id":"5f95d267-fdb7-43aa-998c-918188f277fe","name":"Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"phase1Mapped":true,"manualMappingResolved":true}}}
{"_id":"836f80dd762cf155","name":"Stava Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"martial_arts","benefit":"Grab and Grapple as a larger creature. Grab after Charging.","prerequisite":"Martial Arts I, Running Attack","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["control","feat","feat_chain","grapple","martial_arts","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Martial Arts I<br>,<br>Running Attack</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When making a<br>Grab<br>attack, you are considered to be one size category larger for the purpose of determining the size of the opponent that you can<br>Grab<br>. If you are capable of making a<br>Grapple<br>attack, you are considered to be one size category larger for the purpose of determining your size modifier to<br>Grapple<br>checks.<br><br>When making an<br>Unarmed Attack<br>against a target while<br>Charging<br>an opponent, if your attack roll is successful, you can make an immediate<br>Grab<br>attack against that target as a<br>Free Action<br>.<br><br>You must be wearing<br>Light Armor<br>or no Armor to gain the benefit of this feat.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you have the<br>Stava Expertise<br>Talent, you can add your<br>Strength<br>modifier and your<br>Dexterity<br>modifier to Grapple checks. You must be wearing<br>Light Armor<br>or no Armor to gain this special benefit.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stava_Training</em></p>","martialArtsFeat":true,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"unarmed_charge_grapple_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Stava Training: treat Grab/Grapple as one size larger and add an immediate Grab rider after a successful unarmed charge.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"grapple_size_and_charge_rider_phase16","description":"Stava Training: treat Grab/Grapple as one size larger and add an immediate Grab rider after a successful unarmed charge.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Stava Training: treat Grab/Grapple as one size larger and add an immediate Grab rider after a successful unarmed charge.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"unarmed_charge_grapple_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"GRAPPLE_SIZE_CATEGORY_BONUS","value":1,"description":"Treat yourself as one size category larger for Grab/Grapple sizing."},{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"stavaTrainingChargeGrab","label":"Stava Training: Charge Grab","control":"passive","requiresUnarmed":true,"requiresCharge":true,"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"IMMEDIATE_GRAB","action":"free","description":"After a successful unarmed charge attack, make an immediate Grab as a free action."}],"summary":"Successful unarmed charge attack grants an immediate free Grab attempt."}]},"shortSummary":"Grab and Grapple as a larger creature.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stava_Training","rawImport":{"name":"Stava Training","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Stava_Training","pageTitle":"Stava_Training","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\stava_training.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Martial Arts I\n,\nRunning Attack","prerequisites":["Martial Arts I","Running Attack"],"effect":"When making a\nGrab\nattack, you are considered to be one size category larger for the purpose of determining the size of the opponent that you can\nGrab\n. If you are capable of making a\nGrapple\nattack, you are considered to be one size category larger for the purpose of determining your size modifier to\nGrapple\nchecks.\n\nWhen making an\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst a target while\nCharging\nan opponent, if your attack roll is successful, you can make an immediate\nGrab\nattack against that target as a\nFree Action\n.\n\nYou must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain the benefit of this feat.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"If you have the\nStava Expertise\nTalent, you can add your\nStrength\nmodifier and your\nDexterity\nmodifier to Grapple checks. You must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain this special benefit.","indexPrerequisites":"Martial Arts I , Running Attack","indexBenefit":"Grab and Grapple as a larger creature. Grab after Charging .","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Martial Arts Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nMartial Arts Feats\n\nYou are trained in the Stava\nUnarmed\nfighting style of the\nNoghri\nand can subdue an enemy with ease.\n\nPrerequisites:\nMartial Arts I\n,\nRunning Attack\n\nEffect:\nWhen making a\nGrab\nattack, you are considered to be one size category larger for the purpose of determining the size of the opponent that you can\nGrab\n. If you are capable of making a\nGrapple\nattack, you are considered to be one size category larger for the purpose of determining your size modifier to\nGrapple\nchecks.\n\nWhen making an\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst a target while\nCharging\nan opponent, if your attack roll is successful, you can make an immediate\nGrab\nattack against that target as a\nFree Action\n.\n\nYou must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain the benefit of this feat.\n\nSpecial:\nIf you have the\nStava Expertise\nTalent, you can add your\nStrength\nmodifier and your\nDexterity\nmodifier to Grapple checks. You must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain this special benefit."},"prerequisitesText":"Martial Arts I\n,\nRunning Attack","effect":"When making a\nGrab\nattack, you are considered to be one size category larger for the purpose of determining the size of the opponent that you can\nGrab\n. If you are capable of making a\nGrapple\nattack, you are considered to be one size category larger for the purpose of determining your size modifier to\nGrapple\nchecks.\n\nWhen making an\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst a target while\nCharging\nan opponent, if your attack roll is successful, you can make an immediate\nGrab\nattack against that target as a\nFree Action\n.\n\nYou must be wearing\nLight Armor\nor no Armor to gain the benefit of this feat."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.stava_training"}}}
{"_id":"83abd1c384b58c3c","name":"Intimidating Presence","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You may use Persuasion to intimidate as a swift action instead of a standard action.","prerequisite":"Trained in Persuasion","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":26,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7","21dfe84d159a1b7f"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Intimidate action economy metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"persuasion_intimidate_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Intimidate action economy metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"intimidating_presence_metadata_phase13","skillUseRules":[{"type":"INTIMIDATE_AS_SWIFT_ACTION","skill":"persuasion","description":"Use Persuasion to intimidate as a Swift Action."}]},"shortSummary":"You may use Persuasion to intimidate as a swift action instead of a standard action."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"84d8866a57381620","name":"Dual Weapon Mastery I","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you attack with two weapons, or with both ends of a double weapon as part of a Full Attack Action, you take a -5 penalty (Instead of a -10 penalty) on all attack rolls until the start of your next turn. You only gain this reduced penalty if you are wielding a weapon with which you are proficient.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13, Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"If you use a Full Attack Action to make more than one attack on your turn, you take a -10 penalty on all attack rolls for the round.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["action_economy","dual_wield","feat","general","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you attack with two weapons, or with both ends of a double weapon as part of a<br>Full Attack<br>Action, you take a -5 penalty (Instead of a -10 penalty) on all attack rolls until the start of your next turn. You only gain this reduced penalty if you are wielding a weapon with which you are proficient.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> If you use a<br>Full Attack<br>Action to make more than one attack on your turn, you take a -10 penalty on all attack rolls for the round.</p>\n<h3>Additional Dual Weapon Mastery I Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy<br><br>Vehicle Weapons<br>cannot be used in one hand, so this Feat has no effect on them.<br><br>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Quick Draw<br>):<br>You can draw or holster two weapons with a single<br>Swift Action<br>; you must have both hands free to draw both weapons, and each weapon must be able to be held in one hand.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_I</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13},{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Two-weapon full-attack penalty metadata; consumed once multiattack UI resolves selected attack mode.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"multiattack_penalty_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Two-weapon full-attack penalty metadata; consumed once multiattack UI resolves selected attack mode.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"multiattack_metadata_phase14","multiAttackRules":[{"type":"TWO_WEAPON_FULL_ATTACK_PENALTY","penalty":-5,"description":"Penalty for attacking with two weapons becomes -5."}]},"shortSummary":"Take a -5 penalty on attacks when attacking with two weapons, or both ends of a double weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13, Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy","Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_I","effect":"When you attack with two weapons, or with both ends of a double weapon as part of a\nFull Attack\nAction, you take a -5 penalty (Instead of a -10 penalty) on all attack rolls until the start of your next turn. You only gain this reduced penalty if you are wielding a weapon with which you are proficient."},"effects":[{"_id":"5e1f7aa0-8f41-4f6e-9a16-1710b2de25e9","name":"Dual Weapon Mastery I","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Dual Weapon Mastery I","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Dual Weapon Mastery I"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.dual_weapon_mastery_i","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_I","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8566edcae3a2f18c","name":"Forceful Telekinesis","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You may spend a Force Point to move a target -1 step down the condition track when using Move Object.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use the Force, Move Object","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["feat","force"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Spend a Force Point with Move Object to move target -1 CT step.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"force_power_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Spend a Force Point with Move Object to move target -1 CT step.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"force_power_rider_metadata_phase14","forcePowerRiders":[{"type":"SPEND_FORCE_POINT_MOVE_TARGET_CT","power":"Move Object","steps":-1,"description":"Spend a Force Point when using Move Object to move the target -1 step down the Condition Track."}]},"shortSummary":"You may spend a Force Point to move a target -1 step down the condition track when using Move Object."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.383Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"859d6b9f49118499","name":"Armor Proficiency (heavy)","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you wear Heavy Armor, you take no Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls or Skill Checks. Additionally, you benefit from all of the armor's special Equipment bonuses (if any).","prerequisite":"Armor Proficiency (Light) Feat, Armor Proficiency (Medium) Feat","special":"","normalText":"A character who wears Heavy Armor with which they are not proficient takes a -10 Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls as well as Skill Checks made using the following Skills: Acrobatics, Climb, Endurance, Initiative, Jump, Stealth, and Swim. Additionally, the character gains none of the armor's special Equipment bonuses.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":85,"tags":["armor","build_enabler","defense","feat","general","mapped_phase_1","unlock_grant","choice_variant","armor_access"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"<div class=\"swse-feat-description\">\n<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Source:</strong> https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Heavy)</p>\n<p>You are proficient with Heavy Armor, and can wear it without impediment.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Armor Proficiency (Light) Feat, Armor Proficiency (Medium) Feat</p>\n<h4>Effect</h4>\n<p>When you wear Heavy Armor, you take no Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls or Skill Checks. Additionally, you benefit from all of the armor&#x27;s special Equipment bonuses (if any).</p>\n<h4>Normal</h4>\n<p>A character who wears Heavy Armor with which they are not proficient takes a -10 Armor Check Penalty on attack rolls as well as Skill Checks made using the following Skills: Acrobatics, Climb, Endurance, Initiative, Jump, Stealth, and Swim. Additionally, the character gains none of the armor&#x27;s special Equipment bonuses.</p>\n</div>"},"executionModel":"UNLOCK","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Grants heavy armor proficiency; armor penalty/equipment bonus handling consumes proficiency state.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"grant","applicationScope":"proficiency_grant","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Grants heavy armor proficiency; armor penalty/equipment bonus handling consumes proficiency state.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"proficiency_grant_metadata_phase14","proficiencyGrants":[{"type":"ARMOR_PROFICIENCY","armorCategory":"heavy","description":"Grants proficiency with heavy armor."}]},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"already_resolved_static_variant","required":false,"choiceKind":"armor_proficiency","value":"heavy","grants":["light","medium","heavy"]},"shortSummary":"No penalty on attacks and no Armor Check Penalty while wearing Light Armor, Medium Armor, or Heavy Armor.","prerequisitesText":"Armor Proficiency (Light) Feat, Armor Proficiency (Medium) Feat","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Heavy)"},"effects":[{"_id":"2c536333-89aa-4859-b875-3c23070a7e9b","name":"Armor Proficiency (Heavy)","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.armorProficiency.heavy","mode":5,"value":"true"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Armor Proficiency (Heavy)","effectType":"armor_proficiency"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"phase1Mapped":true,"manualMappingResolved":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Armor_Proficiency_(Heavy)","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"867e3fbd13642016","name":"Heroic Surge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you may take an additional standard or move action on your turn.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["action_economy","burst_turn","defense","extra_action","feat","general","resource_spend","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["turn.on-current-turn","turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Heroic Surge: Heroic Surge is an encounter action resource, not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["turn.on-current-turn","turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Heroic Surge is an encounter action resource, not an attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"non_numeric_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Heroic Surge is an encounter action resource, not an attack bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","actionEconomyRules":[{"type":"GRANT_EXTRA_ACTION","oncePer":"encounter","actions":["standard","move"],"description":"Once per encounter, take one additional standard or move action on your turn."}],"status":"action_economy_phase10","description":"Heroic Surge is an encounter action resource, not an attack bonus."},"shortSummary":"Once per encounter, you may take an additional standard or move action on your turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["turn.on-current-turn","turn.once-per-round"]}}}
{"_id":"8778b4271420f789","name":"Sport Hunter","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make a ranged attack with a slugthrower or sporting weapon with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of weapon you use.\n\n- Slugthrower Pistol: When you use a Slugthrower Pistol at Point-Blank Range, you deal +1 die of damage with the weapon.\n- Slugthrower Rifle: When you use a Slugthrower Rifle, the damage dice increase from d8 to d12.\n- Sporting Blaster Pistol: When you use a Sporting Blaster Pistol, reroll any result of 1 on the damage dice until you get a result other than 1.\n- Sporting Blaster Rifle: When using a Sporting Blaster Rifle, you gain a +1 bonus to attack rolls when you Aim before firing.","prerequisite":"Weapon Proficiency (Pistols) or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":28,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)<br>or<br>Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make a ranged attack with a slugthrower or sporting weapon with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of weapon you use.<br><br>- Slugthrower Pistol : When you use a Slugthrower Pistol at Point-Blank Range , you deal +1 die of damage with the weapon.<br>- Slugthrower Rifle : When you use a Slugthrower Rifle , the damage dice increase from d8 to d12.<br>- Sporting Blaster Pistol : When you use a Sporting Blaster Pistol , reroll any result of 1 on the damage dice until you get a result other than 1.<br>- Sporting Blaster Rifle : When using a Sporting Blaster Rifle , you gain a +1 bonus to attack rolls when you Aim before firing.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sport_Hunter</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Weapon-family bonuses for slugthrower and sporting weapons.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"weapon_family_rules","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Weapon-family bonuses for slugthrower and sporting weapons.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"weapon_family_rules_phase14","rules":[{"type":"WEAPON_DAMAGE_DIE_STEP","weaponGroups":["slugthrower-rifle"],"value":2,"description":"Slugthrower Rifle damage dice improve from d8 to d12."},{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"sportHunterSlugthrowerPistolPointBlank","label":"Sport Hunter (Slugthrower Pistol)","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresWeaponText":["slugthrower-pistol"],"requiresRangeBand":"point-blank","damageExtraWeaponDice":1,"summary":"+1 weapon die with Slugthrower Pistols at point-blank range."},{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"sportHunterSportingBlasterRifleAim","label":"Sport Hunter (Sporting Blaster Rifle)","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresWeaponText":["sporting-blaster-rifle"],"requiresAim":true,"attackModifier":1,"summary":"+1 attack with Sporting Blaster Rifles when aiming."}],"riderRules":[{"type":"DAMAGE_DIE_REROLL","requiresWeaponText":["sporting-blaster-pistol"],"rerollValues":[1],"description":"Sporting Blaster Pistol damage dice reroll 1s until no die shows 1. Metadata only until damage-die reroll UI exists."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain benefits with certain slugthrowers and sporting weapons.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Proficiency (Pistols) or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sport_Hunter","effect":"When you make a ranged attack with a slugthrower or sporting weapon with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of weapon you use.\n\n- Slugthrower Pistol : When you use a Slugthrower Pistol at Point-Blank Range , you deal +1 die of damage with the weapon.\n- Slugthrower Rifle : When you use a Slugthrower Rifle , the damage dice increase from d8 to d12.\n- Sporting Blaster Pistol : When you use a Sporting Blaster Pistol , reroll any result of 1 on the damage dice until you get a result other than 1.\n- Sporting Blaster Rifle : When using a Sporting Blaster Rifle , you gain a +1 bonus to attack rolls when you Aim before firing."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.sport_hunter","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sport_Hunter","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"87969fb8b12ff507","name":"Flawless Pilot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Reroll Pilot checks, always keeping the better result.","prerequisite":"Duros","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["control","feat","grapple","racial","reroll","skill_pilot","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity","vehicle","skill_reroll","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-duros"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Duros</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you reroll a<br>Pilot<br>check, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flawless_Pilot</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_reroll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Flawless Pilot: whenever you reroll pilot, keep the better result.","predicateRequirements":["skill.pilot"],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 continues description-guided implementation by improving teamwork skill feats, skill substitutions, force/dark-side skill context, and several remaining action/resource rider feats.","implementationStatus":"reroll_outcome_upgrade_phase15","description":"Flawless Pilot: improves pilot rerolls to keep the better result.","skillRerollOutcomeUpgrades":[{"id":"flawless-pilot","skillKey":"pilot","outcome":"keepBetter","description":"Whenever you reroll pilot, keep the better result."}],"skillRerolls":[{"id":"flawless-pilot","skillKey":"pilot","outcome":"keepBetter","label":"Flawless Pilot","description":"Flawless Pilot: reroll pilot and keep the better result."}]},"shortSummary":"Reroll Pilot checks, always keeping the better result.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flawless_Pilot","rawImport":{"name":"Flawless Pilot","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Flawless_Pilot","pageTitle":"Flawless_Pilot","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\flawless_pilot.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Duros","prerequisites":["Duros"],"effect":"Whenever you reroll a\nPilot\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Duros","indexBenefit":"Reroll Pilot checks, always keeping the better result.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou know how to handle a Starship better than practically anyone else in the galaxy, and you can make any\nVehicle\ndo exactly what you want it to do.\n\nPrerequisite:\nDuros\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you reroll a\nPilot\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities."},"prerequisitesText":"Duros","effect":"Whenever you reroll a\nPilot\ncheck, you always keep the better result, even if you have multiple reroll abilities."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.flawless_pilot"}}}
{"_id":"88cdedff38b610c0","name":"Two-Weapon Fighting","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You reduce the penalty for fighting with two weapons by 2.","prerequisite":"Dex 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["action_economy","dual_wield","feat","general","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Two-weapon full-attack penalty metadata; consumed once multiattack UI resolves selected attack mode.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"multiattack_penalty_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Two-weapon full-attack penalty metadata; consumed once multiattack UI resolves selected attack mode.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"multiattack_metadata_phase14","multiAttackRules":[{"type":"TWO_WEAPON_FULL_ATTACK_PENALTY","penalty":-8,"description":"Penalty for attacking with two weapons becomes -8."}]},"shortSummary":"You reduce the penalty for fighting with two weapons by 2."},"effects":[{"_id":"4f1d95ad-b4cd-4d39-875e-730213a08d56","name":"Two-Weapon Fighting","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Two-Weapon Fighting","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Two-Weapon Fighting"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"89c5695c7435b733","name":"Halt","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you hit with an Attack of Opportunity, while wielding a weapon for which you possess the Weapon Focus Feat, against an enemy of up to one size larger than you, compare the same die roll against the target's Grapple check. If the die roll succeeds against the Grapple check, the target immediately halts all movement and falls Prone in its current square. The target can spend any remaining Actions normally.\n\nIf your attack exceeds the target's Damage Threshold, the target loses any remaining Actions and ends its turn immediately. Apply damage normally to the target regardless of the results of this Feat.","prerequisite":"Trip, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon), Base Attack Bonus +8","special":"If the target is using the Charge Action when moving past you, its Charge is ended if you successfully knock it Prone, and the target cannot Charge again on this turn.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":21,"tags":["control","damage_threshold","feat","general","knock_prone","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trip<br>,<br>Weapon Focus<br>(Chosen Weapon),<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+8</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you hit with an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>, while wielding a weapon for which you possess the<br>Weapon Focus<br>Feat, against an enemy of up to one size larger than you, compare the same die roll against the target&#x27;s<br>Grapple<br>check. If the die roll succeeds against the<br>Grapple<br>check, the target immediately halts all movement and falls<br>Prone<br>in its current square. The target can spend any remaining<br>Actions<br>normally.<br><br>If your attack exceeds the target&#x27;s<br>Damage Threshold<br>, the target loses any remaining<br>Actions<br>and ends its turn immediately. Apply damage normally to the target regardless of the results of this Feat.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If the target is using the<br>Charge<br>Action when moving past you, its<br>Charge<br>is ended if you successfully knock it<br>Prone<br>, and the target cannot<br>Charge<br>again on this turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Halt</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["target.is-prone"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Halt: Attack-of-opportunity rider with Weapon Focus that can halt movement and knock prone; not a flat attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["target.is-prone"],"conditionSummary":"Attack-of-opportunity rider with Weapon Focus that can halt movement and knock prone; not a flat attack bonus."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"explicit_rider_or_attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Requires a selected weapon/weapon group. The bonus is always available for that choice, but not actor-wide.","predicateRequirements":["target.is-prone"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"halt","label":"Halt","control":"toggle","requiresOpportunityAttack":true,"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"COMPARE_ATTACK_TO_GRAPPLE","successEffects":["haltMovement","prone"],"description":"Compare the same attack roll to target Grapple; on success target halts movement and falls prone."},{"type":"LOSE_REMAINING_ACTIONS_IF_EXCEEDS_DT","description":"If attack also exceeds Damage Threshold, target loses remaining actions and ends turn."}],"summary":"On qualifying AoO with focused weapon, compare same roll to Grapple to halt movement and knock prone."}],"status":"halt_phase12","description":"Attack-of-opportunity rider with Weapon Focus that can halt movement and knock prone; not a flat attack bonus."},"shortSummary":"Knock an enemy Prone after a successful Attack of Opportunity, immediately end the target's remaining Actions when also exceeding its Damage Threshold.","prerequisitesText":"Trip, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon), Base Attack Bonus +8","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Halt","effect":"If you hit with an\nAttack of Opportunity\n, while wielding a weapon for which you possess the\nWeapon Focus\nFeat, against an enemy of up to one size larger than you, compare the same die roll against the target's\nGrapple\ncheck. If the die roll succeeds against the\nGrapple\ncheck, the target immediately halts all movement and falls\nProne\nin its current square. The target can spend any remaining\nActions\nnormally.\n\nIf your attack exceeds the target's\nDamage Threshold\n, the target loses any remaining\nActions\nand ends its turn immediately. Apply damage normally to the target regardless of the results of this Feat."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["target.is-prone"],"id":"swse.feat.halt","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Halt","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8a5cb28f625d6f02","name":"Great Cleave","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As the Cleave Feat, except that you have no limit to the number of times you can use it per round.","prerequisite":"Strength 13, Cleave, Power Attack, Base Attack Bonus +4.","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>13,<br>Cleave<br>,<br>Power Attack<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+4.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As the<br>Cleave<br>Feat, except that you have no limit to the number of times you can use it per round.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Great_Cleave</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rider_effect_phase7","description":"Great Cleave: modeled as a rider/action rule, not a numeric modifier.","rules":[{"type":"EXTRA_ATTACK_LIMIT_OVERRIDE","baseFeat":"Cleave","limit":"unlimitedPerRound"}],"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Great Cleave: numeric scaffold disabled by Phase 7 (description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus)","mechanicsMode":"metadata_note","applicationScope":"not_a_numeric_modifier","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus","metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"extra_attack_on_drop","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Uses Cleave but removes the once-per-round limit.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"No limit to Cleave attacks each round.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13, Cleave, Power Attack, Base Attack Bonus +4.","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Great_Cleave","effect":"As the\nCleave\nFeat, except that you have no limit to the number of times you can use it per round."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.great_cleave","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Great_Cleave","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8a78270d15aa4738","name":"Force Readiness","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can spend Force Points as a Free Action, even if it is not your turn. All other restrictions to Force Point use still apply.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"Unless otherwise specified, you can spend Force Points only on your turn, preventing you from enhancing attacks and Skill Checks made as Reactions.","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":26,"tags":["feat","force_point_spend","general","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can spend<br>Force Points<br>as a<br>Free Action<br>, even if it is not your turn. All other restrictions to<br>Force Point<br>use still apply.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> Unless otherwise specified, you can spend<br>Force Points<br>only on your turn, preventing you from enhancing attacks and<br>Skill Checks<br>made as<br>Reactions<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Readiness</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Force Point timing rule; no static modifier.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"resourceRules":{"forcePoints":[{"type":"SPEND_OUT_OF_TURN","description":"You may spend Force Points even when it is not your turn."}]},"mechanicsMode":"passive_resource","applicationScope":"force_point_timing_context","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Force Point timing rule; no static modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"force_readiness_metadata_phase13"},"shortSummary":"Spend Force Points even if it is not your turn.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Readiness","effect":"You can spend\nForce Points\nas a\nFree Action\n, even if it is not your turn. All other restrictions to\nForce Point\nuse still apply."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.force_readiness","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Readiness","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8a86aa95c54f6dad","name":"Never Surrender","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"The first time you would be reduced to 0 Hit Points in an encounter, you can make an Endurance check as a Reaction, with a DC equal to the number of points of damage being dealt to you. If your check succeeds, you are instead reduced to 1 Hit Point.","prerequisite":"Trained in Endurance","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["durability","feat","general","hit_points","skill_endurance","skill_synergy"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Endurance</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> The first time you would be reduced to 0 Hit Points in an encounter, you can make an<br>Endurance<br>check as a<br>Reaction<br>, with a DC equal to the number of points of damage being dealt to you. If your check succeeds, you are instead reduced to 1 Hit Point.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Never_Surrender</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Endurance check to avoid dropping to 0 HP.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"action_or_reaction_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Endurance check to avoid dropping to 0 HP.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"action_metadata_phase14","actionRules":[{"type":"ENDURANCE_CHECK_AVOID_ZERO_HP"}]},"shortSummary":"Make an Endurance check to prevent falling to 0 Hit Points.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Endurance","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Never_Surrender","effect":"The first time you would be reduced to 0 Hit Points in an encounter, you can make an\nEndurance\ncheck as a\nReaction\n, with a DC equal to the number of points of damage being dealt to you. If your check succeeds, you are instead reduced to 1 Hit Point."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.never_surrender","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Never_Surrender","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8b1a9adee4e2e78e","name":"Steadying Position","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you are Prone and Aim before making a ranged attack, your target does not benefit from its Dexterity bonus to its Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"Careful Shot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":28,"tags":["ability_dexterity","control","feat","general","knock_prone"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Careful Shot</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you are<br>Prone<br>and<br>Aim<br>before making a ranged attack, your target does not benefit from its<br>Dexterity<br>bonus to its<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Steadying_Position</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex","target.is-prone"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Steadying Position: When prone and aiming with a ranged attack, target loses Dexterity bonus to Reflex; represented as a flag option, not +2 attack.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex","target.is-prone"],"conditionSummary":"When prone and aiming with a ranged attack, target loses Dexterity bonus to Reflex; represented as a flag option, not +2 attack."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"explicit_rider_or_attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex","target.is-prone"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"steadyingPosition","label":"Steadying Position","control":"flag","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAim":true,"requiresContextFlags":["attackerProne"],"targetDefenseFlags":["ignoreDexBonusToReflex"],"summary":"When prone and aiming before a ranged attack, the target does not benefit from Dex bonus to Reflex."}],"status":"steadying_position_phase12","description":"When prone and aiming with a ranged attack, target loses Dexterity bonus to Reflex; represented as a flag option, not +2 attack."},"shortSummary":"Deny target's Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense when you are Prone and Aiming.","prerequisitesText":"Careful Shot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Steadying_Position","effect":"When you are\nProne\nand\nAim\nbefore making a ranged attack, your target does not benefit from its\nDexterity\nbonus to its\nReflex Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex","target.is-prone"],"id":"swse.feat.steadying_position","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Steadying_Position","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8b2f7862b3c76e61","name":"Frightening Cleave","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Immediately after you use the Cleave Feat, each enemy within 6 squares of you and within your line of sight takes a -1 penalty to its Reflex Defense, attack rolls, and Skill Checks against you until the end of the encounter. This penalty stacks with itself to a maximum of -5. This is a Mind-Affecting effect.","prerequisite":"Strength 13, Cleave, Power Attack, Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":20,"tags":["control","feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>13,<br>Cleave<br>,<br>Power Attack<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+4</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Immediately after you use the<br>Cleave<br>Feat, each enemy within 6 squares of you and within your line of sight takes a -1 penalty to its<br>Reflex Defense<br>, attack rolls, and<br>Skill Checks<br>against you until the end of the encounter. This penalty stacks with itself to a maximum of -5. This is a<br>Mind-Affecting<br>effect.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Frightening_Cleave</em></p>\n<p><strong>Automation:</strong> Punted to GM/player handling. After you use Cleave, the player/GM should manually apply the stacking -1 encounter penalty to affected enemies within 6 squares and line of sight.</p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Feat: GM/player-managed; no automatic modifier is applied. Punted to GM/player handling. After you use Cleave, the player/GM should manually apply the stacking -1 encounter penalty to affected enemies within 6 squares and line of sight.","mechanicsMode":"gm_managed","applicationScope":"table_adjudicated","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Post-Cleave area debuff; not a flat attack bonus."}],"mechanicsMode":"gm_managed","applicationScope":"table_adjudicated","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Punted to GM/player handling. After you use Cleave, the player/GM should manually apply the stacking -1 encounter penalty to affected enemies within 6 squares and line of sight.","predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"metadataPhase":"phase23-feat-cleanup","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","status":"gm_managed_phase23","description":"Punted to GM/player handling. After you use Cleave, the player/GM should manually apply the stacking -1 encounter penalty to affected enemies within 6 squares and line of sight.","gmManaged":true,"archived_riderRules":[{"type":"RIDER_EFFECT","id":"frighteningCleaveDebuff","trigger":"afterCleave","targets":"enemiesWithin6LineOfSight","effect":{"attack":-1,"skills":-1,"defense.reflex":-1},"stackingMax":-5,"descriptor":"mind-affecting","duration":"encounter"}]},"shortSummary":"When you use the Cleave feat, each enemy within 6 squares and line of sight takes a penalty to Reflex Defense, Skill Checks, and attack rolls against you.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13, Cleave, Power Attack, Base Attack Bonus +4","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Frightening_Cleave","effect":"Immediately after you use the\nCleave\nFeat, each enemy within 6 squares of you and within your line of sight takes a -1 penalty to its\nReflex Defense\n, attack rolls, and\nSkill Checks\nagainst you until the end of the encounter. This penalty stacks with itself to a maximum of -5. This is a\nMind-Affecting\neffect."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.frightening_cleave","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Frightening_Cleave","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8baf83743668f63a","name":"Desperate Gambit","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per turn, when you miss on an attack roll, you reroll the attack, but you take a -2 penalty to Reflex Defense until the end of your next turn. If your first attack missed because you rolled a Natural 1, you can still use this Feat, but you take a -5 penalty to Reflex Defense instead. You must accept the result of the second roll, even if it's worse than the first.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":24,"tags":["feat","general","reroll"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per turn, when you miss on an attack roll, you reroll the attack, but you take a -2 penalty to<br>Reflex Defense<br>until the end of your next turn. If your first attack missed because you rolled a Natural 1, you can still use this Feat, but you take a -5 penalty to<br>Reflex Defense<br>instead. You must accept the result of the second roll, even if it&#x27;s worse than the first.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Desperate_Gambit</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_reroll_with_penalty_implemented","description":"Desperate Gambit: reroll missed attack; -2 penalty to Reflex Defense (or -5 if natural 1). Must accept reroll result.","attackRerolls":[{"type":"ATTACK_REROLL","trigger":"missedAttack","outcome":"keepSecond","cost":"reflexDefensePenalty","description":"Desperate Gambit: reroll a missed attack but take a penalty to Reflex Defense."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"reroll_or_resource_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rerolls/resources are not static sheet modifiers and require a check/encounter/resource context.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Reroll missed attack by taking a penalty to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Desperate_Gambit","effect":"Once per turn, when you miss on an attack roll, you reroll the attack, but you take a -2 penalty to\nReflex Defense\nuntil the end of your next turn. If your first attack missed because you rolled a Natural 1, you can still use this Feat, but you take a -5 penalty to\nReflex Defense\ninstead. You must accept the result of the second roll, even if it's worse than the first."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.desperate_gambit","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Desperate_Gambit","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8cf12d528b0d0478","name":"Opportunistic Trickery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever an opponent provokes an Attack of Opportunity from you, once per turn you can sacrifice that attack to reduce the target's Reflex Defense by 2 for the following round.","prerequisite":"Combat Reflexes, Sneak Attack","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":22,"tags":["feat","general","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Combat Reflexes<br>,<br>Sneak Attack</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever an opponent provokes an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>from you, once per turn you can sacrifice that attack to reduce the target&#x27;s<br>Reflex Defense<br>by 2 for the following round.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Trickery</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Opportunistic Trickery: Sacrifice an AoO to reduce target Reflex by 2; not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Sacrifice an AoO to reduce target Reflex by 2; not an attack bonus."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"explicit_rider_or_attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"opportunisticTrickery","label":"Opportunistic Trickery","control":"flag","requiresOpportunityAttack":true,"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"SACRIFICE_ATTACK_FOR_DEFENSE_PENALTY","defense":"reflex","value":-2,"duration":"followingRound"}],"summary":"Once per turn, sacrifice a provoked AoO to reduce target Reflex by 2 for the following round."}],"status":"opportunistic_trickery_phase12","description":"Sacrifice an AoO to reduce target Reflex by 2; not an attack bonus."},"shortSummary":"Sacrifice Attack of Opportunity to reduce target's Reflex Defense by 2.","prerequisitesText":"Combat Reflexes, Sneak Attack","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Trickery","effect":"Whenever an opponent provokes an\nAttack of Opportunity\nfrom you, once per turn you can sacrifice that attack to reduce the target's\nReflex Defense\nby 2 for the following round."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.opportunistic_trickery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Opportunistic_Trickery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8d164553709dd068","name":"Pall of the Dark Side","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can add one-half your Dark Side Score (Minimum 1) to any Use the Force checks made to resist attempts to detect you with the Sense Force application of the Use the Force skill.","prerequisite":"Dark Side Score 1+","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":26,"tags":["dark_side","feat","force_execution","general","skill_synergy","skill_use_the_force","use_the_force","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dark Side Score<br>1+</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can add one-half your<br>Dark Side Score<br>(Minimum 1) to any<br>Use the Force<br>checks made to resist attempts to detect you with the<br>Sense Force<br>application of the<br>Use the Force<br>skill.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pall_of_the_Dark_Side</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Add half Dark Side Score, minimum +1, to Use the Force checks to resist Sense Force detection.","predicateRequirements":["skill.useTheForce","application.senseForce.resistDetection"],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 continues description-guided implementation by improving teamwork skill feats, skill substitutions, force/dark-side skill context, and several remaining action/resource rider feats.","implementationStatus":"dark_side_detection_skill_bonus_phase15","description":"Pall of the Dark Side: +half Dark Side Score, minimum +1, to Use the Force checks to resist Sense Force detection.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"pall-dark-side-resist-detection","skillKey":"useTheForce","valueFormula":"halfDarkSideScore","minimum":1,"type":"untyped","applications":["Sense Force","resist detection","resist Sense Force"],"requiresContextFlags":["resistDetection"],"description":"Add half Dark Side Score (minimum +1) to resist Sense Force detection."}]},"shortSummary":"Add half your Dark Side Score to Use the Force checks to resist detection.","prerequisitesText":"Dark Side Score 1+","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pall_of_the_Dark_Side","effect":"You can add one-half your\nDark Side Score\n(Minimum 1) to any\nUse the Force\nchecks made to resist attempts to detect you with the\nSense Force\napplication of the\nUse the Force\nskill."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.pall_of_the_dark_side","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pall_of_the_Dark_Side","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8d1747eda25693b0","name":"Cunning Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on attack rolls against a Flat-Footed enemy or one who is denied its Dexterity bonus to its Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +2 bonus on attack rolls against a<br>Flat-Footed<br>enemy or one who is denied its<br>Dexterity<br>bonus to its<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Cunning_Attack</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Automatic roll-context bonus against flat-footed targets.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Automatic roll-context bonus against flat-footed targets.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"cunningAttack","label":"Cunning Attack","control":"passive","requiresTargetFlatFooted":true,"attackModifier":2,"summary":"Gain +2 attack against flat-footed targets."}],"implementationStatus":"cunningAttack_attack_option_phase13"},"shortSummary":"Gain +2 bonus on attack rolls against Flat-Footed enemies.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Cunning_Attack","effect":"You gain a +2 bonus on attack rolls against a\nFlat-Footed\nenemy or one who is denied its\nDexterity\nbonus to its\nReflex Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.cunning_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Cunning_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"8ff15069dbf6270d","name":"Silver Tongue","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can Intimidate or Change Attitude as a Standard Action.","prerequisite":"Trained in Persuasion","special":"","normalText":"To Intimidate or Change Attitude requires a Full-Round Action.","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":24,"tags":["feat","general","social","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Persuasion</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can<br>Intimidate<br>or<br>Change Attitude<br>as a<br>Standard Action<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> To<br>Intimidate<br>or<br>Change Attitude<br>requires a<br>Full-Round Action<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Silver_Tongue</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Persuasion action economy metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"persuasion_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Persuasion action economy metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"silver_tongue_metadata_phase13","skillUseRules":[{"type":"PERSUASION_STANDARD_ACTION","skill":"persuasion","applications":["intimidate","change attitude"],"description":"Intimidate or change attitude as a Standard Action."}]},"shortSummary":"Intimidate a creature or change its Attitude as a Standard Action.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Persuasion","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Silver_Tongue","effect":"You can\nIntimidate\nor\nChange Attitude\nas a\nStandard Action\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.silver_tongue","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Silver_Tongue","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"90a258aae2583994","name":"Survivor of Ryloth","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Make Survival checks to resist Extreme Heat and Extreme Cold.","prerequisite":"Twi'lek","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","skill_survival","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-twi-lek"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Twi&#x27;lek</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per hour when you and your allies are in an environment of<br>Extreme Heat<br>or<br>Extreme Cold<br>, you can make a<br>Survival<br>check. You and up to 10 allies can use the results of the<br>Survival<br>check in place of your<br>Fortitude Defense<br>when the<br>Extreme Heat<br>or<br>Extreme Cold<br>makes its hourly attack roll against your<br>Fortitude Defenses<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Survivor_of_Ryloth</em></p>\n<p><strong>Automation:</strong> If you have this feat, a Survivor of Ryloth extra use is added to Survival. It lets you roll Survival once per hour in extreme heat or cold so you and up to 10 allies can use the result in place of Fortitude Defense against the environmental attack. GM adjudicates timing and affected allies.</p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.fortitude","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.fortitude"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Survivor of Ryloth: Survival check can replace Fortitude Defense against extreme heat/cold for you and up to 10 allies.","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_virtual","applicationScope":"survival_extra_skill_use","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.fortitude"],"conditionSummary":"Survival check can replace Fortitude Defense against extreme heat/cold for you and up to 10 allies."}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_virtual","applicationScope":"survival_extra_skill_use","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Has predicates, but the semantic difference between passive roll-scope and conditional trigger-scope needs manual review.","predicateRequirements":["defense.fortitude"],"metadataPhase":"phase23-feat-cleanup","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","skillUseSubstitutions":[{"id":"survivor_of_ryloth_extreme_environment","fromSkill":"survival","toDefense":"fortitude","applications":["Extreme Heat","Extreme Cold"],"targetCount":11,"description":"Use Survival check result in place of Fortitude Defense against hourly extreme heat/cold attacks."}],"status":"survival_extra_use_phase23","description":"Adds a Survivor of Ryloth Survival extra skill use for extreme heat/cold Fortitude replacement. GM adjudicates environment timing and affected allies.","gmManaged":true,"skillUseEffects":[{"id":"survivor_of_ryloth_extreme_temperature","skill":"survival","application":"Survivor of Ryloth","type":"FORTITUDE_DEFENSE_REPLACEMENT_NOTE","frequency":"oncePerHour","targetLimit":"selfPlusUpTo10Allies","description":"In extreme heat or cold, make a Survival check once per hour. You and up to 10 allies can use the result in place of Fortitude Defense against the hourly environmental attack."}]},"shortSummary":"Make Survival checks to resist Extreme Heat and Extreme Cold.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Survivor_of_Ryloth","rawImport":{"name":"Survivor of Ryloth","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Survivor_of_Ryloth","pageTitle":"Survivor_of_Ryloth","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\survivor_of_ryloth.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Twi'lek","prerequisites":["Twi'lek"],"effect":"Once per hour when you and your allies are in an environment of\nExtreme Heat\nor\nExtreme Cold\n, you can make a\nSurvival\ncheck. You and up to 10 allies can use the results of the\nSurvival\ncheck in place of your\nFortitude Defense\nwhen the\nExtreme Heat\nor\nExtreme Cold\nmakes its hourly attack roll against your\nFortitude Defenses\n.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Twi'lek","indexBenefit":"Make Survival checks to resist Extreme Heat and Extreme Cold .","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou know how to survive on both the night and day sides of your homeworld, allowing you and your allies to weather the harsh environments of the galaxy.\n\nPrerequisite:\nTwi'lek\n\nEffect:\nOnce per hour when you and your allies are in an environment of\nExtreme Heat\nor\nExtreme Cold\n, you can make a\nSurvival\ncheck. You and up to 10 allies can use the results of the\nSurvival\ncheck in place of your\nFortitude Defense\nwhen the\nExtreme Heat\nor\nExtreme Cold\nmakes its hourly attack roll against your\nFortitude Defenses\n."},"prerequisitesText":"Twi'lek","effect":"Once per hour when you and your allies are in an environment of\nExtreme Heat\nor\nExtreme Cold\n, you can make a\nSurvival\ncheck. You and up to 10 allies can use the results of the\nSurvival\ncheck in place of your\nFortitude Defense\nwhen the\nExtreme Heat\nor\nExtreme Cold\nmakes its hourly attack roll against your\nFortitude Defenses\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.fortitude"],"id":"swse.feat.survivor_of_ryloth"}}}
{"_id":"9138c70e1ae07fe1","name":"Improved Knock Prone","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 bonus on attack rolls made to knock an opponent prone.","prerequisite":"Int 13, Knock Prone","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","knock_prone","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":5,"type":"untyped","predicates":["target.is-prone"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Improved Knock Prone: Implemented as an explicit attack option or roll-context rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["target.is-prone"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit attack option or roll-context rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Improved Knock Prone: maneuver-gated +5, not a general attack bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 converts clear description-guided combat feats from scaffold modifiers into CombatOptionResolver metadata.","status":"attack_option_phase9","description":"Improved Knock Prone: maneuver-gated +5, not a general attack bonus.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"improvedKnockProne","label":"Improved Knock Prone","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","requiresManeuver":"knock-prone","attackModifier":5,"summary":"Gain +5 on attack rolls made to knock an opponent prone."}]},"shortSummary":"You gain a +5 bonus on attack rolls made to knock an opponent prone."},"effects":[{"_id":"b1f63e24-9bc9-4ade-a65c-39ddd6f85205","name":"Improved Knock Prone","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Improved Knock Prone","effectType":"combat_bonus","flagType":"Improved Knock Prone"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["target.is-prone"]}}}
{"_id":"9244159a233a101a","name":"Dreadful Rage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While Raging, your Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls increases to +5.","prerequisite":"Rage Species Trait, Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"A character with the Rage Species Trait gains a +2 bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls while Raging.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase9","feat","general","offense_melee","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rage Species Trait,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> While Raging, your Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls increases to +5.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> A character with the Rage Species Trait gains a +2 bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls while Raging.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dreadful_Rage</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rage_rule_phase9","description":"Dreadful Rage: Rage melee attack and damage bonuses increase to +5.","rules":[{"type":"RAGE_ATTACK_DAMAGE_BONUS_OVERRIDE","attackBonus":5,"damageBonus":5,"description":"Rage bonus to melee attacks and damage increases to +5."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"rage_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Only applies while the actor is raging or using rage-specific rules.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Rage bonus to attacks and damage increases to +5.","prerequisitesText":"Rage Species Trait, Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dreadful_Rage","effect":"While Raging, your Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls increases to +5."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.dreadful_rage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dreadful_Rage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"92f927c92ded9fcf","name":"Martial Arts I","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Damage dealt by your Unarmed Attacks increases by one die step. In addition, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense. Additionally, you do not provoke Attacks of Opportunity with Unarmed Attacks.","prerequisite":"None","special":"A situation that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense (if any) also makes you lose any dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses.","normalText":"The amount of damage you deal with a successful Unarmed Attack is based on your size: Small, 1d3; Medium, 1d4; Large, 1d6. You provoke Attacks of Opportunity when making Unarmed Attacks.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed","unarmed_damage_step","unarmed_no_provoke"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Damage dealt by your<br>Unarmed Attacks<br>increases by one die step. In addition, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>. Additionally, you do not provoke<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>with<br>Unarmed Attacks<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> The amount of damage you deal with a successful<br>Unarmed Attack<br>is based on your size: Small, 1d3; Medium, 1d4; Large, 1d6. You provoke Attacks of Opportunity when making<br>Unarmed Attacks<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> A situation that makes you lose your<br>Dexterity<br>bonus to<br>Reflex Defense<br>(if any) also makes you lose any dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_I</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","value":1,"type":"dodge","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Martial Arts I: +1 dodge bonus to Reflex Defense","mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor_and_unarmed_rule_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"include","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Always-on Reflex Defense dodge bonus; unarmed damage/no-AOO portions are handled by rule hooks."}],"rules":[{"type":"UNARMED_DAMAGE_STEP","params":{"steps":1},"description":"Martial Arts I: increase unarmed attack damage by one die step"},{"type":"UNARMED_DOES_NOT_PROVOKE_AOO","description":"Martial Arts I: unarmed attacks do not provoke attacks of opportunity"}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor_and_unarmed_rule_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"include","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Always-on Reflex Defense dodge bonus; unarmed damage/no-AOO portions are handled by rule hooks.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Increases damage from Unarmed attacks by one die step; gain +1 bonus to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_I","effect":"Damage dealt by your\nUnarmed Attacks\nincreases by one die step. In addition, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to your\nReflex Defense\n. Additionally, you do not provoke\nAttacks of Opportunity\nwith\nUnarmed Attacks\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"id":"swse.feat.martial_arts_i","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_I","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"931fae85d3d53c07","name":"Rancor Crush","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you successfully Pin an enemy with the Pin Feat and use the Crush Feat at the same time, the enemy moves -1 step down the Condition Track in addition to taking damage.","prerequisite":"Strength 15, Crush, Pin, Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"The Crush Feat deals damage to a Grappled enemy but does not move the enemy down the Condition Track.","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":21,"tags":["condition_track","feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>15,<br>Crush<br>,<br>Pin<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you successfully<br>Pin<br>an enemy with the<br>Pin<br>Feat and use the<br>Crush<br>Feat at the same time, the enemy moves -1 step down the<br>Condition Track<br>in addition to taking damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> The<br>Crush<br>Feat deals damage to a<br>Grappled<br>enemy but does not move the enemy down the<br>Condition Track<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rancor_Crush</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"str","min":15},{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Condition-track rider when using Crush.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"condition_track_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Condition-track rider when using Crush.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"condition_track_rider_metadata_phase14","riderRules":[{"type":"MOVE_TARGET_CT_ON_CRUSH","steps":-1,"description":"When using Crush, move the target -1 step on the Condition Track."}]},"shortSummary":"Move an enemy -1 step down the Condition Track when using the Crush feat.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 15, Crush, Pin, Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rancor_Crush","effect":"When you successfully\nPin\nan enemy with the\nPin\nFeat and use the\nCrush\nFeat at the same time, the enemy moves -1 step down the\nCondition Track\nin addition to taking damage."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.rancor_crush","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rancor_Crush","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"935212056c7968c8","name":"Power Blast","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Swift Action, before making an attack roll, you can choose to subtract a number from all ranged attack rolls and add the same number to all ranged damage rolls. This number cannot exceed your Base Attack Bonus. The penalty on attacks and bonus on damage applies until the start of your next turn but you gain no bonus to damage with Area Attacks or when attacking objects or Vehicles with this Feat.","prerequisite":"None","special":"If you do not have a Strength score of 13 or higher, you take a -5 penalty to attacks when using this Feat with non- Vehicle Weapons.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":28,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Swift Action<br>, before making an attack roll, you can choose to subtract a number from all ranged attack rolls and add the same number to all ranged damage rolls. This number cannot exceed your<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>. The penalty on attacks and bonus on damage applies until the start of your next turn but you gain no bonus to damage with<br>Area Attacks<br>or when attacking objects or<br>Vehicles<br>with this Feat.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you do not have a<br>Strength<br>score of 13 or higher, you take a -5 penalty to attacks when using this Feat with non-<br>Vehicle Weapons<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Power_Blast</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Power Blast: Implemented as an explicit attack option or roll-context rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"passive_choice_required","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-ranged"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit attack option or roll-context rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Power Blast: explicit ranged slider trading attack for damage.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 converts clear description-guided combat feats from scaffold modifiers into CombatOptionResolver metadata.","status":"attack_option_phase9","description":"Power Blast: explicit ranged slider trading attack for damage.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"powerBlast","label":"Power Blast","control":"slider","max":99,"resource":"baseAttackBonus","requiresAttackType":"ranged","excludesAreaAttack":true,"attackModifierFormula":"-value","damageModifierFormula":"value","summary":"As a swift action, trade ranged attack bonus for ranged damage up to BAB; no area/object/vehicle damage bonus."}]},"shortSummary":"Trade attack bonus for damage on ranged attacks (up to your Base Attack Bonus).","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Power_Blast","effect":"As a\nSwift Action\n, before making an attack roll, you can choose to subtract a number from all ranged attack rolls and add the same number to all ranged damage rolls. This number cannot exceed your\nBase Attack Bonus\n. The penalty on attacks and bonus on damage applies until the start of your next turn but you gain no bonus to damage with\nArea Attacks\nor when attacking objects or\nVehicles\nwith this Feat."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.power_blast","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Power_Blast","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"94023012303ad257","name":"Disabler","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When making a ranged attack with an Ion Weapon with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of weapon you use.\n\n- Ion Grenade: When you use an Ion Grenade, the Grenade's Burst radius is 3 squares instead of 2 squares.\n- Ion Pistol: When you use an Ion Pistol, the damage dice increase from d6 to d8.\n- Ion Rifle: You treat the Ion Rifle as an Accurate Weapon.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":21,"tags":["control","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When making a ranged attack with an<br>Ion<br>Weapon with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of weapon you use.<br><br>- Ion Grenade : When you use an Ion Grenade , the Grenade&#x27;s Burst radius is 3 squares instead of 2 squares.<br>- Ion Pistol : When you use an Ion Pistol , the damage dice increase from d6 to d8.<br>- Ion Rifle : You treat the Ion Rifle as an Accurate Weapon.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disabler</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Ion weapon family bonuses and property hooks.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"weapon_family_rules","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Ion weapon family bonuses and property hooks.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"weapon_family_rules_phase14","rules":[{"type":"WEAPON_DAMAGE_DIE_STEP","weaponGroups":["ion-pistol"],"value":1,"description":"Ion Pistol damage dice improve from d6 to d8."}],"weaponPropertyRules":[{"type":"BURST_RADIUS_OVERRIDE","requiresWeaponText":["ion-grenade"],"radiusSquares":3,"description":"Ion Grenade burst radius is 3 squares."},{"type":"TREAT_AS_ACCURATE","requiresWeaponText":["ion-rifle"],"description":"Treat Ion Rifles as Accurate Weapons."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain benefits when using certain Ion weapons.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disabler","effect":"When making a ranged attack with an\nIon\nWeapon with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of weapon you use.\n\n- Ion Grenade : When you use an Ion Grenade , the Grenade's Burst radius is 3 squares instead of 2 squares.\n- Ion Pistol : When you use an Ion Pistol , the damage dice increase from d6 to d8.\n- Ion Rifle : You treat the Ion Rifle as an Accurate Weapon."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.disabler","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disabler","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"94b8751efb03536a","name":"Rapid Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using a ranged weapon with which you are proficient, you may fire two shots as a single attack against a single target. You take a -2 penalty on your attack roll, but you deal +1 die of damage with a successful attack.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"Using this Feat fires two shots and can only be done if the weapon has sufficient ammunition remaining. The effects of this Feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the Burst Fire Feat or the Deadeye Feat. If you do not have a Strength score of 13 or higher, increase the penalty to attacks to -5 when using this Feat with non- Vehicle Weapons.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","feat_chain","general","offense","offense_ranged","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using a ranged weapon with which you are proficient, you may fire two shots as a single attack against a single target. You take a -2 penalty on your attack roll, but you deal +1 die of damage with a successful attack.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> Using this Feat fires two shots and can only be done if the weapon has sufficient ammunition remaining. The effects of this Feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the<br>Burst Fire<br>Feat or the<br>Deadeye<br>Feat. If you do not have a<br>Strength<br>score of 13 or higher, increase the penalty to attacks to -5 when using this Feat with non-<br>Vehicle Weapons<br>.</p>\n<h3>Additional Rapid Shot Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy<br><br>Special:<br>This Feat works normally with Vehicle Weapons. However, if you are using a<br>Missile<br>or a<br>Torpedo<br>and you miss with your attack roll, the projectile does not gain the benefit of this Feat for the second attack roll.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Shot</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Rapid Shot: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"rapidShot","label":"Rapid Shot","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"ranged","attackModifier":-2,"damageDiceStepBonus":1,"summary":"Take -2 on a ranged attack to deal +1 die of damage."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate attack/combat option, not a passive sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"Take a -2 penalty on a ranged attack roll to deal +1 die of damage.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Shot","effect":"When using a ranged weapon with which you are proficient, you may fire two shots as a single attack against a single target. You take a -2 penalty on your attack roll, but you deal +1 die of damage with a successful attack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.rapid_shot","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"94fc90a53d747f84","name":"Sniper Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When wielding only ranged weapons with which you are proficient, you gain a +2 bonus on all your ranged attacks until the beginning of your next turn, but you take a -5 penalty to Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"None","special":"This Feat cannot be used with Vehicle Weapons or Heavy Weapons.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":30,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When wielding only ranged weapons with which you are proficient, you gain a +2 bonus on all your ranged attacks until the beginning of your next turn, but you take a -5 penalty to<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Feat cannot be used with<br>Vehicle Weapons<br>or<br>Heavy Weapons<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper_Shot</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Sniper Shot: Implemented as an explicit attack option or roll-context rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit attack option or roll-context rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Sniper Shot: explicit ranged attack option with Reflex penalty rider.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 converts clear description-guided combat feats from scaffold modifiers into CombatOptionResolver metadata.","status":"attack_option_phase9","description":"Sniper Shot: explicit ranged attack option with Reflex penalty rider.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"sniperShot","label":"Sniper Shot","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"ranged","excludesWeaponGroups":["heavy","vehicle"],"attackModifier":2,"defenseModifier":{"target":"defense.reflex","type":"untyped","value":-5,"duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn"},"summary":"Gain +2 on ranged attacks until your next turn, but take -5 Reflex; not for heavy or vehicle weapons."}]},"shortSummary":"Increase accuracy at a -5 Reflex Defense penalty.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper_Shot","effect":"When wielding only ranged weapons with which you are proficient, you gain a +2 bonus on all your ranged attacks until the beginning of your next turn, but you take a -5 penalty to\nReflex Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.sniper_shot","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sniper_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"95020f2ce5ad0e88","name":"Quick Skill","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you can Take 10 when rushed on a single Skill Check for a Skill you are Trained in, unless the Skill description explicitly forbids it. Alternatively, you can Take 20 when using a Skill you are Trained in at half the normal time required.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"Taking 20 normally requires 20 times the amount of time needed by a regular Skill Check.","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":29,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, you can<br>Take 10<br>when rushed on a single<br>Skill Check<br>for a<br>Skill<br>you are<br>Trained<br>in, unless the<br>Skill<br>description explicitly forbids it. Alternatively, you can<br>Take 20<br>when using a<br>Skill<br>you are<br>Trained<br>in at half the normal time required.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> Taking 20<br>normally requires 20 times the amount of time needed by a regular<br>Skill Check<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Skill</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Skill-use economy metadata; not a static skill bonus.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"take10_take20_skill_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Skill-use economy metadata; not a static skill bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"quick_skill_metadata_phase13","skillUseRules":[{"type":"TAKE_10_WHEN_RUSHED","description":"You may Take 10 on skill checks even when rushed."},{"type":"TAKE_20_HALF_TIME","description":"You may Take 20 in half the normal time where Take 20 is allowed."}]},"shortSummary":"Take 10 on Skill Checks when rushed, Take 20 in half of the normal time.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Skill","effect":"Once per encounter, you can\nTake 10\nwhen rushed on a single\nSkill Check\nfor a\nSkill\nyou are\nTrained\nin, unless the\nSkill\ndescription explicitly forbids it. Alternatively, you can\nTake 20\nwhen using a\nSkill\nyou are\nTrained\nin at half the normal time required."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.quick_skill","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Quick_Skill","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"9567c9e2fe8416e6","name":"Disarming Charm","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Gain a bonus to Skill Checks on targets whose Attitude you have improved.","prerequisite":"Sullustan","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-sullustan"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Sullustan</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you successfully use the<br>Change Attitude<br>application of the<br>Persuasion<br>Skill to change a target&#x27;s<br>Attitude<br>, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to all<br>Deception<br>or<br>Persuasion<br>checks against that target for the next 24 hours.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disarming_Charm</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attitude_improved_social_skill_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Disarming Charm gives +2 circumstance to Deception or Persuasion checks against a target whose attitude you improved for 24 hours.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"skill_bonus_phase17","description":"Disarming Charm gives +2 circumstance to Deception or Persuasion checks against a target whose attitude you improved for 24 hours.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Disarming Charm gives +2 circumstance to Deception or Persuasion checks against a target whose attitude you improved for 24 hours.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"attitude_improved_social_skill_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"disarming-charm-deception","skillKey":"deception","value":2,"type":"circumstance","requiresContextFlags":["targetAttitudeImprovedByYou"],"description":"Disarming Charm: +2 Deception against a target whose attitude you improved within 24 hours."},{"id":"disarming-charm-persuasion","skillKey":"persuasion","value":2,"type":"circumstance","requiresContextFlags":["targetAttitudeImprovedByYou"],"description":"Disarming Charm: +2 Persuasion against a target whose attitude you improved within 24 hours."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain a bonus to Skill Checks on targets whose Attitude you have improved.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disarming_Charm","rawImport":{"name":"Disarming Charm","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Disarming_Charm","pageTitle":"Disarming_Charm","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\disarming_charm.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Sullustan","prerequisites":["Sullustan"],"effect":"Whenever you successfully use the\nChange Attitude\napplication of the\nPersuasion\nSkill to change a target's\nAttitude\n, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to all\nDeception\nor\nPersuasion\nchecks against that target for the next 24 hours.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Sullustan","indexBenefit":"Gain a bonus to Skill Checks on targets whose Attitude you have improved.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nLike many among your Species, you know how to blend in with galactic society, using your natural gregarious disposition to keep others off guard.\n\nPrerequisite:\nSullustan\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you successfully use the\nChange Attitude\napplication of the\nPersuasion\nSkill to change a target's\nAttitude\n, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to all\nDeception\nor\nPersuasion\nchecks against that target for the next 24 hours."},"prerequisitesText":"Sullustan","effect":"Whenever you successfully use the\nChange Attitude\napplication of the\nPersuasion\nSkill to change a target's\nAttitude\n, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to all\nDeception\nor\nPersuasion\nchecks against that target for the next 24 hours."},"effects":[{"_id":"3ce60f8f-157c-4b02-b329-cd961752b685","name":"Disarming Charm","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Disarming Charm","effectType":"skill_bonus","flagType":"Disarming Charm"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.disarming_charm"}}}
{"_id":"964f0781b3e3fc37","name":"Coordinated Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You are automatically successful when using the Aid Another action to aid an ally's attack, or suppress an enemy as long as the target is adjacent to you or within Point-Blank Range.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +2","special":"","normalText":"You must make an attack roll against a Reflex Defense of 10 to gain the benefits of the Aid Another action.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":85,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+2</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You are automatically successful when using the<br>Aid Another<br>action to aid an ally&#x27;s attack, or suppress an enemy as long as the target is adjacent to you or within Point-Blank<br>Range<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You must make an attack roll against a<br>Reflex Defense<br>of 10 to gain the benefits of the<br>Aid Another<br>action.</p>\n<h3>Additional Coordinated Attack Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy<br><br>You may use this Feat to aid an ally&#x27;s<br>Vehicle<br>attack. You can&#x27;t use the<br>Aid Another<br>action to suppress a<br>Vehicle<br>, but you can suppress an individual<br>Gunner<br>(such as the lead<br>Gunner<br>for a single<br>Weapon Battery<br>). You may use this Feat even if you are using the Aid Another action as a Sensor Operator using a<br>Use Computer<br>check or a<br>Commander<br>using a<br>Knowledge (Tactics)<br>check.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Attack</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":2}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Aid Another auto-success metadata; not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"teamwork_action_rule","applicationScope":"aid_another_context","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Aid Another auto-success metadata; not an attack bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"coordinated_attack_metadata_phase13","aidAnotherRules":[{"type":"AUTO_SUCCESS_ATTACK_AID_ANOTHER","range":"adjacent_or_point_blank","description":"Automatically succeed when using Aid Another to aid an ally's attack or suppress an enemy in the allowed range."}]},"shortSummary":"Automatic success with Aid Another action at Point-Blank Range.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +2","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Attack","effect":"You are automatically successful when using the\nAid Another\naction to aid an ally's attack, or suppress an enemy as long as the target is adjacent to you or within Point-Blank\nRange\n."},"effects":[{"_id":"64b1c39a-2f16-43e4-aa8b-0ee213caf7a2","name":"Coordinated Attack","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Coordinated Attack","effectType":"combat_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.coordinated_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"96666de28ba99b64","name":"Improved Damage Threshold","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You increase your Damage Threshold by 5 points.","prerequisite":"None","special":"You may take this Feat more than once. It's effects stack. Each time you take this Feat, increase your Damage Threshold by 5 points.","normalText":"A creature without this Feat has a Damage Threshold equal to its Fortitude Defense plus its size modifier (+5 for Large, +10 for Huge, +20 for Gargantuan, +50 for Colossal).","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["damage_threshold","defense","execution_mapped_phase8","feat","general","resource_damage_threshold","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You increase your<br>Damage Threshold<br>by 5 points.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> A creature without this Feat has a<br>Damage Threshold<br>equal to its<br>Fortitude Defense<br>plus its size modifier (+5 for Large, +10 for Huge, +20 for Gargantuan, +50 for Colossal).</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You may take this Feat more than once. It&#x27;s effects stack. Each time you take this Feat, increase your<br>Damage Threshold<br>by 5 points.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Damage_Threshold</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.damageThreshold","value":5,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Improved Damage Threshold is implemented by resourceRules.damageThreshold FLAT_BONUS; old modifier disabled to avoid double-counting.","mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Always-on +5 Damage Threshold.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive_resource","applicationScope":"damageThreshold_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Always-on +5 Damage Threshold; reflected in derived damage threshold.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase8-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata.","status":"damage_threshold_rule_phase8","description":"Improved Damage Threshold: +5 Damage Threshold. DerivedCalculator consumes this rule.","resourceRules":{"damageThreshold":[{"type":"FLAT_BONUS","value":5,"description":"Increase Damage Threshold by 5."}]}},"shortSummary":"Damage Threshold increases by 5 points.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Damage_Threshold","effect":"You increase your\nDamage Threshold\nby 5 points."},"effects":[{"name":"Improved Damage Threshold","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.damageThreshold","mode":2,"value":"5","priority":20}],"transfer":true,"disabled":true,"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToPassive":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"id":"swse.feat.improved_damage_threshold","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Damage_Threshold","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"9768963c7a36237d","name":"Fast Talk","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You may make a Persuasion check to feint in combat as a swift action instead of a standard action.","prerequisite":"Trained in Persuasion","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":["21dfe84d159a1b7f"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Feint action economy metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"deception_feint_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Feint action economy metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"fast_talk_metadata_phase13","skillUseRules":[{"type":"FEINT_AS_SWIFT_ACTION","skill":"deception","description":"Use Deception to feint in combat as a Swift Action instead of a Standard Action."}]},"shortSummary":"You may make a Persuasion check to feint in combat as a swift action instead of a standard action."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"97dbebe63aa6af79","name":"Martial Arts III","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Damage dealt by your Unarmed attacks increases by one die step. In addition, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to your Reflex Defense (Which stacks with the dodge bonuses granted by the Martial Arts I and Martial Arts II Feats).","prerequisite":"Martial Arts I, Martial Arts II, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"A situation that makes you lose your Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense (If any) also makes you lose any dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses.","normalText":"The amount of damage you deal with a successful Unarmed attack is based on your size: Small, 1d3; Medium, 1d4; Large, 1d6.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","general","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed","unarmed_damage_step","unarmed_damage_scaling"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Martial Arts I<br>,<br>Martial Arts II<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+6</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Damage dealt by your<br>Unarmed<br>attacks increases by one die step. In addition, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>(Which stacks with the dodge bonuses granted by the<br>Martial Arts I<br>and<br>Martial Arts II<br>Feats).</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> The amount of damage you deal with a successful<br>Unarmed<br>attack is based on your size: Small, 1d3; Medium, 1d4; Large, 1d6.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> A situation that makes you lose your<br>Dexterity<br>bonus to<br>Reflex Defense<br>(If any) also makes you lose any dodge bonuses. Also, dodge bonuses stack with each other, unlike most other types of bonuses.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_III</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":6}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","value":1,"type":"dodge","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Martial Arts III: +1 dodge bonus to Reflex Defense","mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor_and_unarmed_rule_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"include","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Always-on Reflex Defense dodge bonus; unarmed damage portion is handled by rule hooks."}],"rules":[{"type":"UNARMED_DAMAGE_STEP","params":{"steps":1},"description":"Martial Arts III: increase unarmed attack damage by one die step"}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor_and_unarmed_rule_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"include","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Always-on Reflex Defense dodge bonus; unarmed damage portion is handled by rule hooks.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Increases damage from Unarmed attacks by one die step; gain +1 bonus to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Martial Arts I, Martial Arts II, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_III","effect":"Damage dealt by your\nUnarmed\nattacks increases by one die step. In addition, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to your\nReflex Defense\n(Which stacks with the dodge bonuses granted by the\nMartial Arts I\nand\nMartial Arts II\nFeats)."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"id":"swse.feat.martial_arts_iii","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Martial_Arts_III","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"982b00394a73719e","name":"Bantha Herder","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you damage a Large or smaller creature with a ranged attack with a weapon you are proficient with, compare the result of your attack roll to the target's Will Defense. If your result equals or exceeds the target's Will Defense, you can move the target 1 square in any direction as a Free Action.\n\nIf your ranged attack deals damage to multiple eligible creatures, you can use this benefit against all of them. You can't move a target that's being Grabbed or Grappled, and you can't move a target into a solid object or into another creature's Fighting Space.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":20,"tags":["feat","general","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you damage a Large or smaller creature with a ranged attack with a weapon you are proficient with, compare the result of your attack roll to the target&#x27;s<br>Will Defense<br>. If your result equals or exceeds the target&#x27;s<br>Will Defense<br>, you can move the target 1 square in any direction as a<br>Free Action<br>.<br><br>If your ranged attack deals damage to multiple eligible creatures, you can use this benefit against all of them. You can&#x27;t move a target that&#x27;s being<br>Grabbed<br>or<br>Grappled<br>, and you can&#x27;t move a target into a solid object or into another creature&#x27;s<br>Fighting Space<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Bantha_Herder</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"ranged_hit_will_push_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Bantha Herder: ranged damage can push Large-or-smaller targets if the attack total also equals/exceeds Will Defense.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"ranged_push_rider_phase16","description":"Bantha Herder: ranged damage can push Large-or-smaller targets if the attack total also equals/exceeds Will Defense.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Bantha Herder: ranged damage can push Large-or-smaller targets if the attack total also equals/exceeds Will Defense.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"ranged_hit_will_push_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"banthaHerder","label":"Bantha Herder","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"CONDITIONAL_PUSH","distance":1,"requiresAttackTotalVsDefense":"will","maxTargetSize":"large","description":"If attack total equals/exceeds target Will Defense, move eligible target 1 square as a free action."}],"summary":"On damaging a Large-or-smaller target with a ranged attack, compare attack total to Will; if successful, push 1 square."}]},"shortSummary":"Move a target damaged by your attack.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Bantha_Herder","effect":"When you damage a Large or smaller creature with a ranged attack with a weapon you are proficient with, compare the result of your attack roll to the target's\nWill Defense\n. If your result equals or exceeds the target's\nWill Defense\n, you can move the target 1 square in any direction as a\nFree Action\n.\n\nIf your ranged attack deals damage to multiple eligible creatures, you can use this benefit against all of them. You can't move a target that's being\nGrabbed\nor\nGrappled\n, and you can't move a target into a solid object or into another creature's\nFighting Space\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.bantha_herder","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Bantha_Herder","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"987bdca14576cf2f","name":"Mind of Reason","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Use Wisdom instead of Intelligence for Intelligence-based Skill Checks.","prerequisite":"Cerean","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ability_intelligence","ability_wisdom","feat","racial","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-cerean"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Cerean</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You may use your<br>Wisdom<br>bonus instead of your<br>Intelligence<br>bonus for all<br>Intelligence<br>-based<br>Skill Checks<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mind_of_Reason</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"intelligence_skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Mind of Reason: use Wisdom instead of Intelligence for Intelligence-based skill checks when better.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"skill_ability_delta_phase16","description":"Mind of Reason: use Wisdom instead of Intelligence for Intelligence-based skill checks when better.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Mind of Reason: use Wisdom instead of Intelligence for Intelligence-based skill checks when better.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"intelligence_skill_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"mindOfReason.wisdomForIntSkills","skillKeys":["knowledge","knowledgeBureaucracy","knowledgeGalacticLore","knowledgeLifeSciences","knowledgePhysicalSciences","knowledgeSocialSciences","knowledgeTactics","knowledgeTechnology","mechanics","useComputer"],"valueFormula":"abilityDelta","fromAbility":"int","toAbility":"wis","useBetter":true,"type":"untyped","description":"Use Wisdom instead of Intelligence for Intelligence-based skill checks when it is better."}]},"shortSummary":"Use Wisdom instead of Intelligence for Intelligence-based Skill Checks.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mind_of_Reason","rawImport":{"name":"Mind of Reason","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mind_of_Reason","pageTitle":"Mind_of_Reason","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\mind_of_reason.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Cerean","prerequisites":["Cerean"],"effect":"You may use your\nWisdom\nbonus instead of your\nIntelligence\nbonus for all\nIntelligence\n-based\nSkill Checks\n.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Cerean","indexBenefit":"Use Wisdom instead of Intelligence for Intelligence -based Skill Checks .","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou have learnt to consider all sides of an issue carefully before making a decision, allowing you to reason out information that may not be readily apparent.\n\nPrerequisite:\nCerean\n\nEffect:\nYou may use your\nWisdom\nbonus instead of your\nIntelligence\nbonus for all\nIntelligence\n-based\nSkill Checks\n."},"prerequisitesText":"Cerean","effect":"You may use your\nWisdom\nbonus instead of your\nIntelligence\nbonus for all\nIntelligence\n-based\nSkill Checks\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.mind_of_reason"}}}
{"_id":"98d9c2c211a7a458","name":"Unswerving Resolve","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you are targeted by a Fear effect or Mind-Affecting effect that fails to affect you, you gain a temporary Force Point. If this Force Point is not used before the end of your next turn, it goes away. If you negate the contingent effect in any way, you do not gain the benefit of this Feat.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +2","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Jedi Academy Training Manual","page":31,"tags":["defense","feat","force_point_spend","general","resource_spend","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+2</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you are targeted by a Fear effect or<br>Mind-Affecting<br>effect that fails to affect you, you gain a temporary<br>Force Point<br>. If this<br>Force Point<br>is not used before the end of your next turn, it goes away. If you negate the contingent effect in any way, you do not gain the benefit of this Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unswerving_Resolve</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":2}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"resist_fear_mind_affecting_resource_context","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Unswerving Resolve: gain a temporary Force Point when a Fear or Mind-Affecting effect fails to affect you.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"temporary_force_point_metadata_phase16","description":"Unswerving Resolve: gain a temporary Force Point when a Fear or Mind-Affecting effect fails to affect you.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Unswerving Resolve: gain a temporary Force Point when a Fear or Mind-Affecting effect fails to affect you.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"resist_fear_mind_affecting_resource_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"resourceRules":{"forcePoints":[{"type":"TEMPORARY_FORCE_POINT_ON_RESISTED_EFFECT","triggers":["fear","mind-affecting"],"duration":"untilEndOfNextTurn","amount":1,"description":"Gain a temporary Force Point when a Fear or Mind-Affecting effect fails to affect you; it expires at end of next turn."}]}},"shortSummary":"Whenever you resist a Fear or Mind-Affecting effect, you gain a temporary Force Point.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +2","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unswerving_Resolve","effect":"Whenever you are targeted by a Fear effect or\nMind-Affecting\neffect that fails to affect you, you gain a temporary\nForce Point\n. If this\nForce Point\nis not used before the end of your next turn, it goes away. If you negate the contingent effect in any way, you do not gain the benefit of this Feat."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.384Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.unswerving_resolve","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Unswerving_Resolve","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"99b2114bb2fbc209","name":"Mighty Throw","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can add your Strength modifier (in addition to your Dexterity modifier) to your ranged attack bonus when using Thrown Weapons (including Grenades and grenadelike weapons). Also, you can increase the length of each Range category by a number of squares equal to your Strength modifier.","prerequisite":"Strength 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":35,"tags":["ability_strength","feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can add your<br>Strength<br>modifier (in addition to your<br>Dexterity<br>modifier) to your ranged attack bonus when using<br>Thrown Weapons<br>(including<br>Grenades<br>and grenadelike weapons). Also, you can increase the length of each<br>Range<br>category by a number of squares equal to your<br>Strength<br>modifier.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mighty_Throw</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"str","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Mighty Throw: Implemented as structured rule metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-ranged"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as structured rule metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"thrown_weapon_attack","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Mighty Throw: thrown-weapon attacks add Strength modifier; range extension recorded as rule metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 converts clear description-guided feats from scaffold modifiers into structured rule metadata.","status":"attack_ability_rule_phase9","description":"Mighty Throw: thrown-weapon attacks add Strength modifier; range extension recorded as rule metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_ABILITY_BONUS","weaponGroups":["thrown","grenade"],"ability":"str","description":"Add Strength modifier to ranged attacks with thrown weapons and grenades."},{"type":"RANGE_EXTENSION_NOTE","ability":"str","description":"Thrown weapon range categories increase by Strength modifier squares; display/adjudication note until range UI is fully automated."}]},"shortSummary":"Add Strength bonus to ranged attack rolls.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mighty_Throw","effect":"You can add your\nStrength\nmodifier (in addition to your\nDexterity\nmodifier) to your ranged attack bonus when using\nThrown Weapons\n(including\nGrenades\nand grenadelike weapons). Also, you can increase the length of each\nRange\ncategory by a number of squares equal to your\nStrength\nmodifier."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.385Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.mighty_throw","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mighty_Throw","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"99e4f98cbcbdd9e1","name":"Erratic Target","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can reduce your Speed by up to 2 squares to increase your Dodge bonus by 1 for each square of speed you give up, until the start of your next turn. You must move at least 2 squares to gain this benefit.","prerequisite":"Droid, Hovering or Flying Locomotion, Dexterity 13, Dodge","special":"To use this Feat you must be equipped with and using Hovering or Flying Locomotion.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":21,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>,<br>Hovering<br>or<br>Flying<br>Locomotion,<br>Dexterity<br>13,<br>Dodge</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can reduce your Speed by up to 2 squares to increase your<br>Dodge<br>bonus by 1 for each square of speed you give up, until the start of your next turn. You must move at least 2 squares to gain this benefit.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> To use this Feat you must be equipped with and using<br>Hovering<br>or<br>Flying<br>Locomotion.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Erratic_Target</em></p>\n<p><strong>Automation:</strong> Punted to GM/player handling. The player/GM should manually decide how much speed is sacrificed after moving and apply the matching Dodge bonus until the start of the next turn.</p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Feat: GM/player-managed; no automatic modifier is applied. Punted to GM/player handling. The player/GM should manually decide how much speed is sacrificed after moving and apply the matching Dodge bonus until the start of the next turn.","mechanicsMode":"gm_managed","applicationScope":"table_adjudicated","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Trade up to 2 squares of speed for Dodge bonus after moving; not an attack bonus."}],"mechanicsMode":"gm_managed","applicationScope":"table_adjudicated","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Punted to GM/player handling. The player/GM should manually decide how much speed is sacrificed after moving and apply the matching Dodge bonus until the start of the next turn.","predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"metadataPhase":"phase23-feat-cleanup","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","status":"gm_managed_phase23","description":"Punted to GM/player handling. The player/GM should manually decide how much speed is sacrificed after moving and apply the matching Dodge bonus until the start of the next turn.","gmManaged":true,"archived_riderRules":[{"type":"DEFENSE_OPTION","id":"erraticTarget","control":"slider","max":2,"requiresMovementSquares":2,"defense":"reflex","valueFormula":"selectedValue","duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn","description":"Reduce speed by up to 2 squares to increase Dodge bonus by same amount."}]},"shortSummary":"Reduce Speed by up to 2 squares to increase dodge bonus to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Hovering or Flying Locomotion, Dexterity 13, Dodge","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Erratic_Target","effect":"You can reduce your Speed by up to 2 squares to increase your\nDodge\nbonus by 1 for each square of speed you give up, until the start of your next turn. You must move at least 2 squares to gain this benefit."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.385Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.erratic_target","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Erratic_Target","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"9a89576b3cc1347e","name":"Great Fortitude","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus to your Fortitude Defense.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.fortitude","type":"untyped","value":2,"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Migrated from AE system.defenses.fortitude.bonus","mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor","staticSheetPolicy":"include","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Always-on bonus to Fortitude Defense."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor","staticSheetPolicy":"include","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Always-on bonus to Fortitude Defense.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"You gain a +2 bonus to your Fortitude Defense."},"effects":[{"name":"Great Fortitude","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.defenses.fortitude.bonus","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":20}],"disabled":true,"duration":{},"transfer":true,"flags":{"swse":{"type":"defense-bonus","defense":"fortitude","migratedToPassive":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"9ad13542c8370aef","name":"Combat Trickery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can spend two successive Swift Actions on the same turn to make a Deception check against a target's Will Defense. If the check is successful, the target is Flat-Footed against your next attack made before the end of your next turn. Additionally, you can spend a Force Point to extend your target's penalties until the end of encounter.","prerequisite":"Trained in Deception","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":19,"tags":["action_economy","feat","general","skill_deception","skill_synergy","swift_action"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Deception</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can spend two successive<br>Swift Actions<br>on the same turn to make a<br>Deception<br>check against a target&#x27;s<br>Will Defense<br>. If the check is successful, the target is<br>Flat-Footed<br>against your next attack made before the end of your next turn. Additionally, you can spend a<br>Force Point<br>to extend your target&#x27;s penalties until the end of encounter.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Trickery</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Deception combat trick metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"deception_combat_trick_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Deception combat trick metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"combat_trickery_metadata_phase13","skillUseRules":[{"type":"TWO_SWIFTS_MAKE_TARGET_FLAT_FOOTED","skill":"deception","description":"Spend two Swift Actions and make a Deception check to make an enemy flat-footed."}]},"shortSummary":"Spend two Swift Actions to make Deception check to make enemy Flat-Footed.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Deception","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Trickery","effect":"You can spend two successive\nSwift Actions\non the same turn to make a\nDeception\ncheck against a target's\nWill Defense\n. If the check is successful, the target is\nFlat-Footed\nagainst your next attack made before the end of your next turn. Additionally, you can spend a\nForce Point\nto extend your target's penalties until the end of encounter."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.385Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.combat_trickery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Combat_Trickery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"9af3ba38a2c671b8","name":"Feat of Strength","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter as a Full-Round Action, you can Take 20 on a Strength check or Strength -based Skill Check (You must be Trained in that Skill), even if distracted or threatened.","prerequisite":"Strength 15","special":"After using this Feat for the first time in a given encounter, make a DC 15 Endurance check (As a Free Action). If the check succeeds, you can use this Feat once more during the same encounter.","normalText":"You may not Take 20 when distracted or threatened, or in a single round.","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":18,"tags":["ability_strength","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>15</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter as a<br>Full-Round Action<br>, you can<br>Take 20<br>on a<br>Strength<br>check or<br>Strength<br>-based<br>Skill Check<br>(You must be<br>Trained<br>in that<br>Skill<br>), even if distracted or threatened.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You may not<br>Take 20<br>when distracted or threatened, or in a single round.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> After using this Feat for the first time in a given encounter, make a DC 15<br>Endurance<br>check (As a<br>Free Action<br>). If the check succeeds, you can use this Feat once more during the same encounter.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Feat_of_Strength</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"str","min":15}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"strength_check_skill_use_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Feat of Strength: once per encounter Take 10 or Take 20 on one Strength check or Strength-related skill check.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_resource_metadata_phase16","description":"Feat of Strength: once per encounter Take 10 or Take 20 on one Strength check or Strength-related skill check.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Feat of Strength: once per encounter Take 10 or Take 20 on one Strength check or Strength-related skill check.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"strength_check_skill_use_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"TAKE_10_OR_20_ON_STRENGTH_CHECK","oncePer":"encounter","skills":["climb","jump","swim"],"ability":"str","description":"Once per encounter, Take 10 or Take 20 on a Strength check or Strength-related skill check where allowed by the feat."}]},"shortSummary":"Take 10 or Take 20 on one Strength check or related Skill Check per encounter.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 15","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Feat_of_Strength","effect":"Once per encounter as a\nFull-Round Action\n, you can\nTake 20\non a\nStrength\ncheck or\nStrength\n-based\nSkill Check\n(You must be\nTrained\nin that\nSkill\n), even if distracted or threatened."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.385Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.feat_of_strength","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Feat_of_Strength","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"9b7b869a86f39190","name":"Force Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You add to your Force Power Suite a number of Force Powers equal to 1 + your Wisdom modifier (Minimum 1). You can add the same Force Power more than once.","prerequisite":"Force Sensitivity, Trained in Use the Force.","special":"You can take this Feat more than once. Each time you take this Feat, you add to your Force Power Suite a number of new Force Powers equal to 1 + your Wisdom modifier.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":94,"tags":["ability_wisdom","build_enabler","feat","force","force_capacity","force_powers","force_training","forecast_value","new_option","choice_required","grant_choice","deferred_choice","choice_source_grant_pool"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"forcePowerGrants":1,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Sensitivity<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Use the Force<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You add to your<br>Force Power Suite<br>a number of<br>Force Powers<br>equal to 1 + your<br>Wisdom<br>modifier (Minimum 1). You can add the same<br>Force Power<br>more than once.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can take this Feat more than once. Each time you take this Feat, you add to your<br>Force Power Suite<br>a number of new<br>Force Powers<br>equal to 1 + your<br>Wisdom<br>modifier.</p>\n<h3>Additional Force Training Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Improved Disarm<br>):<br>When you use the<br>Force Disarm<br>Force Power, you gain the +5 bonus from<br>Improved Disarm<br>on your<br>Use the Force<br>check as though you were making an attack roll.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Training</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"usetheforce"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Force Training","mechanicsMode":"grant_unlock","applicationScope":"progression_entitlement","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Creates Force power picks equal to 1 + the configured Force Training ability modifier through progression entitlement logic."}],"mechanicsMode":"grant_unlock","applicationScope":"progression_entitlement","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Creates Force power picks equal to 1 + the configured Force Training ability modifier through progression entitlement logic.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"grant_entitlement","required":true,"status":"deferred_grant_step_not_immediate_choice","choiceKind":"force_power_pick","storagePath":"flags.swse.pendingEntitlements.force_power_pick","choiceSource":"grantPool","grantType":"force_power","grantRegistry":"forcePower","countFormula":"max(1, 1 + configuredForceTrainingAbilityModifier)","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.force_power_pick","minimum":1,"dynamic":true,"repeatable":true},"shortSummary":"Learn a number of Force Powers equal to 1 + your Wisdom modifier (minimum 1).","prerequisitesText":"Force Sensitivity, Trained in Use the Force.","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Training","effect":"You add to your\nForce Power Suite\na number of\nForce Powers\nequal to 1 + your\nWisdom\nmodifier (Minimum 1). You can add the same\nForce Power\nmore than once."},"effects":[{"_id":"d1c60a9b-78e6-4601-85a4-320794fa5a91","name":"Force Training","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Force Training","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Force Training"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.385Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.force_training","requiresImmediateChoice":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"9c904590c02fb30a","name":"Targeted Area","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make a successful Area Attack with a weapon with which you are proficient, select a target hit by the attack. That target takes an additional 5 points of damage from the attack, before applying the effect of the Evasion Talent.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +5","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","multi_target"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+5</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make a successful<br>Area Attack<br>with a weapon with which you are proficient, select a target hit by the attack. That target takes an additional 5 points of damage from the attack, before applying the effect of the<br>Evasion<br>Talent.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Targeted_Area</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Area-attack only damage option.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Area-attack only damage option.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"targetedArea","label":"Targeted Area","control":"toggle","requiresAreaAttack":true,"damageModifier":5,"summary":"On a successful area attack, deal +5 damage to one target in the area."}],"implementationStatus":"targetedArea_attack_option_phase13"},"shortSummary":"Deal an additional 5 points of damage against one target within a successful Area Attack.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +5","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Targeted_Area","effect":"When you make a successful\nArea Attack\nwith a weapon with which you are proficient, select a target hit by the attack. That target takes an additional 5 points of damage from the attack, before applying the effect of the\nEvasion\nTalent."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.385Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.targeted_area","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Targeted_Area","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"9c9e98a70538855c","name":"Slammer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Standard Action, you slam two of your Appendages together from either side of an enemy, crushing your target between them. Make a melee attack. If the attack is successful, you deal Unarmed damage with double your Strength bonus. If you also exceed the target's Damage Threshold, it has a Persistent Condition that can only be removed with 8 hours of rest or a DC 20 Treat Injury check.","prerequisite":"Droid, Small size or larger, 2+ Appendages, Strength 13","special":"If you also have the Crush Feat, increase your Unarmed damage by 1 die when using Slammer.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":25,"tags":["ability_strength","feat","general","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>, Small size or larger, 2+<br>Appendages<br>,<br>Strength<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Standard Action<br>, you slam two of your<br>Appendages<br>together from either side of an enemy, crushing your target between them. Make a melee attack. If the attack is successful, you deal<br>Unarmed<br>damage with double your<br>Strength<br>bonus. If you also exceed the target&#x27;s<br>Damage Threshold<br>, it has a<br>Persistent Condition<br>that can only be removed with 8 hours of rest or a DC 20<br>Treat Injury<br>check.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you also have the<br>Crush<br>Feat, increase your<br>Unarmed<br>damage by 1 die when using Slammer.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Slammer</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Slammer: Converted from false melee attack bonus to a Slammer unarmed damage/rider option.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee"],"conditionSummary":"Converted from false melee attack bonus to a Slammer unarmed damage/rider option."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"slammer","label":"Slammer","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","requiresUnarmed":true,"damageAbilityBonus":{"ability":"str","multiplier":1,"minimum":0},"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"PERSISTENT_CONDITION_IF_EXCEEDS_DT","description":"If the Slammer attack also exceeds Damage Threshold, the target gains a persistent condition removable by 8 hours rest or DC 20 Treat Injury."}],"summary":"Standard-action unarmed slam: add Strength bonus again to damage; persistent condition if damage exceeds threshold."}],"status":"slammer_attack_option_phase12","description":"Converted from false melee attack bonus to a Slammer unarmed damage/rider option."},"shortSummary":"Double Strength bonus to damage rolls on this special melee attack.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Small size or larger, 2+ Appendages, Strength 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Slammer","effect":"As a\nStandard Action\n, you slam two of your\nAppendages\ntogether from either side of an enemy, crushing your target between them. Make a melee attack. If the attack is successful, you deal\nUnarmed\ndamage with double your\nStrength\nbonus. If you also exceed the target's\nDamage Threshold\n, it has a\nPersistent Condition\nthat can only be removed with 8 hours of rest or a DC 20\nTreat Injury\ncheck."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.385Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.slammer","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Slammer","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"9d70c309eb95da5e","name":"Inborn Resilience","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Reduce one Defense bonus but increase another.","prerequisite":"Zabrak","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["defense","feat","racial","species","species_opportunity","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-zabrak"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Zabrak</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can reduce your<br>Species<br>bonus to any one<br>Defense<br>to +0 and increase your<br>Species<br>bonus to another<br>Defense<br>to +2. Once you change your<br>Species<br>bonuses in this way, they cannot be changed back.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Inborn_Resilience</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"targetFromSelectedChoice":{"prefix":"defense.","property":"decrease"},"type":"untyped","value":-1,"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Inborn Resilience: reduce selected species Defense bonus by 1","mechanicsMode":"passive_choice_required","applicationScope":"selected_defense_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"selected_choice_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose one species Defense bonus to reduce by 1 and another to increase by 1.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 binds prompt-on-selection metadata to static or contextual mechanics where safe."},{"targetFromSelectedChoice":{"prefix":"defense.","property":"increase"},"type":"untyped","value":1,"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Inborn Resilience: increase selected species Defense bonus by 1","mechanicsMode":"passive_choice_required","applicationScope":"selected_defense_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"selected_choice_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"