{"_id":"a16df0d4edf3e7bf","name":"Heavy Hitter","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When making an attack roll using a Weapon Emplacement or a Weapon System, you add an additional 1 point of damage for every 5 points you roll above the target's Reflex Defense. If you exceed the target's Damage Threshold, then on its next turn the target cannot attack and its speed is reduced by 2 squares (1 square Starship Scale).","prerequisite":"Weapon Focus (Heavy Weapons)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":22,"tags":["damage_threshold","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Focus (Heavy Weapons)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When making an attack roll using a<br>Weapon Emplacement<br>or a<br>Weapon System<br>, you add an additional 1 point of damage for every 5 points you roll above the target&#x27;s<br>Reflex Defense<br>. If you exceed the target&#x27;s<br>Damage Threshold<br>, then on its next turn the target cannot attack and its speed is reduced by 2 squares (1 square<br>Starship Scale<br>).</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Heavy_Hitter</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Heavy Hitter: Implemented as CombatOptionResolver/rider metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as CombatOptionResolver/rider metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Heavy Hitter now has explicit roll-context/rider metadata from its description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"heavyHitter","label":"Heavy Hitter","control":"passive","requiresWeaponGroups":["weapon emplacement","weapon system","vehicle weapon"],"damageModifierFormula":"context.attackMarginDividedBy5","targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"SUPPRESS_TARGET_ATTACK_AND_SPEED","target":"target","requiresExceedsDamageThreshold":true,"speedPenaltySquares":2,"starshipScaleSpeedPenaltySquares":1,"duration":"targetNextTurn","description":"If damage exceeds threshold, target cannot attack and speed is reduced next turn."}],"summary":"Weapon emplacement/system attacks add damage from attack margin; threshold hits suppress target actions/speed."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Heavy Hitter now has explicit roll-context/rider metadata from its description."},"shortSummary":"Add +1 point of damage for every 5 points rolled above the target's Reflex Defense, plus additional benefits when you exceed the target's Damage Threshold.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Focus (Heavy Weapons)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Heavy_Hitter","effect":"When making an attack roll using a\nWeapon Emplacement\nor a\nWeapon System\n, you add an additional 1 point of damage for every 5 points you roll above the target's\nReflex Defense\n. If you exceed the target's\nDamage Threshold\n, then on its next turn the target cannot attack and its speed is reduced by 2 squares (1 square\nStarship Scale\n)."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.heavy_hitter","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Heavy_Hitter","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"a2708e8daf121947","name":"Rapport","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Aid Another Action, you grant an additional +2 insight bonus on Skill Checks and attack rolls to the character you are assisting. This bonus does not stack with any bonus provided by the Noble's Coordinate Talent.","prerequisite":"Wisdom 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":36,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Wisdom<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using the<br>Aid Another<br>Action, you grant an additional +2 insight bonus on<br>Skill Checks<br>and attack rolls to the character you are assisting. This bonus does not stack with any bonus provided by the Noble&#x27;s<br>Coordinate<br>Talent.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapport</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Rapport: No self attack bonus; represented as Aid Another support metadata.","mechanicsMode":"manual","applicationScope":"metadata_only","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"No self attack bonus; represented as Aid Another support metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"aid_another_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Aid Another grants an additional +2 insight bonus to the assisted ally.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase11-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 11 uses refreshed descriptions to replace manual/scaffold metadata with executable defense/skill/attack-option rules or explicit safe metadata for future hooks.","status":"aid_another_rule_phase11","description":"Aid Another grants an additional +2 insight bonus to the assisted ally.","aidAnotherRules":[{"type":"ADDITIONAL_AID_ANOTHER_BONUS","value":2,"bonusType":"insight","appliesTo":["attack","skill"],"doesNotStackWith":["Coordinate"],"description":"When using Aid Another, grant an additional +2 insight bonus to the ally’s attack roll or skill check."}]},"shortSummary":"Grant an additional +2 bonus when using the Aid Another action.","prerequisitesText":"Wisdom 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapport","effect":"When using the\nAid Another\nAction, you grant an additional +2 insight bonus on\nSkill Checks\nand attack rolls to the character you are assisting. This bonus does not stack with any bonus provided by the Noble's\nCoordinate\nTalent."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.rapport","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapport","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"a51721a36b699c7c","name":"Fight Through Pain","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can use your Will Defense instead of your Fortitude Defense when determining your Damage Threshold.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":22,"tags":["damage_threshold","execution_mapped_phase8","feat","general","resource_damage_threshold"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can use your<br>Will Defense<br>instead of your<br>Fortitude Defense<br>when determining your<br>Damage Threshold<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fight_Through_Pain</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Fight Through Pain affects Damage Threshold calculation, not attack rolls.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.will"],"conditionSummary":"Fight Through Pain affects Damage Threshold calculation, not attack rolls."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive_resource","applicationScope":"damageThreshold_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Derived damage threshold uses the better of Fortitude or Will as the base defense.","predicateRequirements":["defense.will"],"metadataPhase":"phase8-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics.","status":"damage_threshold_rule_phase8","description":"Fight Through Pain: use Will Defense instead of Fortitude Defense to determine Damage Threshold when better.","resourceRules":{"damageThreshold":[{"type":"USE_WILL_AS_BASE","useBest":true,"description":"Use Will Defense to determine Damage Threshold when it is better than Fortitude Defense."}]}},"shortSummary":"Use your Will Defense to determine your Damage Threshold.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fight_Through_Pain","effect":"You can use your\nWill Defense\ninstead of your\nFortitude Defense\nwhen determining your\nDamage Threshold\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.fight_through_pain","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fight_Through_Pain","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"a65c4d3ad1c3202f","name":"Resilient Strength","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can use either your Strength modifier or your Constitution modifier to determine your Fortitude Defense.","prerequisite":"Strength 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["ability_constitution","ability_strength","defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can use either your<br>Strength<br>modifier or your<br>Constitution<br>modifier to determine your<br>Fortitude Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resilient_Strength</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Resilient Strength: Implemented by DefenseCalculator as best-of STR/CON Fortitude ability selection; no numeric +2 modifier.","mechanicsMode":"manual","applicationScope":"metadata_only","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Implemented by DefenseCalculator as best-of STR/CON Fortitude ability selection; no numeric +2 modifier."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor","staticSheetPolicy":"include","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Use the better of Strength or Constitution modifier for Fortitude Defense.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase11-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 11 uses refreshed descriptions to replace manual/scaffold metadata with executable defense/skill/attack-option rules or explicit safe metadata for future hooks.","status":"static_defense_ability_phase11","description":"Use the better of Strength or Constitution modifier for Fortitude Defense.","defenseAbilityRules":[{"type":"USE_BETTER_ABILITY","defense":"fortitude","abilities":["con","str"],"description":"Use either Strength or Constitution modifier, whichever is better, to determine Fortitude Defense."}]},"shortSummary":"Use Strength or Constitution to determine Fortitude Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resilient_Strength","effect":"You can use either your\nStrength\nmodifier or your\nConstitution\nmodifier to determine your\nFortitude Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.fortitude","turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.resilient_strength","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Resilient_Strength","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"a6890bb21adad47e","name":"Expert Briber","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using the Haggle or Bribery applications of the Persuasion skill, you reduce the DC to reduce the price of the item haggled over by 10.","prerequisite":"Charisma 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":18,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Charisma<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using the<br>Haggle<br>or<br>Bribery<br>applications of the<br>Persuasion<br>skill, you reduce the DC to reduce the price of the item haggled over by 10.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Expert_Briber</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Expert Briber: No static Persuasion bonus; represented as DC adjustment metadata.","mechanicsMode":"manual","applicationScope":"metadata_only","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"No static Persuasion bonus; represented as DC adjustment metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"persuasion_haggle_bribery_context","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Reduce Haggle/Bribery DCs by 10 where the skill use is applicable.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase11-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 11 uses refreshed descriptions to replace manual/scaffold metadata with executable defense/skill/attack-option rules or explicit safe metadata for future hooks.","status":"skill_use_rule_phase11","description":"Reduce Haggle/Bribery DCs by 10 where the skill use is applicable.","skillUseRules":[{"type":"SKILL_USE_DC_ADJUSTMENT","skillKey":"persuasion","applications":["Haggle","Bribery"],"dcModifier":-10,"description":"Reduce the DC for Haggle or Bribery applications by 10."}]},"shortSummary":"Reduce the time and cost of Bribery attempts.","prerequisitesText":"Charisma 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Expert_Briber","effect":"When using the\nHaggle\nor\nBribery\napplications of the\nPersuasion\nskill, you reduce the DC to reduce the price of the item haggled over by 10."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.expert_briber","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Expert_Briber","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"a717435c8094e7fb","name":"Superior Tech","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Select one of the following: Armor, Weapons, Droids, Vehicles, or Devices. You can install advanced Traits when modifying the selected type of equipment. These Traits replace the Traits granted by the Tech Specialist Feat. You may still use the Tech Specialist options if you so choose.\n\nYou must pay one-fifth the cost of the Device, Armor, Weapon, Droid, or vehicle you wish to modify or 2,000 credits, whichever is more, before beginning the modification. This fee replaces the normal cost of modification from the Tech Specialist Feat. Completing the modification requires 1 day per 1,000 credits of the modification's cost. At the end of this time, make a DC 30 Mechanics check; you cannot Take 10 or Take 20 on this check. If the check succeeds, the modification is completed successfully, and the object gains the desired Trait. If the check fails, you lose all credits spent on making the modification, and the object does not gain the desired Trait. However, you can start over from scratch if you wish.\n\nOnly characters with the Tech Specialist Feat can assist you, reducing proportionately the time needed to complete the modification. At the end of the modification process, they can make a Mechanics check to aid your check.\n\nThe market value of a modified item is equal to the base cost of the item plus double the cost of the modifications made to it (not including credits wasted on failed modification attempts).","prerequisite":"Intelligence 17, Tech Specialist, 9th Character Level","special":"You may select this Feat multiple times. Each time you do so, you must choose a different set of Traits (Armor, Devices, Droids, Vehicles, or Weapons).\n\nARMOR TRAIT | BENEFIT\nMobile Armor | Increases Speed by 1 square (Medium Armor and Heavy Armor only).\nReinforced Armor | Grants Damage Reduction 2.\nSuperior Agile Armor | The Armor's maximum Dexterity bonus increases by +2.\nSuperior Fortifying Armor | The Armor's Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense increases by +2.\nSuperior Helmet Package | Grants wearer a +5 Equipment bonus on Perception checks.\nSuperior Protective Armor | The Armor's Armor bonus to Reflex Defense increases by +2.\nDEVICE TRAIT | BENEFIT\nSuperior Strength | Increase the Device's Strength score by +4.\nSuperior Durability | The Device's Damage Reduction increases by +2, and increase its Hit Points by 150%.\nReinforced Device | The Device's Break DC increases by +5.\nSuperior Mastercraft | Skill Checks made using the device gain a +2 Equipment bonus, or its existing Equipment bonus increases by +2.\nDROID TRAIT | BENEFIT\nIon Dispersal Coating | Droid gains Damage Reduction 5 against Ion damage.\nSuperior Ability | Increase Droids Dexterity, Intelligence, or Strength score by +4.\nVEHICLE TRAIT | BENEFIT\nSuperior Ability | Increase the Vehicle's Dexterity by +4 or its Strength by +2.\nSuperior Sensors | Increase the Vehicle's Perception modifier by +2.\nSuperior Shields | Increase the Vehicle's Shield Rating by +10.\nSuperior Speed | Increase the Vehicle's Speed by one-third of its base Speed (minimum 1 square).\nWEAPON TRAIT | BENEFIT\nSuperior Accuracy | The Weapon gains a +2 Equipment bonus on attack rolls.\nSuperior Capacity | The Weapon's Power Pack provides double the number of shots.\nSuperior Damage | The Weapon deals +5 damage with a successful hit. If the weapon has a damage multiplier apply the extra damage before applying the multiplier.\nSuperior Range | The Weapon's Ranges all increase by 50%.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":29,"tags":["feat","general","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence<br>17,<br>Tech Specialist<br>, 9th Character Level</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Select one of the following: Armor, Weapons, Droids, Vehicles, or Devices. You can install advanced Traits when modifying the selected type of equipment. These Traits replace the Traits granted by the<br>Tech Specialist<br>Feat. You may still use the<br>Tech Specialist<br>options if you so choose.<br><br>You must pay one-fifth the cost of the Device, Armor, Weapon, Droid, or vehicle you wish to modify or 2,000 credits, whichever is more, before beginning the modification. This fee replaces the normal cost of modification from the<br>Tech Specialist<br>Feat. Completing the modification requires 1 day per 1,000 credits of the modification&#x27;s cost. At the end of this time, make a DC 30<br>Mechanics<br>check; you cannot<br>Take 10<br>or<br>Take 20<br>on this check. If the check succeeds, the modification is completed successfully, and the object gains the desired Trait. If the check fails, you lose all credits spent on making the modification, and the object does not gain the desired Trait. However, you can start over from scratch if you wish.<br><br>Only characters with the<br>Tech Specialist<br>Feat can assist you, reducing proportionately the time needed to complete the modification. At the end of the modification process, they can make a<br>Mechanics<br>check to aid your check.<br><br>The market value of a modified item is equal to the base cost of the item plus double the cost of the modifications made to it (not including credits wasted on failed modification attempts).</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You may select this Feat multiple times. Each time you do so, you must choose a different set of Traits (Armor, Devices, Droids, Vehicles, or Weapons).<br><br>ARMOR TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Mobile Armor | Increases Speed by 1 square ( Medium Armor and Heavy Armor only).<br>Reinforced Armor | Grants Damage Reduction 2.<br>Superior Agile Armor | The Armor&#x27;s maximum Dexterity bonus increases by +2.<br>Superior Fortifying Armor | The Armor&#x27;s Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense increases by +2.<br>Superior Helmet Package | Grants wearer a +5 Equipment bonus on Perception checks.<br>Superior Protective Armor | The Armor&#x27;s Armor bonus to Reflex Defense increases by +2.<br>DEVICE TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Superior Strength | Increase the Device&#x27;s Strength score by +4.<br>Superior Durability | The Device&#x27;s Damage Reduction increases by +2, and increase its Hit Points by 150%.<br>Reinforced Device | The Device&#x27;s Break DC increases by +5.<br>Superior Mastercraft | Skill Checks made using the device gain a +2 Equipment bonus, or its existing Equipment bonus increases by +2.<br>DROID TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Ion Dispersal Coating | Droid gains Damage Reduction 5 against Ion damage.<br>Superior Ability | Increase Droids Dexterity , Intelligence , or Strength score by +4.<br>VEHICLE TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Superior Ability | Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Dexterity by +4 or its Strength by +2.<br>Superior Sensors | Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Perception modifier by +2.<br>Superior Shields | Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Shield Rating by +10.<br>Superior Speed | Increase the Vehicle&#x27;s Speed by one-third of its base Speed (minimum 1 square).<br>WEAPON TRAIT | BENEFIT<br>Superior Accuracy | The Weapon gains a +2 Equipment bonus on attack rolls.<br>Superior Capacity | The Weapon&#x27;s Power Pack provides double the number of shots.<br>Superior Damage | The Weapon deals +5 damage with a successful hit. If the weapon has a damage multiplier apply the extra damage before applying the multiplier.<br>Superior Range | The Weapon&#x27;s Ranges all increase by 50%.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Superior_Tech</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"int","min":17}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Superior Tech","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Choose Armor, Weapons, Droids, Vehicles, or Devices.","metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","disabledReason":"Phase 6: choice captured now; execution waits for roll/action context wiring."}],"mechanicsMode":"customization_context_choice_required","applicationScope":"workbench_garage_shipyard_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose Armor, Weapons, Droids, Vehicles, or Devices.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","implementationStatus":"phase21_contextual_customization_ui","description":"Superior Tech advanced traits are available through the Tech Specialist modification UI when the actor has the feat and the selected Superior Tech category matches the item or asset being modified.","customizationCapabilities":[{"type":"SUPERIOR_TECH_MODIFICATION","contexts":["workbench","lightsaber","garage","shipyard"],"requiresSelectedCategory":true,"dc":30,"usesTransactionEngine":true}]},"shortSummary":"Install superior equipment upgrades.","prerequisitesText":"Intelligence 17, Tech Specialist, 9th Character Level","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Superior_Tech","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"tech_category","repeatable":true,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.superior_tech","choiceSource":"fixed","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.tech_category"},"effect":"Select one of the following: Armor, Weapons, Droids, Vehicles, or Devices. You can install advanced Traits when modifying the selected type of equipment. These Traits replace the Traits granted by the\nTech Specialist\nFeat. You may still use the\nTech Specialist\noptions if you so choose.\n\nYou must pay one-fifth the cost of the Device, Armor, Weapon, Droid, or vehicle you wish to modify or 2,000 credits, whichever is more, before beginning the modification. This fee replaces the normal cost of modification from the\nTech Specialist\nFeat. Completing the modification requires 1 day per 1,000 credits of the modification's cost. At the end of this time, make a DC 30\nMechanics\ncheck; you cannot\nTake 10\nor\nTake 20\non this check. If the check succeeds, the modification is completed successfully, and the object gains the desired Trait. If the check fails, you lose all credits spent on making the modification, and the object does not gain the desired Trait. However, you can start over from scratch if you wish.\n\nOnly characters with the\nTech Specialist\nFeat can assist you, reducing proportionately the time needed to complete the modification. At the end of the modification process, they can make a\nMechanics\ncheck to aid your check.\n\nThe market value of a modified item is equal to the base cost of the item plus double the cost of the modifications made to it (not including credits wasted on failed modification attempts)."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.superior_tech","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Superior_Tech","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"a75d5d6b3ce5bc6f","name":"Logic Upgrade: Tactician","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Grant a +5 bonus to attack with a successful Aid Another attempt.","prerequisite":"Droid, Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","knowledge","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{"value":"Grant a +5 bonus to attack with a successful Aid Another attempt."},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Logic Upgrade: Tactician: No self attack bonus; represented as Aid Another support metadata.","mechanicsMode":"manual","applicationScope":"metadata_only","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"No self attack bonus; represented as Aid Another support metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"aid_another_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"A successful Aid Another attempt can grant +5 to an ally’s attack.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase11-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 11 uses refreshed descriptions to replace manual/scaffold metadata with executable defense/skill/attack-option rules or explicit safe metadata for future hooks.","status":"aid_another_rule_phase11","description":"A successful Aid Another attempt can grant +5 to an ally’s attack.","aidAnotherRules":[{"type":"AID_ANOTHER_ATTACK_BONUS_REPLACEMENT","value":5,"appliesTo":["attack"],"description":"When your Aid Another attempt succeeds, grant a +5 bonus to the ally’s attack roll."}]},"shortSummary":"Grant a +5 bonus to attack with a successful Aid Another attempt."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.logic_upgrade_tactician"}}}
{"_id":"a8511e47656ef4dd","name":"Trip","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you succeed on a Grappling attack and your opponent fails the opposed Grapple check, it falls Prone in its space and is no longer considered Grappled. A Prone opponent takes a -5 penalty on melee attack rolls. Melee attacks made against a Prone target gain a +5 bonus, while ranged attack made against a prone target take a -5 penalty.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"You cannot use the Pin and Trip Feats in the same round.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","knock_prone","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you succeed on a<br>Grappling<br>attack and your opponent fails the opposed<br>Grapple<br>check, it falls<br>Prone<br>in its space and is no longer considered<br>Grappled<br>. A<br>Prone<br>opponent takes a -5 penalty on melee attack rolls. Melee attacks made against a<br>Prone<br>target gain a +5 bonus, while ranged attack made against a prone target take a -5 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You cannot use the<br>Pin<br>and Trip Feats in the same round.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trip</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rider_effect_phase7","description":"Trip: modeled as a rider/action rule, not a numeric modifier.","rules":[{"type":"GRAPPLE_RIDER","trigger":"onSuccessfulGrapple","effect":"prone","endsGrapple":true}],"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Trip: numeric scaffold disabled by Phase 7 (description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus)","mechanicsMode":"metadata_note","applicationScope":"not_a_numeric_modifier","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus","metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"grapple_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Successful grapple may knock the opponent prone; this is not an attack modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Trip an opponent that you've Grappled, knocking it Prone.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trip","effect":"If you succeed on a\nGrappling\nattack and your opponent fails the opposed\nGrapple\ncheck, it falls\nProne\nin its space and is no longer considered\nGrappled\n. A\nProne\nopponent takes a -5 penalty on melee attack rolls. Melee attacks made against a\nProne\ntarget gain a +5 bonus, while ranged attack made against a prone target take a -5 penalty."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["target.is-prone"],"id":"swse.feat.trip","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trip","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"a945e2f5ffb5a7ed","name":"Charging Fire","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you Charge, you may make a ranged attack instead of a melee attack at the end of your movement. Unlike a normal Charge, your momentum does not help you overcome your target, so you gain no bonus on your attack roll. As with a normal Charge, you still take a -2 penalty to your Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +4","special":"","normalText":"You can make a single melee attack with a +2 bonus on your attack roll at the end of a Charge.","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["charge","feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+4</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you<br>Charge<br>, you may make a ranged attack instead of a melee attack at the end of your movement. Unlike a normal<br>Charge<br>, your momentum does not help you overcome your target, so you gain no bonus on your attack roll. As with a normal<br>Charge<br>, you still take a -2 penalty to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You can make a single melee attack with a +2 bonus on your attack roll at the end of a<br>Charge<br>.</p>\n<h3>Additional Charging Fire Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Dodge<br>):<br>You reduce your penalty to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>against all opponents to -1 when making a ranged attack at the end of a<br>Charge<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Charging_Fire</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":4}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7_refined","description":"Charging Fire: exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied as a passive sheet modifier.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"chargingFire","label":"Charging Fire","summary":"Make a ranged attack at the end of a charge; do not receive the normal charge attack bonus and take the normal Reflex penalty.","control":"flag","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresCharge":true,"suppresses":["chargeAttackBonus"],"defenseModifier":{"target":"defense.reflex","type":"untyped","value":-2,"duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn"}}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate combat option or passive roll-context option, not a static actor-sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Make ranged attack at end of a Charge; take a -2 penalty to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +4","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Charging_Fire","effect":"When you\nCharge\n, you may make a ranged attack instead of a melee attack at the end of your movement. Unlike a normal\nCharge\n, your momentum does not help you overcome your target, so you gain no bonus on your attack roll. As with a normal\nCharge\n, you still take a -2 penalty to your\nReflex Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex","attack.with-ranged"],"id":"swse.feat.charging_fire","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Charging_Fire","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"a9a59c85cddbda1f","name":"Warrior Heritage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Gain a bonus to Will Defense when using an Atlatl or Cesta.","prerequisite":"Gungan","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-gungan"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Gungan</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +2 morale bonus to your<br>Will Defense<br>when you wield an<br>Atlatl<br>or a<br>Cesta<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Warrior_Heritage</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.will","value":2,"type":"morale","predicates":["defense.will","weapon.atlatl-or-cesta-equipped"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Warrior Heritage: +2 morale bonus to Will Defense while wielding an Atlatl or Cesta.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"contextual_defense","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.will","weapon.atlatl-or-cesta-equipped"],"conditionSummary":"+2 morale bonus to Will Defense while wielding an Atlatl or Cesta."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"equipped_weapon_contextual_defense","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"+2 morale bonus to Will Defense while an Atlatl or Cesta is equipped; removed when unequipped. Never add without equipped-weapon context.","predicateRequirements":["defense.will","weapon.atlatl-or-cesta-equipped"],"metadataPhase":"phase25-suspect-feat-cleanup","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","status":"atlatl_cesta_will_context_phase25","description":"+2 morale bonus to Will Defense while wielding an Atlatl or Cesta."},"shortSummary":"Gain a bonus to Will Defense when using an Atlatl or Cesta.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Warrior_Heritage","rawImport":{"name":"Warrior Heritage","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Warrior_Heritage","pageTitle":"Warrior_Heritage","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\warrior_heritage.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Gungan","prerequisites":["Gungan"],"effect":"You gain a +2 morale bonus to your\nWill Defense\nwhen you wield an\nAtlatl\nor a\nCesta\n.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Gungan","indexBenefit":"Gain a bonus to Will Defense when using an Atlatl or Cesta .","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou come from a proud warrior culture, and your pride fills you with self-assurance.\n\nPrerequisite:\nGungan\n\nEffect:\nYou gain a +2 morale bonus to your\nWill Defense\nwhen you wield an\nAtlatl\nor a\nCesta\n."},"prerequisitesText":"Gungan","effect":"You gain a +2 morale bonus to your\nWill Defense\nwhen you wield an\nAtlatl\nor a\nCesta\n."},"effects":[{"_id":"d81202e0-20b2-409c-8d32-45838433244f","name":"Warrior Heritage","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Warrior Heritage","effectType":"defense_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.warrior_heritage"}}}
{"_id":"a9f6de36f24ef202","name":"Skill Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose one Untrained Skill from your list of Class Skills. You become Trained in that Skill.","prerequisite":"None","special":"This Feat may be selected multiple times. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Class Skill.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["build_enabler","feat","forecast_value","general","new_option","prereq_gateway","skill_recovery","skill_training","choice_required","choice_source_fixed"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7","21dfe84d159a1b7f"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Choose one<br>Untrained Skill<br>from your list of Class Skills. You become<br>Trained<br>in that<br>Skill<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Feat may be selected multiple times. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different Class Skill.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Skill_Training</em></p>","executionModel":"UNLOCK","abilityMeta":{"grants":[{"category":"SKILL_TRAINING","skills":"selectedChoice","description":"Skill Training: selected skill becomes trained."}],"status":"skill_training_implemented","description":"Skill Training: Select one Class Skill. You become trained in that skill.","mechanicsMode":"grant_unlock","applicationScope":"progression_entitlement","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Grants training in one selected skill rather than adding a numeric passive modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"execution_mapped_phase6","choiceKind":"skill_training","choiceSource":"fixed","repeatable":true,"optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.skill_training","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.skill_training","effectTarget":"skillTraining.selected"},"shortSummary":"You become Trained in one Class Skill.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Skill_Training","effect":"Choose one\nUntrained Skill\nfrom your list of Class Skills. You become\nTrained\nin that\nSkill\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.skill_training","requiresImmediateChoice":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Skill_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"aaa730a68f195111","name":"Savage Attack","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose one weapon groups or Exotic Weapon you have selected for the Double Attack Feat. When you use a Full Attack Action and successfully hit the target with your first attack, you deal +1 die of damage on each successful attack remaining in the Full Attack made against that target.","prerequisite":"Double Attack (Chosen Weapon)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Double Attack<br>(Chosen Weapon)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Choose one weapon groups or<br>Exotic Weapon<br>you have selected for the<br>Double Attack<br>Feat. When you use a<br>Full Attack<br>Action and successfully hit the target with your first attack, you deal +1 die of damage on each successful attack remaining in the<br>Full Attack<br>made against that target.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Savage_Attack</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Savage Attack","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Choose the Double Attack weapon choice this feat modifies.","metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","disabledReason":"Phase 6: choice captured now; execution waits for roll/action context wiring."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose the Double Attack weapon choice this feat modifies.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated."},"shortSummary":"Add +1 die of damage when successful on a Full Attack.","prerequisitesText":"Double Attack (Chosen Weapon)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Savage_Attack","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"double_attack_followup_weapon","repeatable":true,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.savage_attack_weapon","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.double_attack_followup_weapon","derivesFrom":["double_attack_weapon"],"consumes":"double_attack_weapon"},"effect":"Choose one weapon groups or\nExotic Weapon\nyou have selected for the\nDouble Attack\nFeat. When you use a\nFull Attack\nAction and successfully hit the target with your first attack, you deal +1 die of damage on each successful attack remaining in the\nFull Attack\nmade against that target."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.savage_attack","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Savage_Attack","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"acb7efcc70769b9f","name":"Mounted Defense","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When riding a Beast as a Mount or on a Speeder Bike (as a passenger or a Pilot), once per encounter you can redirect any attack made against you at your Mount or Vehicle instead. The decision to redirect the attack is made after the result of the attack roll is determined but before damage or other effects are resolved.","prerequisite":"Trained in Pilot or Ride","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Threats of the Galaxy","page":20,"tags":["defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Pilot<br>or<br>Ride</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When riding a<br>Beast<br>as a<br>Mount<br>or on a<br>Speeder Bike<br>(as a passenger or a<br>Pilot<br>), once per encounter you can redirect any attack made against you at your<br>Mount<br>or<br>Vehicle<br>instead. The decision to redirect the attack is made after the result of the attack roll is determined but before damage or other effects are resolved.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mounted_Defense</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"nearby_ally_or_positioning_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_table_context","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Mounted Defense redirects one attack per encounter from you to your mount/speeder after the roll but before damage; mount/vehicle target handling remains reaction metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"table_context_metadata_phase17","description":"Mounted Defense redirects one attack per encounter from you to your mount/speeder after the roll but before damage; mount/vehicle target handling remains reaction metadata.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Mounted Defense redirects one attack per encounter from you to your mount/speeder after the roll but before damage; mount/vehicle target handling remains reaction metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"nearby_ally_or_positioning_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"REDIRECT_ATTACK_TO_MOUNT_OR_SPEEDER","oncePer":"encounter","trigger":"attackRollKnownBeforeDamage","manualResolution":true,"description":"Mounted Defense redirects one attack per encounter from you to your mount/speeder after the roll but before damage; mount/vehicle target handling remains reaction metadata."}]},"shortSummary":"You are able to react to incoming attacks, using you Mount or Speeder Bike to absorb attacks against you.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Pilot or Ride","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mounted_Defense","effect":"When riding a\nBeast\nas a\nMount\nor on a\nSpeeder Bike\n(as a passenger or a\nPilot\n), once per encounter you can redirect any attack made against you at your\nMount\nor\nVehicle\ninstead. The decision to redirect the attack is made after the result of the attack roll is determined but before damage or other effects are resolved."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.mounted_defense","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Mounted_Defense","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ad2b32e5dfa38a3f","name":"Sadistic Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you deliver a Coup de Grace to a Helpless creature, all opponents within line of sight move -1 step on the Condition Track until the end of encounter.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":24,"tags":["condition_track","feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you deliver a<br>Coup de Grace<br>to a Helpless creature, all opponents within line of sight move -1 step on the<br>Condition Track<br>until the end of encounter.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sadistic_Strike</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Move a target -1 CT step when delivering a coup de grace.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"condition_track_trigger","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Move a target -1 CT step when delivering a coup de grace.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"condition_track_listener_phase14","resourceRules":{"conditionTrack":[{"type":"MOVE_TARGET_CT_ON_COUP_DE_GRACE","steps":-1,"description":"When you deliver a coup de grace, move the target -1 step on the Condition Track."}]}},"resourceRules":{"conditionTrack":[{"type":"MOVE_TARGET_CT_ON_COUP_DE_GRACE"}]},"shortSummary":"Move opponents -1 step on the Condition Track when you deliver a Coup de Grace.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sadistic_Strike","effect":"When you deliver a\nCoup de Grace\nto a Helpless creature, all opponents within line of sight move -1 step on the\nCondition Track\nuntil the end of encounter."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.386Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.sadistic_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Sadistic_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ad740c563485664d","name":"Lasting Influence","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"After a successful Persuasion check, gain a bonus to future Persuasion checks.","prerequisite":"Bothan","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","skill_persuasion","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-bothan"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Bothan</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you make a successful<br>Persuasion<br>check against a target&#x27;s<br>Will Defense<br>, you gain<br>Favourable Circumstances<br>on future<br>Persuasion<br>checks against that target for the next 24 hours.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Lasting_Influence</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Lasting Influence: Not a Will Defense bonus; represented as follow-up Persuasion circumstance metadata.","mechanicsMode":"manual","applicationScope":"metadata_only","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Not a Will Defense bonus; represented as follow-up Persuasion circumstance metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"persuasion_followup_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"After a successful Persuasion check against Will Defense, gain favorable circumstances on later Persuasion checks against that target.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase11-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 11 uses refreshed descriptions to replace manual/scaffold metadata with executable defense/skill/attack-option rules or explicit safe metadata for future hooks.","status":"skill_followup_phase11","description":"After a successful Persuasion check against Will Defense, gain favorable circumstances on later Persuasion checks against that target.","skillFollowupRules":[{"type":"PERSUASION_FAVORABLE_CIRCUMSTANCE_AFTER_SUCCESS","skillKey":"persuasion","targetDefense":"will","bonusType":"circumstance","duration":"sameTargetFutureChecks","description":"After succeeding on a Persuasion check against a target’s Will Defense, later Persuasion checks against that target gain favorable circumstances."}]},"shortSummary":"After a successful Persuasion check, gain a bonus to future Persuasion checks.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Lasting_Influence","rawImport":{"name":"Lasting Influence","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Lasting_Influence","pageTitle":"Lasting_Influence","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\lasting_influence.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Bothan","prerequisites":["Bothan"],"effect":"Whenever you make a successful\nPersuasion\ncheck against a target's\nWill Defense\n, you gain\nFavourable Circumstances\non future\nPersuasion\nchecks against that target for the next 24 hours.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Bothan","indexBenefit":"After a successful Persuasion check, gain a bonus to future Persuasion checks.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nWhen you penetrate the mind of your enemy, you can keep your barbs there for a long time.\n\nPrerequisite:\nBothan\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you make a successful\nPersuasion\ncheck against a target's\nWill Defense\n, you gain\nFavourable Circumstances\non future\nPersuasion\nchecks ag