{"_id":"c060d4cb33df501a","name":"Angled Throw","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When throwing a Grenade or grenadelike weapon, you can attempt to bounce it off a wall or other surface close to your target. If you attack roll exceeds a Reflex Defense of 15, you ignore Cover and Improved Cover (but not Total Cover) with your attack.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":32,"tags":["area_pressure","cover_play","feat","general","grenade","offense","offense_melee","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When throwing a<br>Grenade<br>or grenadelike weapon, you can attempt to bounce it off a wall or other surface close to your target. If you attack roll exceeds a<br>Reflex Defense<br>of 15, you ignore<br>Cover<br>and<br>Improved Cover<br>(but not<br>Total Cover<br>) with your attack.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Angled_Throw</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Grenade cover-suppression flag; no static bonus.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Grenade cover-suppression flag; no static bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"angledThrow","label":"Angled Throw","control":"flag","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresWeaponGroups":["grenade","grenades"],"suppresses":["coverFromGrenadeAttack"],"summary":"Ignore cover with grenade and grenadelike thrown attacks where cover would apply."}],"implementationStatus":"angledThrow_attack_option_phase13"},"shortSummary":"Ignore Cover with Grenades and grenadelike weapons.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Angled_Throw","effect":"When throwing a\nGrenade\nor grenadelike weapon, you can attempt to bounce it off a wall or other surface close to your target. If you attack roll exceeds a\nReflex Defense\nof 15, you ignore\nCover\nand\nImproved Cover\n(but not\nTotal Cover\n) with your attack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.angled_throw","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Angled_Throw","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c0bd186e6fb23619","name":"Knock Heads","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"After successfully using the Multi-Grab Feat against two targets that are both adjacent to you and each other, you can immediately knock their heads together, dealing automatic bludgeoning damage to each creature equal to 1d6 plus your Strength modifier. When comparing the damage to each creature's Damage Threshold, treat their Damage Thresholds as if they were 5 points lower. Both creatures are still considered Grabbed at the end of using this Feat.","prerequisite":"Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Multi-Grab","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":20,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>13,<br>Dexterity<br>13,<br>Multi-Grab</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> After successfully using the<br>Multi-Grab<br>Feat against two targets that are both adjacent to you and each other, you can immediately knock their heads together, dealing automatic bludgeoning damage to each creature equal to 1d6 plus your<br>Strength<br>modifier. When comparing the damage to each creature&#x27;s<br>Damage Threshold<br>, treat their<br>Damage Thresholds<br>as if they were 5 points lower. Both creatures are still considered<br>Grabbed<br>at the end of using this<br>Feat<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knock_Heads</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13},{"type":"attribute","ability":"str","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"multi_grab_followup_damage","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Knock Heads is a Multi-Grab follow-up that deals 1d6 + Strength modifier bludgeoning damage to both grabbed adjacent targets and treats DT as 5 lower.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"multi_grab_rider_metadata_phase17","description":"Knock Heads is a Multi-Grab follow-up that deals 1d6 + Strength modifier bludgeoning damage to both grabbed adjacent targets and treats DT as 5 lower.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Knock Heads is a Multi-Grab follow-up that deals 1d6 + Strength modifier bludgeoning damage to both grabbed adjacent targets and treats DT as 5 lower.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"multi_grab_followup_damage","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"KNOCK_HEADS_AFTER_MULTI_GRAB","requiresFeat":"Multi-Grab","damageFormula":"1d6 + strMod","damageType":"bludgeoning","targetCount":2,"requiresTargetsAdjacentToActorAndEachOther":true,"targetDamageThresholdPenalty":-5,"description":"After successful Multi-Grab on two adjacent targets, deal 1d6 + Strength modifier bludgeoning to both and treat DT as 5 lower."}]},"shortSummary":"You may knock two opponents' heads together after a successful Multi-Grab.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13, Dexterity 13, Multi-Grab","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knock_Heads","effect":"After successfully using the\nMulti-Grab\nFeat against two targets that are both adjacent to you and each other, you can immediately knock their heads together, dealing automatic bludgeoning damage to each creature equal to 1d6 plus your\nStrength\nmodifier. When comparing the damage to each creature's\nDamage Threshold\n, treat their\nDamage Thresholds\nas if they were 5 points lower. Both creatures are still considered\nGrabbed\nat the end of using this\nFeat\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.knock_heads","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Knock_Heads","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c120ef1fe27225af","name":"Controlled Rage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You enter a Rage as a Free Action. Your Rage ends 1 round after you declare it is finished.","prerequisite":"Rage Species Trait","special":"You may not use this Feat to extend the number of rounds of Rage available to your character.","normalText":"You must use a Swift Action to begin a Rage and may not end it at will.","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":33,"tags":["action_economy","execution_mapped_phase9","feat","free_action","general","offense_melee","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rage Species Trait</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You enter a Rage as a<br>Free Action<br>. Your Rage ends 1 round after you declare it is finished.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You must use a<br>Swift Action<br>to begin a Rage and may not end it at will.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You may not use this Feat to extend the number of rounds of Rage available to your character.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Controlled_Rage</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rage_rule_phase9","description":"Controlled Rage: enter Rage as a free action and end it at will.","rules":[{"type":"RAGE_ACTION_MODE","activation":"free","canEndAtWill":true,"description":"Enter Rage as a free action and end Rage at will."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"rage_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Only applies while the actor is raging or using rage-specific rules.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Enter Rage as a Free Action, and end Rage at will.","prerequisitesText":"Rage Species Trait","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Controlled_Rage","effect":"You enter a Rage as a\nFree Action\n. Your Rage ends 1 round after you declare it is finished."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.controlled_rage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Controlled_Rage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c180eee7d3bc29b2","name":"Precise Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can shoot or throw a ranged weapon at an opponent engaged in melee combat with one or more of your allies without taking the standard -5 penalty.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot","special":"If another Vehicle fires into a Dogfight, it takes a -5 penalty on its attack roll, unless the Gunner has the Precise Shot feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["accuracy","anti_cover","feat","feat_chain","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614","b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can shoot or throw a ranged weapon at an opponent engaged in melee combat with one or more of your allies without taking the standard -5 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If another Vehicle fires into a<br>Dogfight<br>, it takes a -5 penalty on its attack roll, unless the<br>Gunner<br>has the<br>Precise Shot<br>feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Precise_Shot</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Precise Shot: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"preciseShot","label":"Precise Shot","control":"flag","requiresAttackType":"ranged","suppresses":["firingIntoMeleePenalty"],"summary":"Ignore firing-into-melee penalties where the attack engine applies them."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate attack/combat option, not a passive sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"No -5 penalty for shooting into melee.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Precise_Shot","effect":"You can shoot or throw a ranged weapon at an opponent engaged in melee combat with one or more of your allies without taking the standard -5 penalty."},"effects":[{"_id":"77e126ab-16c9-4116-9d67-b5550c007b1b","name":"Precise Shot","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Precise Shot","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Precise Shot"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.precise_shot","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Precise_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c238f3f722689a3a","name":"Pin","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you succeed on a Grappling attack and your opponent fails the opposed Grapple check, your opponent is automatically Pinned until the start of your next turn. A Pinned creature can't move or take any Actions while Pinned, and it loses its Dexterity bonus (if any) to Reflex Defense.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"You cannot use the Pin and Trip Feats during the same round. You can use the Pin and Crush Feats in the same round, however.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["ability_dexterity","control","feat","general","grapple"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you succeed on a<br>Grappling<br>attack and your opponent fails the opposed<br>Grapple<br>check, your opponent is automatically Pinned until the start of your next turn. A Pinned creature can&#x27;t move or take any<br>Actions<br>while Pinned, and it loses its<br>Dexterity<br>bonus (if any) to<br>Reflex Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You cannot use the Pin and<br>Trip<br>Feats during the same round. You can use the Pin and<br>Crush<br>Feats in the same round, however.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pin</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rider_effect_phase7","description":"Pin: modeled as a rider/action rule, not a numeric modifier.","rules":[{"type":"GRAPPLE_RIDER","trigger":"onSuccessfulGrapple","effect":"pinned","duration":"untilStartOfYourNextTurn","targetLosesDexToReflex":true}],"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Pin: numeric scaffold disabled by Phase 7 (description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus)","mechanicsMode":"metadata_note","applicationScope":"not_a_numeric_modifier","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"description grants a conditional rider/action effect rather than a standing attack or defense bonus","metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"grapple_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Successful grapple may pin the opponent; this is not an attack modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Grappled opponent is Pinned for one round, can't move, and and loses its Dexterity bonus to Reflex Defense.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pin","effect":"If you succeed on a\nGrappling\nattack and your opponent fails the opposed\nGrapple\ncheck, your opponent is automatically Pinned until the start of your next turn. A Pinned creature can't move or take any\nActions\nwhile Pinned, and it loses its\nDexterity\nbonus (if any) to\nReflex Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.pin","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pin","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c2538c3a906700ae","name":"Forceful Blast","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"When you damage a Large or smaller creature with a Grenade or Thermal Detonator, compare the result of your attack roll to the target's Fortitude Defense. If your result equals or exceeds the target's Fortitude Defense, you can move the target 1 square in any direction as a Free Action.\n\nIf the Grenade deals damage to multiple eligible creatures, you can use this benefit against all of them. You can't move a target that's being Grabbed or Grappled, and you can't move a target into a solid object or into another creature's Fighting Space.","prerequisite":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons), Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["area_pressure","feat","force","grenade","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["fec1f8af44fcc35a"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons)<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you damage a Large or smaller creature with a<br>Grenade<br>or<br>Thermal Detonator<br>, compare the result of your attack roll to the target&#x27;s<br>Fortitude Defense<br>. If your result equals or exceeds the target&#x27;s<br>Fortitude Defense<br>, you can move the target 1 square in any direction as a<br>Free Action<br>.<br><br>If the<br>Grenade<br>deals damage to multiple eligible creatures, you can use this benefit against all of them. You can&#x27;t move a target that&#x27;s being<br>Grabbed<br>or<br>Grappled<br>, and you can&#x27;t move a target into a solid object or into another creature&#x27;s<br>Fighting Space<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Blast</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Grenade hit rider metadata carried through the attack card.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Grenade hit rider metadata carried through the attack card.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"forcefulBlast","label":"Forceful Blast","control":"flag","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresWeaponGroups":["grenade","grenades"],"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"forcedMovement","distanceSquares":1,"direction":"away","trigger":"grenadeDamage"}],"summary":"When your grenade attack damages a target, move that target 1 square."}],"implementationStatus":"forcefulBlast_attack_option_phase13"},"shortSummary":"Move a target damaged by your Grenade attack.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons), Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Blast","effect":"When you damage a Large or smaller creature with a\nGrenade\nor\nThermal Detonator\n, compare the result of your attack roll to the target's\nFortitude Defense\n. If your result equals or exceeds the target's\nFortitude Defense\n, you can move the target 1 square in any direction as a\nFree Action\n.\n\nIf the\nGrenade\ndeals damage to multiple eligible creatures, you can use this benefit against all of them. You can't move a target that's being\nGrabbed\nor\nGrappled\n, and you can't move a target into a solid object or into another creature's\nFighting Space\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.forceful_blast","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Forceful_Blast","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c2da9691c1bb9742","name":"Focused Rage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While Raging, you can use Skills that require patience and concentration, at a -5 penalty.","prerequisite":"Rage Species Trait, Controlled Rage","special":"","normalText":"While Raging, you cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force.","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":34,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase9","feat","general","offense_melee","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rage Species Trait,<br>Controlled Rage</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> While Raging, you can use<br>Skills<br>that require patience and concentration, at a -5 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> While Raging, you cannot use<br>Skills<br>that require patience and concentration, such as<br>Mechanics<br>,<br>Stealth<br>, or<br>Use the Force<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Focused_Rage</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"rage_rule_phase9_partial","description":"Focused Rage: permits patience/concentration skill uses while raging at a -5 penalty when those rolls are flagged by the caller.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"focused-rage-patience-penalty","skillKeys":["any"],"value":-5,"type":"rage","requiresContextFlags":["raging","requiresPatience"],"description":"Focused Rage: use patience-based skills while raging at -5."}],"rules":[{"type":"RAGE_ALLOW_PATIENCE_SKILLS","penalty":-5,"description":"When Raging, use skills that require patience at a -5 penalty."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"rage_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Only applies while the actor is raging or using rage-specific rules.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"When Raging, use Skills that require patience at a -5 penalty.","prerequisitesText":"Rage Species Trait, Controlled Rage","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Focused_Rage","effect":"While Raging, you can use\nSkills\nthat require patience and concentration, at a -5 penalty."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.focused_rage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Focused_Rage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c41814601364b643","name":"Weapon Focus","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Choose a single Exotic Weapon or weapon group, you gain a +1 bonus on all attack rolls you make using the selected Exotic Weapon or weapon group.","prerequisite":"Proficient with Chosen Weapon","special":"You can gain this Feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the Feat, it applies to a new Exotic Weapon or weapon group.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["accuracy","feat","general","weapon_mastery","choice_required","immediate_choice","weapon_choice","choice_source_prerequisite"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Proficient with Chosen Weapon</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Choose a single<br>Exotic Weapon<br>or weapon group, you gain a +1 bonus on all attack rolls you make using the selected<br>Exotic Weapon<br>or weapon group.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can gain this Feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the Feat, it applies to a new<br>Exotic Weapon<br>or weapon group.</p>\n<h3>Additional Weapon Focus Effects</h3><p>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Weapon Finesse<br>):<br>When you are wielding a single one-handed weapon for which you have Weapon Focus, you can treat that weapon as a<br>Light Weapon<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Focus</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack.bonus","value":1,"type":"untyped","enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Weapon Focus: +1 attack with selected proficient weapon group or exotic weapon","predicates":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"conditionSummary":"Always available after selection, but only for attack rolls with the selected weapon group or exotic weapon."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"selected_weapon_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Always available after selection, but only for attack rolls with the selected weapon group or exotic weapon.","predicateRequirements":["attack.weapon-matches-selected-choice"],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"execution_mapped_phase6","choiceKind":"weapon_focus","repeatable":true,"optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.weapon_focus","storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.weapon_focus","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","derivesFrom":["weapon_proficiency"],"consumes":"weapon_proficiency","provides":"weapon_focus","effectTarget":"attack.bonus","effectValue":1},"shortSummary":"+1 bonus on attack rolls with chosen weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Proficient with Chosen Weapon","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Focus","effect":"Choose a single\nExotic Weapon\nor weapon group, you gain a +1 bonus on all attack rolls you make using the selected\nExotic Weapon\nor weapon group."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.weapon_focus","requiresImmediateChoice":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Weapon_Focus","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c51d23038e2862e6","name":"Coordinated Barrage","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you Aid Another ally's attack, for every 3 points that the ally's attack roll beats the target's Reflex Defense, the attack deals +1 die of damage. The maximum number of bonus damage dice the attack receives is equal to the number of allies with this Feat that aided on the attack roll or +5 dice, whichever is lower.","prerequisite":"Coordinated Attack, Base Attack Bonus +5","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":21,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general","offense","offense_melee","offense_ranged","rage","resource_spend"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Coordinated Attack<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+5</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you<br>Aid Another<br>ally&#x27;s attack, for every 3 points that the ally&#x27;s attack roll beats the target&#x27;s<br>Reflex Defense<br>, the attack deals +1 die of damage. The maximum number of bonus damage dice the attack receives is equal to the number of allies with this<br>Feat<br>that aided on the attack roll or +5 dice, whichever is lower.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Barrage</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":5}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"aid_another_damage_scaling_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_table_context","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Coordinated Barrage scales an aided ally attack by +1 die per 3 points over target Reflex, capped by aiding allies with the feat or +5 dice; ally-count handling remains table/context metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"aid_another_rider_metadata_phase17","description":"Coordinated Barrage scales an aided ally attack by +1 die per 3 points over target Reflex, capped by aiding allies with the feat or +5 dice; ally-count handling remains table/context metadata.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Coordinated Barrage scales an aided ally attack by +1 die per 3 points over target Reflex, capped by aiding allies with the feat or +5 dice; ally-count handling remains table/context metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"aid_another_damage_scaling_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"aidAnotherRules":[{"type":"AIDED_ATTACK_DAMAGE_DICE_BY_MARGIN","marginPerDie":3,"maxDice":"min(alliesWithFeat,5)","description":"When you Aid Another on an ally attack, add +1 damage die per 3 points the attack beats Reflex, capped by allies with feat or 5 dice."}]},"shortSummary":"Allow an ally to deal more damage when you aid their attack.","prerequisitesText":"Coordinated Attack, Base Attack Bonus +5","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Barrage","effect":"When you\nAid Another\nally's attack, for every 3 points that the ally's attack roll beats the target's\nReflex Defense\n, the attack deals +1 die of damage. The maximum number of bonus damage dice the attack receives is equal to the number of allies with this\nFeat\nthat aided on the attack roll or +5 dice, whichever is lower."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.coordinated_barrage","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Coordinated_Barrage","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c58e69ff5adb5e71","name":"Recall","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per day, you can reroll any check for a Knowledge Skill that you are Trained in, using the better result.","prerequisite":"Trained in at least one Knowledge Skill","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":36,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","knowledge","reroll","skill_knowledge","skill_synergy","utility","skill_reroll","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in at least one<br>Knowledge<br>Skill</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per day, you can reroll any check for a<br>Knowledge<br>Skill that you are<br>Trained<br>in, using the better result.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recall</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"atleastoneknowledgeskill"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"skill_reroll_phase8","description":"Recall: reroll a Knowledge skill check and keep the better result.","skillRerolls":[{"id":"recall","skillKeys":["knowledge","knowledgeBureaucracy","knowledgeGalacticLore","knowledgeLifeSciences","knowledgePhysicalSciences","knowledgeSocialSciences","knowledgeTactics","knowledgeTechnology"],"outcome":"keepBetter","label":"Recall","description":"Recall: reroll a Knowledge skill check and keep the better result."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"reroll_or_resource_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rerolls/resources are not static sheet modifiers and require a check/encounter/resource context.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Reroll Knowledge skill check, keeping the better result.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in at least one Knowledge Skill","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recall","effect":"Once per day, you can reroll any check for a\nKnowledge\nSkill that you are\nTrained\nin, using the better result."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.recall","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Recall","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c7c99a77ebee1c0c","name":"Dual Weapon Mastery II","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you attack with two weapons, or with both ends of a double weapon as part of a Full Attack Action, you take a -2 penalty (Instead of a -10 penalty) on all attack rolls until the start of your next turn. You only gain this reduced penalty if you are wielding a weapon with which you are proficient.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 15, Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"If you use a Full Attack Action to make more than one attack on your turn, you take a -10 penalty on all attack rolls for the round.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["action_economy","dual_wield","feat","general","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>15,<br>Dual Weapon Mastery I<br>,<br>Base Attack Bonus<br>+6</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you attack with two weapons, or with both ends of a double weapon as part of a<br>Full Attack<br>Action, you take a -2 penalty (Instead of a -10 penalty) on all attack rolls until the start of your next turn. You only gain this reduced penalty if you are wielding a weapon with which you are proficient.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> If you use a<br>Full Attack<br>Action to make more than one attack on your turn, you take a -10 penalty on all attack rolls for the round.</p>\n<h3>Additional Dual Weapon Mastery II Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy<br><br>Vehicle Weapons<br>cannot be used in one hand, so this Feat has no effect on them.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_II</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":15},{"type":"bab","min":6}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Two-weapon full-attack penalty metadata; consumed once multiattack UI resolves selected attack mode.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"multiattack_penalty_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Two-weapon full-attack penalty metadata; consumed once multiattack UI resolves selected attack mode.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"multiattack_metadata_phase14","multiAttackRules":[{"type":"TWO_WEAPON_FULL_ATTACK_PENALTY","penalty":-2,"description":"Penalty for attacking with two weapons becomes -2."}]},"shortSummary":"Take a -2 penalty on attacks when attacking with two weapons, or both ends of a double weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 15, Dual Weapon Mastery I, Base Attack Bonus +6","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_II","effect":"When you attack with two weapons, or with both ends of a double weapon as part of a\nFull Attack\nAction, you take a -2 penalty (Instead of a -10 penalty) on all attack rolls until the start of your next turn. You only gain this reduced penalty if you are wielding a weapon with which you are proficient."},"effects":[{"_id":"fa217f33-b718-45d3-b256-9226da60389d","name":"Dual Weapon Mastery II","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Dual Weapon Mastery II","effectType":"special","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.dual_weapon_mastery_ii","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Dual_Weapon_Mastery_II","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"c9522152ffa425f9","name":"Knock Prone","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You may attempt to knock an opponent prone with a melee attack. If successful, the target falls prone.","prerequisite":"Int 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["control","feat","general","knock_prone","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee","target.is-prone"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Knock Prone: Implemented as CombatOptionResolver/rider metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee","target.is-prone"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as CombatOptionResolver/rider metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Knock Prone now has explicit roll-context/rider metadata from its description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 continued replacing false scaffold modifiers with concrete or diagnostics-ready metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"knockProne","label":"Knock Prone","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"KNOCK_PRONE","target":"target","description":"If the melee attack succeeds, the target falls prone."}],"summary":"Attempt to knock a target prone with a melee attack."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Knock Prone now has explicit roll-context/rider metadata from its description."},"shortSummary":"You may attempt to knock an opponent prone with a melee attack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee","target.is-prone"]}}}
{"_id":"c973e43c85382068","name":"Autofire Assault","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When wielding a weapon for which you possess the Weapon Focus Feat, and you target the same area with an Autofire attack that you made an Autofire attack against on your last turn, the penalty on the Autofire attack is reduced to -2 (-1 if using a Braced Autofire -only weapon or the Controlled Burst Talent) and you deal +1 die of damage on a hit.","prerequisite":"Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","special":"This Feat cannot be used with the Autofire Sweep Feat or the Burst Fire Feat.","normalText":"A -5 penalty applies to Autofire attack rolls, and there are no bonuses for consecutive rounds of fire in the same squares.","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":23,"tags":["area_pressure","autofire","feat","full_attack_synergy","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Focus<br>(Chosen Weapon)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When wielding a weapon for which you possess the<br>Weapon Focus<br>Feat, and you target the same area with an<br>Autofire<br>attack that you made an<br>Autofire<br>attack against on your last turn, the penalty on the<br>Autofire<br>attack is reduced to -2 (-1 if using a<br>Braced<br>Autofire<br>-only weapon or the<br>Controlled Burst<br>Talent) and you deal +1 die of damage on a hit.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> A -5 penalty applies to<br>Autofire<br>attack rolls, and there are no bonuses for consecutive rounds of fire in the same squares.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Feat cannot be used with the<br>Autofire Sweep<br>Feat or the<br>Burst Fire<br>Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Autofire_Assault</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"autofire_sustained_area_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Autofire Assault: sustained autofire with a Weapon Focus weapon reduces the autofire penalty and adds +1 weapon die.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"attack_option_phase16","description":"Autofire Assault: sustained autofire with a Weapon Focus weapon reduces the autofire penalty and adds +1 weapon die.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Autofire Assault: sustained autofire with a Weapon Focus weapon reduces the autofire penalty and adds +1 weapon die.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"autofire_sustained_area_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"autofireAssault","label":"Autofire Assault","control":"toggle","requiresAutofire":true,"requiresFeatSelectedChoiceMatch":["Weapon Focus"],"requiresContextFlags":["sameAutofireAreaAsLastTurn"],"attackModifier":3,"damageExtraWeaponDice":1,"excludesOptions":["autofireSweep","burstFire"],"summary":"When sustaining autofire into the same area with a Weapon Focus weapon, reduce the normal -5 penalty to -2 and add +1 die damage."}]},"shortSummary":"Decrease penalty on Autofire attack and inflict extra damage when sustaining fire in the same squares in consecutive rounds.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Autofire_Assault","effect":"When wielding a weapon for which you possess the\nWeapon Focus\nFeat, and you target the same area with an\nAutofire\nattack that you made an\nAutofire\nattack against on your last turn, the penalty on the\nAutofire\nattack is reduced to -2 (-1 if using a\nBraced\nAutofire\n-only weapon or the\nControlled Burst\nTalent) and you deal +1 die of damage on a hit."},"effects":[{"_id":"870f5168-26b8-487a-8255-fbf32ddc06ff","name":"Autofire Assault","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[{"key":"system.combat.autofireDamageBonus","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Autofire Assault","effectType":"damage_bonus"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.autofire_assault","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Autofire_Assault","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"caad1a8c13bf01a1","name":"Withdrawal Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When taking this Feat, select a single Exotic Weapon (Melee) or melee weapon group with which you are proficient. When wielding that chosen Exotic Weapon (Melee) or melee weapon from the chosen group, adjacent opponents may not Withdraw from squares you threaten. They may still make Acrobatics checks to Tumble as normal.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +5","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":30,"tags":["feat","general","mobility","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+5</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When taking this Feat, select a single<br>Exotic Weapon (Melee)<br>or melee weapon group with which you are proficient. When wielding that chosen<br>Exotic Weapon (Melee)<br>or melee weapon from the chosen group, adjacent opponents may not<br>Withdraw<br>from squares you threaten. They may still make<br>Acrobatics<br>checks to<br>Tumble<br>as normal.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Withdrawal_Strike</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":5}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":0,"type":"untyped","predicates":[],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"[REQUIRES MANUAL MAPPING] Withdrawal Strike","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Choose a melee weapon group or melee exotic weapon.","metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated.","disabledReason":"Phase 6: choice captured now; execution waits for roll/action context wiring."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"roll_or_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Choose a melee weapon group or melee exotic weapon.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase6-choice-backfill","metadataNotes":"Phase 6 captures the required persistent choice; roll/action execution remains context-gated."},"shortSummary":"Adjacent opponents can not use the Withdraw Action.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +5","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Withdrawal_Strike","choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"phase6_choice_backfilled","choiceKind":"melee_weapon_or_group","repeatable":true,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.withdrawal_strike_weapon","choiceSource":"prerequisiteDerived","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.melee_weapon_or_group","derivesFrom":["weapon_proficiency"],"consumes":"weapon_proficiency"},"effect":"When taking this Feat, select a single\nExotic Weapon (Melee)\nor melee weapon group with which you are proficient. When wielding that chosen\nExotic Weapon (Melee)\nor melee weapon from the chosen group, adjacent opponents may not\nWithdraw\nfrom squares you threaten. They may still make\nAcrobatics\nchecks to\nTumble\nas normal."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.withdrawal_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Withdrawal_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cab4954728195119","name":"Hyperblazer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When traversing the Hyperspace Tangle, you reduce by half the calculation time and penalties on Use Computer checks to Astrogate (See Hyperspace Navigation Challenges). You also reduce Hyperspace Mapping time by half when mapping new Hyperspace Routes.","prerequisite":"Trained in Use Computer","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":23,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","skill_synergy","skill_use_computer"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Use Computer</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When traversing the Hyperspace Tangle, you reduce by half the calculation time and penalties on<br>Use Computer<br>checks to<br>Astrogate<br>(See<br>Hyperspace Navigation Challenges<br>). You also reduce Hyperspace Mapping time by half when mapping new Hyperspace Routes.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hyperblazer</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rule","applicationScope":"use_computer_astrogation_hyperspace_tangle","staticSheetPolicy":"skill_use_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Hyperblazer halves Hyperspace Tangle astrogation time/penalties and halves hyperspace mapping time; stored as Use Computer astrogation metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"skill_use_rule_phase17","description":"Hyperblazer halves Hyperspace Tangle astrogation time/penalties and halves hyperspace mapping time; stored as Use Computer astrogation metadata.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Hyperblazer halves Hyperspace Tangle astrogation time/penalties and halves hyperspace mapping time; stored as Use Computer astrogation metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"use_computer_astrogation_hyperspace_tangle","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"skillUseRules":[{"type":"ASTROGATION_HYPERSPACE_TANGLE_BONUS","skillKey":"useComputer","applications":["astrogate","hyperspace navigation","hyperspace mapping"],"calculationTimeMultiplier":0.5,"penaltyMultiplier":0.5,"mappingTimeMultiplier":0.5,"description":"Halve Hyperspace Tangle astrogation calculation time/penalties and hyperspace mapping time."}]},"shortSummary":"Cut all calculation time and Use Computer penalties by half when making Use Computer checks for Astrogation in the Hyperspace tangle. Reduce Hyperspace mapping time by half.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Use Computer","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hyperblazer","effect":"When traversing the Hyperspace Tangle, you reduce by half the calculation time and penalties on\nUse Computer\nchecks to\nAstrogate\n(See\nHyperspace Navigation Challenges\n). You also reduce Hyperspace Mapping time by half when mapping new Hyperspace Routes."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.hyperblazer","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hyperblazer","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cb6aea7e256e4c8c","name":"Improved Rapid Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using a Light Melee Weapon or Lightsaber with the Rapid Strike Feat, you can take a -5 penalty to your attack roll to gain +2 dice of damage on a successful strike.","prerequisite":"Rapid Strike","special":"This does not stack with the Rapid Strike Feat or extra damage provided by any source that does not stack with the Rapid Strike Feat (such as Mighty Swing). If you do not have a Dexterity of 13 or higher, the penalty to your attack roll is -10 instead of -5.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":27,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Rapid Strike</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using a Light Melee Weapon or<br>Lightsaber<br>with the<br>Rapid Strike<br>Feat, you can take a -5 penalty to your attack roll to gain +2 dice of damage on a successful strike.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This does not stack with the<br>Rapid Strike<br>Feat or extra damage provided by any source that does not stack with the<br>Rapid Strike<br>Feat (such as<br>Mighty Swing<br>). If you do not have a<br>Dexterity<br>of 13 or higher, the penalty to your attack roll is -10 instead of -5.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Rapid_Strike</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Light-melee Rapid Strike upgrade as a selectable attack option.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Light-melee Rapid Strike upgrade as a selectable attack option.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"improvedRapidStrike","label":"Improved Rapid Strike","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","requiresWeaponGroups":["light melee","light melee weapons","lightsaber"],"attackModifier":-5,"damageExtraWeaponDice":2,"summary":"With a light melee weapon, take -5 attack to deal +2 weapon dice."}],"implementationStatus":"improvedRapidStrike_attack_option_phase13"},"shortSummary":"Trade -5 penalty on attack roll for +2 dice of damage when using a Light Melee Weapon.","prerequisitesText":"Rapid Strike","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Rapid_Strike","effect":"When using a Light Melee Weapon or\nLightsaber\nwith the\nRapid Strike\nFeat, you can take a -5 penalty to your attack roll to gain +2 dice of damage on a successful strike."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.improved_rapid_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Rapid_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cbea70febcf834cd","name":"Burst of Speed","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Move Action, you can Move up to twice your speed. At the end of your movement, you move -1 step along the Condition Track.","prerequisite":"Trained in Endurance","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":24,"tags":["action_economy","feat","general","mobility","move_action"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Endurance</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Move Action<br>, you can Move up to twice your speed. At the end of your movement, you move -1 step along the<br>Condition Track<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Burst_of_Speed</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"35df8faa4878f2c5"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["turn.once-per-round"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Burst of Speed: Burst of Speed is a movement/condition-track cost rule, not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Burst of Speed is a movement/condition-track cost rule, not an attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"non_numeric_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Burst of Speed is a movement/condition-track cost rule, not an attack bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","movementRules":[{"type":"MOVE_UP_TO_DOUBLE_SPEED","action":"move","conditionTrackCost":1,"description":"Move up to twice speed as a move action, then move -1 step on the Condition Track."}],"status":"movement_rule_phase10","description":"Burst of Speed is a movement/condition-track cost rule, not an attack bonus."},"shortSummary":"Move Speed twice as Move Action.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Endurance","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Burst_of_Speed","effect":"As a\nMove Action\n, you can Move up to twice your speed. At the end of your movement, you move -1 step along the\nCondition Track\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["turn.once-per-round"],"id":"swse.feat.burst_of_speed","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Burst_of_Speed","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ccb33e58342499a3","name":"Rapid Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using a melee weapon with which you are proficient, you may make two strikes as a single attack against a single target. You take a -2 penalty on your attack roll, but deal +1 die of damage with a successful attack.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"The effects of this feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the Mighty Swing Feat. If you do not have a Dexterity score of 13 or higher, increase the penalty to attacks to -5 when using this Feat with non-Light Weapons.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":88,"tags":["damage_scaling","feat","feat_chain","general","lightsaber_compatible","offense","offense_melee","standard_action"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using a melee weapon with which you are proficient, you may make two strikes as a single attack against a single target. You take a -2 penalty on your attack roll, but deal +1 die of damage with a successful attack.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> The effects of this feat do not stack with the extra damage provided by the<br>Mighty Swing<br>Feat. If you do not have a<br>Dexterity<br>score of 13 or higher, increase the penalty to attacks to -5 when using this Feat with non-Light Weapons.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Strike</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7","description":"Rapid Strike: attack option exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied automatically.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"rapidStrike","label":"Rapid Strike","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","attackModifier":-2,"damageDiceStepBonus":1,"summary":"Take -2 on a melee attack to deal +1 die of damage."}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate attack/combat option, not a passive sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"subType":"STATE","shortSummary":"Take a -2 penalty on a melee attack roll to deal +1 die of damage.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Strike","effect":"When using a melee weapon with which you are proficient, you may make two strikes as a single attack against a single target. You take a -2 penalty on your attack roll, but deal +1 die of damage with a successful attack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.rapid_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Rapid_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ccc7a6e191e811a4","name":"Hobbling Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you would deal extra damage by using Sneak Attack, Rapid Shot, or Rapid Strike, you can reduce the target's Speed by 1 square until the end of the encounter, instead of dealing the extra damage.","prerequisite":"Sneak Attack or Rapid Shot or Rapid Strike.","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":20,"tags":["control","feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Sneak Attack<br>or<br>Rapid Shot<br>or<br>Rapid Strike<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you would deal extra damage by using<br>Sneak Attack<br>,<br>Rapid Shot<br>, or<br>Rapid Strike<br>, you can reduce the target&#x27;s Speed by 1 square until the end of the encounter, instead of dealing the extra damage.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hobbling_Strike</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"extra_damage_tradeoff_speed_reduction","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Hobbling Strike: trade Sneak Attack/Rapid Shot/Rapid Strike extra damage to reduce target speed by 1 square until encounter end.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"attack_rider_metadata_phase16","description":"Hobbling Strike: trade Sneak Attack/Rapid Shot/Rapid Strike extra damage to reduce target speed by 1 square until encounter end.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Hobbling Strike: trade Sneak Attack/Rapid Shot/Rapid Strike extra damage to reduce target speed by 1 square until encounter end.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"extra_damage_tradeoff_speed_reduction","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"hobblingStrike","label":"Hobbling Strike","control":"flag","requiresContextFlags":["extraDamageAvailable"],"suppresses":["extraDamageDice"],"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"SPEED_PENALTY","value":-1,"duration":"encounter","description":"Target speed reduced by 1 square until end of encounter instead of extra damage."}],"summary":"Trade eligible extra damage for -1 target speed until encounter end."}]},"shortSummary":"Reduce the target's Speed instead of dealing damage.","prerequisitesText":"Sneak Attack or Rapid Shot or Rapid Strike.","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hobbling_Strike","effect":"Whenever you would deal extra damage by using\nSneak Attack\n,\nRapid Shot\n, or\nRapid Strike\n, you can reduce the target's Speed by 1 square until the end of the encounter, instead of dealing the extra damage."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.hobbling_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Hobbling_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cda6cb7b58f96a2f","name":"Acrobatic Dodge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, as a Reaction, if a melee attack misses you, you can immediately move into an adjacent square without provoking an Attack of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13, Dodge, Mobility, Skill Focus (Acrobatics)","special":"You must be aware of the attacker to benefit from this Feat. You can use this Feat a second time during the encounter by spending a Force Point.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":19,"tags":["defense","feat","general","reaction","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13,<br>Dodge<br>,<br>Mobility<br>,<br>Skill Focus (Acrobatics)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, as a<br>Reaction<br>, if a melee attack misses you, you can immediately move into an adjacent square without provoking an<br>Attack of Opportunity<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You must be aware of the attacker to benefit from this Feat. You can use this Feat a second time during the encounter by spending a<br>Force Point<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Dodge</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.with-melee"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Acrobatic Dodge: Implemented as reaction metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.with-melee"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as reaction metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"reaction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Acrobatic Dodge now exposes reaction metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","reactionRules":[{"type":"MOVE_AFTER_MISSED_MELEE_ATTACK","trigger":"missedByMeleeAttack","action":"reaction","oncePer":"encounter","movement":"adjacentSquareNoAoO","description":"After a melee attack misses you, move to an adjacent square without provoking."}],"status":"reaction_rule_phase10","description":"Acrobatic Dodge now exposes reaction metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"When a melee attack misses you, move into an adjacent square without provoking an Attack of Opportunity.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13, Dodge, Mobility, Skill Focus (Acrobatics)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Dodge","effect":"Once per encounter, as a\nReaction\n, if a melee attack misses you, you can immediately move into an adjacent square without provoking an\nAttack of Opportunity\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.acrobatic_dodge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Acrobatic_Dodge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ce009e054ef1681f","name":"Implant Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You are not moved an extra step down the Condition Track when you would normally be moved down the Condition Track.","prerequisite":"Must possess an Implant","special":"","normalText":"Characters with an Implant move one extra step down the Condition Track when moved down the Condition Track for any reason, and take a -2 penalty to their Will Defense without this Feat.","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":26,"tags":["condition_track","feat","general","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Must possess an<br>Implant</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You are not moved an extra step down the<br>Condition Track<br>when you would normally be moved down the<br>Condition Track<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> Characters with an<br>Implant<br>move one extra step down the<br>Condition Track<br>when moved down the<br>Condition Track<br>for any reason, and take a -2 penalty to their<br>Will Defense<br>without this Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Implant_Training</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_capability","applicationScope":"implant_condition_track_context","staticSheetPolicy":"condition_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Implant Training: suppresses the extra implant condition-track step and implant Will Defense penalty.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"condition_defense_metadata_phase16","description":"Implant Training: suppresses the extra implant condition-track step and implant Will Defense penalty.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Implant Training: suppresses the extra implant condition-track step and implant Will Defense penalty.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"implant_condition_track_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"resourceRules":{"conditionTrack":[{"type":"SUPPRESS_EXTRA_IMPLANT_CT_STEP","description":"Do not move an extra step down the Condition Track due to implants."}],"defense":[{"type":"SUPPRESS_IMPLANT_WILL_PENALTY","description":"Ignore the normal implant Will Defense penalty."}]}},"resourceRules":{"damage":[{"type":"PREVENT_IMPLANT_CT_PENALTIES","status":"BLOCKED_NO_IMPLANT_SYSTEM","note":"This feat assumes an implant system that applies CT penalties. Currently, implants are equipment only; no implant-triggered CT penalty system exists. Feat is awaiting future implant system implementation.","blockedSince":"2026-05-11"}]},"shortSummary":"You don't move additional steps down the Condition Track due to your Implants.","prerequisitesText":"Must possess an Implant","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Implant_Training","effect":"You are not moved an extra step down the\nCondition Track\nwhen you would normally be moved down the\nCondition Track\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.implant_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Implant_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ce473e52f90b160a","name":"Improved Disarm","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +5 bonus on any melee attack roll made to Disarm an opponent. In addition, if you fail to Disarm an opponent, he doesn't get to make a free attack against you.","prerequisite":"Intelligence 13, Melee Defense","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":87,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence<br>13,<br>Melee Defense</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +5 bonus on any melee attack roll made to<br>Disarm<br>an opponent. In addition, if you fail to<br>Disarm<br>an opponent, he doesn&#x27;t get to make a free attack against you.</p>\n<h3>Additional Improved Disarm Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide<br><br>Combined Feat<br>(<br>Force Training<br>):<br>When you use the<br>Force Disarm<br>Force Power, you gain the +5 bonus from Improved Disarm on your<br>Use the Force<br>check as though you were making an attack roll.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Disarm</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"attack_option_phase7_refined","description":"Improved Disarm: exposed through CombatOptionResolver; not applied as a passive sheet modifier.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"improvedDisarm","label":"Improved Disarm","summary":"Gain +5 on a melee attack made specifically to disarm an opponent.","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","requiresManeuver":"disarm","attackModifier":5,"suppresses":["failedDisarmCounterattack"]}],"mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Exposed as a deliberate combat option or passive roll-context option, not a static actor-sheet modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase7-description-reimplementation","metadataNotes":"Phase 7 re-read refreshed descriptions and converted old scaffold bonuses into explicit static/resource/attack-option/rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"Gain +5 bonus on melee attacks to Disarm an opponent.","prerequisitesText":"Intelligence 13, Melee Defense","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Disarm","effect":"You gain a +5 bonus on any melee attack roll made to\nDisarm\nan opponent. In addition, if you fail to\nDisarm\nan opponent, he doesn't get to make a free attack against you."},"effects":[{"_id":"11028f88-1c7b-4f68-8cb6-352d73d94b1b","name":"Improved Disarm","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Improved Disarm","effectType":"combat_bonus","flagType":"Improved Disarm"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.with-melee"],"id":"swse.feat.improved_disarm","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Improved_Disarm","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"ce946668c5b57410","name":"Harm’s Way","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a reaction, you may take damage dealt to an adjacent ally instead of them.","prerequisite":"Base attack bonus +6","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":25,"tags":["defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["proximity.ally-nearby"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Harm’s Way: Harm’s Way is a damage redirection reaction, not an attack bonus.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["proximity.ally-nearby"],"conditionSummary":"Harm’s Way is a damage redirection reaction, not an attack bonus.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"non_numeric_rule","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Harm’s Way is a damage redirection reaction, not an attack bonus.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","reactionRules":[{"type":"TAKE_DAMAGE_FOR_ADJACENT_ALLY","trigger":"adjacentAllyDamaged","action":"reaction","description":"As a reaction, take damage dealt to an adjacent ally instead of them."}],"status":"reaction_rules_phase10","description":"Harm’s Way is a damage redirection reaction, not an attack bonus."},"shortSummary":"As a reaction, you may take damage dealt to an adjacent ally instead of them."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.ally-nearby"]}}}
{"_id":"cefb9edb540745d6","name":"Multi-Targeting","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can use Swift Actions across more than one round to Aim at a target with a weapon with which you are proficient. You can attack different targets prior to the completion of your Aim Action. If the subject of your Aim is out of your line of sight for any reason, you lose your Aim and must start again.","prerequisite":"Droid, Intelligence 13","special":"","normalText":"You must normally use two consecutive Swift Actions in the same round to Aim.","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":23,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>,<br>Intelligence<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can use<br>Swift Actions<br>across more than one round to<br>Aim<br>at a target with a weapon with which you are proficient. You can attack different targets prior to the completion of your<br>Aim<br>Action. If the subject of your<br>Aim<br>is out of your line of sight for any reason, you lose your<br>Aim<br>and must start again.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You must normally use two consecutive<br>Swift Actions<br>in the same round to<br>Aim<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Targeting</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"aim_action_persistence_context","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Multi-Targeting lets a Droid spread Aim swift actions across rounds and attack other targets without losing Aim unless the aimed subject leaves line of sight.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"aim_metadata_phase17","description":"Multi-Targeting lets a Droid spread Aim swift actions across rounds and attack other targets without losing Aim unless the aimed subject leaves line of sight.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Multi-Targeting lets a Droid spread Aim swift actions across rounds and attack other targets without losing Aim unless the aimed subject leaves line of sight.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"aim_action_persistence_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"AIM_ACTIONS_PERSIST_ACROSS_ROUNDS","actorRequirement":"droid","allowsAttacksAgainstOtherTargets":true,"breakCondition":"aimedSubjectLeavesLineOfSight","description":"Use Aim swift actions across rounds; attacking other targets does not break Aim."}]},"shortSummary":"You can spread your Aim action across multiple consecutive rounds.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Intelligence 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Targeting","effect":"You can use\nSwift Actions\nacross more than one round to\nAim\nat a target with a weapon with which you are proficient. You can attack different targets prior to the completion of your\nAim\nAction. If the subject of your\nAim\nis out of your line of sight for any reason, you lose your\nAim\nand must start again."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.multi_targeting","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Multi-Targeting","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"cf278001c780f3f9","name":"Momentum Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When riding a Beast as a Mount or on a Speeder Bike (as a passenger or a Pilot), you add +1 die of damage to any melee attacks if your Mount or Vehicle has already moved at least its speed this turn.","prerequisite":"Trained in Pilot or Ride","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Threats of the Galaxy","page":20,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Pilot<br>or<br>Ride</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When riding a<br>Beast<br>as a<br>Mount<br>or on a<br>Speeder Bike<br>(as a passenger or a<br>Pilot<br>), you add +1 die of damage to any melee attacks if your<br>Mount<br>or<br>Vehicle<br>has already moved at least its speed this turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Momentum_Strike</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"mounted_or_speeder_melee_damage_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Momentum Strike adds +1 weapon die to melee attacks while riding a mount or speeder bike if the mount/vehicle has already moved at least its speed this turn.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"attack_option_phase17","description":"Momentum Strike adds +1 weapon die to melee attacks while riding a mount or speeder bike if the mount/vehicle has already moved at least its speed this turn.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Momentum Strike adds +1 weapon die to melee attacks while riding a mount or speeder bike if the mount/vehicle has already moved at least its speed this turn.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"mounted_or_speeder_melee_damage_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"momentumStrike","label":"Momentum Strike","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"melee","requiresContextFlags":["mountedOrSpeeder","mountOrVehicleMovedAtLeastSpeed"],"damageExtraWeaponDice":1,"summary":"While mounted/on speeder after mount/vehicle moved at least its speed, add +1 weapon die to melee attacks."}]},"shortSummary":"You know how to put the weight of your momentum into attacks while riding a Mount or Speeder Bike.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Pilot or Ride","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Threats of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Momentum_Strike","effect":"When riding a\nBeast\nas a\nMount\nor on a\nSpeeder Bike\n(as a passenger or a\nPilot\n), you add +1 die of damage to any melee attacks if your\nMount\nor\nVehicle\nhas already moved at least its speed this turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.momentum_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Momentum_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
