{"_id":"d518e8c1220af930","name":"Droid Shield Mastery","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You automatically succeed on Endurance checks to restore your Shield Rating by 5 points (up to your normal Shield Rating). Additionally, you replenish your shields in two Swift Actions.","prerequisite":"Droid, Shield Generator (Droid Accessory)","special":"","normalText":"Three Swift Actions and a DC 20 Endurance check are normally required to restore lost shield power.","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":20,"tags":["action_economy","ally_support","charge","feat","general","swift_action","tech","utility"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>,<br>Shield Generator<br>(<br>Droid Accessory<br>)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You automatically succeed on<br>Endurance<br>checks to restore your<br>Shield Rating<br>by 5 points (up to your normal<br>Shield Rating<br>). Additionally, you replenish your shields in two<br>Swift Actions<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> Three<br>Swift Actions<br>and a DC 20<br>Endurance<br>check are normally required to restore lost shield power.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Shield_Mastery</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"droid_shield_recharge_context","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Droid Shield Mastery: automatically succeed to restore SR by 5 and recharge shields using two swift actions.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"shield_action_metadata_phase16","description":"Droid Shield Mastery: automatically succeed to restore SR by 5 and recharge shields using two swift actions.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Droid Shield Mastery: automatically succeed to restore SR by 5 and recharge shields using two swift actions.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"droid_shield_recharge_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"AUTO_SUCCEED_RECHARGE_SHIELDS","skillKey":"endurance","amount":5,"description":"Automatically succeed on checks to restore SR by 5 up to normal SR."},{"type":"RECHARGE_SHIELDS_ACTION_ECONOMY","swiftActions":2,"description":"Recharge shields in two swift actions."}]},"shortSummary":"Automatically Recharge Shields in two Swift Actions.","prerequisitesText":"Droid, Shield Generator (Droid Accessory)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Shield_Mastery","effect":"You automatically succeed on\nEndurance\nchecks to restore your\nShield Rating\nby 5 points (up to your normal\nShield Rating\n). Additionally, you replenish your shields in two\nSwift Actions\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.droid_shield_mastery","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Shield_Mastery","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"d612e7a708edf75b","name":"Frightening Presence","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use Frightful Presence, targets that fail their Will Defense check move -2 steps down the condition track instead of -1.","prerequisite":"Charisma 15, Frightful Presence","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":25,"tags":["control","feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":["8c58016e587dd2c7"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Improves Frightful Presence CT movement to -2 steps.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"condition_track_rider","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Improves Frightful Presence CT movement to -2 steps.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase14-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 14 continues description-guided feat implementation: Force-skill bonuses, attack rerolls, condition-track rules, weapon-family rules, and safe action/resource metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"condition_track_rider_metadata_phase14","riderRules":[{"type":"FRIGHTFUL_PRESENCE_CT_STEPS_OVERRIDE","steps":-2,"description":"Failed Frightful Presence targets move -2 CT steps instead of -1."}]},"shortSummary":"When you use Frightful Presence, targets that fail their Will Defense check move -2 steps down the condition track instead of -1."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.387Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"]}}}
{"_id":"d6e528de87b25b95","name":"Wary Defender","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use the Fight Defensively Action, you gain a +2 competence bonus to your Fortitude Defense and Will Defense until the beginning of your next turn.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Clone Wars Campaign Guide","page":29,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you use the<br>Fight Defensively<br>Action, you gain a +2 competence bonus to your<br>Fortitude Defense<br>and<br>Will Defense<br>until the beginning of your next turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wary_Defender</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.fortitude","defense.will"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Wary Defender: Implemented as conditional defense metadata; excluded from static sheet totals.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.fortitude","defense.will"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as conditional defense metadata; excluded from static sheet totals.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"defense_context","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Wary Defender now exposes conditional defense metadata instead of a false attack/static modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","conditionalDefenseBonuses":[{"type":"CONDITIONAL_DEFENSE_BONUS","targets":["defense.fortitude","defense.will"],"value":2,"bonusType":"competence","requiresContextFlags":["fightingDefensively"],"duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn","description":"While fighting defensively, gain +2 competence to Fortitude and Will until next turn."}],"status":"conditional_defense_phase10","description":"Wary Defender now exposes conditional defense metadata instead of a false attack/static modifier."},"shortSummary":"Gain a +2 bonus to Fortitude Defense and Will Defense while Fighting Defensively.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Clone Wars Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wary_Defender","effect":"When you use the\nFight Defensively\nAction, you gain a +2 competence bonus to your\nFortitude Defense\nand\nWill Defense\nuntil the beginning of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.fortitude","defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.wary_defender","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wary_Defender","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"d7736c072de9b86c","name":"Vehicle Systems Expertise","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You may use the Recharge Shields or Reroute Power Actions by spending two Swift Actions. Also, once per encounter, you may attempt to use either of these Actions as a single Swift Action by making a DC 30 Mechanics check.","prerequisite":"Tech Specialist, Trained in Mechanics.","special":"","normalText":"The Recharge Shields and Reroute Power Actions normally requires you to spend three Swift Actions.","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":22,"tags":["charge","feat","general","tech","utility","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Tech Specialist<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Mechanics<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You may use the<br>Recharge Shields<br>or<br>Reroute Power<br>Actions by spending two<br>Swift Actions<br>. Also, once per encounter, you may attempt to use either of these Actions as a single<br>Swift Action<br>by making a DC 30<br>Mechanics<br>check.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> The<br>Recharge Shields<br>and<br>Reroute Power<br>Actions normally requires you to spend three<br>Swift Actions<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicle_Systems_Expertise</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"745a5686d6f21e8c"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"vehicle_systems_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Vehicle Systems Expertise: Recharge Shields or Reroute Power with two swift actions, with once/encounter DC 30 one-swift option.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"vehicle_action_metadata_phase16","description":"Vehicle Systems Expertise: Recharge Shields or Reroute Power with two swift actions, with once/encounter DC 30 one-swift option.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Vehicle Systems Expertise: Recharge Shields or Reroute Power with two swift actions, with once/encounter DC 30 one-swift option.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"vehicle_systems_action_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"VEHICLE_SYSTEM_ACTION_ECONOMY","actions":["Recharge Shields","Reroute Power"],"swiftActions":2,"description":"Use Recharge Shields or Reroute Power by spending two swift actions."},{"type":"VEHICLE_SYSTEM_ACTION_ECONOMY_CHECK","oncePer":"encounter","skillKey":"mechanics","dc":30,"swiftActions":1,"actions":["Recharge Shields","Reroute Power"],"description":"Once per encounter, DC 30 Mechanics to use either action as one swift action."}]},"shortSummary":"Recharge Shields or Reroute Power on a Vehicle faster than normal.","prerequisitesText":"Tech Specialist, Trained in Mechanics.","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicle_Systems_Expertise","effect":"You may use the\nRecharge Shields\nor\nReroute Power\nActions by spending two\nSwift Actions\n. Also, once per encounter, you may attempt to use either of these Actions as a single\nSwift Action\nby making a DC 30\nMechanics\ncheck."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.vehicle_systems_expertise","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Vehicle_Systems_Expertise","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"d7a139003afc04b8","name":"Indomitable Personality","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you can add your Charisma modifier to your Will Defense as a Reaction; this benefit lasts until the end of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Charisma 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":21,"tags":["ability_charisma","feat","general","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Charisma<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, you can add your<br>Charisma<br>modifier to your<br>Will Defense<br>as a<br>Reaction<br>; this benefit lasts until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Indomitable_Personality</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Indomitable Personality: Implemented as reaction metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.will"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as reaction metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"reaction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Indomitable Personality now exposes reaction metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","reactionRules":[{"type":"TEMP_DEFENSE_BONUS_ABILITY_MOD","defense":"will","ability":"cha","trigger":"incomingAttack","action":"reaction","oncePer":"encounter","duration":"untilEndOfNextTurn","description":"Add Charisma modifier to Will Defense until end of next turn."}],"status":"reaction_rule_phase10","description":"Indomitable Personality now exposes reaction metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"Add your Charisma bonus to your Will Defense as a Reaction.","prerequisitesText":"Charisma 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Indomitable_Personality","effect":"Once per encounter, you can add your\nCharisma\nmodifier to your\nWill Defense\nas a\nReaction\n; this benefit lasts until the end of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.indomitable_personality","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Indomitable_Personality","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"d874a33284de77e4","name":"Fast Swimmer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Gain a bonus to your Swim Speed.","prerequisite":"Mon Calamari","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","skill_swim","skill_synergy","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-mon-calamari"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Mon Calamari</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Your Swim Speed increases by 2 squares.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fast_Swimmer</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"MODIFIER","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"movement.swim","type":"untyped","value":2,"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Fast Swimmer: swim speed increases by 2 squares. This never modifies land/base speed.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"swim_movement_only","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude_from_land_speed","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":[],"conditionSummary":"Swim Speed increases by 2 squares only. Do not add to normal/base land speed."}],"rules":[{"type":"MOVEMENT_MODE_ADJUST","mode":"swim","value":2,"unit":"squares","description":"Your Swim Speed increases by 2 squares.","displayAsCondition":true,"displayLabel":"Fast Swimmer","displayNote":"Swim Speed +2 squares only; this does not modify land speed."}],"mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"swim_movement_only","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude_from_land_speed","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Swim Speed increases by 2 squares only. Do not add to normal/base land speed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase25-suspect-feat-cleanup","metadataNotes":"Corrected from speed.base to swim-only metadata so Fast Swimmer never inflates land speed.","status":"swim_speed_only_metadata_phase25"},"shortSummary":"Gain a bonus to your Swim Speed.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fast_Swimmer","rawImport":{"name":"Fast Swimmer","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Fast_Swimmer","pageTitle":"Fast_Swimmer","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\fast_swimmer.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Mon Calamari","prerequisites":["Mon Calamari"],"effect":"Your Swim Speed increases by 2 squares.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Mon Calamari","indexBenefit":"Gain a bonus to your Swim Speed.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou are naturally gifted at swimming and move through the water more quickly than do others of your Species.\n\nPrerequisite:\nMon Calamari\n\nEffect:\nYour Swim Speed increases by 2 squares."},"prerequisitesText":"Mon Calamari","effect":"Your Swim Speed increases by 2 squares."},"effects":[{"_id":"023f0cf2-0c15-4090-ac2d-78a65e120824","name":"Fast Swimmer","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":true,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Fast Swimmer","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Fast Swimmer","migratedToPassive":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"id":"swse.feat.fast_swimmer"}}}
{"_id":"d976f03c298fb1be","name":"Officer Candidacy Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus to your Rank and Privilege Organization Score.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":25,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +2 bonus to your<br>Rank and Privilege<br>Organization Score.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Officer_Candidacy_Training</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"organization_score_context","staticSheetPolicy":"metadata_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Officer Candidacy Training grants +2 to Rank and Privilege Organization Score.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"organization_score_metadata_phase17","description":"Officer Candidacy Training grants +2 to Rank and Privilege Organization Score.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Officer Candidacy Training grants +2 to Rank and Privilege Organization Score.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"organization_score_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"organizationScoreBonuses":[{"type":"RANK_AND_PRIVILEGE_SCORE_BONUS","value":2,"description":"Gain +2 bonus to Rank and Privilege Organization Score."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain a bonus to your Rank and Privilege Score.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Officer_Candidacy_Training","effect":"You gain a +2 bonus to your\nRank and Privilege\nOrganization Score."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.officer_candidacy_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Officer_Candidacy_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"d9ecf143e6a9f889","name":"Critical Strike","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"While wielding a weapon for which you possess the Weapon Focus feat, you can take two consecutive Swift Actions in the same round to increase the critical threat range of your next melee attack by 1.\n\nThus, if a weapon scores a Critical Hit on a Natural 20, it can score a Critical Hit on a natural roll of 19 or 20 instead. However, any roll other than a Natural 20 is not considered an automatic hit; if you roll a Natural 19 and miss the target, you do not score a Critical Hit. You lose the benefits of Critical Strike if you lose line of sight to your target or if you take any other Action before making your attack.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +9, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":25,"tags":["feat","general","offense","offense_melee"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+9,<br>Weapon Focus<br>(Chosen Weapon)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> While wielding a weapon for which you possess the<br>Weapon Focus<br>feat, you can take two consecutive<br>Swift Actions<br>in the same round to increase the critical threat range of your next melee attack by 1.<br><br>Thus, if a weapon scores a Critical Hit on a Natural 20, it can score a Critical Hit on a natural roll of 19 or 20 instead. However, any roll other than a Natural 20 is not considered an automatic hit; if you roll a Natural 19 and miss the target, you do not score a Critical Hit. You lose the benefits of Critical Strike if you lose line of sight to your target or if you take any other Action before making your attack.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Critical_Strike</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":9}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"melee_critical_attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Critical Strike: spend two swift actions to improve the critical threat of a melee attack with a Weapon Focus weapon.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"attack_option_phase16","description":"Critical Strike: spend two swift actions to improve the critical threat of a melee attack with a Weapon Focus weapon.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Critical Strike: spend two swift actions to improve the critical threat of a melee attack with a Weapon Focus weapon.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"melee_critical_attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"criticalStrike","label":"Critical Strike","control":"toggle","requiresAttackType":"melee","requiresSwiftActions":2,"requiresFeatSelectedChoiceMatch":["Weapon Focus"],"criticalThreatNaturalMin":19,"summary":"Two swift actions: next melee attack with a Weapon Focus weapon threatens on natural 19-20, but 19 is not an automatic hit."}]},"shortSummary":"Increase critical threat range of an attack.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +9, Weapon Focus (Chosen Weapon)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Critical_Strike","effect":"While wielding a weapon for which you possess the\nWeapon Focus\nfeat, you can take two consecutive\nSwift Actions\nin the same round to increase the critical threat range of your next melee attack by 1.\n\nThus, if a weapon scores a Critical Hit on a Natural 20, it can score a Critical Hit on a natural roll of 19 or 20 instead. However, any roll other than a Natural 20 is not considered an automatic hit; if you roll a Natural 19 and miss the target, you do not score a Critical Hit. You lose the benefits of Critical Strike if you lose line of sight to your target or if you take any other Action before making your attack."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.critical_strike","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Critical_Strike","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"da2e6fb7a11b3d63","name":"Pistoleer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make a ranged attack with a Pistol with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of Pistol you use.\n\n- Blaster Pistol: You treat the Blaster Pistol as an Accurate Weapon.\n- Heavy Blaster Pistol: You do not treat the Heavy Blaster Pistol as an Inaccurate Weapon.\n- Hold-Out Blaster Pistol: If you fire a Hold-Out Blaster Pistol at a target that has not yet acted in combat, you gain a +2 bonus to your attack rolls with that weapon against that target. This bonus applies to all such attacks until the target attacks.","prerequisite":"Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":26,"tags":["feat","general","offense_ranged","weapon_pistol"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make a ranged attack with a<br>Pistol<br>with which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of<br>Pistol<br>you use.<br><br>- Blaster Pistol : You treat the Blaster Pistol as an Accurate Weapon.<br>- Heavy Blaster Pistol : You do not treat the Heavy Blaster Pistol as an Inaccurate Weapon.<br>- Hold-Out Blaster Pistol : If you fire a Hold-Out Blaster Pistol at a target that has not yet acted in combat, you gain a +2 bonus to your attack rolls with that weapon against that target. This bonus applies to all such attacks until the target attacks.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pistoleer</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"pistol_family_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Pistoleer: pistol-family benefits are explicit metadata; Hold-Out Blaster early-combat attack bonus is roll-context supported.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"weapon_family_metadata_phase16","description":"Pistoleer: pistol-family benefits are explicit metadata; Hold-Out Blaster early-combat attack bonus is roll-context supported.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Pistoleer: pistol-family benefits are explicit metadata; Hold-Out Blaster early-combat attack bonus is roll-context supported.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"pistol_family_roll_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"rules":[{"type":"WEAPON_PROPERTY_OVERRIDE","requiresWeaponText":["blaster pistol"],"addProperty":"accurate","description":"Treat Blaster Pistol as Accurate."},{"type":"WEAPON_PROPERTY_OVERRIDE","requiresWeaponText":["heavy blaster pistol"],"removeProperty":"inaccurate","description":"Do not treat Heavy Blaster Pistol as Inaccurate."},{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"pistoleerHoldOut","label":"Pistoleer: Hold-Out Opening Shot","control":"passive","requiresWeaponText":["hold-out blaster","hold out blaster"],"requiresContextFlags":["targetHasNotActed"],"attackModifier":2,"summary":"+2 with Hold-Out Blaster against a target that has not yet acted until that target attacks."}]},"shortSummary":"Gain benefits when using certain Pistols.","prerequisitesText":"Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pistoleer","effect":"When you make a ranged attack with a\nPistol\nwith which you are proficient, you gain one of the following benefits, depending on the kind of\nPistol\nyou use.\n\n- Blaster Pistol : You treat the Blaster Pistol as an Accurate Weapon.\n- Heavy Blaster Pistol : You do not treat the Heavy Blaster Pistol as an Inaccurate Weapon.\n- Hold-Out Blaster Pistol : If you fire a Hold-Out Blaster Pistol at a target that has not yet acted in combat, you gain a +2 bonus to your attack rolls with that weapon against that target. This bonus applies to all such attacks until the target attacks."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.pistoleer","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Pistoleer","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"da8e272f5dae09b9","name":"Tactical Genius","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You regain all spent Starship Maneuvers at the end of any round in which you roll a Natural 20 on an attack roll.","prerequisite":"Starship Tactics, Vehicular Combat, Trained in Pilot","special":"","normalText":"Only a Natural 20 rolled on a Pilot check to activate a Starship Maneuver restores all Starship Maneuvers.","sourcebook":"Starships of the Galaxy","page":30,"tags":["feat","general","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Starship Tactics<br>,<br>Vehicular Combat<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Pilot</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You regain all spent<br>Starship Maneuvers<br>at the end of any round in which you roll a Natural 20 on an attack roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> Only a Natural 20 rolled on a<br>Pilot<br>check to activate a<br>Starship Maneuver<br>restores all<br>Starship Maneuvers<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tactical_Genius</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"starship_maneuver_recovery_context","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Tactical Genius refreshes all spent Starship Maneuvers at the end of any round in which you roll a natural 20 on an attack roll.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"starship_maneuver_metadata_phase17","description":"Tactical Genius refreshes all spent Starship Maneuvers at the end of any round in which you roll a natural 20 on an attack roll.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Tactical Genius refreshes all spent Starship Maneuvers at the end of any round in which you roll a natural 20 on an attack roll.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"starship_maneuver_recovery_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"starshipManeuverRules":[{"type":"RECOVER_ALL_SPENT_MANEUVERS_ON_NATURAL_20_ATTACK_ROUND","trigger":"endOfRoundAfterNatural20AttackRoll","description":"Regain all spent Starship Maneuvers at end of round after rolling a natural 20 on an attack."}]},"shortSummary":"You are a master at using multiple starship tactics over the course of long space combats.","prerequisitesText":"Starship Tactics, Vehicular Combat, Trained in Pilot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Starships of the Galaxy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tactical_Genius","effect":"You regain all spent\nStarship Maneuvers\nat the end of any round in which you roll a Natural 20 on an attack roll."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.tactical_genius","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Tactical_Genius","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"daf0594fbb48e61e","name":"Wilderness Specialists","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"team","benefit":"Gain bonuses on Survival checks when near allies.","prerequisite":"Trained in Survival","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["ally_support","feat","skill_survival","skill_synergy","team","teamwork","conditional_skill_bonus","execution_mapped_phase8","manual_resolution","teamwork_base_skill_bonus_phase15"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Survival</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +3 competence bonus on<br>Survival<br>checks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).<br><br>Additionally, when you use the<br>Aid Another<br>Action to assist an ally who has this Feat with a<br>Survival<br>check, you provide a bonus of +4 instead of +2.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wilderness_Specialists</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_with_manual_teamwork","applicationScope":"skill_roll_plus_manual_teamwork","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Wilderness Specialists: +3 competence skill bonus applies normally; nearby-ally scaling and other battlefield/teamwork clauses are GM/player managed.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 avoids automating nearby-ally/battlefield positioning clauses; base skill bonuses are implemented where unambiguous and teamwork clauses are preserved as manual metadata.","implementationStatus":"base_skill_bonus_manual_teamwork_phase15","description":"Wilderness Specialists: base +3 competence skill bonus implemented; nearby-ally scaling and special teamwork clauses remain table-managed flavor/manual metadata.","skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"wilderness-specialists","skillKey":"survival","type":"competence","featName":"Wilderness Specialists","description":"Wilderness Specialists: +3 competence bonus to survival checks. Nearby-ally scaling is manual/table-managed.","value":3}],"teamworkRules":[{"type":"AID_ANOTHER_BONUS_OVERRIDE","skillKey":"survival","bonus":4,"requiresAllyHasFeat":true,"description":"Aid Another provides +4 instead of +2 when assisting an ally with this feat on Survival.","automation":"manual","manualResolution":true}]},"shortSummary":"Gain bonuses on Survival checks when near allies.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wilderness_Specialists","rawImport":{"name":"Wilderness Specialists","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wilderness_Specialists","pageTitle":"Wilderness_Specialists","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\wilderness_specialists.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nSurvival","prerequisites":["Trained\nin\nSurvival"],"effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nSurvival\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nSurvival\ncheck, you provide a bonus of +4 instead of +2.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Trained in Survival","indexBenefit":"Gain bonuses on Survival checks when near allies.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Team Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nTeam Feats\n\nYou and your allies have been trained to survive in the wild and can live off the land.\n\nPrerequisite:\nTrained\nin\nSurvival\n\nEffect:\nYou gain a +3 competence bonus on\nSurvival\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nSurvival\ncheck, you provide a bonus of +4 instead of +2."},"prerequisitesText":"Trained\nin\nSurvival","effect":"You gain a +3 competence bonus on\nSurvival\nchecks. At the time you make a check, for each ally within 12 squares of you who also has this Feat, the competence bonus increases by +1 (to a maximum of +7).\n\nAdditionally, when you use the\nAid Another\nAction to assist an ally who has this Feat with a\nSurvival\ncheck, you provide a bonus of +4 instead of +2."},"effects":[{"_id":"4e6b6849-eae9-4126-ab01-44509e3fe819","name":"Wilderness Specialists","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Wilderness Specialists","effectType":"skill_bonus","requiresCustomLogic":true}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":["proximity.count-allies-within-12"],"id":"swse.feat.wilderness_specialists"}}}
