{"_id":"ddbeb23013d9e917","name":"Force Sensitivity","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You can make Use the Force checks, and Use the Force is considered a Class Skill for you. In addition, whenever you gain a Talent, you have the option of selecting a Force Talent instead. You must meet the prerequisites of the Force Talent to select it.","prerequisite":"Cannot be a Droid","special":"","normalText":"You can't make Use the Force checks or select Force Talents unless you have the Force Sensitivity Feat.","sourcebook":"Saga Edition Core Rulebook","page":86,"tags":["feat","force","force_execution","skill_synergy","skill_use_the_force","use_the_force","mapped_phase_1","unlock_grant"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Reference Book:</strong> Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Cannot be a<br>Droid</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can make<br>Use the Force<br>checks, and<br>Use the Force<br>is considered a Class Skill for you. In addition, whenever you gain a<br>Talent<br>, you have the option of selecting a<br>Force Talent<br>instead. You must meet the prerequisites of the<br>Force Talent<br>to select it.</p>\n<p><strong>Normal:</strong> You can&#x27;t make<br>Use the Force<br>checks or select<br>Force Talents<br>unless you have the Force Sensitivity Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Sensitivity</em></p>","executionModel":"UNLOCK","abilityMeta":{"grants":[{"category":"SYSTEM_ACCESS","capability":"force_sensitivity","description":"Actor is Force-sensitive and may access Force-sensitive rules and prerequisites."}],"mechanicsMode":"grant_unlock","applicationScope":"system_access","staticSheetPolicy":"not_a_modifier","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Unlocks Force-sensitive rules/prerequisites. RAW/default behavior does not directly grant a Force power.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"You can make Use the Force checks and gain access to Force Talents.","prerequisitesText":"Cannot be a Droid","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Core Rulebook"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Sensitivity","effect":"You can make\nUse the Force\nchecks, and\nUse the Force\nis considered a Class Skill for you. In addition, whenever you gain a\nTalent\n, you have the option of selecting a\nForce Talent\ninstead. You must meet the prerequisites of the\nForce Talent\nto select it."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.force_sensitivity","phase1Mapped":true,"manualMappingResolved":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Force_Sensitivity","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"de584ec0aaddcbad","name":"Wookiee Grip","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When using a weapon in which you are proficient and that normally requires two hands, you can wield that weapon with a single hand. You take a -2 penalty to attack rolls with the weapon when it is used in this manner.","prerequisite":"Strength 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":27,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase10","feat","general","species_prerequisite_phase10","species_rule"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Strength<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When using a weapon in which you are proficient and that normally requires two hands, you can wield that weapon with a single hand. You take a -2 penalty to attack rolls with the weapon when it is used in this manner.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wookiee_Grip</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"species_rule_phase10_executable_hook","description":"Wookiee Grip: may wield two-handed weapons in one hand. Exposed as a weapon handling rule hook.","rules":[{"type":"WEAPON_HANDLING_OVERRIDE","twoHandedAsOneHanded":true,"description":"Wield two-handed weapons in a single hand.","displayAsCondition":true,"displayLabel":"Wookiee Grip","displayNote":"May wield two-handed weapons in one hand."}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"rule_hook","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Implemented by a rule hook; exact static-sheet behavior depends on the consuming engine.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"species","species":["Wookiee"]}],"_source":"phase10_species_prereq"},"shortSummary":"Wield two-handed weapons in a single hand.","prerequisitesText":"Strength 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wookiee_Grip","effect":"When using a weapon in which you are proficient and that normally requires two hands, you can wield that weapon with a single hand. You take a -2 penalty to attack rolls with the weapon when it is used in this manner."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.wookiee_grip","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Wookiee_Grip","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"dec7203bc81176dc","name":"Prime Shot","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If none of your allies are closer to your target than you are when you make a ranged attack, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the attack roll. Your target must be at Short Range or closer to gain this bonus.","prerequisite":"Point-Blank Shot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Rebellion Era Campaign Guide","page":20,"tags":["ally_support","feat","general","offense","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Point-Blank Shot</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If none of your allies are closer to your target than you are when you make a ranged attack, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the attack roll. Your target must be at Short<br>Range<br>or closer to gain this bonus.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Prime_Shot</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Contextual ranged attack bonus when the user flags the Prime Shot positioning condition.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Contextual ranged attack bonus when the user flags the Prime Shot positioning condition.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"primeShot","label":"Prime Shot","control":"passive","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresContextFlags":["attackerCloserThanAllies"],"attackModifier":1,"summary":"Gain +1 ranged attack when you are closer to the target than your allies."}],"implementationStatus":"primeShot_attack_option_phase13"},"shortSummary":"Gain a bonus to attack rolls when closer to your target than your allies.","prerequisitesText":"Point-Blank Shot","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Prime_Shot","effect":"If none of your allies are closer to your target than you are when you make a ranged attack, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the attack roll. Your target must be at Short\nRange\nor closer to gain this bonus."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.prime_shot","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Prime_Shot","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"df58db54c4b53539","name":"Shrewd Bargainer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Suppress opponents' insight and morale bonuses to Will Defense.","prerequisite":"Quarren","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-quarren"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Quarren</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you make<br>Persuasion<br>checks against a target&#x27;s<br>Will Defense<br>, the target does not receive the benefit of insight or morale bonuses to its<br>Will Defense<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Shrewd_Bargainer</em></p>\n<p><strong>Automation:</strong> Metadata only. When resolving Persuasion checks against a target&#x27;s Will Defense, ignore that target&#x27;s insight and morale bonuses to Will Defense. The GM/player applies this during social resolution.</p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.will","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.will"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Shrewd Bargainer: Suppress opponents' insight and morale bonuses to Will Defense in bargaining/social contexts; metadata only until opposed social resolution consumes it.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"social_resolution_note","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.will"],"conditionSummary":"Suppress opponents' insight and morale bonuses to Will Defense in bargaining/social contexts; metadata only until opposed social resolution consumes it."}],"mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"social_resolution_note","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["defense.will"],"metadataPhase":"phase23-feat-cleanup","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","socialRules":[{"id":"shrewd_bargainer_suppress_will_bonuses","type":"SUPPRESS_TARGET_DEFENSE_BONUS_TYPES","defense":"will","bonusTypes":["insight","morale"],"context":"bargaining"}],"status":"metadata_only_phase23","description":"Metadata only: when this character makes Persuasion checks against a target's Will Defense, the target does not benefit from insight or morale bonuses to Will Defense.","gmManaged":true},"shortSummary":"Suppress opponents' insight and morale bonuses to Will Defense.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Shrewd_Bargainer","rawImport":{"name":"Shrewd Bargainer","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Shrewd_Bargainer","pageTitle":"Shrewd_Bargainer","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\shrewd_bargainer.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Quarren","prerequisites":["Quarren"],"effect":"Whenever you make\nPersuasion\nchecks against a target's\nWill Defense\n, the target does not receive the benefit of insight or morale bonuses to its\nWill Defense\n.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Quarren","indexBenefit":"Suppress opponents' insight and morale bonuses to Will Defense .","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou know how to break down the defenses of your opponents, ensuring that you gain the upper hand in any negotiation.\n\nPrerequisite:\nQuarren\n\nEffect:\nWhenever you make\nPersuasion\nchecks against a target's\nWill Defense\n, the target does not receive the benefit of insight or morale bonuses to its\nWill Defense\n."},"prerequisitesText":"Quarren","effect":"Whenever you make\nPersuasion\nchecks against a target's\nWill Defense\n, the target does not receive the benefit of insight or morale bonuses to its\nWill Defense\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.will"],"id":"swse.feat.shrewd_bargainer"}}}
{"_id":"e0cdeb7d44cf44fd","name":"Brilliant Defense","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Once per encounter, you can add your Intelligence modifier to your Reflex Defense as a Reaction; this benefit lasts until the start of your next turn.","prerequisite":"Intelligence 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy of Intrigue","page":16,"tags":["ability_intelligence","defense","feat","general","reaction","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Once per encounter, you can add your<br>Intelligence<br>modifier to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>as a<br>Reaction<br>; this benefit lasts until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Brilliant_Defense</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Brilliant Defense: Implemented as reaction metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as reaction metadata; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"reaction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Brilliant Defense now exposes reaction metadata instead of a false numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","reactionRules":[{"type":"TEMP_DEFENSE_BONUS_ABILITY_MOD","defense":"reflex","ability":"int","trigger":"incomingAttack","action":"reaction","oncePer":"encounter","duration":"untilStartOfNextTurn","description":"Add Intelligence modifier to Reflex Defense until start of next turn."}],"status":"reaction_rule_phase10","description":"Brilliant Defense now exposes reaction metadata instead of a false numeric modifier."},"shortSummary":"Add your Intelligence bonus to your Reflex Defense as a Reaction.","prerequisitesText":"Intelligence 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy of Intrigue"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Brilliant_Defense","effect":"Once per encounter, you can add your\nIntelligence\nmodifier to your\nReflex Defense\nas a\nReaction\n; this benefit lasts until the start of your next turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.reflex"],"id":"swse.feat.brilliant_defense","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Brilliant_Defense","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"e18eecc0f21a95f4","name":"Friends in Low Places","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Whenever you would acquire a license for a Restricted or Military object, you can substitute a Gather Information check for a Knowledge (Bureaucracy) check. Reduce the Black Market cost multiplier of such items by 1.","prerequisite":"Trained in Gather Information","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":23,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Gather Information</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Whenever you would acquire a license for a<br>Restricted<br>or<br>Military<br>object, you can substitute a<br>Gather Information<br>check for a<br>Knowledge (Bureaucracy)<br>check. Reduce the<br>Black Market<br>cost multiplier of such items by 1.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Friends_in_Low_Places</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"gatherinformation"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"passive_capability","applicationScope":"license_black_market_context","staticSheetPolicy":"commerce_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Friends in Low Places substitutes Gather Information for Knowledge (Bureaucracy) for licenses and reduces Restricted/Military Black Market multipliers by 1.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"commerce_metadata_phase17","description":"Friends in Low Places substitutes Gather Information for Knowledge (Bureaucracy) for licenses and reduces Restricted/Military Black Market multipliers by 1.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Friends in Low Places substitutes Gather Information for Knowledge (Bureaucracy) for licenses and reduces Restricted/Military Black Market multipliers by 1.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"license_black_market_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"commerceRules":[{"type":"LICENSE_SKILL_SUBSTITUTION","fromSkill":"knowledgeBureaucracy","toSkill":"gatherInformation","itemRestriction":["restricted","military"],"description":"Use Gather Information instead of Knowledge (Bureaucracy) to acquire licenses for Restricted/Military goods."},{"type":"BLACK_MARKET_COST_MULTIPLIER_REDUCTION","value":1,"minimumMultiplier":1,"itemRestriction":["restricted","military"],"description":"Reduce Restricted/Military Black Market cost multiplier by 1."}]},"shortSummary":"Reduce Black Market cost multiplier for Restricted Items by 1.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Gather Information","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Friends_in_Low_Places","effect":"Whenever you would acquire a license for a\nRestricted\nor\nMilitary\nobject, you can substitute a\nGather Information\ncheck for a\nKnowledge (Bureaucracy)\ncheck. Reduce the\nBlack Market\ncost multiplier of such items by 1."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.friends_in_low_places","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Friends_in_Low_Places","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"e306ecce877537a9","name":"Grab Back","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus to your Reflex Defense against Grab and Grapple attacks. If an enemy misses you when making a Grab or Grapple attack, you can immediately make your own Grab attack against the same enemy as a Reaction.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13","special":"If you have a Feat that enables you to make a Grapple attack (such as Pin or Trip), you can make a Grapple attack instead.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":21,"tags":["control","feat","general","grapple","reaction"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain a +2 bonus to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>against<br>Grab<br>and<br>Grapple<br>attacks. If an enemy misses you when making a<br>Grab<br>or<br>Grapple<br>attack, you can immediately make your own<br>Grab<br>attack against the same enemy as a<br>Reaction<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you have a<br>Feat<br>that enables you to make a<br>Grapple<br>attack (such as<br>Pin<br>or<br>Trip<br>), you can make a<br>Grapple<br>attack instead.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grab_Back</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"grab_grapple_defense_reaction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"reaction_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Grab Back grants +2 Reflex against Grab/Grapple and lets you make a Grab/Grapple reaction when an enemy misses you with one.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"grapple_reaction_phase17","description":"Grab Back grants +2 Reflex against Grab/Grapple and lets you make a Grab/Grapple reaction when an enemy misses you with one.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Grab Back grants +2 Reflex against Grab/Grapple and lets you make a Grab/Grapple reaction when an enemy misses you with one.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"grab_grapple_defense_reaction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"grappleRules":[{"type":"RESIST_GRAB_AND_GRAPPLE","bonus":2,"description":"Gain +2 Reflex Defense against Grab and Grapple attacks."}],"reactionRules":[{"type":"COUNTER_GRAB_OR_GRAPPLE_ON_MISS","trigger":"enemyMissesGrabOrGrappleAgainstYou","action":"reaction","canUseGrappleFeatIfAvailable":true,"description":"When an enemy misses you with Grab/Grapple, make your own Grab or qualifying Grapple attack as a reaction."}]},"shortSummary":"As a Reaction, make a Grab or Grapple attack following a failed Grab or Grapple attack made against you.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grab_Back","effect":"You gain a +2 bonus to your\nReflex Defense\nagainst\nGrab\nand\nGrapple\nattacks. If an enemy misses you when making a\nGrab\nor\nGrapple\nattack, you can immediately make your own\nGrab\nattack against the same enemy as a\nReaction\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.grab_back","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Grab_Back","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"e3b2b8360fb05d82","name":"Shield Surge","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Reaction, when your Vehicle takes damage above its Shield Rating, after the Shield Rating is reduced you can reduce the amount of damage sustained by the Vehicle by an amount up to the remaining Shield Rating. However, the Shield Rating is immediately reduced by one point for every point of damage reduced.","prerequisite":"Droid or Cyborg Hybrid, Trained in Mechanics","special":"The Recharge Shields Action cannot be used on the Vehicle until a full round after the use of Shield Surge. You must have a Scomp Link or similar direct data link to the Vehicle to use this Feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":25,"tags":["defense","feat","general","survivability","vehicle"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Droid<br>or<br>Cyborg Hybrid<br>,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Mechanics</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Reaction<br>, when your<br>Vehicle<br>takes damage above its<br>Shield Rating<br>, after the<br>Shield Rating<br>is reduced you can reduce the amount of damage sustained by the<br>Vehicle<br>by an amount up to the remaining<br>Shield Rating<br>. However, the<br>Shield Rating<br>is immediately reduced by one point for every point of damage reduced.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> The<br>Recharge Shields<br>Action cannot be used on the<br>Vehicle<br>until a full round after the use of Shield Surge. You must have a<br>Scomp Link<br>or similar direct data link to the<br>Vehicle<br>to use this Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Shield_Surge</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"vehicle_shield_damage_reduction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"reaction_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Shield Surge lets a Droid/Cyborg with a vehicle data link trade remaining vehicle SR to reduce damage after shields are reduced.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"shield_reaction_metadata_phase17","description":"Shield Surge lets a Droid/Cyborg with a vehicle data link trade remaining vehicle SR to reduce damage after shields are reduced.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Shield Surge lets a Droid/Cyborg with a vehicle data link trade remaining vehicle SR to reduce damage after shields are reduced.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"vehicle_shield_damage_reduction_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"reactionRules":[{"type":"TRADE_VEHICLE_SR_FOR_DAMAGE_REDUCTION","trigger":"vehicleDamageAboveShieldRatingAfterSrReduction","requiresDataLink":true,"damageReductionLimit":"remainingShieldRating","shieldRatingCost":"onePerDamageReduced","locksRechargeShieldsFor":"1round","description":"As reaction, reduce vehicle damage by up to remaining SR, reducing SR by the same amount; Recharge Shields unavailable for 1 round."}]},"shortSummary":"Trade Vehicle's Shield Rating for damage taken.","prerequisitesText":"Droid or Cyborg Hybrid, Trained in Mechanics","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Shield_Surge","effect":"As a\nReaction\n, when your\nVehicle\ntakes damage above its\nShield Rating\n, after the\nShield Rating\nis reduced you can reduce the amount of damage sustained by the\nVehicle\nby an amount up to the remaining\nShield Rating\n. However, the\nShield Rating\nis immediately reduced by one point for every point of damage reduced."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.shield_surge","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Shield_Surge","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"e4de79f4993a6690","name":"Deep Sight","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Gain Darkvision and ignore Total Concealment from darkness.","prerequisite":"Quarren","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["cover_play","execution_mapped_phase10","feat","racial","species","species_opportunity","species_rule"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-quarren"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Quarren</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You gain Darkvision, ignoring<br>Concealment<br>(including<br>Total Concealment<br>) from darkness. You cannot perceive colors in total darkness.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deep_Sight</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"species_rule_phase10_executable_hook","description":"Deep Sight: grants Darkvision and ignores Total Concealment from darkness.","rules":[{"type":"SENSE_GRANT","sense":"darkvision","description":"Gain Darkvision.","displayAsCondition":true,"displayLabel":"Deep Sight","displayNote":"Darkvision active; ignore Total Concealment from darkness."},{"type":"IGNORE_CONCEALMENT","concealment":"total","source":"darkness","description":"Ignore Total Concealment from darkness."}],"conditionNotes":[{"id":"deep-sight","label":"Deep Sight","severity":"info","text":"Darkvision active; ignore Total Concealment from darkness.","mechanical":true,"gmEnforced":false}],"mechanicsMode":"passive","applicationScope":"static_actor_or_capability","staticSheetPolicy":"include_or_display_condition","requiresRuntimeContext":false,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rule grants a persistent capability or movement/sense mode.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase3-static-vs-context","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics."},"shortSummary":"Gain Darkvision and ignore Total Concealment from darkness.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deep_Sight","rawImport":{"name":"Deep Sight","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Deep_Sight","pageTitle":"Deep_Sight","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\deep_sight.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Quarren","prerequisites":["Quarren"],"effect":"You gain Darkvision, ignoring\nConcealment\n(including\nTotal Concealment\n) from darkness. You cannot perceive colors in total darkness.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Quarren","indexBenefit":"Gain Darkvision and ignore Total Concealment from darkness.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou have spent so much time in the deepest parts of your home planet that you can see even in total darkness.\n\nPrerequisite:\nQuarren\n\nEffect:\nYou gain Darkvision, ignoring\nConcealment\n(including\nTotal Concealment\n) from darkness. You cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},"prerequisitesText":"Quarren","effect":"You gain Darkvision, ignoring\nConcealment\n(including\nTotal Concealment\n) from darkness. You cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.deep_sight"}}}
{"_id":"e5a77e8e4754fa5b","name":"Trample","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you use the Mounted Charge Action, your Mount can make a single melee attack as a Free Action. While Charging, compare the result to the Reflex Defense of each enemy whose square you Charge through. Each enemy hit by the attack takes Claw, Gore, or Slam damage from the Mount's Natural Weapons plus the Mount's Strength modifier. You or your Mount still can make a regular attack at the end of the Charge.","prerequisite":"Trained in Ride","special":"You can use this Feat if either you or your Mount has taken it. Mounts with this Feat do not require the prerequisite.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":27,"tags":["charge","feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Ride</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you use the<br>Mounted Charge<br>Action, your<br>Mount<br>can make a single melee attack as a<br>Free Action<br>. While<br>Charging<br>, compare the result to the<br>Reflex Defense<br>of each enemy whose square you<br>Charge<br>through. Each enemy hit by the attack takes Claw, Gore, or Slam damage from the Mount&#x27;s Natural Weapons plus the Mount&#x27;s<br>Strength<br>modifier. You or your<br>Mount<br>still can make a regular attack at the end of the<br>Charge<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can use this Feat if either you or your<br>Mount<br>has taken it.<br>Mounts<br>with this Feat do not require the prerequisite.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trample</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"mounted_charge_area_attack_context","staticSheetPolicy":"action_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Trample lets a mount make a free natural weapon attack against each enemy whose square it charges through, plus the normal end-of-charge attack.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"mounted_charge_metadata_phase17","description":"Trample lets a mount make a free natural weapon attack against each enemy whose square it charges through, plus the normal end-of-charge attack.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Trample lets a mount make a free natural weapon attack against each enemy whose square it charges through, plus the normal end-of-charge attack.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"mounted_charge_area_attack_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"actionRules":[{"type":"MOUNTED_CHARGE_TRAMPLE_ATTACKS","trigger":"mountedCharge","attackSource":"mountNaturalWeapon","targetSelection":"enemiesWhoseSquaresAreChargedThrough","damageIncludes":"mountStrengthModifier","description":"During Mounted Charge, mount makes one natural weapon attack result compared to each enemy whose square is charged through."}]},"shortSummary":"When using the Mounted Charge Action, attack enemies between you and your target.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Ride","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trample","effect":"When you use the\nMounted Charge\nAction, your\nMount\ncan make a single melee attack as a\nFree Action\n. While\nCharging\n, compare the result to the\nReflex Defense\nof each enemy whose square you\nCharge\nthrough. Each enemy hit by the attack takes Claw, Gore, or Slam damage from the Mount's Natural Weapons plus the Mount's\nStrength\nmodifier. You or your\nMount\nstill can make a regular attack at the end of the\nCharge\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.trample","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Trample","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"e5ab9392378400ec","name":"Resilient Reflexes","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You gain a +2 bonus on Reflex Defense against effects that target Dexterity and may reroll a failed check once per encounter.","prerequisite":"Dex 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":27,"tags":["defense","feat","general","survivability"],"bonus_feat_for":["b5bed5d1b5f42958"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.reflex","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.reflex","effect.targets-dexterity"],"enabled":true,"priority":500,"description":"Resilient Reflexes: +2 Reflex Defense against effects that target Dexterity; failed check reroll once per encounter.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"contextual_defense","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex","effect.targets-dexterity"],"conditionSummary":"+2 Reflex Defense against effects that target Dexterity; failed check reroll once per encounter."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"contextual_defense","staticSheetPolicy":"contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["defense.reflex","turn.once-per-round"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","defenseRerolls":[{"id":"dexterity_reflex_reroll","type":"DEFENSE_REROLL","defense":"reflex","oncePer":"en