{"_id":"f0afba1763ddff90","name":"Intimidator","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you successfully use the Intimidate application of the Persuasion skill against a creature, instead of the normal results, the creature takes a -5 penalty to all Skill Checks (including Use the Force) and a -2 penalty to all attacks when you are within its line of sight, until the end of your next turn.\n\nIf aboard another Vehicle, your enemy must be able to see or detect your Vehicle.","prerequisite":"Trained in Persuasion","special":"You cannot use this Feat with the Maniacal Charge feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Unknown Regions","page":25,"tags":["feat","general","social"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Persuasion</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you successfully use the<br>Intimidate<br>application of the<br>Persuasion<br>skill against a creature, instead of the normal results, the creature takes a -5 penalty to all<br>Skill Checks<br>(including<br>Use the Force<br>) and a -2 penalty to all attacks when you are within its line of sight, until the end of your next turn.<br><br>If aboard another<br>Vehicle<br>, your enemy must be able to see or detect your<br>Vehicle<br>.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You cannot use this Feat with the<br>Maniacal Charge<br>feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Intimidator</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Successful intimidate debuff rider metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"skill_use_rider","applicationScope":"persuasion_intimidate_rider_context","staticSheetPolicy":"rider_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Successful intimidate debuff rider metadata.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"intimidator_metadata_phase13","skillUseRules":[{"type":"INTIMIDATE_DEBUFF_ON_SUCCESS","skill":"persuasion","targetEffects":[{"target":"skills","value":-5,"duration":"1 round"},{"target":"attack","value":-2,"duration":"1 round"}],"description":"Successful intimidate imposes -5 skill checks and -2 attack for one round."}]},"shortSummary":"When you successfully Intimidate, enemy takes -5 to Skill Checks and -2 to attack for one round.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Persuasion","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Unknown Regions"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Intimidator","effect":"When you successfully use the\nIntimidate\napplication of the\nPersuasion\nskill against a creature, instead of the normal results, the creature takes a -5 penalty to all\nSkill Checks\n(including\nUse the Force\n) and a -2 penalty to all attacks when you are within its line of sight, until the end of your next turn.\n\nIf aboard another\nVehicle\n, your enemy must be able to see or detect your\nVehicle\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.388Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.intimidator","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Intimidator","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f2cbe2ac10195858","name":"Follow Through","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"If you deal enough damage to your opponent with a melee attack to reduce it to 0 Hit Points, you can immediately move up to your Speed. You can use this ability once per turn.","prerequisite":"None","special":"If you have the Cleave Feat, you can move up to your Speed before making the extra melee attack granted by the Cleave Feat.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Jedi Academy Training Manual","page":28,"tags":["durability","feat","general","hit_points"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> If you deal enough damage to your opponent with a melee attack to reduce it to 0 Hit Points, you can immediately move up to your Speed. You can use this ability once per turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you have the<br>Cleave<br>Feat, you can move up to your Speed before making the extra melee attack granted by the<br>Cleave<br>Feat.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Follow_Through</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["attack.when-hit"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Follow Through: Old migrated numeric modifier disabled; represented by non-numeric rider/resource metadata.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit"],"conditionSummary":"Old migrated numeric modifier disabled; represented by non-numeric rider/resource metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"rider_effect","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"After dropping a target with melee damage, move up to speed once per turn.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase9-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 9 removes false numeric scaffolding and records description-driven rider metadata.","status":"rider_effect_phase9","description":"After dropping a target with melee damage, move up to speed once per turn.","rules":[{"type":"RIDER_EFFECT","trigger":"meleeDamageDropsTarget","effect":"moveUpToSpeed","oncePer":"turn"}]},"shortSummary":"Move when you reduce an enemy to 0 Hit Points.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Jedi Academy Training Manual"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Follow_Through","effect":"If you deal enough damage to your opponent with a melee attack to reduce it to 0 Hit Points, you can immediately move up to your Speed. You can use this ability once per turn."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":["attack.when-hit"],"id":"swse.feat.follow_through","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Follow_Through","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f313d17068d1cdea","name":"Informer","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You can use your Perception modifier instead of your Gather Information modifier when making Gather Information checks. You are considered Trained in the Gather Information skill. If you are entitled to a Gather Information check reroll, you can reroll your Perception check instead (subject to the same circumstances and limitations).\n\nAdditionally, when you have favorable conditions for your Gather Information check (such as from operating on your home planet), you reduce by half the time it takes to make a Gather Information check.","prerequisite":"Trained in Perception","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":35,"tags":["feat","general","skill_gather_information","skill_perception","skill_synergy","social","skill_use_substitution","execution_mapped_phase8"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Perception</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can use your<br>Perception<br>modifier instead of your<br>Gather Information<br>modifier when making<br>Gather Information<br>checks. You are considered<br>Trained<br>in the<br>Gather Information<br>skill. If you are entitled to a<br>Gather Information<br>check reroll, you can reroll your<br>Perception<br>check instead (subject to the same circumstances and limitations).<br><br>Additionally, when you have favorable conditions for your<br>Gather Information<br>check (such as from operating on your home planet), you reduce by half the time it takes to make a<br>Gather Information<br>check.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Informer</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"43c5941072ec78af"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"status":"skill_use_substitution_phase8","description":"Informer: Gather Information checks can be resolved with Perception; favorable-condition Gather Information time is halved.","skillUseSubstitutions":[{"id":"informer-gather-information-with-perception","fromSkill":"gatherInformation","toSkill":"perception","applications":["Gather Information","Learn Secret Information","Find Black Market Object","Analysis"],"description":"Use Perception for Gather Information checks and related applications."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"skill_use_substitution_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Use Perception instead of Gather Information and reduce favorable-condition time by half.","predicateRequirements":["skill.gatherInformation"],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 continues description-guided implementation by improving teamwork skill feats, skill substitutions, force/dark-side skill context, and several remaining action/resource rider feats.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","implementationStatus":"informer_skill_substitution_phase15","skillUseRules":[{"type":"CONSIDERED_TRAINED","skillKey":"gatherInformation","description":"You are considered trained in Gather Information."},{"type":"TIME_REDUCTION","skillKey":"gatherInformation","applications":["Gather Information"],"requiresContextFlags":["favorableConditions"],"multiplier":0.5,"description":"With favorable conditions, halve the time required for Gather Information."},{"type":"REROLL_SUBSTITUTION","fromSkill":"gatherInformation","toSkill":"perception","description":"If entitled to reroll Gather Information, reroll the substituted Perception check instead."}]},"shortSummary":"Gather Information with Perception skill, and do it faster.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Perception","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Informer","effect":"You can use your\nPerception\nmodifier instead of your\nGather Information\nmodifier when making\nGather Information\nchecks. You are considered\nTrained\nin the\nGather Information\nskill. If you are entitled to a\nGather Information\ncheck reroll, you can reroll your\nPerception\ncheck instead (subject to the same circumstances and limitations).\n\nAdditionally, when you have favorable conditions for your\nGather Information\ncheck (such as from operating on your home planet), you reduce by half the time it takes to make a\nGather Information\ncheck."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.informer","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Informer","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f362e5a4ad0a98bd","name":"Echani Training","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"martial_arts","benefit":"You can double the damage bonus provided by your Strength modifier to Unarmed Attacks (minimum +1) provided you make only one Unarmed attack this turn.\n\nOnce per encounter when you deal damage to a target with an Unarmed Attack you may make an immediate Unarmed Attack against the target's Fortitude Defense as a Free Action; if successful, you knock your opponent to the ground (Prone) in their current square, provided they are no more than one size larger than you.","prerequisite":"Dexterity 13, Martial Arts I","special":"Targets gain a bonus to their Fortitude Defense against being knocked Prone based on their size: Large +5, Huge +10, Gargantuan +20, Colossal +50. Unusually stable creatures (such as those with four legs) gain a +5 bonus to their Fortitude Defense against being knock Prone as well.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["control","feat","feat_chain","knock_prone","martial_arts","martial_style","offense_melee","unarmed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Dexterity<br>13,<br>Martial Arts I</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You can double the damage bonus provided by your<br>Strength<br>modifier to<br>Unarmed Attacks<br>(minimum +1) provided you make only one<br>Unarmed<br>attack this turn.<br><br>Once per encounter when you deal damage to a target with an<br>Unarmed Attack<br>you may make an immediate<br>Unarmed Attack<br>against the target&#x27;s<br>Fortitude Defense<br>as a<br>Free Action<br>; if successful, you knock your opponent to the ground (<br>Prone<br>) in their current square, provided they are no more than one size larger than you.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> Targets gain a bonus to their<br>Fortitude Defense<br>against being knocked<br>Prone<br>based on their size: Large +5, Huge +10, Gargantuan +20, Colossal +50. Unusually stable creatures (such as those with four legs) gain a +5 bonus to their<br>Fortitude Defense<br>against being knock<br>Prone<br>as well.</p>\n<h3>Additional Echani Training Effects</h3><p>Reference Book:<br>Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War<br><br>If you have the<br>Echani Expertise<br>Talent, whenever you score a Critical Hit with an<br>Unarmed<br>attack, the target is immediately knocked to the ground (<br>Prone<br>) in its current square, provided that the target is no more than one size larger than you</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Echani_Training</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"dex","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"martialArtsFeat":true,"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"defense.fortitude","value":1,"type":"untyped","predicates":["defense.fortitude","attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round","target.is-prone"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Echani Training: Implemented the single-unarmed-attack damage bonus as an optional roll toggle and preserved the once/encounter knock-prone rider metadata.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"explicit_rule_metadata","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","defense.fortitude","target.is-prone","turn.once-per-round"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented the single-unarmed-attack damage bonus as an optional roll toggle and preserved the once/encounter knock-prone rider metadata."}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Rules text is conditional and current metadata has predicates. It must only apply when the runtime context satisfies those predicates.","predicateRequirements":["attack.when-hit","defense.fortitude","target.is-prone","turn.once-per-round"],"metadataPhase":"phase12-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 12 continues description-guided feat implementation by replacing false scaffold bonuses with explicit roll options, contextual predicates, resource/rider metadata, or supported static rules.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"echaniSingleUnarmedStrike","label":"Echani Single Unarmed Strike","control":"toggle","requiresUnarmed":true,"damageAbilityBonus":{"ability":"str","multiplier":1,"minimum":1},"targetEffectsOnHit":[{"type":"FOLLOW_UP_ATTACK","defense":"fortitude","effect":"prone","oncePer":"encounter","description":"Once per encounter after damaging with an unarmed attack, make an immediate unarmed attack vs Fortitude to knock the target prone."}],"summary":"When making only one unarmed attack this turn, add your Strength modifier again to unarmed damage."}],"status":"echaniSingleUnarmedStrike_attack_option_phase12","description":"Implemented the single-unarmed-attack damage bonus as an optional roll toggle and preserved the once/encounter knock-prone rider metadata."},"shortSummary":"In Unarmed combat, increase damage, and knock opponent Prone on Critical Hit.","prerequisitesText":"Dexterity 13, Martial Arts I","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","Star Wars Saga Edition Galaxy at War"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Echani_Training","effect":"You can double the damage bonus provided by your\nStrength\nmodifier to\nUnarmed Attacks\n(minimum +1) provided you make only one\nUnarmed\nattack this turn.\n\nOnce per encounter when you deal damage to a target with an\nUnarmed Attack\nyou may make an immediate\nUnarmed Attack\nagainst the target's\nFortitude Defense\nas a\nFree Action\n; if successful, you knock your opponent to the ground (\nProne\n) in their current square, provided they are no more than one size larger than you."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":["defense.fortitude","attack.when-hit","turn.once-per-round","target.is-prone"],"id":"swse.feat.echani_training","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Echani_Training","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f401ac70ee67def1","name":"Impetuous Move","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you catch a Second Wind, you can choose to regain only half of the Hit Points you normally would with a Second Wind and immediately Move up to half of your Speed. This movement does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity.","prerequisite":"Constitution 13","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":25,"tags":["execution_mapped_phase8","feat","general","recovery","resource_second_wind","second_wind"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Constitution<br>13</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you catch a<br>Second Wind<br>, you can choose to regain only half of the Hit Points you normally would with a<br>Second Wind<br>and immediately Move up to half of your Speed. This movement does not provoke<br>Attacks of Opportunity<br>.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impetuous_Move</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"con","min":13}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"secondWind_resource","staticSheetPolicy":"resource_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Optional Second Wind rider: half healing for half-speed movement without provoking.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase8-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 3 classification separates true static sheet bonuses from roll/target/action/choice-specific mechanics.","status":"second_wind_rule_phase8_partial","description":"Impetuous Move: if selected at activation, halve Second Wind healing and gain movement.","resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"HALF_HEALING_FOR_MOVEMENT","movement":"halfSpeed","provokesAoO":false,"description":"Choose to regain half healing and immediately move up to half speed without provoking attacks of opportunity."}]}},"resourceRules":{"secondWind":[{"type":"GRANT_MOVEMENT_ON_USE"}]},"shortSummary":"Move when you catch a Second Wind.","prerequisitesText":"Constitution 13","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impetuous_Move","effect":"When you catch a\nSecond Wind\n, you can choose to regain only half of the Hit Points you normally would with a\nSecond Wind\nand immediately Move up to half of your Speed. This movement does not provoke\nAttacks of Opportunity\n."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.impetuous_move","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Impetuous_Move","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f4604b0d477e5fe7","name":"Strafe","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you make an Autofire attack, instead of attacking a 2-square-by-2-square area, you may attack a line 1 square wide and 4 squares long.","prerequisite":"Base Attack Bonus +1","special":"If you are using a Jet Pack, you can use the Strafe feat to make an Autofire attack against all squares you fly over.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":36,"tags":["feat","general","offense_ranged"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Base Attack Bonus<br>+1</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make an<br>Autofire<br>attack, instead of attacking a 2-square-by-2-square area, you may attack a line 1 square wide and 4 squares long.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> If you are using a<br>Jet Pack<br>, you can use the Strafe feat to make an<br>Autofire<br>attack against all squares you fly over.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strafe</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"bab","min":1}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"attack","value":2,"type":"untyped","predicates":["movement.while-moving"],"enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Strafe: Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"runtime_predicate_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"predicateRequirements":["movement.while-moving"],"conditionSummary":"Implemented as an explicit CombatOptionResolver rule; old migrated numeric modifier disabled.","metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Strafe now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase10-feat-implementation-continuation","metadataNotes":"Phase 10 uses refreshed descriptions to replace old migrated scaffold modifiers with concrete defense, skill, attack-option, reaction, or resource metadata.","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","option":"strafe","label":"Strafe","control":"flag","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAutofire":true,"areaShape":"line1x4","summary":"Autofire may attack a 1-square-wide, 4-square-long line instead of a 2x2 area."}],"status":"attack_option_phase10","description":"Strafe now has explicit roll-context attack option metadata from its refreshed description."},"shortSummary":"Attack multiple targets as you move past them.","prerequisitesText":"Base Attack Bonus +1","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Force Unleashed Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strafe","effect":"When you make an\nAutofire\nattack, instead of attacking a 2-square-by-2-square area, you may attack a line 1 square wide and 4 squares long."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":["movement.while-moving"],"id":"swse.feat.strafe","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Strafe","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f4e8244a4c8bb9a0","name":"Brink of Death","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"When you deal sufficient damage on an attack to kill a target, you may instead choose to reduce the target to 0 Hit Points, leaving it Unconscious but alive. Normal rules for being at 0 Hit Points apply.","prerequisite":"None","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":17,"tags":["durability","feat","general","hit_points"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> None</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you deal sufficient damage on an attack to kill a target, you may instead choose to reduce the target to 0 Hit Points, leaving it<br>Unconscious<br>but alive. Normal rules for being at 0<br>Hit Points<br>apply.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Brink_of_Death</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"damage_resolution_nonlethal_choice","staticSheetPolicy":"damage_resolution_metadata","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Brink of Death lets you choose to reduce a target to 0 HP and unconscious instead of killing it when your attack would kill.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 17 clears the remaining Phase 16 active backlog by implementing engine-supported skill/reroll/attack-option rules where possible, and explicitly reclassifying table-state/picker-heavy feats as manual, punted, or deferred instead of leaving them as unincorporated placeholders.","implementationStatus":"damage_resolution_metadata_phase17","description":"Brink of Death lets you choose to reduce a target to 0 HP and unconscious instead of killing it when your attack would kill.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Brink of Death lets you choose to reduce a target to 0 HP and unconscious instead of killing it when your attack would kill.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"damage_resolution_nonlethal_choice","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase17-next-feat-batch"}],"damageResolutionRules":[{"type":"OPTIONAL_REDUCE_TO_ZERO_HP_INSTEAD_OF_KILL","trigger":"attackWouldKillTarget","targetState":"unconsciousAtZeroHp","description":"When your attack would kill a target, choose to leave it unconscious at 0 HP instead."}]},"shortSummary":"Attacks that would kill your enemy reduces them to 0 Hit Points instead.","prerequisitesText":"None","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Legacy Era Campaign Guide"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Brink_of_Death","effect":"When you deal sufficient damage on an attack to kill a target, you may instead choose to reduce the target to 0 Hit Points, leaving it\nUnconscious\nbut alive. Normal rules for being at 0\nHit Points\napply."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.brink_of_death","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Brink_of_Death","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f4f3706e393976b3","name":"Droid Focus","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"Select a degree of Droid (1st-Degree, 2nd-Degree, 3rd-Degree, 4th-Degree, or 5th-Degree). You gain a +1 bonus to Deception, Mechanics, Perception, Persuasion, and Use Computer checks when used on or against a Droid of the selected degree, and a +1 bonus to all Defenses against attack rolls and Skill Checks made by Droids of the selected degree.","prerequisite":"Trained in Mechanics and Use Computer","special":"You can gain this Feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different degree of Droid (1st-Degree, 2nd-Degree, 3rd-Degree, 4th-Degree, or 5th-Degree).","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scavenger's Guide to Droids","page":20,"tags":["feat","general","tech","utility","choice_required","immediate_choice","droid_choice","choice_source_fixed"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Trained<br>in<br>Mechanics<br>and<br>Use Computer</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Select a degree of Droid (<br>1st-Degree<br>,<br>2nd-Degree<br>,<br>3rd-Degree<br>,<br>4th-Degree<br>, or<br>5th-Degree<br>). You gain a +1 bonus to<br>Deception<br>,<br>Mechanics<br>,<br>Perception<br>,<br>Persuasion<br>, and<br>Use Computer<br>checks when used on or against a Droid of the selected degree, and a +1 bonus to all<br>Defenses<br>against attack rolls and<br>Skill Checks<br>made by Droids of the selected degree.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> You can gain this Feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take this Feat, it applies to a different degree of Droid (<br>1st-Degree<br>,<br>2nd-Degree<br>,<br>3rd-Degree<br>,<br>4th-Degree<br>, or<br>5th-Degree<br>).</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Focus</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional_choice_required","applicationScope":"selected_droid_degree_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Droid Focus: selected droid-degree context gives +1 on listed skills and +1 defenses against that droid degree.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 16 applies the latest user triage, implements another description-guided feat batch, and keeps positioning/GM-heavy rules as explicit metadata instead of false numeric bonuses.","implementationStatus":"choice_skill_defense_metadata_phase16","description":"Droid Focus: selected droid-degree context gives +1 on listed skills and +1 defenses against that droid degree.","modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Droid Focus: selected droid-degree context gives +1 on listed skills and +1 defenses against that droid degree.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"selected_droid_degree_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase16-next-feat-batch"}],"skillCheckBonuses":[{"id":"droidFocus.selectedDegreeSkills","skillKeys":["deception","mechanics","perception","persuasion","useComputer"],"value":1,"type":"feat","requiresTargetType":"droid","requiresTargetSelectedChoice":true,"description":"+1 on listed skill checks used on or against the selected droid degree."}],"riderRules":[{"type":"CONDITIONAL_DEFENSE_BONUS","value":1,"targets":["defense.reflex","defense.fortitude","defense.will"],"requiresAttackerType":"droid","requiresAttackerSelectedChoice":true,"description":"+1 defenses against attacks and skill checks from selected droid degree."}],"choiceKind":"droid_class_focus"},"choiceMeta":{"resolution":"immediate","required":true,"status":"tagged_for_later_dialog_backfill","choiceKind":"droid_class_focus","repeatable":false,"storagePath":"flags.swse.choices.droid_class_focus","choiceSource":"fixed","optionRegistry":"data/feat-choice-options.json#choiceKinds.droid_class_focus"},"shortSummary":"+1 bonus to certain Skills and Defenses when dealing with a selected class of Droid.","prerequisitesText":"Trained in Mechanics and Use Computer","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scavenger's Guide to Droids"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Focus","effect":"Select a degree of Droid (\n1st-Degree\n,\n2nd-Degree\n,\n3rd-Degree\n,\n4th-Degree\n, or\n5th-Degree\n). You gain a +1 bonus to\nDeception\n,\nMechanics\n,\nPerception\n,\nPersuasion\n, and\nUse Computer\nchecks when used on or against a Droid of the selected degree, and a +1 bonus to all\nDefenses\nagainst attack rolls and\nSkill Checks\nmade by Droids of the selected degree."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.droid_focus","requiresImmediateChoice":true,"featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Droid_Focus","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f504c1a7962f08d8","name":"Friendly Fire Avoidance","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"You may choose to exclude a number of squares equal to your Dexterity modifier from the area of effect of your autofire attacks.","prerequisite":"Dex 13, Point Blank Shot","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Galaxy at War","page":25,"tags":["feat","general","offense"],"bonus_feat_for":["f62ca2e639cab614"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":{},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Autofire targeting flag; no numeric modifier.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude"}],"mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"attack_option","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Autofire targeting flag; no numeric modifier.","predicateRequirements":[],"metadataPhase":"phase13-next-feat-implementation-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 13 converts clear remaining manual/scaffold feats into skill bonuses, attack options, action/resource metadata, or safer non-static rider metadata.","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","rules":[{"type":"ATTACK_OPTION","id":"friendlyFireAvoidance","label":"Friendly Fire Avoidance","control":"flag","requiresAttackType":"ranged","requiresAutofire":true,"flags":{"excludeAutofireSquaresByDex":true},"summary":"Exclude a number of autofire area squares up to your Dexterity modifier."}],"implementationStatus":"friendlyFireAvoidance_attack_option_phase13"},"shortSummary":"You may choose to exclude a number of squares equal to your Dexterity modifier from the area of effect of your autofire attacks."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":[]}}}
{"_id":"f59c9679c02b8896","name":"Metamorph","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"general","benefit":"As a Full-Round Action, you can change your mass when you use your Shapeshift Species Trait, increasing or decreasing your size by one step. You can maintain this form for a number of rounds per day equal to your Constitution score.\n\nIf you reduce your size to Small, you gain a +1 size bonus to your Reflex Defense and a +5 size bonus on Stealth checks, but your Carrying Capacity is three-quarters of what it was prior to your use of Metamorph.\n\nIf you increase your size to Large, you take a -1 penalty to your Reflex Defense and a -5 penalty on Stealth checks. However, your Carrying Capacity doubles, you gain a +5 size bonus to your Damage Threshold, and your Reach increases by 1 square.","prerequisite":"Constitution 13, Shapeshift Species Trait, Trained in Deception","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Scum and Villainy","page":26,"tags":["feat","general"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Constitution<br>13, Shapeshift Species Trait,<br>Trained<br>in<br>Deception</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> As a<br>Full-Round Action<br>, you can change your mass when you use your Shapeshift Species Trait, increasing or decreasing your size by one step. You can maintain this form for a number of rounds per day equal to your<br>Constitution<br>score.<br><br>If you reduce your size to Small, you gain a +1 size bonus to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>and a +5 size bonus on<br>Stealth<br>checks, but your<br>Carrying Capacity<br>is three-quarters of what it was prior to your use of Metamorph.<br><br>If you increase your size to Large, you take a -1 penalty to your<br>Reflex Defense<br>and a -5 penalty on<br>Stealth<br>checks. However, your<br>Carrying Capacity<br>doubles, you gain a +5 size bonus to your<br>Damage Threshold<br>, and your<br>Reach<br>increases by 1 square.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Metamorph</em></p>","prerequisitesStructured":{"type":"all","conditions":[{"type":"attribute","ability":"con","min":13},{"type":"skillTrained","skill":"9410ce2dfb6cefcb"}],"_source":"canonical-csv"},"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"ACTIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"active","applicationScope":"shapeshift_size_context","staticSheetPolicy":"manual_or_contextual_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":true,"conditionSummary":"Active shapeshift size change with size-based defense/skill effects; requires a size-selection UI hook.","predicateRequirements":["species.shapeshift"],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 continues description-guided implementation by improving teamwork skill feats, skill substitutions, force/dark-side skill context, and several remaining action/resource rider feats.","implementationStatus":"shapeshift_size_metadata_phase15","description":"Metamorph: full-round Shapeshift can increase or decrease size one step for Con-score rounds/day; chosen size drives contextual size modifiers.","activeRules":[{"type":"SHAPESHIFT_SIZE_STEP_CHOICE","sizeStepChoices":[-1,1],"durationFormula":"constitutionScoreRoundsPerDay","smallSizeEffects":{"defense.reflex":1,"skill.stealth":5},"largeSizeEffects":{"defense.reflex":-1,"grapple.sizeModifier":5},"description":"Change size by one step with Shapeshift; size effects are contextual and should not be permanent static sheet bonuses."}],"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Metamorph changes size temporarily through Shapeshift; old generic modifiers are disabled until the size-choice hook applies contextual effects.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch"}]},"shortSummary":"Change your size.","prerequisitesText":"Constitution 13, Shapeshift Species Trait, Trained in Deception","referenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Scum and Villainy"],"sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Metamorph","effect":"As a\nFull-Round Action\n, you can change your mass when you use your Shapeshift Species Trait, increasing or decreasing your size by one step. You can maintain this form for a number of rounds per day equal to your\nConstitution\nscore.\n\nIf you reduce your size to Small, you gain a +1 size bonus to your\nReflex Defense\nand a +5 size bonus on\nStealth\nchecks, but your\nCarrying Capacity\nis three-quarters of what it was prior to your use of Metamorph.\n\nIf you increase your size to Large, you take a -1 penalty to your\nReflex Defense\nand a -5 penalty on\nStealth\nchecks. However, your\nCarrying Capacity\ndoubles, you gain a +5 size bonus to your\nDamage Threshold\n, and your\nReach\nincreases by 1 square."},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.metamorph","featContentRefresh":{"source":"swse_feats.json","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Metamorph","updatedFields":["system.description.value","system.benefit","system.prerequisite","system.special","system.normalText","system.shortSummary"]}}}}
{"_id":"f5be1207aa6b1817","name":"Read the Winds","type":"feat","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"featType":"species","benefit":"Detect hidden enemies within 10 squares of you.","prerequisite":"Kel Dor","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Star Wars Saga Edition","page":0,"tags":["feat","racial","species","species_opportunity"],"bonus_feat_for":["species-kel-dor"],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"costNumeric":null,"description":"<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Kel Dor</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> You ignore<br>Concealment<br>and<br>Cover<br>for the purposes of<br>Perception<br>checks against targets within 10 squares of you.</p>\n<p><em>Source URL: https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Read_the_Winds</em></p>","executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"STATE","abilityMeta":{"executionModel":"PASSIVE","subType":"RULE","mechanicsMode":"conditional","applicationScope":"perception_context","staticSheetPolicy":"roll_context_only","requiresRuntimeContext":true,"requiresSelectedChoice":false,"conditionSummary":"Ignore cover and concealment on Perception checks against targets within 10 squares.","predicateRequirements":["skill.perception","range.within10Squares"],"metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch","metadataNotes":"Phase 15 continues description-guided implementation by improving teamwork skill feats, skill substitutions, force/dark-side skill context, and several remaining action/resource rider feats.","implementationStatus":"perception_ignore_cover_concealment_phase15","description":"Read the Winds: ignore cover and concealment for Perception checks against targets within 10 squares.","skillUseRules":[{"type":"IGNORE_COVER_AND_CONCEALMENT","skillKey":"perception","maxSquares":10,"description":"Ignore cover and concealment for Perception against targets within 10 squares."}],"modifiers":[{"target":"metadata","value":0,"type":"untyped","enabled":false,"priority":500,"description":"Read the Winds changes Perception context, not an attack/static modifier.","mechanicsMode":"metadata_only","applicationScope":"non_static_context","staticSheetPolicy":"exclude","metadataPhase":"phase15-next-feat-batch"}]},"shortSummary":"Detect hidden enemies within 10 squares of you.","sourceUrl":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Read_the_Winds","rawImport":{"name":"Read the Winds","url":"https://swse.fandom.com/wiki/Read_the_Winds","pageTitle":"Read_the_Winds","htmlCachePath":"C:\\Users\\Owner\\Downloads\\swse_cache\\feats_html\\read_the_winds.html","referenceBooks":[],"prerequisitesText":"Kel Dor","prerequisites":["Kel Dor"],"effect":"You ignore\nConcealment\nand\nCover\nfor the purposes of\nPerception\nchecks against targets within 10 squares of you.","benefit":"","normal":"","special":"","indexPrerequisites":"Kel Dor","indexBenefit":"Detect hidden enemies within 10 squares of you.","indexPage":"Specialization_Feats","indexSection":"Species Feats","indexReferenceBooks":["Star Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide"],"sections":[],"rawText":"Reference Book:\nStar Wars Saga Edition Rebellion Era Campaign Guide\n\nSee also:\nFeats\n,\nSpecies Feats\n\nYou are so attuned to the wind patterns of your world that you can detect subtle shifts in air pressure around you.\n\nPrerequisite:\nKel Dor\n\nEffect:\nYou ignore\nConcealment\nand\nCover\nfor the purposes of\nPerception\nchecks against targets within 10 squares of you."},"prerequisitesText":"Kel Dor","effect":"You ignore\nConcealment\nand\nCover\nfor the purposes of\nPerception\nchecks against targets within 10 squares of you."},"effects":[{"_id":"488fdaa6-0b80-46ba-a625-e4a4facbd8fb","name":"Read the Winds","icon":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{},"flags":{"swse":{"source":"feat","featName":"Read the Winds","effectType":"passive_effect","flagType":"Read the Winds"}}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"swse":{"migratedToState":true,"migrationDate":"2026-03-08T18:22:17.389Z","detectedPredicates":[],"id":"swse.feat.read_th